(475, 141, 'Trail-specific footwear', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Trekking Boots</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Waterproof, high-ankle support boots (break them in before the trek)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Â Camp Shoes / Sandals</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For walking around lodges and teahouses</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Â Socks (Moisture-Wicking, Warmth-Retaining)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3-4 pairs Merino wool trekking socks (for cold and warmth regulation)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2 pairs liner socks (to prevent blisters)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Â Gaiters (For Snow &amp; Muddy Trails)</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Recommended for Everest, Annapurna, and Manaslu treks in winter</p>', 2, '2025-07-23 15:07:05', '2025-08-20 17:38:13'),
