(244, 163, 'Weather Condition', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Spring season (March - May)Â </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Average Temperature:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara: 10Â°C â€“ 30Â°C</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Everest Base Camp &amp; Annapurna Base Camp: -5Â°C â€“ 15Â°C</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">Â </span><strong>Weather &amp; Conditions:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Stable weather, clear mornings, occasional afternoon clouds.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Flowers and rhododendrons bloom, making the trails scenic.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Increasing humidity in late May, signaling the approaching monsoon.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">Â </span><strong>Best Treks for Spring:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Everest Base Camp (EBC) Trek â€“ Best visibility of Everest.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Annapurna Circuit â€“ Lush landscapes and moderate temperatures.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Langtang Valley Trek â€“ Ideal for nature lovers with vibrant forests.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Summer/Monsoon (June â€“ August)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Average Temperature:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara: 20Â°C â€“ 35Â°C</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Everest Base Camp &amp; Annapurna Base Camp: 0Â°C â€“ 20Â°C</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Weather &amp; Conditions:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Heavy rainfall (average 200â€“500mm per month), especially in July and August.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Frequent landslides and flight cancellations, especially in hilly areas.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Leeches on lower-altitude trails due to humidity.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Best Treks for Summer: (Only in rain-shadow areas with minimal rainfall)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Upper Mustang Trek â€“ Lies behind the Himalayas, shielded from monsoon.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Dolpo Trek â€“ Dry, high-altitude desert with unique Tibetan culture.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Autumn (September â€“ November) â€“ Best Trekking Season</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Average Temperature:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara: 10Â°C â€“ 28Â°C</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Everest Base Camp &amp; Annapurna Base Camp: -5Â°C â€“ 15Â°C</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Weather &amp; Conditions:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Stable weather, crystal-clear skies and moderate temperatures.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Best visibility of Himalayan peaks, making it the most popular season.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Crowded trekking trails, especially on Everest Base Camp and Annapurna Circuit.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Best Treks for Autumn:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Everest Base Camp Trek â€“ Peak visibility of Everest.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Manaslu Circuit Trek â€“ Challenging but scenic and less crowded.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Gokyo Lakes Trek â€“ Stunning turquoise glacial lakes.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Winter (December â€“ February)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Average Temperature:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara: 2Â°C â€“ 20Â°C</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Everest Base Camp &amp; Annapurna Base Camp: -15Â°C â€“ 10Â°C</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Weather &amp; Conditions:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Cold temperatures, snowfall at higher elevations.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Shorter daylight hours, some high passes (e.g., Thorong La) may be closed.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Fewer trekkers, offering solitude.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Best Treks for Winter: (Lower-altitude treks to avoid extreme cold)</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Ghorepani Poon Hill Trek â€“ Short, scenic trek with snow-capped views.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Everest Panorama Trek â€“ Lower-altitude trek with Everest views.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Helambu Trek â€“ Close to Kathmandu, no high passes.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â </p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 7, 1, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-07 22:09:42'),
(250, 163, 'Food and Accommodation', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Food (meal plan) and accommodation are among the most important things when in Nepal and in course of the trek. Please make sure to let the booking agency know of your allergies if you have any and also let them know if you are in any personal medication and need special attention at any time during the trek.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation in Kathmandu and Pokhara</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Hotel Standards â€“ Most trekkers stay in 2-3 star hotels in Thamel (Kathmandu) or Lakeside (Pokhara) before and after trekking.</li>\r\n<li>Twin-Sharing Basis â€“ Standard bookings are twin-sharing, but single rooms can be arranged at an extra cost.</li>\r\n<li>Facilities â€“ Hotels offer hot showers, Wi-Fi, laundry services, and 24-hour electricity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Accommodation in Trekking Regions</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Teahouses / Lodges â€“ These are family-run guesthouses with dorm-style or twin rooms.</li>\r\n<li>Basic Bedding â€“ Rooms have wooden beds, foam mattresses, blankets and pillows, but heating is not available in most lodges.</li>\r\n<li>Shared Bathrooms â€“ Most lodges have shared toilets and limited hot water (solar-heated in some places).</li>\r\n<li>Dining Areas â€“ Warm communal dining halls serve as social hubs for trekkers.</li>\r\n<li>Electricity &amp; Wi-Fi â€“ Available in lower-altitude teahouses but may require extra charges at higher altitudes.</li>\r\n<li>No Single Rooms at Higher Altitudes â€“ In remote areas, multi-bedded rooms may be the only option.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meals in Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Breakfast &amp; Dinner â€“ Served at hotels or local restaurants.</li>\r\n<li>Wide Food Selection â€“ Includes Nepali, Indian, Chinese and Western cuisine.</li>\r\n<li>Popular Dishes â€“ Dal Bhat (lentils &amp; rice), Momos (dumplings), Thukpa (Tibetan noodle soup), pizza, pasta, curries and grilled meats.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Meals During Trekking</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Standard Trekking Meal Plan â€“ Breakfast, lunch and dinner included in most trekking packages.</li>\r\n<li>Dining at Lodges â€“ Meals are prepared in teahouse kitchens, with all trekkers typically eating the same menu.</li>\r\n<li>Ordering in Advance â€“ Due to limited supplies in remote areas, meals must be ordered in advance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Common Meals on Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Breakfast: porridge, pancakes, Tibetan bread, chapati, eggs, tea/coffee.</li>\r\n<li>Lunch &amp; Dinner: Dal Bhat (lentil soup, rice, vegetables), noodles, pasta, potatoes, soups and curries.</li>\r\n<li>Vegetarian Options Available: Meat is available at lower altitudes but not recommended at high altitudes due to storage concerns.</li>\r\n<li>Soup &amp; Hydration: Garlic soup is often recommended as it helps with acclimatization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Water &amp; Hydration</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Drinking Water Safety â€“ Tap water is not safe for drinking in Nepal.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Filtered/Boiled Water Provided â€“ Teahouses offer boiled or filtered water (often at extra cost).</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Water Purification Recommended â€“ Trekkers should bring purification tablets, LifeStraw or Water-to-Go bottles.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Avoid Plastic Bottles â€“ Buying bottled water is expensive and environmentally harmful.</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 10, 1, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-07 22:09:42'),
