n<ul>\r\n<li>Tourist Police: 1144</li>\r\n<li>General Police: 100</li>\r\n<li>Ambulance: 102</li>\r\n<li>Nepal Immigration Office: +977 1-4113045</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 9, 1, '2025-07-23 19:16:15', '2025-08-21 13:10:19'),
(1015, 144, 'Best Treks & Destination', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>In summer</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Upper Mustang Trek â€“ Lies behind the Himalayas, shielded from the monsoon.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Dolpo Trek â€“ Dry, high-altitude desert with unique Tibetan culture.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Best destination in Nepal</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This is tough to say because every destination in Nepal is a wonder on itself. Broadly, from adventure perspective, youâ€™ll find two major types of destinations. The first ones are the most popular ones which often are the most accessible and will have huge number of trekkers in seasons. These destinations often have a long history of exploration and something of global sensation what make them popular every year. These destinations include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Everest Base Camp Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Annapurna Circuit Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Annapurna Sanctuary Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Upper Mustang Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Upper Dolpo Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Manaslu Circuit Trek, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Then, there are these other groups of destinations which are not as popular but offer an unmatched level of serenity, peace and wilderness that is hardly found anywhere. They offer the true sense of adventure, experience and the thrill of exploration. These destinations in Nepal include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Ruby Valley Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Tamang Heritage Trail</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Api Himal Base Camp Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">The Great Himalayan Trail</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Makalu Base Camp Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Sherpini Col Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Kanchenjunga Base Camp Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Dhaulagiri Circuit Trek</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Sisne Himal Trek, and so on.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The choice of your destination depends on your time, cost, and the experience you wish to have.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 8, 1, '2025-07-23 19:16:15', '2025-08-21 13:10:19'),
(1016, 144, 'Weather condition in Nepal', '<p><strong>Spring season (March - May)Â </strong></p>\r\n<p>Average Temperature:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara: 10Â°C â€“ 30Â°C</li>\r\n<li>Everest Base Camp &amp; Annapurna Base Camp: -5Â°C â€“ 15Â°C</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Â <strong>Weather &amp; Conditions:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stable weather, clear mornings, occasional afternoon clouds.</li>\r\n<li>Flowers and rhododendrons bloom, making the trails scenic.</li>\r\n<li>Increasing humidity in late May, signaling the approaching monsoon.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Â <strong>Best Treks for Spring:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Everest Base Camp (EBC) Trek â€“ Best visibility of Everest.</li>\r\n<li>Annapurna Circuit â€“ Lush landscapes and moderate temperatures.</li>\r\n<li>Langtang Valley Trek â€“ Ideal for nature lovers with vibrant forests.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Summer/Monsoon (June â€“ August)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Average Temperature:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara: 20Â°C â€“ 35Â°C</li>\r\n<li>Everest Base Camp &amp; Annapurna Base Camp: 0Â°C â€“ 20Â°C</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Weather &amp; Conditions:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Heavy rainfall (average 200â€“500mm per month), especially in July and August.</li>\r\n<li>Frequent landslides and flight cancellations, especially in hilly areas.</li>\r\n<li>Leeches on lower-altitude trails due to humidity.</li>\r\n<li>Best Treks for Summer: (Only in rain-shadow areas with minimal rainfall)</li>\r\n<li>Upper Mustang Trek â€“ Lies behind the Himalayas, shielded from monsoon.</li>\r\n<li>Dolpo Trek â€“ Dry, high-altitude desert with unique Tibetan culture.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>Autumn (September â€“ November) â€“ Best Trekking Season</strong></p>\r\n<p>Average Temperature:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara: 10Â°C â€“ 28Â°C</li>\r\n<li>Everest Base Camp &amp; Annapurna Base Camp: -5Â°C â€“ 15Â°C</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Weather &amp; Conditions:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stable weather, crystal-clear skies, and moderate temperatures.</li>\r\n<li>Best visibility of Himalayan peaks, making it the most popular season.</li>\r\n<li>Crowded trekking trails, especially on Everest Base Camp and Annapurna Circuit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Best Treks for Autumn:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Everest Base Camp Trek â€“ Peak visibility of Everest.</li>\r\n<li>Manaslu Circuit Trek â€“ Challenging but scenic and less crowded.</li>\r\n<li>Gokyo Lakes Trek â€“ Stunning turquoise glacial lakes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Winter (December â€“ February)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Average Temperature:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara: 2Â°C â€“ 20Â°C</li>\r\n<li>Everest Base Camp &amp; Annapurna Base Camp: -15Â°C â€“ 10Â°C</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Weather &amp; Conditions:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cold temperatures, snowfall at higher elevations.</li>\r\n<li>Shorter daylight hours, some high passes (e.g., Thorong La) may be closed.</li>\r\n<li>Fewer trekkers, offering solitude.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Best Treks for Winter: (Lower-altitude treks to avoid extreme cold)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ghorepani Poon Hill Trek â€“ Short, scenic trek with snow-capped views.</li>\r\n<li>Everest Panorama Trek â€“ Lower-altitude trek with Everest views.</li>\r\n<li>Helambu Trek â€“ Close to Kathmandu, no high passes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Â </p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 7, 1, '2025-07-23 19:16:15', '2025-08-21 13:10:19'),
(1017, 144, 'Best time to visit Nepal', '<p>Frankly, Nepal is an all-season tourism destination. However, for adventure enthusiasts, there are 2 major seasons to visit Nepal. Here is a detailed look at the seasons and their weather patterns in Nepal for you to decide when best to visit:</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9505%;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 25.0132%;\"><col style=\"width: 25.0132%;\"><col style=\"width: 25.0132%;\"><col style=\"width: 25.0132%;\"></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"83\">\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"90\">\r\n<p><strong>Months</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"168\">\r\n<p><strong>Weather Characteristics</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"155\">\r\n<p><strong>Trekking Conditions</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"83\">\r\n<p>Spring</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"90\">\r\n<p>March â€“ May</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"168\">\r\n<p>Mild temperatures, clear skies, blooming rhododendrons</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"155\">\r\n<p>Excellent for trekking, colorful landscapes</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"83\">\r\n<p>Summer/ Monsoon</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"90\">\r\n<p>June â€“ August</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"168\">\r\n<p>Heavy rainfall, humid, cloudy</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"155\">\r\n<p>Difficult due to slippery trails and poor visibility</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"83\">\r\n<p>Autumn</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"90\">\r\n<p>September â€“ November</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"168\">\r\n<p>Stable weather, clear skies, moderate temperatures</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"155\">\r\n<p>Best season for trekking, peak tourist time</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"83\">\r\n<p>Winter</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"90\">\r\n<p>December â€“ February</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"168\">\r\n<p>Cold temperatures, snowfall at high altitudes</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"bottom\" width=\"155\">\r\n<p>Suitable for lower-altitude treks, high passes may be closed</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Â </p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 6, 1, '2025-07-23 19:16:15', '2025-07-25 17:47:38'),
(1018, 144, 'Tips and Gratitude', '<p>Tipping is a long-standing tradition in the adventure sector in Nepal and a meaningful way to show appreciation for the hard work of guides, porters, and trekking staff. While not mandatory, it is customary to tip at the end of the trek, usually as a group, to ensure a fair and organised distribution. Your trek guide will advise on an appropriate amount based on the trek duration and team size. Many groups present tips with a small farewell gathering or celebration on the last evening, marking the end of their trek. Additionally, trekkers often choose to donate equipment such as boots, gloves, hats, scarves, and trekking poles to the porters and crew. These items are highly valued and appreciated, especially by those working in the mountains. Tour leaders can be tipped separately during the final group dinner in Kathmandu or Pokhara. Though not obligatory, a small personal token of gratitude for their efforts enhances the spirit of mutual respect and appreciation.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 5, 1, '2025-07-23 19:16:15', '2025-07-25 17:47:38'),
(1019, 144, 'Currency & Payments', '<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li>Accepted Currencies â€“ Nepali Rupees (NPR), US Dollars (USD), Euros (EUR), and British Pounds (GBP) are widely accepted.</li>\r\n<li>ATMs &amp; Card Payments â€“ Available in Kathmandu &amp; Pokhara, but limited in trekking areas. Carry cash for mountain regions.</li>\r\n<li>Higher Prices at Altitude â€“ Expect higher costs as supplies are carried up manually or by yaks.</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 4, 1, '2025-07-23 19:16:15', '2025-07-25 17:47:38'),
(1020, 144, 'Personal Expenses', '<p>Trekking in Nepal includes most major costs, but PERSONAL EXPENSES vary depending on individual spending habits. On average, â‚¬200 ($200-250 USD) should cover:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Beverages â€“ Soft drinks, tea, coffee, and alcoholic drinks (prices increase with altitude).</li>\r\n<li>Snacks &amp; Extras â€“ Chocolates, energy bars, and personal food purchases along the trek.</li>\r\n<li>Souvenirs â€“ Handicrafts, prayer flags, and traditional items from trekking villages.</li>\r\n<li>Tips for Guides &amp; Porters â€“ Tipping is customary in Nepal; recommended $5-$10 per day for guides and $3-$5 for porters.</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 3, 1, '2025-07-23 19:16:15', '2025-08-19 14:34:36'),
(1021, 144, 'What\'s not included', '<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Travel Insurance</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">International flight</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Tips for porters and other trek staff</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"FR\">Drinks, souvenirs, Wifi internet, etc.</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Anything not listed under \" price includes\"</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 1, '2025-07-23 19:16:15', '2025-10-14 17:47:31');
