(118, '2025-09-30 07:46:45', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Story from Mingmar Sarkee Sherpa', 'Founder', '<p><strong>The Founder / Director</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mingmar Sarkee Sherpa, born in 1988 in Leplu village, Solukhumbu (the home of Everest), grew up in a farming family with limited financial resources. Despite economic challenges, he completed his early education while assisting in familyâ€™s agricultural work.</p>\r\n<p>Since childhood, Mingmar wanted to get into the adventure sector which he had heard from his seniors of the village. He started his career in trekking industry at a young age of 14 years. Eventually Mingmar took on trainings, honed skills, gaining extensive experience as a trekking guide. Over the years, he led numerous international adventurers across Nepal Himalayaâ€™s trekking routes and participated in professional training programs in Kathmandu, refining his skills in safety, navigation, and customer service. His expertise and reliability secured him positions with several established trekking companies. He worked with reputed adventure operators in Nepal for almost 18 years before establishing Lhakpa Trekking.</p>\r\n<p>Beyond tourism, Mingmar has been actively involved in education and community development. He collaborated with sponsors to provide qualified English teachers, scholarships, and educational materials to local schools. Today, Sagarmatha Basic School, Janadibya School, Bhagawati School in Solukhumbu are counted among the areaâ€™s best schools offering quality education â€“ thanks to Mingmar. He also helped establish health clinics to improve medical access in remote areas. Additionally, he played a key role in preserving Sherpa culture by organizing training for traditional dances like Shili and Shyabru and promoting cultural events such as the Lhosar festival. He also served as the Central Executive Member for the Sherpa Association of Nepal. Currently, he is working to improve educational infrastructure in his village, addressing issues like teacher shortages, inadequate facilities, and limited learning resources. His goal is to establish a structured educational support system by recruiting experienced instructors.</p>\r\n<p>With decades of trekking experience and a strong commitment to sustainable tourism and community development, Mingmar with his better half Lhakpa Sherpa founded Lhakpa Trekking to offer authentic trekking experiences while directly contributing to local progress.</p>', NULL, 'who-we-are', '1689315062939', 22, NULL, 0, 0, '1748916873.jpg', '14194-Pslan.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 1033, 'en', '2023-07-14 06:11:02', '2025-09-30 12:00:33'),
(124, '2025-08-07 03:09:16', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Story from Lhakpa Sherpa', 'Founder', '<p><strong>The Co-Founder</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lhakpa Sherpa was born in Solukhumbu into an agrarian family. Life is Solukhumbu is already hard due to a very little arable land and harsh weather. At the age of three, she lost her mother to domestic violence, and her father was imprisoned. With no immediate family support, she was taken in by her maternal uncle, Speed Kaji Sherpa, a mountaineer recognized for his record-fast Everest ascent. Through an INGO initiative, he ensured that Lhakpa received formal education, and she completed her School Leaving Certificate (SLC).</p>\r\n<p>Lhakpa later pursued higher secondary education in Mass Communication and Journalism, developing skills in communication, management, and leadership. She also undertook specialized trekking guide training, gaining the qualifications necessary to work as a professional trekking guide.</p>\r\n<p>Despite the challenges of her past, Lhakpa Sherpa has built a career in an industry where women are significantly underrepresented. As a certified trekking guide and business leader, she is one of the few women in Nepal to hold an executive role in adventure tourism. Through training programs and employment opportunities, she actively supports women entering the trekking industry, helping them secure leadership roles that have traditionally been male-dominated.</p>\r\n<p>Unlike many trekking companies that operate purely for profit, Lhakpa Trekking Pvt. Ltd. integrates ethical tourism with social responsibility. A portion of the companyâ€™s earnings directly supports Nepal Care Concern (NCC), an organization focused on education and community welfare. The company also prioritizes fair wages, ethical treatment of staff, and eco-friendly trekking practices, making it a business that values impact over profit.</p>', NULL, 'why-us', '1689573175716', 22, NULL, 0, 6, '1724250592.jpg', 'untitled-lhakpa-9qOZq.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 780, 'en', '2023-07-17 05:52:55', '2025-08-07 19:10:18'),
(128, '2025-05-23 10:54:12', 1, 'single', NULL, 'HELPING IN VARIOUS SCHOOLS', 'HELPING IN VARIOUS SCHOOLS', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">With decades of experience in Nepalâ€™s trekking industry, Mingmar established the company to offer a higher standard of trekking services, ensuring that guests receive safe, well-organized, and culturally immersive experiences led by industry professionals.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">The company is also committed to minimizing environmental impact by promoting responsible trekking practices, including waste reduction, eco-friendly trekking routes and practices, and community-based tourism initiatives.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Another core mission of Lhakpa Trekking is womenâ€™s empowerment. Named afterÂ <strong>Lhakpa Sherpa</strong>, a professional trekking guide and the companyâ€™s <strong>co-founder</strong>, the company actively supports womenâ€™s participation in Nepalâ€™s adventure tourism industry. It provides leadership opportunities for female guides and encourages more women to explore careers in trekking.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">By integrating expertise, sustainability, and inclusivity, Lhakpa Trekking aims to set a new standard in responsible adventure tourism in Nepal.</span></p>', 'Lhakpa Trekking was founded with a clear purpose:Â to provide expertly guided trekking experiences while promoting sustainable tourism and women empowerment in Nepal.', 'gear-list', '1689582480636', 24, NULL, 130, 9, '1747976772.jpg', 'img-20241214-wa0030-X11yk.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 570, 'en', '2023-07-17 08:28:00', '2025-05-23 14:55:11'),
(130, '2025-07-18 11:10:43', 1, 'single', NULL, 'HIGH SOCIAL WELFARE EXPERIENCED', 'HIGH SOCIAL WELFARE EXPERIENCED', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Extensive Experience in Social Welfare and Community Leadership</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">With a deep-rooted dedication to social impact, Mingmar, he has been actively engaged in a wide range of community-driven initiatives over the past decade. From 2018 to 2025, he served as a central and active member of the Sherpa Association of Nepal, playing a vital role in preserving Sherpa culture, supporting mountain communities, and advocating for the rights and welfare of indeginous people.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">He has over ten years of experience in photojournalism, using visual storytelling to document social realities, cultural heritage, and the environmental challenges faced by remote Himalayan regions. His work has helped bring awarenessss to under-represented voices and issues in Nepalâ€™s mountainous communities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Between 2016 and 2024, I held the position of Chairman of a Village School Management Committee, where he has been working to improve the quality of education, promote girlâ€™s education, and ensure better infrastructure and teacher support in rural areas.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In addition, He has organized numerous cultural and social events aimed at fostering community unity, preserving indigenous traditions, and supporting youth and womenâ€™s empowerment. These events have included cultural festivals, health and sanitation awareness programs, environmental clean-up campaigns, and leadership workshops.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This long-standing involvement in grassroots efforts reflects my strong belief in inclusive development, education, and cultural preservationâ€”core values that continue to guide my personal and professional journey</p>', 'Helping male student', 'faqs', '1689582554623', 24, NULL, 0, 11, '1749706414.jpg', 'untitled-1-tINuY.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 598, 'en', '2023-07-17 08:29:14', '2025-07-18 15:17:42'),
(134, '2025-09-30 08:50:51', 1, 'single', NULL, 'WORK FOR WOMEN EMPOWERMENT', 'CONTRIBUTION FOR VARIOUS FEMALE JOBS', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Nepalâ€™s trekking and mountaineering industry has traditionally been dominated by men, with women often overlooked, excluded from opportunities, or underpaid for their work. This imbalance not only limits womenâ€™s potential but also prevents the industry from benefiting from their skills, knowledge, and leadership.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">At Lhakpa Trekking, co-founded by professional female guide Lhakpa Sherpa, we are committed to changing this reality. We actively train and employ women as guides and porters, ensuring they receive equal pay and fair treatment. Beyond employment, we organise women-led treks that highlight female leadership in the mountains, support female-run lodges and local businesses, and provide skill-building and professional development for women in tourism and mountaineering.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Our mission is to foster a trekking and climbing industry where women are not only included but empowered to grow, thrive, and take on leadership rolesâ€”helping to shape a more equitable and inspiring future for Himalayan tourism.</p>', 'Helping female employee', 'terms-and-conditions', '1689834953562', 24, NULL, 0, 14, NULL, 'untitled-13-gclYr.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 510, 'en', '2023-07-20 06:35:53', '2025-09-30 12:51:51'),
(151, '2025-09-30 09:35:16', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Short Story', 'Education in hilly region', '<p data-start=\"122\" data-end=\"438\">The <strong data-start=\"126\" data-end=\"148\">Mingmar Foundation</strong>, formally known as <strong data-start=\"168\" data-end=\"196\">Nepal Care Concern (NCC)</strong>, was founded by <strong data-start=\"213\" data-end=\"238\">Mingmar Sarkee Sherpa</strong>. Through this INGO, Mingmar has led numerous social and educational initiatives across Nepalâ€™s Himalayan regions, focusing on uplifting communities in some of the most remote and underserved areas.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"440\" data-end=\"885\">In <strong data-start=\"443\" data-end=\"451\">2015</strong>, during the devastating earthquake that claimed thousands of lives and left tens of thousands missing, Mingmar witnessed firsthand the destruction of homes, schools, and historic monuments. This life-changing experience revealed how quickly everything can be lost and strengthened his conviction that <strong data-start=\"753\" data-end=\"832\">investing in education is one of the most powerful ways to rebuild a nation</strong>â€”even in the face of poverty and limited resources.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"887\" data-end=\"1092\">During the <strong data-start=\"898\" data-end=\"919\">COVID-19 pandemic</strong>, the foundation supported students and teachers by providing essential safety equipment and protective supplies, ensuring education could continue despite the challenges.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1094\" data-end=\"1520\">NCCâ€™s journey began with support for <strong data-start=\"1131\" data-end=\"1158\">Sagarmatha Basic School</strong>. After its success, the foundation expanded to <strong data-start=\"1206\" data-end=\"1233\">Jana Dibya Basic School</strong>, located at a higher elevation, and more recently to <strong data-start=\"1287\" data-end=\"1313\">Bhagawati Basic School</strong>, in an even more remote mountain area. Step by step, the foundation is working to ensure that children in Nepalâ€™s Himalayas have access to quality education, opportunities, and hope for a brighter future.</p>', NULL, 'partners-with', '1722163607619', 27, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, '306952202-461859815976556-5865803237083666637-n-1-BuRpC.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2024-07-28 10:46:47', '2025-09-30 13:35:27'),
(157, '2025-12-20 02:59:02', 1, 'single', NULL, 'CO-CREATE YOUR GROUP TRIP WITH LHAKPA TREKKING', NULL, '<p data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"484\"><strong>Lhakpa Trekking Pvt.Ltd.</strong> offers a comprehensive range of trekking and touring programmes throughout Nepal. With decades of experience, our professional team is dedicated to delivering exceptional service and complete client satisfaction. Each journey is carefully crafted to combine Nepalâ€™s spectacular landscapes, rich cultural heritage, and the highest standards of safety.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"486\" data-end=\"733\">For guides, tour leaders, and group organisers, we provide flexible pricing options and fully tailored itineraries to suit your specific requirementsâ€”whether for individual travellers or organised groupsâ€”ensuring a smooth and rewarding experience.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"735\" data-end=\"948\">We would be pleased to work with you personally. Please share your plans, enquiries, or special requests, and allow us to design a well-planned adventure that meets your expectations with professionalism and care.</p>', NULL, 'cocreate-your-group-trip-with-lhakpa-trekking', '1741003036926', 29, NULL, 0, 25, '1756618475.jpg', 'img-0038-dGhv8.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-03-03 11:57:16', '2025-12-20 19:59:33'),
(158, '2025-08-07 03:48:37', 1, 'single', NULL, 'To Our Valued Clients', 'For your quality travel', '<p>We highly advise choosing guides who are both licensed and experienced, ensuring your trek is safe and well-supported.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Such guides:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>âœ” Have undergone formal training in high-altitude trekking and first aid<br>âœ” Carry all necessary emergency equipment<br>âœ” Are proficient in English or your preferred language for clear communication<br>âœ” Can present trustworthy references from former clients<br>âœ” Are connected with recognized and reputable organizations like Lhakpa Trekking</p>', 'For your quality travel', 'controlling-the-controllable', '1741089556962', 30, NULL, 0, 4, '1752981583.jpg', 'cli-qrJUz.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-03-04 11:59:16', '2025-08-07 19:49:04'),
(160, '2025-08-22 11:19:45', 1, 'single', NULL, 'GUIDES', 'Suggestion From Experienced Guides', '<ul class=\"uk-list uk-highlight uk-list-divider uk-light-bg uk-padding border\">\r\n<li>Follow the Itinerary â€“ The trek is planned considering altitude, weather, and your endurance. Stick to the schedule to avoid exhaustion or altitude sickness.</li>\r\n<li>Respect the Guideâ€™s Instructions â€“ Your guide knows the terrain, weather conditions, and potential risks. Always listen to their advice regarding route changes, rest points, and safety measures.</li>\r\n<li>Acclimatization is Key â€“ Altitude sickness is a serious concern. The guide may suggest rest days or slow ascents to help you adjust. Follow their recommendations to stay healthy.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'The guide is the one who plays major role during your journey. He can make your trip beautiful with lots of unforgettable memories along with your safety. All the trekkers must need to listen the guide rather than deciding oneself. Following is the guide suggestion for your successful trek', 'from-experienced-guides', '1741090492867', 31, NULL, 0, 28, NULL, '1-HH1Ne.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-03-04 12:14:52', '2025-08-22 15:20:33'),
