(164, '2025-08-10 09:55:09', 1, 'template-news', NULL, 'Gelmu Sherpa On Everest with Nepal Care Concern (NCC)', 'Breaking Barriers at the Top of the World', '<p data-start=\"168\" data-end=\"470\"><strong data-start=\"168\" data-end=\"207\">Kathmandu, Nepal â€“ <strong data-start=\"186\" data-end=\"233\">May 18, 2025</strong></strong>Â â€“ In a powerful display of skill, resilience, and leadership, <strong data-start=\"270\" data-end=\"290\">Ms. Gelmu Sherpa</strong>, professional womenâ€™s climbing guide, has reached the <strong data-start=\"345\" data-end=\"381\">summit of Mount Everest (8,849m)</strong> â€” proudly carrying the <strong data-start=\"405\" data-end=\"427\">Nepal Care Concern</strong> logo to the very highest point on Earth.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"472\" data-end=\"733\">This remarkable achievement is more than a personal triumph. It is a beacon of inspiration for women in mountaineering, a testament to the strength of Nepalâ€™s guiding community, and a celebration of the dedication required to conquer the worldâ€™s tallest peak.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"735\" data-end=\"1046\">By standing on Everestâ€™s summit, Ms. Sherpa not only represented the spirit of adventure but also showcased the cause of <strong data-start=\"856\" data-end=\"878\">Nepal Care Concern</strong>, amplifying its message from the rooftop of the world. Her courage, determination, and unyielding energy embody the qualities we deeply admire and strive to promote.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1048\" data-end=\"1279\">We extend our <strong data-start=\"1062\" data-end=\"1115\">heartfelt respect, gratitude, and congratulations</strong> to Ms. Gelmu Sherpa on this historic accomplishment. Her journey is a shining example that with perseverance and passion, even the highest dreams can be reached</p>', 'Congratulations on this historic accomplishment!', 'top-10-great-reasons-to-visit-nepal', '1741154338569', 32, NULL, 0, 2, NULL, 'gel-5H4nO.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 115, 'en', '2025-03-05 05:58:58', '2025-12-13 08:02:41'),
(166, '2025-08-08 02:49:39', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Empower women', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For decades, Nepalâ€™s trekking and mountaineering industry has been dominated by men, with women facing limited opportunities, unequal wages, and societal barriers that discouraged them from pursuing careers in adventure tourism. A case in history, when the first of western visitors arrived in Rolwaling valley, the women too wanted to participate in the portering jobs but were denied by men. Thus they used to sleep with their head strap under the pillow and wake up in the middle of the night to walk miles to join the expedition as porters and eventually built a strong economic foundation for their families.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">At Lhakpa Trekking, we are deeply committed promoting gender equality in Nepalâ€™s adventure tourism industry. The company is co-founded byÂ <strong>Lhakpa Sherpa</strong>, a professional female trekking guide, and actively works towards increasing womenâ€™s participation in trekking and mountaineeringâ€”a field traditionally dominated by men.Â </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Lhakpa Trekking hires and trains female trekking guides and porters, providing them with equal opportunities, fair wages, and career growth. By breaking gender barriers in adventure tourism, the company ensures that women can pursue careers as professional guides with the same recognition as their male counterparts. Additionally, women-led treks are available, offering a comfortable and supportive experience for female travelers who prefer to trek with female guides.Â </p>', 'For decades, Nepalâ€™s trekking and mountaineering industry has been dominated by men, with women facing limited opportunities, unequal wages, and societal barriers that discouraged them from pursuing careers in adventure tourism. A case in history, when the first of western visitors arrived in Rolwaling valley, the women too wanted to participate in the portering jobs but were denied by men. Thus they used to sleep with their head strap under the pillow and wake up in the middle of the night to walk miles to join the expedition as porters and eventually built a strong economic foundation for their families.', 'images', '1741159360862', 33, NULL, 0, 34, NULL, 'a-JssR8.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-03-05 07:22:40', '2025-08-08 18:49:59'),
(167, '2025-08-08 02:54:06', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Women in adventure', NULL, '<p data-start=\"113\" data-end=\"553\">opportunities for women in trekking operations. Safety and inclusiveness are key priorities, creating an environment where all trekkersâ€”regardless of genderâ€”are treated with respect and professionalism. By maintaining a strong focus on gender balance, Lhakpa Trekking promotes an industry where women are not just participants but leaders in adventure tourism.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"555\" data-end=\"899\">Beyond hiring female guides, Lhakpa Trekking in collaboration with <a href=\"https://www.nepalcareconcern.org/\">NCC </a>is involved in training and education programs that help women develop skills in trekking, mountaineering, and tourism management. The company also supports women entrepreneurs by partnering with women-run lodges, homestays, and small businesses in remote trekking regions.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"901\" data-end=\"1036\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">These initiatives help strengthen economic independence and provide sustainable career paths for women in Nepalâ€™s mountain communities.</p>', 'For decades, Nepalâ€™s trekking and mountaineering industry has been dominated by men, with women facing limited opportunities, unequal wages, and societal barriers that discouraged them from pursuing careers in adventure tourism. A case in history, when the first of western visitors arrived in Rolwaling valley, the women too wanted to participate in the portering jobs but were denied by men. Thus they used to sleep with their head strap under the pillow and wake up in the middle of the night to walk miles to join the expedition as porters and eventually built a strong economic foundation for their families.', 'our-mission', '1741162555750', 33, NULL, 0, 35, NULL, 'h-s8sWT.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-03-05 08:15:55', '2025-08-08 18:57:09'),
