(210, '2025-08-15 12:30:24', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Why Lhakpa Trekking Prioritizes Safety ?', 'quality trek', '<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li data-start=\"124\" data-end=\"277\"><strong data-start=\"124\" data-end=\"144\">Protecting Lives</strong><br data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"147\">The Himalayas are beautiful yet unpredictable. Keeping trekkers safe is our foremost duty, ensuring everyone returns home healthy.</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"279\" data-end=\"475\"><strong data-start=\"279\" data-end=\"314\">Preserving Trust and Reputation</strong><br data-start=\"314\" data-end=\"317\">Decades of experience have shown that a strong safety record builds trust with clients, partners, and local communities, and keeps our operations sustainable.</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"477\" data-end=\"610\"><strong data-start=\"477\" data-end=\"505\">Enhancing the Experience</strong><br data-start=\"505\" data-end=\"508\">When safety is assured, trekkers can fully enjoy the landscapes and culture without unnecessary worry.</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"612\" data-end=\"762\"><strong data-start=\"612\" data-end=\"632\">Minimising Risks</strong><br data-start=\"632\" data-end=\"635\">By proactively managing altitude sickness, accidents, and other hazards, we reduce emergencies and medical issues on the trail.</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"764\" data-end=\"909\"><strong data-start=\"764\" data-end=\"801\">Supporting Communities and Nature</strong><br data-start=\"801\" data-end=\"804\">Safe, responsible trekking helps protect the environment and maintains respectful ties with local people.</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"911\" data-end=\"1027\"><strong data-start=\"911\" data-end=\"934\">Caring for Our Team</strong><br data-start=\"934\" data-end=\"937\">Strict safety protocols protect our guides and staff, boosting morale and professionalism</li>\r\n</ul>', 'quality trek', 'why-lhakpa-trekking-prioritizes-safety', '1752985614564', 30, NULL, 0, 65, NULL, 'mmmm-qO3wf.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-07-20 14:11:54', '2025-08-15 16:30:41'),
(211, '2025-07-20 10:22:23', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Proper Guiding Skills', 'Safety & Security', '<p data-start=\"60\" data-end=\"225\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><em>At Lhakpa Trekking, our guides serve not only as trail leaders but as your primary safety officers, decision-makers, and caretakers throughout your mountain journey.</em></span></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"227\" data-end=\"385\"><strong data-start=\"227\" data-end=\"265\">Risk Assessment and Route Planning</strong><br data-start=\"265\" data-end=\"268\">Our guides meticulously evaluate risks and design routes to ensure the safest and most efficient trekking experience.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"387\" data-end=\"597\"><strong data-start=\"387\" data-end=\"410\">Altitude Management</strong><br data-start=\"410\" data-end=\"413\">We prioritise acclimatisation through gradual ascents, incorporation of additional rest days, and regular health monitoring using tools such as pulse oximeters and symptom assessments.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"599\" data-end=\"857\"><strong data-start=\"599\" data-end=\"635\">First Aid and Emergency Response</strong><br data-start=\"635\" data-end=\"638\">All guides are certified in high-altitude first aid and proficient in the use of emergency equipment, including Gamow bags and satellite phones. They are fully trained to coordinate helicopter evacuations when necessary.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"859\" data-end=\"1065\"><strong data-start=\"859\" data-end=\"903\">Local Knowledge and Cultural Sensitivity</strong><br data-start=\"903\" data-end=\"906\">Our team possesses deep understanding of local terrain, customs, and languages, enabling them to prevent potential issues and enhance your cultural experience.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1067\" data-end=\"1250\"><strong data-start=\"1067\" data-end=\"1087\">Group Management</strong><br data-start=\"1087\" data-end=\"1090\">Guides maintain group cohesion, monitor early signs of fatigue, illness, or psychological stress, and make decisions that prioritise the welfare of all members.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1252\" data-end=\"1397\"><strong data-start=\"1252\" data-end=\"1269\">Communication</strong><br data-start=\"1269\" data-end=\"1272\">Through clear instructions and daily briefings, our guides keep every member well-informed and confident throughout the trek.</p>', 'for safety travel', 'proper-guiding-skills', '1752985836930', 30, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'a-UjtXt.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-07-20 14:15:36', '2025-07-20 14:22:40'),
(212, '2025-07-20 10:55:35', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Proper Guiding Skills', 'quality guiding skill', '<p data-start=\"88\" data-end=\"229\">At Lhakpa Trekking, our guides are more than trail leaders â€” they are your safety officers, caretakers, and decision-makers in the Himalayas.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"231\" data-end=\"371\"><strong data-start=\"231\" data-end=\"267\">Risk Assessment &amp; Route Planning</strong><br data-start=\"267\" data-end=\"270\">They carefully plan routes and assess conditions to keep each trek as safe and efficient as possible.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"373\" data-end=\"530\"><strong data-start=\"373\" data-end=\"396\">Altitude Management</strong><br data-start=\"396\" data-end=\"399\">By setting a gradual pace, adding rest days, and monitoring health with pulse oximeters, our guides help prevent altitude sickness.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"532\" data-end=\"741\"><strong data-start=\"532\" data-end=\"559\">First Aid &amp; Emergencies</strong><br data-start=\"559\" data-end=\"562\">All guides are certified in high-altitude first aid and trained to use emergency tools like Gamow bags and satellite phones, and can coordinate helicopter evacuations when needed.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"743\" data-end=\"902\"><strong data-start=\"743\" data-end=\"781\">Local Knowledge &amp; Cultural Respect</strong><br data-start=\"781\" data-end=\"784\">Deep familiarity with local terrain, customs, and language helps avoid problems and enriches your cultural experience.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"904\" data-end=\"1100\"><strong data-start=\"904\" data-end=\"940\">Group Management &amp; Communication</strong><br data-start=\"940\" data-end=\"943\">They keep groups together, watch for signs of fatigue or illness, and provide daily briefings to ensure everyone feels informed and confident on the journey</p>', 'Travel in secure', 'gggg', '1752985884593', 30, NULL, 0, 1, NULL, 'proper-SMdSL.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-07-20 14:16:25', '2025-07-20 14:55:51'),
(213, '2025-12-15 01:57:24', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Spain Italy', 'Guest coordinateur', '<p data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"26\"><strong data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"26\">Michele â€“ Coordinateur</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"28\" data-end=\"275\">Michele is an experienced globetrotter from Italy, passionate about travel and cultural discovery. After studying tourism, he spent 20 years in Spain and worked 15 years as a tour guide across countries like Egypt, Mexico, Brazil, and many more.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"277\" data-end=\"557\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">In 2015, a six-month solidarity journey brought him to Nepal, where he met Mingmar and formed an immediate friendship. Captivated by Nepalâ€™s peaceful nature and warm people, he has returned often for trekking and volunteer work with childrenâ€™s homes, making Nepal his second home.</p>', 'Experienced Global Guide', 'spain-italy', '1753789397816', 39, NULL, 0, 66, NULL, 'download-10-jok5y.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-07-29 21:28:17', '2025-12-15 18:58:00'),
(214, '2025-10-17 12:19:00', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Switzerland', NULL, '<p data-start=\"82\" data-end=\"477\">At Lhakpa Trekking, our guest collectors and guest coordinators are much more than collaborators or representatives. They are valued guests whose stories, experiences, and passion enrich our journey together. For us, they become part of the Lhakpa Trekking familyâ€”a bond that lasts far beyond a single trip, built on shared respect, friendship, and a love for the mountains that endures forever.</p>', 'At Lhakpa Trekking, our guest collectors and guest coordinators are not just partnersâ€”they are cherished guests and part of our family forever.', 'switzerland', '1753794413960', 39, NULL, 0, 2, NULL, 'swiss-iSiny.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-07-29 22:51:53', '2025-10-17 16:25:22'),
(215, '2025-12-02 12:20:47', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Korea', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'korea', '1754383700580', 39, NULL, 0, 67, NULL, 'download-7-mIIzN.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2025-08-05 18:33:20', '2025-12-02 17:20:56'),
(216, '2025-08-10 09:15:33', 1, 'single', NULL, 'On Everest Terre d\'Espoir Armor', 'Thanks for the honesty, hard work, and empathy that TEA embodies', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Our IFMGA mountain guide, Mr Anup Gurung, successfully reached the summit of Everest. At the top of the world, he proudly displayed the logo of TEA (the donor of NCC).</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We extend our heartfelt gratitude and congratulations to Mr. Gurung for this remarkable achievement, and we wish him every success in his future expeditions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We remain deeply grateful to the family of TEA and to everyone who supports TEA and NCC. Your contributions, no matter how small, truly change the lives of village students in the mountains. We also sincerely thank our donor association, TEA.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By taking the TEA logo to the summit, we wanted to show the honesty, hard work, and empathy that TEA embodies â€” from the top of the world. Today, thanks to Mr. Anup Gurung, this dream became a reality. Our greatest happiness lies in seeing students in remote villages enjoy a more comfortable and hopeful life, and for that, we thank everyone who has contributed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This gesture has given us a moment we will always cherish. For many of us, standing on Everest is a lifelong dream that may never come true â€” yet through this act, it feels as if a part of us truly reached the highest point on Earth.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This climb reflects not only the courage and dedication of our professional guide but also our deep respect and appreciation for TEA and everyone â€” whether regular or occasional supporters â€” who help TEA and NCC continue their mission.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">From the bottom of our hearts, thank you. This is more than just a climb; it is a powerful symbol of shared hope, vision, and unity. Your support will always be remembered and valued</p>', 'Terre d\'Espoir Armor is the parents of NCC.', 'terre-despoir-armor', '1754796632959', 32, NULL, 0, 68, '1754796632.jpg', 'anup-tea-uwP11.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 40, 'en', '2025-08-10 13:15:32', '2025-12-11 07:06:02'),
(217, '2025-08-10 09:54:40', 1, 'single', NULL, 'Top of the World â€” Once Again!', 'With LOGO', '<p data-start=\"186\" data-end=\"449\"><strong data-start=\"186\" data-end=\"233\">Kathmandu, Nepal â€“ May 18, 2025, 10:12 a.m.</strong> â€“ In an extraordinary feat of skill, endurance, and determination, <strong data-start=\"301\" data-end=\"320\">Mr. Anup Gurung</strong>, internationally certified <strong data-start=\"348\" data-end=\"372\">IFMGA mountain guide</strong>, stood on the summit of <strong data-start=\"397\" data-end=\"423\">Mount Everest (8,849m)</strong> for the <strong data-start=\"432\" data-end=\"446\">sixth time</strong>.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"451\" data-end=\"666\">With the world stretched out beneath him, Anup proudly unfurled the <strong data-start=\"519\" data-end=\"538\">Lhakpa Trekking</strong> logo at the very top of the globe â€” a symbol of our unwavering dedication to excellence, safety, and the spirit of adventure.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"668\" data-end=\"997\">This achievement is not just a personal milestone for Mr. Gurung, but a moment of pride for the entire Lhakpa Trekking family. We extend our <strong data-start=\"809\" data-end=\"858\">deepest gratitude and warmest congratulations</strong> to him for this remarkable accomplishment. His professionalism, courage, and perseverance continue to inspire climbers across the globe.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"999\" data-end=\"1125\">Hereâ€™s to many more summits and safe returns, Anup â€” may your footsteps in the snow continue to lead others to their dreams!</p>', 'Summit Success on Mt Everest 8848.86 m', 'stepped-up-to-the-top-of-the-world-once-again', '1754797308760', 32, NULL, 0, 69, '1754797308.jpg', 'l1-t4OOB.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 70, 'en', '2025-08-10 13:26:48', '2025-12-23 18:17:39'),
