(122, 'Everest Expedition 57 days', 'The Everest Expedition is a tough, two-month climb to the worldâ€™s highest peak. Climbers follow the southern route, use oxygen and ropes, and summit during a short weather window in May.', 57, '8,848.86M', 'spring', '4-6 hours', '2-15 Pax', 'Lodges & Tent', 'Sky Challenge', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Previous high-altitude experience is required (preferably above 6,000â€“7,000 m).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Strong physical &amp; mental fitness is essential for success and safety.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Proper acclimatisation is critical to avoid altitude sickness.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Unpredictable weather may delay summit plans â€” reserve days are necessary.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Technical gear &amp; climbing skills are mandatory for glacier and fixed rope travel.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experienced Sherpa support greatly increases safety and success chances.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Helicopter rescue insurance is required for emergencies.</p>', 'Private Vechile & air', 2, NULL, 'c9d9c0b3-a67f-47fd-a3f3-8656895f7ed9-iMA6X.jpeg', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical material</em></p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Everest Expedition is a demanding journey to the summit of Mount Everest (8,848.86 m), the highest mountain in the world. Most climbers take the southern route from Nepal, starting with a trek through the Khumbu region to Everest Base Camp. The climb includes dangerous sections like the Khumbu Icefall, Lhotse Face, and South Col, with several rotations between camps to adjust to the high altitude. Supplementary oxygen, fixed ropes, and support from experienced Sherpa guides are essential.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The expedition usually takes around two months, giving climbers time to acclimatize before attempting the summit during a short weather window in May or sometimes in autumn. It requires strong fitness, mountaineering experience, and mental toughness. Reaching the summit of Everest is a major achievement and a dream for many climbers around the world.</p>', 7, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 7: Extreme / High-Altitude Mountaineering Expeditions</strong>Â </p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Typically aboveâ€¯8,000 meters, often including 8,000ers (the worldâ€™s highest peaks)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: Long expeditions, often 4â€“8 weeks or more; climbing days can involve 10â€“16 hours of effort under extreme conditions</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Highly technical ice, rock, and mixed climbing; glaciers, crevasses, seracs, avalanche-prone slopes, and exposed ridgelines</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Only suitable for veteran mountaineers with extensive high-altitude and technical climbing experience, knowledge of fixed rope systems, self-rescue, and expedition logistics</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest, K2, Kangchenjunga, Lhotse, Dhaulagiri, and other major Himalayan 8,000-meter expeditions</li>\r\n</ul>', 'everest-expedition-57-days', 93, 'N208043', 'MT. EVEREST EXPEDITION (8,848.86M)', NULL, NULL, 'img-8051-p60cs.JPG', '1724424865_everest-speed-rnebY.jpg', '', 1057, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Test Your Limits, Touch the Sky\"', 1, NULL, '2023-07-28 20:57:00', '2025-12-23 15:06:48'),
(125, 'Island Peak 17 days', 'Island Peak (6,189 m) is an ideal first Himalayan climb. With expert guides and proper safety measures, it is suitable for fit beginners. Reaching the summit is a truly memorable achievement.', 17, '6,189', 'lukla / Lukla', '4-7 hours walking', '2-12', 'Tea House / Tent', 'Ideal climb', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Island Peak is a great first Himalayan climb for trekkers aiming to reach a real summit.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy breathtaking views of Everest, Lhotse, Ama Dablam, and surrounding peaks from the top.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Walk through beautiful Sherpa villages, forests, and high mountain valleys on the way to the base.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our experienced climbing guides ensure your safety with proper gear and training.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The itinerary includes enough rest days to help your body adjust to the altitude.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Perfect for Adventurous Beginners:<br>Reaching the summit is a powerful and emotional experience you will remember forever</p>', 'Plane /Private /Vechile /jeep', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Â Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). InsulatedÂ  gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p>Â <strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended).Â  Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders. WaterÂ  purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p>NB: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Join us on an exciting adventure to climb Island Peak (6,189 m), one of the most popular trekking peaks in Nepal. This is a great choice if you want to try your first real mountain climb in the Himalayas. We start with a beautiful flight to Lukla and trek through famous Sherpa villages, forests, and valleys with amazing views of Everest, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam. Before the climb, you have time to adjust to the altitude and enjoy the beauty of the Everest region. The climb is challenging but possible for anyone who is fit and determined. You will cross a glacier, use ropes, and reach the summit ridge, where the view is simply unforgettable. From the top, youâ€™ll see some of the highest mountains in the world. Our experienced guides will support you every step of the way. If you dream of standing on a Himalayan peak, Island Peak is the perfect place to start.</p>', 5, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 5: Very Strenuous/Challenging Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Above 6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 7â€“9 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: High-altitude passes, glaciers, and technical sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for seasoned trekkers with high-altitude experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Circuit with Pisang, Chulu peak via Thorong La Pass, Makalu Base Camp with Larkya peak, Mera peak, 3 passes with Lobuche, Island peak</li>\r\n</ul>', 'island-peak-17-days', 96, 'N208239', 'ISLAND PEAK EXPEDITION (6,476M)', NULL, 'Island Peak (6,189m/20,305ft), also known as Imja Tse, is a popular trekking peak located in the Khumbu region of Nepal.', '12-PB7hP.jpg', '3406485124island-8aLX2.png', '1755232730_island-peak-17-day1-JvkcG.pdf', 644, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Climb Safe Dream Big\"', 1, NULL, '2023-07-28 21:19:12', '2025-12-23 15:27:04'),
(128, 'Upper Mustang 19 days', 'Upper Mustang is a unique trek through arid landscapes and the walled city of Lo Manthang, rich in Tibetan culture and spiritual heritage', 19, '4048', 'Pokhara - Pokhara', '4-6 hours walking', '2-12', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Ancient Majesty', '<p>Lo Manthang: Explore the ancient walled city, the last forbidden kingdom of Nepal.</p>\r\n<p>Sky Caves: Mysterious caves carved into cliffs, holding ancient Buddhist artifacts.</p>\r\n<p>Tiji Festival: A three-day Buddhist festival promoting world peace.</p>\r\n<p>Muktinath Temple: A sacred site for both Hindus and Buddhists.</p>\r\n<p>Kaligandaki Gorge: One of the world\'s deepest canyons.</p>\r\n<p>Unique Landscapes: Arid terrain, towering cliffs andÂ  beautiful Himalayan views.</p>\r\n<p>Rich Tibetan Culture: Experience monasteries, prayer flags and traditional villages.</p>\r\n<p>Restricted Trekking Area: Requires special permits, offering an exclusive experience.</p>', 'Plane /Private /Vechile /jeep', 0, NULL, 'upper-mustang-19-days-rwX0R.png', NULL, '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why do we choose private transport instead of flights for the Mustang trek?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We prefer using private vehicles because road conditions have significantly improved in recent years, making land travel more reliable and comfortable. In contrast, mountain flights are often delayed or canceled due to unpredictable weather, causing unnecessary stress and schedule changes. Private transport is not only more dependable but also more affordable and flexible, allowing us to manage the itinerary smoothly and ensure a better experience for our guests.</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Upper Mustang, known as the \"Last Forbidden Kingdom,\" is a unique place where Tibetan-influenced culture is still well preserved. Set in Nepalâ€™s dry, high-altitude region, it features ancient monasteries, cave homes, and the historic walled city of Lo Manthang. As a restricted area, you must travel with a guide. It\'s also one of the few treks in Nepal you can do during the summer monsoon, offering a deep cultural and spiritual experience. This trek is less difficulties than round Mustang.</p>', 3, 5, '<p>Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p><strong>Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li>Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li>Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li>Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li>Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li>Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'upper-mustang-19-days', 99, 'N208233', 'UPPER MUSTANG Dolpo annapurna', NULL, 'The historical remote Mustang trek unseal the once Forbidden Kingdom of Mustang, tucked away from the rest of the world, lies just north of the main Himalayan range of Nepal.', 'artboard-1-IqBNl.png', '1749533434_15x1500-WM09V.jpg', '1753778615_upper-mustang-19-days-1okDh.pdf', 1070, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1800.00, 0, '\"Where Ancient Kingdoms - Meet the Himalayan Sky\"', 1, NULL, '2023-07-28 21:42:06', '2025-12-23 14:39:19'),
(131, 'Everest Base Camp Trek 16 days', 'Experience Everest Base Camp, surrounded by towering Himalayan peaks, while immersing yourself in rich Sherpa culture and traditionsâ€”a journey you will never forget.', 16, '5644', 'Kathmandu / Kathmandu', '4 -6 hours', '2-15 pax', 'Tea houses', 'Healing serenity', '<p data-start=\"104\" data-end=\"163\">Spectacular journey through Nepalâ€™s iconic Khumbu region.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"167\" data-end=\"239\">Ascent to Kala Patthar (5,644 m), the best viewpoint of Mount Everest.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"243\" data-end=\"304\">Pass the worldâ€™s highest webcam with live views of Everest.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"308\" data-end=\"390\">Stunning 360-degree panoramas of Everest, Lhotse, Pumori, and surrounding peaks.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"394\" data-end=\"463\">A challenging yet highly rewarding trek for true adventure seekers.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"467\" data-end=\"525\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Deep immersion in Himalayan landscapes and Sherpa culture.</p>', 'Private vehicle /Plane', 1, NULL, 'everest-base-camp-trek-15-days-ljoLs.png', NULL, 'altitude-chart-fsTeC.jpeg', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Everest Base Camp Trek is one of the most famous trekking routes in the Himalayas, offering access to the worldâ€™s highest mountain, Mount Everest (8,848.86â€¯m)â€”known as Sagarmatha in Nepali and Chomolungma in Sherpa (Tibetan). The mountain is considered sacred, and the local Sherpa people worship it as a god. The trek passes through Sagarmatha National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, reaching Everest Base Camp (5,364â€¯m), the starting point for climbing expeditions. The journey begins with a scenic flight to Lukla, followed by a trek along the Dudh Koshi River to Namche Bazaar, a historic trading centre and Sherpa cultural hub. The global trail is relatively easy, but the high altitude makes it challenging. An excursion at Namche for acclimatisation can be perfect. Nearby villages, including Khumjung and Khunde, reflect the regionâ€™s rich history and Sir Edmund Hillaryâ€™s humanitarian contributions. The Khumjung and Pangboche monasteries are notable for preserving well-known Yeti skulls, a fascinating local legend.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The trail passes numerous cultural landmarks, including mani stones, chortens, and monasteries. Pangboche Monastery, the oldest in the region, and Tengboche Monastery, the largest, are key spiritual highlights. Tengboche has long been the centre of Sherpa religious life and ceremonial gatherings, while Pangboche preserves centuries-old relics and legends of monks (Lama) meditating for decades. The route continues through Pheriche, Dingboche, Lobuche, and Gorak Shep, offering expansive views of Everest, Lhotse, Nuptse, Ama Dablam, Pumori, and Thamserku, alongside tales of local spirits and mountain guardians.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The ascent of Kala Patthar (5,545â€¯m) provides a close-up view of Everest. Combining breathtaking landscapes, Sherpa heritage, and high-altitude adventure, the trek delivers a safe, structured, and unforgettable Himalayan experience, enriched with cultural history, local legends, and spiritual traditions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â </p>', 4, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categoriesconsider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'everest-base-camp-trek-16-days', 101, 'N208217', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mg-0151-EMsyh.jpg', '1756538698_mg-0098-NhmoB.jpg', '1753696699_everest-base-camp-trek-16-days-yNkV7.pdf', 4445, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1220.00, 0, 'â€œBeyond Limits, Into Everest\"', 1, '<p>latest information comes here</p>', '2023-07-30 17:05:06', '2025-12-24 10:12:30'),
(132, 'Langtang Trek & Yala Peak 13 days', 'Yala Peak invites you to explore vibrant Himalayan culture amidst stunning mountain landscapes. Reach the summit for breathtaking panoramic views of some of Nepalâ€™s most majestic peaks.', 13, '5732', 'Syabru besi / Dhunche', '4-6 hours walking', '2-15', 'Tea House /camping', 'Majestic Adventure', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Langtang region, combining cultural immersion, beautiful landscapes</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trekkers experience Sherpa and Tamang villages, Buddhist monasteries</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Langtang National Park, home to red pandas and Himalayan black bears.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Best undertaken in spring or autumn, this trek is ideal for those seeking scenic beauty, cultural exploration and Himalayan trekking challenges.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Amazing Summit Views: At 5,732 metres, you can see amazing wide views of big Himalayan mountains like Shishapangma, Langtang Lirung and Ganesh Himal.</p>', 'private bus/car', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</em></p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Langtang region, home to Yala Peak, offers an unforgettable trekking experience filled with rich culture and beautiful nature. Along the trail, youâ€™ll walk through vibrant rhododendron forests and visit traditional Tamang and Tibetan villages, where centuries-old monasteries add a peaceful, spiritual touch. The scenery unfolds with sweeping landscape views of towering Himalayan giants like Langtang Lirung (7227 m), Ganesh Himal, Dorje Lakpa and Tserko Ri (4984 m). Crystal-clear glacial rivers and vibrant alpine meadows envelop you, while the pristine Langtang Glacier near Kyanjin Gompa enhances the regionâ€™s enchanting allure. This journey perfectly balances cultural immersion with beautiful mountain landscapes, all at a moderate altitude that makes it accessible yet deeply rewarding.</p>', 5, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 5: Very Strenuous/Challenging Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Above 6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 7â€“9 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: High-altitude passes, glaciers, and technical sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for seasoned trekkers with high-altitude experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Circuit with Pisang, Chulu peak via Thorong La Pass, Makalu Base Camp with Larkya peak, Mera peak, 3 passes with Lobuche, Island peak</li>\r\n</ul>', 'langtang-trek-yala-peak-13-days', 102, 'N208240', 'YALA PEAK Langtang trek', NULL, 'A great way to experience the beauty of the Langtang region and to challenge yourself with a relatively easy climb.', '1212-YJ3mT.jpg', '1755233854_untitled-2hgh-CXvt4.jpg', '1755233854_langtang-trek-baBn6.pdf', 689, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'â€œTrek Beyond, Experience Yala Peak\"', 1, NULL, '2023-07-30 17:10:47', '2025-12-23 15:27:13'),
(141, 'Everest 3 Passes Trek 20 days', 'Traversing a challenging 103 mile (166 km) route, the trek offers an immersive experience into the harsh beauty of the Himalayas, where rugged trails, icy winds, and soaring altitudes test both physical endurance and mental resilience', 20, '5,644', 'Lukla - Lukla', '6-8 hours', '4-10 Pax', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Embrace Legends', '<p data-start=\"42\" data-end=\"97\">Cross three high passes: Renjo La, Cho La, Kongma La.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"101\" data-end=\"144\">Reach Everest Base Camp and Kala Patthar.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"148\" data-end=\"187\">Explore Gokyo Valley and Gokyo Lakes.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"191\" data-end=\"226\">Walk beside the Ngozumpa Glacier.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"230\" data-end=\"283\">Climb Gokyo Ri and Chhukung Ri for panoramic views.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"287\" data-end=\"327\">Visit Thame and Tengboche monasteries.</p>', 'Private Vechile / flight', 1, NULL, 'everest-3-high-base-camp-trek-19-days-kGHwO.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Everest Three High Passes Trek is one of Nepalâ€™s most spectacular and rewarding trekking circuits, leading deep into the heart of the Everest region. The journey offers high-altitude landscapes, vast glaciers, and iconic Himalayan mountains. Mount Everest (8,848.86â€¯m), the worldâ€™s highest peak, is known as Sagarmatha in Nepali and Chomolungma in Sherpa (Tibetan). The mountain is considered sacred, and the local Sherpa people worship it as a god. The adventure begins with a scenic flight from Kathmandu to Lukla, situated to the north-east of the capital, a bustling Sherpa town and the main gateway to the region. From Lukla, the trail follows the north-flowing Dudh Koshi River, crosses the famous Hillary suspension bridges, and passes through traditional Sherpa villages before reaching Namche Bazaar, the vibrant Sherpa capital. The global trail is relatively easy, but the high altitude makes it challenging. An excursion at Namche for acclimatisation can be perfect.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The trek crosses three legendary and challenging high passes: Renjo La (5,360â€¯m), Cho La (5,420â€¯m), and Kongma La (5,535â€¯m). Highlights include Everest Base Camp and Kala Patthar (5,545â€¯m). The ascent of Kala Patthar offers unforgettable close-up views of Everest. The route passes the serene Gokyo Valley, sacred Gokyo Lakes, the vast Ngozumpa Glacier, the longest glacier in the world, and the Khumbu Glacier. Ascents to Gokyo Ri and Chhukung Ri provide sweeping views of Everest, Lhotse, Makalu, Cho Oyu, and surrounding mountains. The trek also showcases Sherpa culture, with ancient monasteries such as Thame (Upper Pangboche) and the iconic Tengboche Monastery, as well as mani stones and chortens along the trail.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The return journey passes Pheriche, Pangboche, and Tengboche, reaching Lukla, where the adventure concludes with a sense of accomplishment and awe. This trek leaves lasting memories of towering peaks, rich Sherpa culture, and the extraordinary landscapes of the Everest region.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â </p>', 4, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'everest-3-passes-trek-20-days', 111, 'N208219', 'EVEREST REGION', NULL, NULL, 'img20231112125848-XVKjD.jpg', '1756537730_img20231110171037-WTbuv.jpg', '1753696529_everest-3-high-pass-trek-19-day1-1TOwy.pdf', 686, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1325.00, 0, 'â€œHigh Passes, Higher Dreams\"', 0, NULL, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-24 02:23:45'),
(144, 'Mustang Round  20 days', 'Upper round Mustang, the \"Last Forbidden Kingdom,\" reveals preserved Tibetan culture amid Nepalâ€™s arid Himalayan terrain. Its ancient monasteries, cave dwellings, and Lo Manthang offer a unique, monsoon-season tre', 20, '4065', 'Pokhara - Pokhara', '4-6 hours walking', '2-12', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Forbidden Kingdom', '<p>Lo Manthang: Explore the ancient walled city, the last forbidden kingdom of Nepal.</p>\r\n<p>Sky Caves: Mysterious caves carved into cliffs, holding ancient Buddhist artifacts.</p>\r\n<p>Tiji Festival: A three-day Buddhist festival promoting world peace.</p>\r\n<p>Muktinath Temple: A sacred site for both Hindus and Buddhists.</p>\r\n<p>Kaligandaki Gorge: One of the world\'s deepest canyons.</p>\r\n<p>Unique Landscapes: Arid terrain, towering cliffs and amazing Himalayan views.</p>\r\n<p>Rich Tibetan Culture: Experience monasteries, prayer flags and traditional villages.</p>\r\n<p>Restricted Trekking Area: Requires special permits, offering an exclusive experience.</p>', 'private bus/car', 1, NULL, 'mustang-round-20-days-l9rSV.png', NULL, '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why do we choose private transport instead of flights for the Mustang trek?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We prefer using private vehicles because road conditions have significantly improved in recent years, making land travel more reliable and comfortable. In contrast, mountain flights are often delayed or canceled due to unpredictable weather, causing unnecessary stress and schedule changes. Private transport is not only more dependable but also more affordable and flexible, allowing us to manage the itinerary smoothly and ensure a better experience for our guests.</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Upper Mustang, known as the \"Last Forbidden Kingdom,\" is a unique place where Tibetan-influenced culture is still well preserved. Set in Nepalâ€™s dry, high-altitude region, it features ancient monasteries, cave homes, and the historic walled city of Lo Manthang. As a restricted area, you must travel with a guide. It\'s also one of the few treks in Nepal you can do during the summer monsoon, offering a deep cultural and spiritual experience.</p>', 4, 5, '<p>Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li>Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li>Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li>Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li>Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li>Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'mustang-round-20-days', 114, 'N208234', 'MUSTANG REGION', NULL, NULL, 'artboard-1-uVJJO.png', '1752471894_untitled-3-opyx3.jpg', '1753778505_mustang-round-20-day1-9f9lE.pdf', 507, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1900.00, 0, 'â€œForbidden Kingdom Revealed\"', 1, NULL, '2024-01-08 07:13:05', '2025-12-23 14:40:49'),
(147, 'Pisang Peak & Thorong La 17 days', 'The Pisang Peak Expedition is a thrilling journey into the heart of the Himalayas. It combines adventure, culture, and breathtaking mountain views for an unforgettable experience.', 17, '6,091M', 'Besisahar / Pokhara', '4-7 hours walking', '2 -15', 'Tea House /camping', 'Peak Journey', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â <!--[endif]-->A thrilling Himalayan expedition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><!--[endif]-->Climb Pisang Peak (6,091â€¯m).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy panoramic Himalayan views.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore traditional villages and local culture.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trek through valleys, forests, and alpine meadows.</p>', 'private bus/car', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</em></p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Pisang Peak Expedition is an unforgettable journey for trekkers and climbers. Starting in green valleys, the trail passes through forests, alpine meadows, and traditional villages before reaching the high-altitude terrain.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The highlight is summiting Pisang Peak (6,091â€¯m), offering breathtaking views of the Himalayas. Along the way, experience local culture and dramatic landscapes, making this expedition a truly memorable Himalayan adventure.</p>', 5, 4, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 5: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 5: Very Strenuous/Challenging Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"square\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Above 6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 7â€“9 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: High-altitude passes, glaciers, and technical sections</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for seasoned trekkers with high-altitude experience</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Circuit with Pisang, Chulu peak via Thorong La Pass, Makalu Base Camp with Larkya peak, Mera peak, 3 passes with Lobuche, Island peak</li>\r\n</ul>', 'pisang-peak-thorong-la-17-days', 117, 'N208246', 'Pisang Peak Climbing', NULL, NULL, 'img-5011-0wGQ7.jpeg', '1705768007_img-5012-RCnNF.jpeg', '1755442761_pisang-peak-expedition-pdf-ljwAP.pdf', 204, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Conquer Heights, Embrace Himalayas\"', 1, NULL, '2024-01-08 10:42:06', '2025-12-23 15:27:26'),
(149, 'Himlung Himal Expedition 29 day', 'Climb the thrilling Himlung in a remote valley. Explore Tibetan villages, dramatic terrain, and enjoy panoramic views of towering Himalayan peaks.', 29, '7,126M', 'Besisahar / Bessisahar', '4-6 hours walking', NULL, 'Tea House /camping', 'Himalayan Challenge', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A thrilling 7126 m Himalayan peak, ideal for experienced climbers aiming for technical, yet achievable, summits in a remote setting.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore centuries-old monasteries, stone houses, and colourful prayer flags in these hidden Tibetan-influenced settlements.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trek through a rarely visited valley offering a dramatic change in sceneryâ€”deep gorges, alpine meadows, and towering snow peaks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Constant views of the Manaslu range, Annapurna massif, and the hidden peaks of the Damodar Himal throughout the journey.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience traditional Buddhist rituals, local hospitality, and a peaceful escape from the crowded trails of the popular circuits</p>', 'private bus/car', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</em></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%;\">Deep within the Annapurna Conservation Area lies the beautiful Nar-Phu Valley, a hidden gem where time seems to stand still. This remote, serene region rich in Tibetan culture invites trekkers to explore ancient villages, peaceful monasteries, and amazing mountain landscapes. Trekking here feels like stepping into a timeless story. Untouched and peaceful, Nar-Phu offers an authentic Himalayan experience for those seeking natural beauty, spiritual calm, and the soft whispers of the mountains. The expedition culminates with the thrilling ascent of Himlung Himal, a majestic peak that challenges climbers and rewards them with spectacular landscsape views and an unforgettable adventure.</span></p>', 6, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 6: Expedition-Level / Extreme Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square; text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Altitude: Above 7000 meters, often including peaks over 7,000 meters</li>\r\n<li>Duration: 8â€“12 hours of walking/climbing per day, sometimes with multi-day ascents</li>\r\n<li>Terrain: Technical climbing sections, glaciers, icefalls, exposed ridges, and potentially use of fixed ropes</li>\r\n<li>Experience Required: Only for highly experienced mountaineers with prior technical climbing and high-altitude expedition experience</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"3\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Examples: Ama Dablam, Himlung Himal, Baruntse expedition, Langtang Lirung Annapurna II, III, Gyachung Kang,</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â </p>', 'himlung-himal-expedition-29-day', 119, 'N208242', 'Himlung Himal Expedition', NULL, NULL, 'himlung-himal-expedition-CxNUq.jpg', '1705767515_img-5006-b3wnR.jpeg', '1755250176_himlung-himal-expedition-29-da1-gDN6F.pdf', 330, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Dare to Dream, Climb Himlung\"', 1, NULL, '2024-01-09 05:42:21', '2025-12-23 15:04:30'),
(152, 'Tamang Heritage & Langtang 15 days', 'The Langtang Trek is a popular Himalayan route offering breathtaking views of alpine forests, snow-capped peaks, and scenic valleys. Along the way, trekkers experience authentic Tamang culture through', 15, '4984', 'Shyabru Besi - Dunche', '4/6 hours waliking', '2-15', 'Lodge / teahouse', 'Cultural adventure', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience traditional Tamang language, music, festivals and Buddhist practices unique to this Himalayan ethnic group.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Visit charming Tamang villages along the trek, where warm hospitality and age-old customs are still preserved.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore ancient monasteries and prayer sites that reflect the deep spiritual roots of the Tamang people.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trek through lush rhododendron forests, alpine meadows and landscape views of Langtangâ€™s snow-capped peaks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Langtang Trek offers a perfect mix of cultural immersion and thrilling mountain trekking in a less crowded, pristine region.</p>', 'Bus. Jeep', 1, NULL, 'tamang-heritage-langtang-15-days-aJ9bZ.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Native to Nepalâ€™s Himalayan highlands, the Tamang people are an indigenous ethnic group celebrated for their vivid customs, rich culture and deep-rooted Buddhist beliefs. Their distinctive language, traditional music, festivals and craftsmanship reflect centuries of spiritual legacy and harmonious coexistence with nature, especially in the Langtang region where they have lived for millennia.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Langtang Trek is a popular Himalayan route offering beautiful views of alpine forests, snow-capped peaks and scenic valleys. Along the way, trekkers experience authentic Tamang culture through visits to vibrant villages and historic Buddhist monasteries, blending adventure with cultural immersion.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Adding to this rich journey, Gosaikunda, a sacred alpine lake revered in both Hindu and Buddhist traditions, provides a serene spiritual stop surrounded by pristine mountain beauty. Nearby, Shivapuri National Park offers lush forests, diverse wildlife and peaceful trails just outside Kathmandu, perfect for nature lovers seeking tranquillity and biodiversity.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Together, these destinations showcase Nepalâ€™s unique blend of cultural heritage, spiritual depth and beautiful natural landscapes.</p>', 3, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'tamang-heritage-langtang-15-days', 122, 'N208214', 'Tamang Heritage Trek', NULL, NULL, 'artboard-1-iDtDt.jpg', '1705758069_img-4969-jm8y8.jpeg', '1760753975_pdf-arouu.pdf', 465, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 795.00, 0, '\"Walk the Sacred Trails of Tamang Heritage and Himalayan Beauty\"', 1, NULL, '2024-01-09 06:22:17', '2025-12-23 14:41:46'),
(157, 'Manaslu Trek and Larkey Peak 21 days', 'Discover the peaceful Manaslu region, home to sacred sites and breathtaking views from Larkya La Pass. Climbers can summit Larkya Peak for an unforgettable Himalayan adventure', 21, '6249 m', 'Machhakhola / Jagat', '4-7 hours walking', '4-10 Pax', 'Tea House /camping', 'â€œSilent Majestyâ€', '<p>Manaslu (8,163 m) is a high mountain with fewer crowds than Annapurna.</p>\r\n<p>The Larkya Peak trek goes through a quiet and beautiful valley.</p>\r\n<p>Local villages show different cultures and mountain lifestyles.</p>\r\n<p>A peaceful monastery adds a spiritual feel to the journey.</p>\r\n<p>Larkya La Pass (5,135 m) is the hardest part, with great mountain views.</p>\r\n<p>Climbing Larkya Peak is an exciting challenge with amazing scenery.</p>', 'private bus/car', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</em></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%;\">Explore the quiet and beautiful Manaslu region, a peaceful alternative to the busy trekking routes. Trek through remote valleys and traditional villages rich in culture. Visit the Sama Gompa monastery and the sacred Pungyen Gumba cave, both important spiritual sites. Cross the challenging but rewarding Larkya La Pass, enjoying beautiful mountain views. For climbers, ascend Larkya Peak for spectacular views of the surrounding high mountains. This journey offers a perfect blend of nature, culture, and adventure for an unforgettable Himalayan experience.</span></p>', 5, 5, '<p>Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p><strong>Grade 5: Very Strenuous/Challenging Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li>Altitude: Above 6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li>Duration: 7â€“9 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li>Terrain: High-altitude passes, glaciers, and technical sections</li>\r\n<li>Experience Required: Suitable for seasoned trekkers with high-altitude experience</li>\r\n<li>Examples: Annapurna Circuit with Pisang, Chulu peak via Thorong La Pass, Makalu Base Camp with Larkya peak, Mera peak, 3 passes with Lobuche, Island peak</li>\r\n</ul>', 'manaslu-trek-and-larkey-peak-21-days', 127, 'N208241', 'Larkey Peak Climbing', NULL, NULL, 'm-PJYmX.jpg', '1705757669_img-4965-JeTK9.jpeg', '1755234641_manaslu-trek-9zWJU.pdf', 324, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Culture, and Peak Adventure\"', 1, NULL, '2024-01-09 09:17:00', '2025-12-23 15:27:41');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_details` (`id`, `trip_title`, `sub_title`, `duration`, `max_altitude`, `best_season`, `walking_per_day`, `group_size`, `accommodation`, `route`, `trip_highlight`, `peak_name`, `trip_type`, `starting_price`, `trip_map`, `trip_video`, `trip_chart`, `trip_excerpt`, `trip_content`, `trip_grade`, `rating`, `status_text`, `uri`, `ordering`, `trip_code`, `meta_key`, `meta_title`, `meta_description`, `banner`, `thumbnail`, `trip_pdf`, `visiter`, `is_draft`, `status`, `trip_of_the_month`, `video_status`, `show_in_home`, `start_date`, `price`, `price_euro`, `flight`, `discount`, `guided`, `latest_info`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(159, 'Manaslu Expedition 32 days', 'An unforgettable journey to Nepalâ€™s majestic Mt. Manasluâ€”trek through charming villages, cross a stunning high pass, acclimate to the altitude, then conquer the summit before flying back to Kathmandu by helicopter.', 32, '8,163m', 'Spring/Autumn', '3-7 Hours', '2 - 15 People', 'Tea House/Tents', 'Conquer Manaslu', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Physical Fitness: Requires strong endurance and prior high-altitude experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Acclimatization: Follow the schedule; never rush to prevent altitude sickness.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Weather: Be ready for sudden changes and possible delays.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Technical Skills: Glacier, crevasse and ice slope travel require proper training and gear.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Guides: Climb with experienced Sherpas for safety and success.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Environment: Respect nature and culture; pack out all waste.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Insurance: Must include travel, medical and high-altitude helicopter rescue.</p>', 'Private Vehicle / Helicaptor', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical material</em></p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Manaslu Expedition starts with a scenic trek from Dharapani in the Annapurna region, gradually ascending through remote villages and diverse landscapes toward the iconic Larkya La Pass (5106 m). Before crossing the Larkya la pass, an acclimatisation day is spent at Bhimthang (3,720 m) to help the body adjust safely to the altitude. The trail then proceeds to Samagaon and continues on to Manaslu Base Camp (4,800 m), where climbers make preparations for their ascent. The summit phase involves several rotations between high camps, followed by the final push to reach the 8,163 metre peak of Manaslu. After a successful summit, a helicopter flight provides a quick and scenic return to Kathmandu.</p>', 7, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Grade 7: Extreme / High-Altitude Mountaineering Expeditions</p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Typically aboveâ€¯8,000 meters, often including 8,000ers (the worldâ€™s highest peaks)</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: Long expeditions, often 4â€“8 weeks or more; climbing days can involve 10â€“16 hours of effort under extreme conditions</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Highly technical ice, rock, and mixed climbing; glaciers, crevasses, seracs, avalanche-prone slopes, and exposed ridgelines</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Only suitable for veteran mountaineers with extensive high-altitude and technical climbing experience, knowledge of fixed rope systems, self-rescue, and expedition logistics</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest, K2, Kangchenjunga, Lhotse, Dhaulagiri, and other major Himalayan 8,000-meter expeditions</li>\r\n</ul>', 'manaslu-expedition-32-days', 129, 'N208244', NULL, NULL, 'Manasalu Expedition', 'img-5051-qLHeN.jpeg', '1725280576_manaslu-exped-RbKAs.jpg', '', 613, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Adventure Awaits Above the Clouds!\"', 1, NULL, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-12-23 15:06:31'),
(163, 'Annapurna Classic Full 17 days', 'The Annapurna circuit is a dream for many mountain travelers, enjoying superb views of the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri and the ever-changing scenery', 17, '5416 M', 'Besishahar Pokhara', '4-6 hours walking', '2-15 pax', 'Lodges teahouse', 'Nature Awakening', '<p data-start=\"68\" data-end=\"122\">Journey from green valleys to high Himalayan deserts</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"125\" data-end=\"199\">Cross <strong data-start=\"131\" data-end=\"160\">Thorong La Pass (5,416 m)</strong> â€” a legendary high-altitude crossing</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"202\" data-end=\"268\">Encounter the living cultures of <strong data-start=\"235\" data-end=\"266\">Manang, Mustang &amp; Muktinath</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"271\" data-end=\"336\">Epic views of <strong data-start=\"285\" data-end=\"334\">Annapurna, Dhaulagiri, Manaslu &amp; Tilicho Peak</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"339\" data-end=\"435\"><strong data-start=\"339\" data-end=\"356\">Jump-up trips</strong> to <strong data-start=\"360\" data-end=\"402\">Ice Lake, Tatopani hot springs &amp; Lupra</strong>, ending in <strong data-start=\"414\" data-end=\"435\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Jomsom or Pokhara</strong></p>', 'Private Vechile / flight', 1, NULL, 'annapurna-classic-full-17-days-X7jcP.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"905\">The <strong data-start=\"122\" data-end=\"159\">Annapurna Full with Ice Lake Trek</strong> is an amazing journey through the Annapurna and Mustang regions, combining high mountains with rich cultural experiences. The trek starts in green valleys and traditional mountain villages, following the <strong data-start=\"368\" data-end=\"388\">Marsyangdi River</strong>. The route moves through varied landscapes to reach Manang, the largest village in the region, and an important place for acclimatisation. According to local legend, the surrounding peaks are said to be protected by guardian spirits, and villagers still perform rituals to honour them. From Manang, the journey continues along the Marsyangdi Valley before climbing toward <strong data-start=\"782\" data-end=\"811\">Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m)</strong>, with time built in for proper acclimatisation to make the ascent safer and more comfortable.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"907\" data-end=\"1284\">After crossing Thorong La Pass, the journey drops into the <strong data-start=\"966\" data-end=\"989\">Kali Gandaki Valley</strong>, home to the deepest gorge in the world and famous for its fossils. The sacred pilgrimage site Muktinath along the way, known for its temples, eternal flame, and 108 holy water spouts. Local stories say the flame has burned for centuries, protecting the valley and its people.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1286\" data-end=\"1914\">The journey then moved into the dry and culturally special lower Mustang region, known for its desert-like landscapes and strong Tibetan influence. Traditional villages such asÂ <strong data-start=\"1465\" data-end=\"1482\">Lupra Village</strong>, one of Nepalâ€™s last Bon communities, offer a glimpse into ancient spiritual practices and mountain life. Legends speak of hidden caves where monks meditated for decades and of sacred stones that grant blessings to those who pass. The trek concludes at <strong data-start=\"1736\" data-end=\"1752\">Mohare Danda</strong>, where the final sunrise over the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri ranges creates a calm and unforgettable end to this challenging yet rewarding Himalayan adventure.</p>', 4, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'annapurna-classic-full-17-days', 131, 'N20829', '#Poonhill #Annapurna_Trekking #Lhakpatrekking #Women_Empowerment #ActForTheBest', NULL, '#Women Empowerment Focus\r\n\r\nâ€œDiscover Nepal with Lhakpa Trekkingâ€”expert local guides, women-led teams, sustainable travel, and unforgettable Himalayan adventures designed with your safety in mind.â€', 'b-yp79A.png', '1752122475_3-fzOf9.jpg', '1760497551_annapurna-classic-full-17-day-Z7H3z.pdf', 1929, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 955.00, 0, '\"One Trail, a Thousand Landscapes\"', 1, NULL, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-23 15:40:37'),
(165, 'Annapurna B.C & Poonhill 15 days', 'This journey is ideal for those who want to enjoy the beauty of the Annapurna range without committing to challenging high-altitude trekking.', 15, '4130 meters', 'Pokhara - Pokhara', '4-6 hours', '2-15', 'Lodges. Teahouse', 'Himalayan Heartbeat', '<p data-start=\"71\" data-end=\"131\">Sunrise over <strong data-start=\"84\" data-end=\"110\">Annapurna &amp; Dhaulagiri</strong> from <strong data-start=\"116\" data-end=\"129\">Poon Hill</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"134\" data-end=\"193\"><strong data-start=\"134\" data-end=\"157\">Annapurna Base Camp</strong>, surrounded by majestic mountains</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"196\" data-end=\"267\">Iconic views of <strong data-start=\"212\" data-end=\"265\">Annapurna I, Machapuchare, Hiunchuli &amp; Dhaulagiri</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"270\" data-end=\"324\">Trails through forests, terraces, meadows &amp; glaciers</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"327\" data-end=\"381\">Authentic <strong data-start=\"337\" data-end=\"355\">Gurung &amp; Magar</strong> culture and hospitality</p>', 'Private Vechile / flight', 1, NULL, 'screenshot-2025-06-08-092202-lspq0.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"79\" data-end=\"639\">The Annapurna Base Camp and Balcony (ABC) Trek is a short and scenic journey with beautiful mountain views. The trek stays at relatively low altitudes, reaching a maximum of 4,230â€¯m, making it suitable for a wide range of people. The journey starts from Kathmandu to Pokhara, either by drive or flight, and then continues by road to Kimche, the starting point of the route. Along the way, the trail passes through terraced fields, rhododendron forests, and traditional Gurung and Magar villages, offering a harmonious blend of natural beauty and local culture.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"641\" data-end=\"1062\">Ghandruk is a large and well-known village in the region. A Gurung museum and a Buddhist monastery provide insights into local culture and traditions. The balcony section includes famous viewpoints such as Poon Hill. The sunrise from Poon Hill, with the golden morning light, is a memorable experience, offering views of Annapurna I, Annapurna South, Hiunchuli, Machhapuchhre (Fishtail), and the distant Dhaulagiri range.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1064\" data-end=\"1378\">The trek continues to Annapurna Base Camp, passing Machhapuchhre Base Camp along the way. Annapurna Base Camp sits in a natural mountain amphitheatre, surrounded by towering Himalayan mountains. Accessible, culturally rich, and visually striking, this trek offers a memorable Himalayan adventure in a short time.</p>', 3, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'annapurna-bc-poonhill-15-days', 133, 'N20807', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'img-1226-w0xe5-Gne2v.jpg', '1756532461_img-1230-2-HBRRc.jpg', '1753693283_poonhill-annapurna-1-MJW2Y.pdf', 726, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 921.00, 0, '\"Where Every Step Meets a Mountain Smile\"', 1, NULL, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-23 15:40:55'),
(166, 'Tamang Heritage Trek 11 days', 'Tamang people are an indigenous ethnic group celebrated for their vivid customs, rich culture, and deep-rooted Buddhist beliefs', 11, '3165', 'Shyabru besi / Dunche', '4-6 hours walking', '2-15 pax.', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Living Heritage', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore ancient monasteries and prayer sites that reflect the deep spiritual roots of the Tamang people.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trek through lush rhododendron forests, alpine meadows and landscape views of Langtangâ€™s snow-capped peaks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Tamang Heritage Trek offers a perfect mix of cultural immersion and thrilling mountain trekking in a less crowded, pristine region.</p>', 'Private vehicle / Jeep / Bus', 1, NULL, 'tamang-heritage-trek-11-days-G1y0l.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Native to Nepalâ€™s Himalayan highlands, the Tamang people are an indigenous ethnic group celebrated for their vivid customs, rich culture and deep-rooted Buddhist beliefs. Their distinctive language, traditional music, festivals and craftsmanship reflect centuries of spiritual legacy and harmonious coexistence with nature, especially in the Langtang region where they have lived for millennia.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Tamang Heritage Trek is a popular Himalayan route offering beautiful views of alpine forests, snow-capped peaks and scenic valleys. Along the way, trekkers experience authentic Tamang culture through visits to vibrant villages and historic Buddhist monasteries, blending adventure with cultural immersion.</p>', 2, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 2: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li>Altitude: Up to 3,000 meters</li>\r\n<li>Â <!--[endif]-->Duration: 4â€“6 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li>Terrain: Well-maintained paths with gentle ascents</li>\r\n<li><!--[endif]-->Experience Required: Suitable for beginners and families</li>\r\n<li>Examples: Ghorepani Poon Hill Trek, Chisapani Nagarkot Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'tamang-heritage-trek-11-days', 134, 'N208223', 'Tamang Heritage Trek â€“ Explore Culture & Mountains in Langtang. Tamang Heritage Trek â€“ Off-the-Beaten-Path Adventure in Nepal', NULL, 'Discover the rich culture of the Tamang people with this scenic trek through the Langtang region â€“ perfect for culture and mountain lovers.\r\n\r\nAn immersive trekking experience through traditional Tamang villages, terraced fields, and Himalayan landscapes near Langtang National Park.\r\n\r\nUncover hidden traditions, warm hospitality, and breathtaking views on the Tamang Heritage Trek in Nepal.', 'artboard-1-GwMHN.jpg', '1752480809_2-zqIIf.jpg', '1760758190_tamang-heritage-trek-X4qst.pdf', 422, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 845.00, 0, '\"Discover the Living Legacy of the Tamang\"', 1, NULL, '2024-08-26 15:46:11', '2025-12-23 14:42:46'),
(169, 'Mera Peak Trek & Summit 19 days', 'The journey to Mera Peak travels through an area rich in culture, the terraced agriculture and woodland of Nepal\'s \'Middle Hills,\' passing small villages and settlements inhabited by the tough Sherpas and Rai', 19, '6476', 'Patale / Lukla', '5-7 hours', '2-12 Pax', 'Tea house/tent', '\"Majestic Five\"', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A traditional village known for its unique culture, warm hospitality, and terraced fields..</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A scenic spot along the trail with beautiful landscapes and amazing mountain views.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Witness the mesmerizing morning sunrise over the Annapurnas and Dhaulagiri from Poon Hill</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">An extraordinary beautiful view of the Annapurna from base camp.</p>', 'Private Vechile/ Jeep / Bus', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Â Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â </p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One of Nepal\'s most visited hiking summits, Mera Peak (6476 m), provides stunning vistas and an exhilarating experience. The journey to Mera Peak travels through an area rich in culture, the terraced agriculture and woodland of Nepal\'s \'Middle Hills,\' passing small villages and settlements inhabited by the tough Sherpas and Rai.Â Five of the world\'s 8000M mountains; Kangchenjunga, Makalu, Lhotse, Everest, and Cho Oyuâ€”are included in the Mera Summit Panorama.</p>', 5, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 5: Very Strenuous/Challenging Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Above 6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 7â€“9 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: High-altitude passes, glaciers, and technical sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for seasoned trekkers with high-altitude experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Circuit with Pisang, Chulu peak via Thorong La Pass, Makalu Base Camp with Larkya peak, Mera peak, 3 passes with Lobuche, Island peak</li>\r\n</ul>', 'mera-peak-trek-summit-19-days', 137, 'N208225', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mca-NjkQe.jpg', '1749110073_thumnail-15x15-uNa5T.jpg', '1755150624_mera-peak-summit-MVhOP.pdf', 431, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Climb to the Worldâ€™s Greatest View\"', 0, NULL, '2024-08-26 21:55:15', '2025-12-23 15:26:52'),
(171, 'Everest Dream Trek 15 days', 'Explore the Himalayas, seeing Everest and nearby peaks. Visit Sherpa villages, monasteries, and beautiful Gokyo Lakes. Hike to top viewpoints and finish with a helicopter ride from Kongde.', 15, '5360', 'Lukla - Lukla', '5-6 Hours', '2-15 pax', 'Lodges / Teahouse', 'Fly Down from Kongde', '<p data-start=\"62\" data-end=\"133\"><strong data-start=\"62\" data-end=\"104\">Explore Gokyo Lakes &amp; Ngozumba Glacier</strong> â€“ worldâ€™s longest glacier.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"137\" data-end=\"199\"><strong data-start=\"137\" data-end=\"163\">Enjoy Gokyo Ri Sunrise</strong> â€“ Everest, Makalu, Cho Oyu views.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"203\" data-end=\"253\"><strong data-start=\"203\" data-end=\"226\">Cross Renjo La Pass</strong> â€“ challenging high pass.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"257\" data-end=\"316\"><strong data-start=\"257\" data-end=\"286\">Experience Sherpa Culture</strong> â€“ villages and monasteries.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"320\" data-end=\"379\"><strong data-start=\"320\" data-end=\"353\">Helicopter Flight from Kongde</strong> â€“ Everest massif views.</p>', 'Private Vehicles/ Air', 1, NULL, 'everest-dream-trek-15-days-zRijy.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"114\" data-end=\"662\">The Everest Dream Trek is an iconic journey in Nepalâ€™s Khumbu region within Sagarmatha National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The adventure reaches Gokyo and the Ngozumba Glacier, the longest glacier in the world, offering a true high-altitude Himalayan experience. It starts with a scenic flight from Kathmandu to Lukla, followed by a walk along the Dudh Koshi River to Namche Bazaar, the Sherpa hub for acclimatisation, markets, and stunning Himalayan views. The global trail is generally easy, but the high altitude makes it challenging.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"664\" data-end=\"1139\">Along the route, the trail passes through charming Sherpa villages like Phortse, Machhermo, and Gokyo. Khumjung Monastery, home to the famous Yeti skull, is a notable highlight. The largest of Gokyoâ€™s five lakes, with an optional climb of Gokyo Peak for spectacular sunsets over the 8,000â€¯m mountains, adds to the journeyâ€™s allure. Every step reveals breathtaking landscapes, from glacial valleys to towering mountains, making this a once-in-a-lifetime Himalayan adventure.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1141\" data-end=\"1550\">The trail continues over the challenging Renjo La Pass and through Thame to the luxurious Konde Resort. From Konde, panoramic views of the Everest Valley unfold, including towering mountains, deep valleys, and the Khumbu glaciers. After soaking in the scenery, the path descends to Taktok, or a helicopter flight over the Everest massif from Konde provides a final breathtaking perspective of the Himalayas.</p>', 4, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'everest-dream-trek-15-days', 138, 'N208235', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'everest-drea-n79kb.jpg', '1749617867_1-WVMpC.jpg', '1753777867_everest-dream-trek-15-day1-PGBau.pdf', 544, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 1450.00, 0, '\"Step into the Himalayas\"', 1, NULL, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-12-24 07:06:59'),
(178, 'Bardia National Park', 'Enjoy a five-day journey that starts with Kathmanduâ€™s cultural highlights and continues to the wild beauty of Bardia National Park, with exciting safaris, nature walks, and a relaxing return to the city.', 6, NULL, 'Kathmandu / Kathmandu (Pokhara)', NULL, '2-20 pax', 'Tea House /camping', 'From Temples to Tigers', '<ul>\r\n<li>Discover Kathmanduâ€™s magic with visits to ancient temples and lively squares.</li>\r\n<li>Journey to wild Bardia by quick flight plus scenic drive or adventurous road trip.</li>\r\n<li>Dive into nature with exciting safaris and peaceful walks in Bardia National Park.</li>\r\n<li>Unwind at a cosy lodge surrounded by jungle beauty.</li>\r\n<li>Smooth return to Kathmandu by flight or enjoy the scenic bus ride home.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Private Vechile', 0, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<article dir=\"auto\" data-testid=\"conversation-turn-4\" data-scroll-anchor=\"true\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div tabindex=\"-1\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\" data-message-author-role=\"assistant\" data-message-id=\"b4e00937-37c9-4070-9e80-8c0ef6894b9b\" data-message-model-slug=\"gpt-4o\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p data-start=\"53\" data-end=\"238\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">\"Enjoy a five-day trip that starts with Kathmanduâ€™s culture and takes you to the wild beauty of Bardia National Park, with safaris, nature walks, and a relaxing return to the city.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"53\" data-end=\"238\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">This trip can easily be added after your mountain trek. Chitwan National Park is a relaxing destination that\'s easy to explore, especially on a safari</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Â </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Â </div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</article>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-language: HI;\">This five-day trip starts in Kathmandu with a warm welcome and a tour of the city\'s cultural landmarks, including Durbar Square, Pashupatinath, and Swayambhunath. You then take a flight and drive or a picturesque road trip to Bardia National Park, where you can take part in thrilling safaris, nature hikes, and wildlife observation in the midst of pristine jungle surroundings. To end your journey comfortably and easily, take a bus or plane back to Kathmandu after spending the entire day in the great outdoors.</span></p>', 1, 5, NULL, 'bardia-national-park', 140, 'N208231', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'b-UQjQg.jpg', '1749381385_jeep-lfeiO.jpg', '', 226, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'Discover Nepal in Five Days!', 1, NULL, '2024-08-28 14:41:21', '2025-12-20 20:53:35'),
(179, 'Pikey Peak Trek 12 days', 'Experience life deeply influenced by Buddhism, visiting Thupten Chholing Gumba and Jhapre Gumba, with prayer flags, mani walls, and chortens. The trek passes through quiet, remote areas, offering a glimpse of authentic Nepalese village life.', 12, '4065m', 'Phaplu- Kundar', '4-6 hours', '2-15 Pax', 'Tea houses', 'Scenic heritage', '<p data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"217\">Climb Pikey Peak (4,065â€¯m) for <strong data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"176\">panoramic sunrise views</strong> of Everest and other Himalayan giants.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"221\" data-end=\"289\">Cross Renjo La Pass, one of Khumbuâ€™s most <strong data-start=\"263\" data-end=\"286\">dramatic viewpoints</strong>.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"293\" data-end=\"364\">Experience <strong data-start=\"304\" data-end=\"331\">authentic Nepalese life</strong> in Sherpa and Tamang villages.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"368\" data-end=\"439\">Explore Buddhist heritage at Thupten Chholing Gumba and Jhapre Gumba.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"443\" data-end=\"505\">Enjoy <strong data-start=\"449\" data-end=\"471\">exceptional vistas</strong> from Thala Danda and Chagsthan.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"509\" data-end=\"583\">Trek peaceful, remote trails through forests, fields, and high pastures.</p>', 'Private jeep Bus', 1, NULL, 'pikey-peak-day-12-6LOtZ.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"64\" data-end=\"525\">The Pikey Peak Trek is a short and peaceful trek in Nepalâ€™s Lower Everest region. It is perfect for those seeking stunning mountain views, local culture, and quiet trails away from the busy Everest routes. Pikey Peak (4,065â€¯m) offers amazing sunrise views of Mount Everest, Kanchenjunga, Makalu, Lhotse, and other high mountains. The trek also provides views of surrounding hills, valleys, and remote landscapes, giving a sense of peace and isolation.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"527\" data-end=\"958\">The route passes through traditional Sherpa and Tamang villages in the lower Everest region, where life is simple and strongly influenced by Buddhism. Along the way, notable monasteries such as Thupten Chholing Gumba and Jhapre Gumba can be visited, along with prayer flags, mani walls, and chortens. Two other viewpoints, Thala Danda and Chagsthan, offer incredible panoramic views of the Everest region.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"960\" data-end=\"1338\">The trail goes through rhododendron forests, terraced fields, open hills, and high pastures, showing different scenery each day. There are chances for bird watching, meeting locals, and seeing seasonal farming practices. With moderate altitude and gentle slopes, the trek is suitable for beginners and experienced walkers, making it a great introduction to Himalayan trekking.</p>', 3, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'pikey-peak-trek-12-days', 141, 'N208224', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'img-0704-i1T8C.jpg', '1749096600_thumnail-8YQOz.jpg', '1749096755_lower-everest-region-x8joq.pdf', 855, 0, '1', '0', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 720.00, 0, '\"Serenity, Culture, Everest Views\"', 1, NULL, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-24 15:20:10'),
(180, 'Annapurna Balcony Trek 9 days', 'A short, scenic trek at moderate altitudes, passing rhododendron forests and traditional Gurung and Magar villages. See a golden sunrise from Poon Hill with views of Annapurna I, Annapurna South, Hiunchuli, Machhapuchhre, and Dhaulagiri.', 9, '3200m', 'Pokhara - Pokhara', '4-5', '2-12', 'Tea house / Lodges', 'Scenic Splendor', '<p data-start=\"96\" data-end=\"132\"><strong data-start=\"96\" data-end=\"115\">Annapurna views</strong> from Poon Hill</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"135\" data-end=\"184\"><strong data-start=\"135\" data-end=\"154\">Magical sunrise</strong> over Annapurna &amp; Dhaulagiri</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"187\" data-end=\"259\">Famous peaks: <strong data-start=\"201\" data-end=\"257\">Dhaulagiri, Annapurna South, Hiunchuli, Machapuchare</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"262\" data-end=\"314\">Trek <strong data-start=\"267\" data-end=\"286\">verdant forests</strong> with spring rhododendrons</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"317\" data-end=\"376\">Explore a <strong data-start=\"327\" data-end=\"345\">Gurung village</strong>, home of <strong data-start=\"355\" data-end=\"374\">Gurkha warriors</strong></p>', 'Private Vechile / flight', 1, NULL, 'annapurna-balcony-9-days-KJ1EF.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This is a short and scenic journey with amazing mountain views. The trek stays at relatively low altitudes, reaching a maximum of 3,210â€¯m, making it suitable for many people. The trip starts from Kathmandu to Pokhara by private drive or flight, followed by a drive to Hile. The route passes through terraced fields, rhododendron forests, and traditional Gurung and Magar villages, offering a blend of nature and local life.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Poon Hill is a key viewpoint of the trek. The sunrise from Poon Hill, with the golden morning light, is a truly memorable experience, with views of Annapurna I, Annapurna South, Hiunchuli, Machhapuchhre (Fishtail), and the distant Dhaulagiri range.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The trek concludes at Ghandruk, a large and well-known village in the region. The Gurung museum and a Buddhist monastery provide insights into local culture and traditions. Easy to access, culturally rich, and visually captivating, this trek offers an unforgettable Himalayan adventure.</p>', 2, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â <strong>Grade 2: Easy Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Up to 3,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 4â€“6 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Well-maintained paths with gentle ascents</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for beginners and families</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Ghorepani Poon Hill Trek, Chisapani Nagarkot Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'annapurna-balcony-trek-9-days', 142, 'N20824', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'img-1217-8amVd.jpg', '1756539128_whatsapp-image-2025-08-30-at-13-yh3a6.jpg', '1753693342_annapurna-balcony-trek-9-day1-xK88p.pdf', 687, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 930.00, 0, 'â€œPoonhill Panoramaâ€', 1, NULL, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-23 15:41:07'),
(184, 'Discovery Nepal', 'This 15-day trip through Nepal combines beautiful nature, peaceful spiritual sites, and rich culture, taking you from busy cities and ancient temples to quiet villages, jungle safaris, and stunning mountain views.', 15, NULL, 'Kathmandu / Kathmandu', NULL, '2-10 pax', 'Hotel / lodge', 'Sacred Horizons', '<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore UNESCO World Heritage Sites like Swayambhunath, Pashupatinath, Boudhanath and the historic towns of Bhaktapur, Patan and Kirtipur.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy serene Phewa Lake, sunrise views from Sarangkot and visit the World Peace Pagoda and Tibetan refugee camps.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Visit the birthplace of Buddha, including the Maya Devi Temple and various international monasteries.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience jungle safaris, boat rides on the Rapti River and cultural visits to Tharu villages.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Witness beautiful Himalayan sunrises and explore the scenic towns of Nagarkot and Dhulikhel.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â Savor Newari cuisine in Bhaktapur, Tharu dishes in Chitwan and Tibetan specialties in Pokhara.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'private bus/car', 0, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This 15-day trip in Nepal skilfully combines beautiful natural scenery, peaceful spiritual locations and a rich cultural heritage. Every day provides a different adventure, from touring historic temples and busy bazaars in Kathmandu and Patan to taking in serene moments at Lumbini, the birthplace of Buddha, and thrilling animal safaris in Chitwan National Park. You\'ll experience charming local customs, serene villages and beautiful sunsets in addition to beautiful Himalayan views in Pokhara, Nagarkot and Dhulikhel. These experiences will weave a vibrant web of memories that honour Nepal\'s essence.</p>', 1, 5, NULL, 'discovery-nepal', 145, 'N208228', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'artboard-1-r6dsC.jpg', '1749359981_1515-6xeJ6.jpg', '', 228, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Heritage, Nature, and Harmony.\"', 1, NULL, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-12-21 10:22:39'),
(194, '3 High Passes & Island Peak 20 days', 'This remarkable journey unveils the awe inspiring landscapes that surround Mount Everest, capturing the dramatic ascent of terrain that culminates in the highest point on Earth.', 20, '6189', 'Lukla - Lukla', '5-8 hours', '2-15 Pax', 'Tea House/Tents', 'More than just a trek', '<p data-start=\"84\" data-end=\"152\">Summit Island Peak for an unforgettable high-altitude achievement.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"156\" data-end=\"225\">Cross three legendary high passes: Renjo La, Cho La, and Kongma La.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"229\" data-end=\"304\">Trek to Everest Base Camp and Kala Patthar for close-up views of Everest.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"308\" data-end=\"365\">Explore the serene Gokyo Valley and sacred Gokyo Lakes.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"369\" data-end=\"433\">Walk along the vast Ngozumpa Glacier, Nepalâ€™s largest glacier.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"437\" data-end=\"501\">Climb Gokyo Ri and Chhukung Ri for panoramic Himalayan vistas.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"505\" data-end=\"586\">Visit iconic Sherpa monasteries: Thame, the oldest, and Tengboche, the largest.</p>', 'Private vehicle /Plane', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</em></p>', '<p data-start=\"91\" data-end=\"735\">The Everest 3 High Passes &amp; Island Peak Trek is one of Nepalâ€™s most spectacular and rewarding circuits, taking you deep into the Everest region with high-altitude landscapes, massive glaciers, and iconic Himalayan peaks. The adventure starts with a scenic flight from Kathmandu to Lukla, the main gateway and a bustling Sherpa town. You trek along the Dudh Koshi River, cross suspension bridges, and pass traditional Sherpa villages before reaching Namche Bazaar, the Sherpa capital. On your rest day, explore Khumjung Village, where Sir Edmund Hillary helped establish a school, and Khunde, home to Khunde Hospital, founded with his support.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"737\" data-end=\"1563\">The trek crosses three legendary high passes: Renjo La (5,360 m), Cho La (5,420 m), and Kongma La (5,535 m). Highlights include Everest Base Camp and Kala Patthar (5,545 m) for incredible close-up views of Everest. Along the route, you pass the serene Gokyo Valley, sacred Gokyo Lakes, and the vast Ngozumpa Glacier, Nepalâ€™s largest. Ascents to Gokyo Ri and Chhukung Ri provide sweeping views of Everest, Lhotse, Makalu, Cho Oyu, and surrounding peaks. For climbers seeking an additional challenge, Island Peak (Imja Tse, 6,189 m) offers a thrilling summit experience with unforgettable Himalayan vistas. The trek also highlights Sherpa culture with visits to ancient monasteries such as Thame, the oldest in Upper Pangbuche, and the iconic Tengboche Monastery, along with mani stones and chortens scattered along the trail.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1565\" data-end=\"1855\">The return journey passes through Pheriche, Pangboche, and Tengboche, reaching Lukla via Namche. The final night is a special moment to thank your porters and guides, often celebrated with dancing, sharing, and lasting memoriesâ€”marking the completion of this epic high-altitude adventure.</p>', 5, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 5: Very Strenuous/Challenging Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Above 6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 7â€“9 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: High-altitude passes, glaciers, and technical sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for seasoned trekkers with high-altitude experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Circuit with Pisang, Chulu peak via Thorong La Pass, Makalu Base Camp with Larkya peak, Mera peak, 3 passes with Lobuche, Island peak</li>\r\n</ul>', '3-high-passes-island-peak-20-days', 154, 'N208220', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'three-MuVBd.jpg', '1755155497_4-s4p2s.jpg', '', 175, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'â€œThree Passes to the Peak of Adventure\"', 1, NULL, '2024-09-02 17:53:57', '2025-12-23 15:01:37'),
(195, 'Annapurna & Tilicho 18 days', 'Cross Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m) with views of Annapurna I, Dhaulagiri, and Manaslu, then descend to the sacred Muktinath with its temples, eternal flame, and 108 holy water spouts.', 18, '5,416 meters', 'Spring/autonm', '4-7  hours', '2-15 Pax', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Untamed Frontiers', '<p data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"176\">Journey from green valleys to <strong data-start=\"148\" data-end=\"174\">high Himalayan deserts</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"179\" data-end=\"268\"><strong data-start=\"179\" data-end=\"214\">Discover Tilicho Lake (4,920â€¯m)</strong>, one of the worldâ€™s highest lakes, and <strong data-start=\"254\" data-end=\"266\">Ice Lake</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"271\" data-end=\"345\">Cross <strong data-start=\"277\" data-end=\"306\">Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m)</strong> â€” a legendary high-altitude crossing</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"348\" data-end=\"424\">Encounter the living cultures of <strong data-start=\"381\" data-end=\"422\">Manang, Mustang &amp; Lupra (Bon village)</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"427\" data-end=\"492\">Epic views of <strong data-start=\"441\" data-end=\"490\">Annapurna, Dhaulagiri, Manaslu &amp; Tilicho Peak</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"495\" data-end=\"579\">Jump-up trips to <strong data-start=\"512\" data-end=\"536\">Tatopani hot springs</strong> and <strong data-start=\"541\" data-end=\"577\">golden sunrise from Mohare Danda</strong></p>', 'Private vehicle / local jeep', 1, NULL, 'annapurna-circuti-tilicho-18-days-1MTRA.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"129\" data-end=\"829\">The Annapurna with Tilicho Lake and Ice Lake Trek is an extraordinary journey through the Annapurna and Mustang regions, combining dramatic high-altitude landscapes with rich cultural experiences. The trek begins in verdant valleys and traditional mountain villages, gradually ascending northwards to Tilicho Lake (4,919â€¯m)â€”one of the worldâ€™s highest lakes. According to local legend, Tilicho was formed when the mountain goddess Tilicho flooded the valley to protect her devotees, and the lakeâ€™s serene waters are believed to possess spiritual powers. Nearby, Ice Lake (4,600â€¯m) offers equally stunning alpine views, with stories of local spirits said to guard its frozen shores.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"831\" data-end=\"1339\">One of the most spectacular moments of the trek is the crossing of Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m), one of the Himalayaâ€™s highest trekking passes, offering magnificent views of Annapurna I, Dhaulagiri, and Manaslu. From here, the trail descends to Muktinath, a sacred Hindu-Buddhist pilgrimage site. Pilgrims have visited Muktinath for centuries to worship at its temples, eternal flame, and 108 holy water spouts, with legends claiming that the flames have burned continuously since ancient times.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1341\" data-end=\"1898\">The journey then moves into the dry and culturally distinctive Mustang region, north-east of the pass, known for its desert-like landscapes and strong Tibetan influence. Villages such as Lupra, one of Nepalâ€™s last Bon communities, hold stories of ancient rituals and spiritual practices that have been preserved for generations. The trek concludes at Mohare Danda, where the final sunrise over the western Annapurna and Dhaulagiri ranges provides a serene and unforgettable end to this challenging, yet deeply rewarding, Himalayan adventure.</p>', 4, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'annapurna-tilicho-18-days', 155, 'N20822', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'img20231125102313-sgn9r.jpg', '1749705854_img-0341-sn2ow.jpg', '1753693532_annapurna-circuit-tilicho-18-days-dDVAh.pdf', 733, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1610.00, 0, 'â€œBeyond peaks, beyond paths\"', 1, NULL, '2024-09-02 18:12:32', '2025-12-23 14:23:37');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_details` (`id`, `trip_title`, `sub_title`, `duration`, `max_altitude`, `best_season`, `walking_per_day`, `group_size`, `accommodation`, `route`, `trip_highlight`, `peak_name`, `trip_type`, `starting_price`, `trip_map`, `trip_video`, `trip_chart`, `trip_excerpt`, `trip_content`, `trip_grade`, `rating`, `status_text`, `uri`, `ordering`, `trip_code`, `meta_key`, `meta_title`, `meta_description`, `banner`, `thumbnail`, `trip_pdf`, `visiter`, `is_draft`, `status`, `trip_of_the_month`, `video_status`, `show_in_home`, `start_date`, `price`, `price_euro`, `flight`, `discount`, `guided`, `latest_info`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(198, 'EBC via Chola & Heli Back 14 days', 'The trek moves through the Gokyo Valley, passing the turquoise Gokyo Lakes and climbing Gokyo Peak for panoramic mountain views. This section crosses the Ngozumpa Glacier, the worldâ€™s longest glacier, before tackling the challenging Cho La Pass', 14, '5644', 'Lukla/ Lukla', '4-6  hours', '2-16 Pax', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Majestic Adventure', '<p data-start=\"153\" data-end=\"208\">Close-up views of Everest and other Himalayan giants.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"212\" data-end=\"268\">Experience authentic Sherpa culture in local villages.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"272\" data-end=\"324\">Explore Upper Pangboche and Tengboche monasteries.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"328\" data-end=\"372\">Trek Kala Patthar for unforgettable views.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"376\" data-end=\"419\">Scenic helicopter return from Gorak Shep.</p>\r\n<p>Cross the worldâ€™s longest Ngozumpa Glacier.</p>', 'Private vehicle /Helicapter', 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-start=\"47\" data-end=\"229\"><strong data-start=\"55\" data-end=\"71\">Please note:</strong> The helicopter flight to Lukla or Kathmandu must be confirmed before leaving Namche Bazaar. This ensures all necessary flight formalities are completed.</p>', '<p data-start=\"145\" data-end=\"951\">The Everest Base Camp with Heli Back trek is a stunning journey in Nepalâ€™s Khumbu region, taking in the worldâ€™s highest mountains and the heart of Sherpa land. Sagarmatha National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, is home to the trek, which reaches Gokyo Peak, Cho La Pass (5,420â€¯m), and Everest Base Camp (5,364â€¯m), the starting point for climbers attempting Mount Everest (8,848â€¯m). The journey begins in Lukla in the south and follows the Dudh Koshi River north to Namche Bazaar, the vibrant hub of Sherpa (Shepa) and Tibetan culture. Nearby villages, including Khumjung and Khunde, feature a school and hospital supported by Sir Edmund Hillary. The global trail is generally easy, but the high altitude makes it challenging, although an excursion at Namche provides a perfect chance to acclimatise.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"953\" data-end=\"1571\">The trek continues north and slightly west through the Gokyo Valley, where turquoise Gokyo Lakes and the ascent to Gokyo Peak offer panoramic mountain views. The route crosses the Ngozumpa Glacier, the worldâ€™s longest glacier, before tackling the challenging Cho La Pass, which connects Gokyo Valley with the main Everest Base Camp trail. Moving east through Zongla, Lobuche, and Gorak Shep, the trek offers spectacular views of Everest to the north, Lhotse to the east, Nuptse to the south, and Ama Dablam, Pumori, and Thamserku across the surrounding valleys, while the Khumbu Glacier adds dramatic icy landscapes.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1573\" data-end=\"2145\">The journey culminates at Everest Base Camp, with the ascent to Kala Patthar (5,545â€¯m) providing an unforgettable close-up view of Everest to the north. Cultural highlights along the route include mani stones, chortens, and monasteries at Upper Pangboche and Tengboche. The trek concludes with a scenic helicopter flight from Gorak Shep, offering a final breathtaking aerial perspective. Combining Sherpa (Shepa) and Tibetan culture, rich heritage, dramatic landscapes, and high-altitude adventure, this trek is a safe, inspiring, and life-changing Himalayan experience.</p>', 4, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Â Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'ebc-via-chola-heli-back-14-days', 158, 'N208236', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'heli-16x55-WmJ0S.jpg', '1756629080_img-0425-DksbR.jpg', '1753778007_ebc-trek-FG5aj.pdf', 488, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 1015.00, 0, 'â€œDiscover Everestâ€™s Majesty, Fly Home in Style\"', 1, NULL, '2024-09-03 21:16:26', '2025-12-23 22:04:46'),
(199, 'Gosaikund Pass & Helumbu 16 days', 'Trek is a beautiful trek across the Langtang region of Nepal that combines high-altitude adventure. Trekkers explore the holy alpine lake of Gosaikunda, a Buddhist and Hindu pilgrimage', 16, '4984', 'Shyabru Besi - Sundarijal', '4-6  hours', '2-12 Pax', 'Tea Houses', 'Himalayan majesty.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Langtang Gosaikunda Pass (Helambu) Trek is a 15-16 day journey through Nepalâ€™s Langtang region, combining cultural immersion, an amazing landscapes and high-altitude adventure.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The trek features Langtang Valley, sacred Gosaikunda Lake and the Lauribinayak Pass (4,600m), offering beautiful views of Langtang Lirung, Ganesh Himal and Tibetan peaks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trekkers experience Sherpa and Tamang villages, Buddhist monasteries and Langtang National Park, home to red pandas and Himalayan black bears.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Best undertaken in spring or autumn, this trek is ideal for those seeking scenic beauty, cultural exploration and Himalayan trekking challenges.</p>', 'Private vehicle / Bus / Jeep', 1, NULL, 'gosaikunda-pass-helambu-16-days-aKKJJ.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">The Langtang Gosaikunda Pass (Helambu) Trek is a beautiful trek across the Langtang region of Nepal that combines high-altitude adventure, cultural diversity and scenic beauty. Starting in the Langtang Valley, this circuitous route travels by the revered Gosaikunda Lake before coming to an end in the Helambu Valley.<br><br>Trekkers explore the holy alpine lake of Gosaikunda, a Buddhist and Hindu pilgrimage site, go through traditional Tamang and Sherpa villages and stop at the ancient Kyanjin Gompa. The trek includes crossing the Lauribinayak Pass (4,600m), which provides panoramic views of the Himalayas. It is a sing</span></p>', 3, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â <!--[endif]-->Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><!--[endif]-->Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'gosaikund-pass-helumbu-16-days', 159, 'N208222', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'as-gi9T9.jpg', '1752481798_15x15-k0xPg.jpg', '1760759090_langtang-gosaikunda-pas1-F45re.pdf', 286, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 860.00, 0, 'â€œSacred Lakes, Scenic Trails\"', 1, NULL, '2024-09-09 10:19:58', '2025-12-23 14:45:09'),
(200, 'Langtang Classic 11 days', 'This trek offers a perfect blend of spiritual connection, cultural immersion, and Himalayan exploration without the extreme altitudes found in some other popular trekking regions.', 11, '4984', 'Shyabru Besi - Dunche', '4-6 hours', '2-15 pax', 'Tea House', 'moderate-altitude adventure', '<p>Langtang region, combining cultural immersion,Â  beautiful landscapesÂ </p>\r\n<p>Trekkers experience Sherpa and Tamang villages, Buddhist monasteries</p>\r\n<p>Langtang National Park, home to red pandas and Himalayan black bears.</p>\r\n<p>Best undertaken in spring or autumn, this trek is ideal for those seeking scenic beauty, cultural exploration, and Himalayan trekking challenges.</p>', 'Private jeep / Bus/ Car', 1, NULL, 'langtang-classic-11-day-6ThYv.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">The Langtang Trek is an amazing journey, through the Langtang region of Nepal that beautifully combines moderate-altitude adventure, rich cultural diversity, and beautiful natural scenery. This circuitous route weaves through dense rhododendron forests, charming traditional Tamang and Tibetan villages, and sacred monasteries revered by local communities. Trekkers are rewarded with spectacular landscape views of majestic peaks such as Langtang Lirung (7,227m), Ganesh Himal, Dorje Lakpa and Tserko Ri (4,984m). Along the trail, you will encounter sparkling glacial rivers, alpine meadows, and the pristine Langtang Glacier near Kyanjin Gompa. This trek offers a perfect blend of spiritual connection, cultural immersion, and Himalayan exploration without the extreme altitudes found in some other popular trekking regions.</span></p>', 3, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Â Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'langtang-classic-11-days', 160, 'N208221', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2-uCB7E.jpg', '1725917954_d5be1771-a09b-47f1-887b-7e9e4d995fc4-qG2OR.png', '1760759735_langtang-classic-tre1-8sru4.pdf', 318, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 685.00, 0, '\"Heritage, Harmony, Heights\"', 1, NULL, '2024-09-09 18:35:52', '2025-12-23 14:49:47'),
(202, 'Soul of Nepal 12 day', 'Discover UNESCO monuments and ancient temples in Kathmandu, including Swayambhunath and Pashupatinath. Explore the historic cities of Patan, Bhaktapur, and Panauti before hiking to charming villages like Namobuddha and Balthali', 12, NULL, 'Kathmandu / Kathmandu', NULL, '2-20pax', 'Hotel / Lodge', 'â€œSacred Nepalâ€', '<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Start your adventure with vibrant cultural immersion at Swayambhunath, Pashupatinath, Patan and Boudhanath, embracing both Hindu and Buddhist traditions.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Discover the charm of Bhaktapur, Panauti and Balthali with gentle hikes through terraced farms and peaceful landscapes.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience spiritual serenity at Namobuddha Monastery and catch magical Himalayan sunsets in Dhulikhel.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Relish the timeless beauty of Bandipur and connect with Magar culture in the quiet hill village of Ramkot.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Unwind by Phewa Lake, hike to Dhampus for close-up mountain views and enjoy the vibrant lakeside life of Pokhara.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">End with thrilling canoe rides, nature walks and jeep safaris in Chitwan National Park, spotting exotic wildlife and soaking in nature\'s calm.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'private bus/car', 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore the heart of Nepal on an adventure that blends spiritual tradition, stunning hikes, wildlife encounters and a vibrant culture. Discover UNESCO monuments and ancient temples in Kathmandu, including Swayambhunath and Pashupatinath. Explore the historic cities of Patan, Bhaktapur and Panauti before hiking to charming villages like Namobuddha and Balthali. Enjoy Dhulikhel\'s Himalayan scenery and the cultural attraction of Kirtipur and Bandipur. For beautiful mountain views, walk to Dhampus and rest at Phewa Lake in Pokhara. Experience the untamed splendor of Chitwan National Park by going on safaris, boating and hiking in the forest. Stop spiritually at Boudhanath Stupa to complete your trip and bring back great memories.</p>', 1, 1, NULL, 'soul-of-nepal-12-day', 162, '208229', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1600x550-qQeew.jpg', '1749373154_untitled-1-4LQ9N.jpg', '1753778103_soul-of-nepal-12-da1-nH3B1.pdf', 363, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'â€œMountains, Monuments, Memories.â€', 0, NULL, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-12-20 05:25:21'),
(204, 'Everest B. C. via Gokyo 18 days', 'The journey culminates at Everest Base Camp, with an optional climb to Kala Patthar (5,545â€¯m) for an unforgettable close-up view of Everest. Cultural highlights along the route include mani stones, chortens, and monasteries at Upper Pangboche', 18, '5420', 'Lukla - Lukla', '6-8 hours', '2-15 pax', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Dream fulfillment', '<p data-start=\"139\" data-end=\"202\">Spectacular views of Everest, Lhotse, Nuptse, and Ama Dablam.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"139\" data-end=\"202\">Explore Gokyo Valley and climb Gokyo Peak.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"254\" data-end=\"290\">Cross the challenging Cho La Pass.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"294\" data-end=\"345\">Experience Sherpa culture and famous monasteries.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"349\" data-end=\"405\">Optional Kala Patthar climb for a close-up of Everest.</p>\r\n<p>Cross the worldâ€™s longest Ngozumpa Glacier.</p>', 'Airplane', 1, NULL, 'ebc-gokyo-17-days-SRUzT.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"100\" data-end=\"938\">The Everest Base Camp Trek via Gokyo and Cho La Pass is one of the Himalayasâ€™ most iconic journeys, taking in the worldâ€™s highest mountains and Sherpa land. The trek lies within Sagarmatha National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and reaches Gokyo Peak, Cho La Pass (5,420â€¯m), Kala Patthar (5,545â€¯m), and Everest Base Camp (5,364â€¯m), the starting point for climbers attempting Mount Everest (English), also known as Sagarmatha in Nepali and Chomolungma in Sherpa and Tibetan (8,848.86â€¯m). The journey begins in Lukla, following the Dudh Koshi River north to Namche Bazaar, the vibrant Sherpa hub. Nearby villages, including Khumjung and Khunde, feature a school and hospital supported by Sir Edmund Hillary. Local legends regard Chomolungma as the â€œMother Goddess of the World,â€ with prayers offered at monasteries for safe passage.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"940\" data-end=\"1564\">The trek moves north through the Gokyo Valley, passing the sacred turquoise Gokyo Lakes and crossing the Ngozumpa Glacier, the worldâ€™s longest glacier. The challenging Cho La Pass connects Gokyo Valley with the main Everest Base Camp trail. Moving east through Zongla, Lobuche, and Gorak Shep, the route offers breathtaking views of Everest to the north, Lhotse to the east, Nuptse to the south, and Ama Dablam, Pumori, and Thamserku across the valleys, while the Khumbu Glacier adds dramatic icy landscapes. Legends speak of early Sherpas navigating these glaciers long before Everest became famous to climbers worldwide.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1566\" data-end=\"2046\">The journey culminates at Everest Base Camp, with the ascent to Kala Patthar providing an unforgettable close-up view of Everest. Cultural highlights include mani stones, chortens, and Tengboche Monastery, established about 350 years back under Lama Sangwa Dorje, and still a spiritual centre for blessings. Combining high-altitude adventure, spectacular mountain scenery, and rich Sherpa (Shepa) and Tibetan culture, this trek offers a truly unforgettable Himalayan experience.</p>', 4, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li>Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li>Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li>Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li>Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li>Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'everest-b-c-via-gokyo-18-days', 164, 'N208218', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'gokyo-lake-trek-QnVco.jpg', '1752119597_df-fXv71.jpg', '1758163952_everest-base-camp-via-gokyo-17-days-OIjEo.pdf', 465, 0, '1', '0', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, 1435.00, 0, 'â€œSherpa Heartland Journeyâ€', 1, NULL, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-12-24 09:03:28'),
(214, 'Chitwan Jungle Safari', 'Enjoy a peaceful birdwatching walk to learn about some of the park\'s more than 500 bird species before involving yourself in the unique society of the Tharu people during a village visit. It\'s the ideal fusion of nature, culture, and adventure.', 5, NULL, 'Kathmandu / Kathmandu (Pokhra)', '2-10 Pax', '2- +++ Pax', NULL, 'Short but gain more', '<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy a picturesque drive or quick flight from Kathmandu to Chitwan.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Relax in a cozy lodge nestled near the lush national park.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Glide along the Rapti River spotting crocodiles and aquatic birds.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Spot rhinos, deer, monkeys, and more on a jungle walk and jeep safari.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Visit a traditional Tharu village and experience their rich heritage.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Begin your final day with a peaceful walk to see Chitwanâ€™s colorful birdlife.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Plane /Private /Vechile /jeep', 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-start=\"53\" data-end=\"238\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Enjoy a five-day trip that starts with Kathmanduâ€™s culture and takes you to the wild beauty of Bardia National Park, with safaris, nature walks and a relaxing return to the city.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-start=\"53\" data-end=\"238\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">This trip can easily be added after your mountain trek. Chitwan National Park is a relaxing destination that\'s easy to explore, especially on a safari</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">An amazing journey into the heart of Nepal\'s wilderness is provided by this 3 day Chitwan Jungle Safari. Take a scenic drive or a quick flight from Kathmandu to Chitwan, where you can stay in a tranquil jungle lodge. With a peaceful Rapti River canoe trip, a guided jungle walks and a thrilling jeep safari, where you might see rhinos, deer, monkeys and even a Bengal tiger, discover the rich biodiversity of Chitwan National Park. Enjoy a peaceful birdwatching walk to learn about some of the park\'s more than 500 bird species before involving yourself in the unique society of the Tharu people during a village visit. It\'s the ideal fusion of nature, culture and adventure.</p>', 1, 1, NULL, 'chitwan-jungle-safari', 174, 'N208230', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'chitwan-BNk1R.jpg', '1749377592_chitwan1-GJGCh.jpg', '', 340, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'â€œChitwan: Wildlife, Culture, Wonder.â€', 1, NULL, '2024-10-03 02:57:00', '2025-12-21 03:10:39'),
(215, 'High Route of Annapurna 21 days', 'Narâ€“Phu, recently opened to trekkers, offers a rare glimpse into authentic Tibetan and Nepalese mountain life. The journey includes major highlights such as Kang La Pass, Manang, Tilicho Lake, and Thorong La Pass.â€', 21, '5,416m/17,770ft', 'Besishahar Pokhara', '6-8 hours', '2-10 Pax', 'Tea Houses', 'Hidden Narâ€“Phu', '<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\">Nar-Phu Valley â€“ Hidden Tibetan villages and ancient mountain life.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\">Kang La Pass (5,313â€¯m) â€“ Dramatic high-altitude views of Annapurna,Gangapurna many more.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\">TTilicho Lake (4,919â€¯m) â€“ One of the worldâ€™s highest lakes with stunning alpine scenery.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\">Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m) â€“ Lofty Himalayan crossing with panoramic peak views.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\">Mustang and Mohare Danda â€“ Tibetan culture, Bon villages, and a golden sunrise finale.</p>\r\n<p>Â </p>', 'Private Vechile', 1, NULL, 'screenshot-2025-06-08-092049-S3RWK.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<div align=\"justify\">\r\n<p data-start=\"146\" data-end=\"920\">The <strong data-start=\"150\" data-end=\"177\">high route of Annapurna</strong> combines the remote <strong data-start=\"198\" data-end=\"216\">Nar-Phu Valley</strong> with the classic Annapurna and Mustang regions, offering one of Nepalâ€™s most authentic high-Himalayan experiences. The Nar-Phu Valley, shaped by Tibetan culture, features ancient stone villages, monasteries, chortens, and traditional pastoral life, giving a rare glimpse of centuries-old mountain life. Local legend says guardian spirits protect the valley, and villagers still perform rituals to honour them. Recently opened to visitors, it offers a unique Himalayan experience. The journey continues through dramatic alpine landscapes, crossing <strong data-start=\"764\" data-end=\"790\">Kang La Pass (5,313â€¯m)</strong> with sweeping views of <strong data-start=\"814\" data-end=\"842\">Annapurna II, Gangapurna</strong>, and surrounding peaks before reaching <strong data-start=\"882\" data-end=\"892\">Manang.</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"922\" data-end=\"1527\">The trek then joins the classic Annapurna with Tilicho Lake Trek, ascending to Tilicho Lake (4,919â€¯m)â€”one of the worldâ€™s highest lakesâ€”whose waters, said to be created by the goddess Tilicho, are considered sacred. The route crosses Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m) with panoramic views of Annapurna I, Dhaulagiri, and Manaslu, before descending into the Kali Gandaki Valley, home to the worldâ€™s deepest gorge and fossil-rich cliffs. At the sacred Muktinath site, pilgrims worship at temples, an eternal flame, and 108 holy water spouts, believed to have burned for hundreds of years.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1529\" data-end=\"2121\">The trek then entered in the arid Mustang region, known for its desert-like landscapes and Tibetan-influenced culture. Traditional villages such as <strong data-start=\"1681\" data-end=\"1704\">Lupra (Bon village)</strong> reveal ancient spiritual practices, rituals, and resilient mountain lifestyles. Legends speak of hidden caves where monks meditated for decades, and local festivals still celebrate these mystical traditions. The journey concludes at <strong data-start=\"1938\" data-end=\"1954\">Mohare Danda</strong>, where the first rays of sunrise over Annapurna and Dhaulagiri leave trekkers with a profound sense of awe and lasting memories of the Himalayaâ€™s timeless beauty.</p>\r\n</div>', 4, 5, '<p>Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration and required experience.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li>Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li>Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li>Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths and potential snow</li>\r\n<li>Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li>Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'high-route-of-annapurna-21-days', 175, 'L20253', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'artboard-1-XANDp.jpg', '1752485774_untitled-1-U3A00.jpg', '1760506175_nar-CoZob.pdf', 795, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1275.00, 0, '\"A complete change of scenery\"', 1, NULL, '2024-10-03 03:00:43', '2025-12-23 14:23:47'),
(218, 'Tsum Valley via Barpak 19 days', 'Situated close to the Tibetan borderâ€”just a day\'s walk awayâ€”this proximity meant that access to the northern side was restricted until recent years, when trekkers were finally permitted to cross.', 19, '3800', 'Baluwa / Dovan', '4-6 hours walking', '2-12', 'Lodge / Teahouse', 'Hidden Gem', '<p data-start=\"62\" data-end=\"100\"><strong data-start=\"62\" data-end=\"77\">Tsum Valley</strong> â€“ Remote and sacred.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"104\" data-end=\"150\"><strong data-start=\"104\" data-end=\"120\">Hidden Beyul</strong> â€“ Blessed by Guru Rinpoche.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"154\" data-end=\"188\"><strong data-start=\"154\" data-end=\"166\">Milarepa</strong> â€“ Meditation caves.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"192\" data-end=\"234\"><strong data-start=\"192\" data-end=\"210\">Tsumba Culture</strong> â€“ Tibetan traditions.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"238\" data-end=\"275\"><strong data-start=\"238\" data-end=\"256\">Mountain Views</strong> â€“ 7,000â€¯m peaks.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"279\" data-end=\"324\" data-is-last-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"279\" data-end=\"295\">Mu Monastery</strong> â€“ Last village before Tibet.</p>', 'Jeep / Bus', 1, NULL, 'manaslu-tsum-19-days-nxevq.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"86\" data-end=\"502\">The Tsum Valley is found in the remote northern part of Nepal within the Manaslu region, close to the Tibetan border. Long isolated from the outside world, this sacred Himalayan valley is known for its dramatic landscapes, strong Tibetan Buddhist heritage, and well-preserved traditions. Officially opened to trekking only in 2007, the region remains one of Nepalâ€™s most culturally and spiritually significant areas.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"504\" data-end=\"1083\">This remarkable journey begins in Barpak, with striking views of Buddha Himal (6,672 m) and Ganesh Himal (7,100 m). The route follows the Manaslu Circuit before turning right at Lokpa into the hidden Tsum Valley. Inhabited mainly by the Tsumbas, an ethnic group of Tibetan origin, the valley reflects a way of life centred on farming, yak herding, and monastic traditions. Mani walls, chortens, and monasteries shape daily life, and local belief holds that Tsum is a <em data-start=\"971\" data-end=\"978\">beyul</em>, a sacred hidden land blessed by Guru Rinpoche, where violence and hunting were traditionally forbidden.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1085\" data-end=\"1552\">The great yogi Milarepa is believed to have meditated in caves of this region, and his legacy remains strong in local prayers and oral traditions. Over six memorable days, the trail passes through fertile fields and remote villages beneath towering 7,000-metre peaks, gradually ascending to Mu Monastery, the last inhabited village before the Tibetan border. Monks and villagers continue to offer prayers here for peace, protection, and harmony in the high mountains.</p>', 3, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'tsum-valley-via-barpak-19-days', 178, 'N208211', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1212-cLjBE.jpg', '1748511410_1-13-g8FQC.jpg', '1753778293_tsum-valley-19-day1-uXYBL.pdf', 540, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1145.00, 0, '\"Hidden valley & tibetan culture\"', 1, NULL, '2024-10-03 03:15:08', '2025-12-23 14:36:10'),
(240, 'Nar-Phu & Annapurna 19 days', 'touched by Tibetan culture, welcomes visitors to discover its old villages, peaceful monasteries, and amazing mountain views', 19, '5,416m', 'Besishahar Pokhara', '4-7 hours walking', '2-15', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Secret Paradise', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This area is a hidden gem for those seeking a unique blend of natural beauty, cultural exploration, and trekking adventure</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore the ancient monasteries, traditional houses, and vibrant prayer flags that the landscape of Phu Gaon and Nar Valley</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A complete change of scenery brought by this trek: dazzling in front of the Himalayas</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The glacial lake Tilicho, the highest lake in the world</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The exceptional view from Khang La pass (5313 m)</p>', 'private / bus / Car', 1, NULL, 'nar-phu-annapurna-19-days-60Fq8.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%;\">Softly in the heart of the Annapurna Conservation Area, the Nar-Phu Valley is a special, hidden place in Nepal where time feels slow. This beautiful land, touched by Tibetan culture, welcomes visitors to discover its old villages, peaceful monasteries, and amazing mountain views. Trekking here feels like walking through a timeless story, especially when crossing the high Kang La Pass, where you see wide views of snowy peaks. Nar-Phu stays calm and untouched, offering a quiet and pure place for those who want real beauty, peace and the soft sounds of the Himalayas.</span></p>', 4, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categoriesconsider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'narphu-annapurna-19-days', 180, 'N208226', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'artboard-1-sWErF.jpg', '1749199105_artboard-1-4uDkJ.jpg', '1760764201_nar-phu-annapurna-19-days-zxqkc.pdf', 379, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1090.00, 0, '\"We act for the best\"', 1, NULL, '2025-04-18 14:29:22', '2025-12-23 14:50:57'),
(242, 'Mardi Himal Trek 10 days', 'Continuing to High Camp, the trail traverses rocky alpine terrain with panoramic views of towering mountains and deep valleys, showcasing the full rewards of high-altitude exploration.', 10, '4500 m', 'Pokhara - Pokhara', '4-6 hours walking', '2-15', NULL, 'Himalayan Sunrise', '<p data-start=\"78\" data-end=\"145\">Discover traditional Magar and Gurung villages and local culture.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"226\">Hike through forests, alpine pastures, and high ridges with mountain views.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"230\" data-end=\"300\">Traverse gradual altitude gain, suitable for beginners and families.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"304\" data-end=\"380\">Peaceful, less commercialized trek offering a serene Himalayan experience.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"384\" data-end=\"456\">Experience rocky alpine terrain and rewarding high-altitude adventure.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"460\" data-end=\"513\">End with a golden sunrise over the Annapurna range.</p>', 'Private Vechile / flight', 1, NULL, 'screenshot-2025-06-08-092412-Dvpkw.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"79\" data-end=\"413\">The journey starts in Kathmandu with a drive or scenic flight to Pokhara, followed by a trip to Kande or Dhampusâ€”charming villages near Pokhara. From here, the route passes through tranquil Gurung and Magar villages, terraced farmland, and vibrant rhododendron and tropical forests, offering a true immersion in local life and nature.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"415\" data-end=\"843\">From Badal Danda, the trail runs along a ridge between two valleys, above the tree line, creating the feeling of walking on a natural balcony with Machhapuchhre (Fishtail), Annapurna South, Hiunchuli, and Annapurna I as an incredible backdrop. Continuing to High Camp, the trail traverses rocky alpine terrain with panoramic views of towering mountains and deep valleys, showcasing the full rewards of high-altitude exploration.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"845\" data-end=\"1212\">The journey culminates at Mardi Himal Base Camp or View Point, where dramatic, sweeping vistas include Annapurna I, Annapurna South, Machhapuchhre, Hiunchuli, Gangapurna, and Lamjung Himal. Suitable for both beginners and those with moderate fitness, this trail offers a safe, well-paced, and unforgettable experience through one of Nepalâ€™s most remarkable regions.</p>', 3, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorised based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'mardi-himal-trek-10-days', 181, 'N20826', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'img-8959-tML98.jpg', '1756700104_img20250104172801-rFdWb.jpg', '1753693617_mardi-himal-trek-10-day1-Ktvlf.pdf', 547, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 830.00, 0, '\"For families, beginners and beyond\"', 1, NULL, '2025-05-26 17:23:28', '2025-12-23 14:24:35'),
(243, 'Annapurna Classic 15 days', 'The Annapurna circuit is a dream for many mountain travelers, enjoying superb views of the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri and the ever-changing scenery', 15, '5,416m/17,770ft', 'Besishahar Pokhara', '4-6 hours walking', '2-15', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Discover Yourself.', '<p data-start=\"68\" data-end=\"122\">Journey from green valleys to high Himalayan deserts</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"125\" data-end=\"199\">CrossÂ <strong data-start=\"131\" data-end=\"160\">Thorong La Pass (5,416 m)</strong>Â â€” a legendary high-altitude crossing</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"202\" data-end=\"268\">Encounter the living cultures ofÂ <strong data-start=\"235\" data-end=\"266\">Manang, Mustang &amp; Muktinath</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"271\" data-end=\"336\">Epic views ofÂ <strong data-start=\"285\" data-end=\"334\">Annapurna, Dhaulagiri, Manaslu Tilicho Peak</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"339\" data-end=\"435\"><strong data-start=\"339\" data-end=\"356\">Jump-up trips</strong>Â toÂ <strong data-start=\"360\" data-end=\"402\">Ice Lake, Tatopani hot springs &amp; Lupra</strong>, ending inÂ <strong data-start=\"414\" data-end=\"435\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Jomsom or Pokhara</strong></p>', 'private bus/car', 1, NULL, 'annapurna-classic-15-days-rHzo6.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"107\" data-end=\"869\">The <strong data-start=\"111\" data-end=\"148\">Annapurna Full with Ice Lake Trek</strong> offers an unforgettable journey through the Annapurna and Mustang regions, blending towering Himalayan summits with rich cultural experiences. The trek begins in verdant valleys and traditional mountain villages along the <strong data-start=\"379\" data-end=\"399\">Marsyangdi River</strong>, passing through diverse landscapes to reach <strong data-start=\"445\" data-end=\"455\">Manang</strong>, the regionâ€™s largest village and a key stop for acclimatisation. Local legends speak of guardian spirits watching over the surrounding heights, with villagers still performing rituals to honour them. From Manang, the trail continues through the Marsyangdi Valley before ascending toward <strong data-start=\"748\" data-end=\"777\">Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m)</strong>, allowing ample time for acclimatisation to ensure a safer and more comfortable crossing.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"871\" data-end=\"1620\">After crossing Thorong La Pass, the route descends into theÂ <strong data-start=\"931\" data-end=\"954\">Kali Gandaki Valley</strong>, home to the worldâ€™s deepest gorge and famed for its fossil-rich cliffs. The s<strong data-start=\"1032\" data-end=\"1057\">acred site </strong>Muktinath, renowned for its temples, eternal flame, and 108 holy water spouts, adds spiritual significance to the journey. Local stories say the flame has burnt for centuries, protecting the valley and its people. The trek then entered the arid<strong data-start=\"1277\" data-end=\"1312\"> Mustang </strong>region, known for its desert-like landscapes and strong Tibetan influence. Villages such as <strong data-start=\"1398\" data-end=\"1407\">Lupra</strong>, one of Nepalâ€™s last Bon communities, reveal ancient spiritual practices and mountain traditions. Legends speak of monks meditating in hidden caves for decades and sacred stones granting blessings to passersby.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1622\" data-end=\"2036\">The journey concludes with a scenic drive through theÂ Kali Gandaki Valley, crossing the famous village of <strong data-start=\"1732\" data-end=\"1742\">Marpha</strong>, celebrated for its <strong data-start=\"1763\" data-end=\"1836\">a</strong>pple brandy, characteristic village architecture, and apple orchards, before arriving at the rejuvenating <strong data-start=\"1874\" data-end=\"1901\">hot springs </strong>at Tatopaniâ€”â€œTatoâ€ meaning hot and â€œPaniâ€ meaning water in Nepaliâ€”offering a perfect, relaxing finale to this extraordinary Himalayan adventure.</p>', 3, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Â Grade 3: Moderate Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'annapurna-classic-15-days', 182, 'N20828', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'img-1233-9Rb6g.jpg', '1748341245_tho-azY5r.jpg', '1753520936_annapurna-classic-15-with-logo-and-page-number-final-one-utjzs.pdf', 528, 0, '1', '0', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, 1100.00, 0, '\"One Trail, a Thousand Landscapes\"', 1, NULL, '2025-05-27 16:00:18', '2025-12-23 14:25:36'),
(244, 'Khopra Ridge & Balcony 12 days', 'At a comfortable, moderate altitude, the trail avoids the busier routes, giving a quieter and more personal trekking experience than the traditional Annapurna Balcony Trek', 12, '4000', 'Ghandruk - Pokhara', '4/6 hours waliking', '2-15', 'Lodge / teahouse', 'Breathtaking scenery', '<p data-start=\"77\" data-end=\"140\">Explore Gurung and Magar villages and vibrant alpine forests.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"213\">Hike ridges with panoramic views of Annapurna South and Dhaulagiri.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"217\" data-end=\"275\">Witness the golden sunrise from Muldai and Mohare Danda.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"279\" data-end=\"344\">Feel the thrill of walking on the â€œbalconyâ€ of Annapurna South.</p>', 'Bus. Jeep. Flight', 1, NULL, 'khorpa-ridge-balcony-12-days-9kjyx.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"75\" data-end=\"560\">The Khopra Ridge Trek is an easy route, away from busier trails, making it ideal for families and anyone seeking a peaceful Himalayan experience. The journey begins in Kathmandu, followed by a flight to Pokhara and then a drive to Kimche, from where the trek starts in the Annapurna region. Along the way, the trail passes through Gurung and Magar villages, terraced farmlands, and vibrant rhododendron and oak forests, reflecting the authentic mountain lifestyle and local traditions.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"562\" data-end=\"1140\">As the trail climbs, expansive views of the Himalayan giants unfold. From the ridges and viewpoints along the route, Annapurna South (7,219 m), Dhaulagiri I (8,167 m), Machhapuchhre (Fishtail, 6,993 m), Hiunchuli (6,441 m), Gangapurna (7,455 m), and Lamjung Himal (6,983 m) come into view. Scenic spots such as Muldai, Khopra Danda, and Mohare Danda offer unforgettable sunrise and sunset panoramas across these towering mountains. Walking along the natural â€œbalconyâ€ of Annapurna South and Dhaulagiri, high ridges provide sweeping vistas and a true sense of Himalayan grandeur.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1142\" data-end=\"1660\">Along the route, the trail passes near Khayer, a holy lake visited by many pilgrims once a year, though it is not the main destination. The objective is to reach a maximum altitude of around 4,000 m before Khayer, ensuring a rewarding high-altitude experience. The route continues through tranquil alpine landscapes, providing a strong sense of remoteness. With its combination of natural beauty, cultural encounters, and quiet trails, the Khopra Ridge Trek delivers a memorable, family-friendly Himalayan adventure.</p>', 3, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Grade 3: Moderate Treks</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 3,000â€“4,500 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 5â€“7 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Mixed trails with some steep sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for those with prior trekking experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Base Camp Trek, Langtang Valley Trek</li>\r\n</ul>', 'khopra-ridge-balcony-12-days', 183, 'N208210', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mg-0367-gWDUB.jpg', '1752127070_k-8l3l6.jpg', '1753693198_khopra-ridg1-9PNEB.pdf', 463, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 955.00, 0, '\"Near the Annapurna South & Dhaulagiri\"', 1, NULL, '2025-05-29 13:05:56', '2025-12-23 14:26:22');
