(245, 'Manaslu Round 15 days', 'Experience the daily life of Gurung and Tibetan-influenced communities, with mani walls, fluttering prayer flags, sacred chortens, forest wildlife, and breathtaking views of the majestic Himalayan mountains', 15, '5106', 'Machhakhola / Jagat', '4 - 7 hours walking', '2-12', 'Lodges / Teahouse', 'A Remote Himalayan Odyssey', '<p data-start=\"2\" data-end=\"33\"><strong data-start=\"2\" data-end=\"31\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Towering Himalayan peaks.</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"36\" data-end=\"88\"><strong data-start=\"36\" data-end=\"86\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Traditional villages and Buddhist monasteries.</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"91\" data-end=\"151\"><strong data-start=\"91\" data-end=\"113\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Wildlife spotting:</strong> Red Panda, monkeys, Himalayan thar.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"154\" data-end=\"211\"><strong data-start=\"154\" data-end=\"188\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Cross Larkya La Pass (5,135 m)</strong> for panoramic views.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"214\" data-end=\"258\" data-is-last-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"214\" data-end=\"258\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Remote villages near the Tibetan border.</strong></p>', 'Jeep / Bus', 1, NULL, 'manaslu-round-15-days-uLUnA.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"140\" data-end=\"874\">This beautiful trek, the Manaslu Circuit, explores the remote and pristine Manaslu region in northern Nepal, surrounding Mount Manaslu (8,163â€¯m), the worldâ€™s eighth-highest peak. This restricted Himalayan area features deep valleys, terraced farmland, dense forests, and glacial landscapes. Known for its strong Tibetan influence, the region is home to Gurung, Sherpa, and Tibetan-influenced communities, with Buddhist practices and centuries-old monasteries. Villagers offer prayers at mani walls, chortens, and monasteries to ensure safety and prosperity. The circuit offers a complete experience, combining high-altitude adventure, breathtaking scenery, and rich cultural immersion while looping around the mighty Manaslu massif.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"876\" data-end=\"1488\">The trek begins in the lower Budhi Gandaki Valley, following the Budhi Gandaki River through forests, terraced fields, and traditional villages. From Saula Gaon onward, the high mountains loom closer as the valley narrows. Along the trail, the daily life of Gurung and Tibetan-influenced communities unfolds. Mani walls, prayer flags, and chortens reflect the regionâ€™s strong Buddhist culture. Wildlife sightings, including Red Panda, monkeys, and Himalayan thar, are possible in the forested sections. Local stories also speak of spirits guarding sacred lakes and caves, adding a mystical element to the trek.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1490\" data-end=\"2108\">Before reaching Sama Gaon, the trail leads to Pungen Gumba, a natural cave near a large glacier where Guru Rimboche is said to have meditated centuries ago. From Samdo, the Tibetan border feels near, adding a sense of Himalayan frontier to the journey. The trek crosses the high Larkya La Pass (5,135â€¯m), offering wide mountain views, before descending through glacial valleys, remote villages, and yak pastures. The Manaslu Circuit provides an authentic and rewarding Himalayan adventure, combining culture, nature, and high-altitude challenge, enriched by the regionâ€™s fascinating legends and spiritual traditions</p>', 4, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'manaslu-round-15-days', 184, 'N208212', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'maa-MRIzE.jpg', '1748520168_img-20241213-wa0048-rXhE3.jpg', '1753778360_manaslu-round-15-day1-89TbE.pdf', 401, 0, '1', '0', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, 995.00, 0, 'â€œRaw, Remote, Remarkable\"', 1, NULL, '2025-05-29 21:11:00', '2025-12-23 14:37:11'),
(246, 'Manaslu Round & Tsum 21 days', 'A remote and culturally rich trek, the Manaslu and Tsum Valley route offers stunning Himalayan views and deep Buddhist heritage in an off-the-beaten-path adventure', 21, '5135', 'Machhakhola / Jagat', '4-7 hours walking', '2-12', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Hidden valley', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Crowned by the landscape view from Pung Gyen Gompa â€“ the raw, icy splendor of the Manaslu massif itself</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Begin in the vibrant, terraced rice fields â€“ the realm of agriculture and subtropical life.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ascend into the culturally rich Tsum Valley â€“ ancient villages and serene monasteries nestled in temperate forests, showcasing resilient mountain communities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Approach the stark, powerful landscapes near the massif â€“ glacial moraines, turquoise lakes, and the challenging, beautiful Larkya La passFraming the trek as a profound journey upwards through Earth\'s layers and human adaptation.</p>', 'private bus/car', 1, NULL, 'round-manaslu-tsum-valley-21-days-L4uEd.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This exceptional itinerary begins on the classic Manaslu Circuit and soon reaches Lokpa, where a discreet and lesser-travelled valley opens to the rightâ€”the Tsum Valley. Only opened to tourism in 2007, the Tsum Valley remains one of Nepal\'s most preserved and culturally rich regions. Over six days, the journey ventures deep into a valley shaped by Tibetan Buddhist traditions, passing through fertile agricultural lands, ancient monasteries and remote stone-built villages. The trail culminates at Mu Monastery, the last inhabited settlement before the Tibetan border, nestled beneath towering peaks exceeding 7,000 metres. The following days lead to the majestic Larkya La Pass (5,135 m), with each stage offering extraordinary landscape views and a profound sense of Himalayan solitude.</p>', 4, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'manaslu-round-tsum-21-days', 185, 'N208215', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'manaslu-1600x550-m93vT.jpg', '1752469946_1515-uOpIq.jpg', '1753778419_round-manaslu-tsum-valley-21-days-lg8B0.pdf', 359, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1175.00, 0, 'â€œMu Monastery to Larkya La: A Timeless Journeyâ€', 1, NULL, '2025-05-30 12:01:17', '2025-12-23 14:38:14'),
(254, 'Nar-Phu Trek 13 days', 'This beautiful land, touched by Tibetan culture, welcomes visitors to discover its old villages, peaceful monasteries, and amazing mountain views', 13, '5313', 'Besisahar / Bessisahar', '4-6 hours walking', '2-15', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Feel naturel', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This area is a hidden gem for those seeking a unique blend of natural beauty, cultural exploration, and trekking adventure</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore the ancient monasteries, traditional houses, and vibrant prayer flags that the landscape of Phu Gaon and Nar Valley.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A complete change of scenery brought by this trek: dazzling in front of the Himalayas</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The glacial lake Tilicho, the highest lake in the world</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The exceptional view from Khang La pass (5313 m)</p>', 'private bus/car', 1, NULL, 'nar-phu-trek-13-days-PH7Nj.png', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%;\">Softly in the heart of the Annapurna Conservation Area, the Nar-Phu Valley is a special, hidden place in Nepal where time feels slow. This beautiful land, touched by Tibetan culture, welcomes visitors to discover its old villages, peaceful monasteries, and amazing mountain views. Trekking here feels like walking through a timeless story, especially when crossing the high Kang La Pass, where you see wide views of snowy peaks. Nar-Phu stays calm and untouched, offering a quiet and pure place for those who want real beauty, peace, and the soft sounds of the Himalayas.</span></p>', 4, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'narphu-trek-13-days', 187, 'N208227', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1555-QFkLI.jpg', '1749200690_1515-tEr4X.jpg', '1760767749_nar-9FHLL.pdf', 326, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 840.00, 0, '\"Touch the natural\"', 1, NULL, '2025-06-06 18:38:31', '2025-12-23 14:51:49'),
(255, 'Rafting in himalaya', 'Experience the thrill of rafting on Himalayan rivers with exciting rapids, stunning mountain views, and rich local culture. Perfect for both beginners and seasoned adventurers, itâ€™s an unforgettable way to explore Nepalâ€™s natural beauty.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2-4 Rafting', NULL, NULL, 'Dive in deep', NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p>We are not specialised in rafting in Nepal, as our main focus is on mountain and cultural experiences. However, rafting can easily be arranged upon request.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"288\" data-end=\"407\">Below are a couple of our available itineraries with day-by-day breakdowns to help you explore different possibilities:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li data-start=\"288\" data-end=\"407\">Trishuli River (2 Days / Short Trips)</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"288\" data-end=\"407\">Sun Koshi River (9 Days / Expedition Style)</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"288\" data-end=\"407\">Seti River (gentle &amp; scenic)</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"288\" data-end=\"407\">Kali Gandaki (adventurous &amp; spiritual)</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"288\" data-end=\"407\">Bhote Koshi (intense, short bursts)</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"288\" data-end=\"407\">Tamur (trek + raft combo)</li>\r\n</ul>', 2, 5, NULL, 'rafting-in-himalaya', 188, 'N208232', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'banner-ubnKh.jpg', 'real-shortcut-6IGXj.jpg', '', 182, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'We act for the best', 1, NULL, '2025-06-08 21:35:46', '2025-12-24 08:12:23'),
(256, 'Mustang cycling 17 days', 'Pedal to the Forbidden Kingdom is a thrilling ride through Upper Mustangâ€™s ancient trails and windswept Himalayan landscapes. Discover Lo Manthang and the spirit of Tibet on two wheels.', 17, '4065', 'Pokhara - Pokhara', '4-7 hours walking', '2-15', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Mustang Unchained', '<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Lo Manthang: Explore the ancient walled city, the last forbidden kingdom of Nepal.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Sky Caves: Mysterious caves carved into cliffs, holding ancient Buddhist artifacts.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Tiji Festival: A three-day Buddhist festival promoting world peace.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Muktinath Temple: A sacred site for both Hindus and Buddhists.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Kaligandaki Gorge: One of the world\'s deepest canyons.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Unique Landscapes: Arid terrain, towering cliffs, and stunning Himalayan views.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Rich Tibetan Culture: Experience monasteries, prayer flags, and traditional villages.</li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Restricted Trekking Area: Requires special permits, offering an exclusive experience.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Private Vechile', 0, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Why do we choose private transport instead of flights for the Mustang trek?</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We prefer using private vehicles because road conditions have significantly improved in recent years, making land travel more reliable and comfortable. In contrast, mountain flights are often delayed or canceled due to unpredictable weather, causing unnecessary stress and schedule changes. Private transport is not only more dependable but also more affordable and flexible, allowing us to manage the itinerary smoothly and ensure a better experience for our guests.</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Upper Mustang, known as the \"Last Forbidden Kingdom,\" is a remote and special part of Nepal where Tibetan culture is still alive and well. It lies in a dry, high-altitude region and features ancient monasteries, cave homes, and the historic walled city of Lo Manthang. Because itâ€™s a restricted area, you must travel with a licensed guide. Itâ€™s also one of the few treks in Nepal you can enjoy during the summer monsoon.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Upper and Lower Mustang offer exciting mountain biking routes. The desert-like landscapes of Upper Mustang make cycling here a thrilling adventure with amazing views. Lower Mustang, which borders Dolpo and Manang, is home to Muktinath, a sacred pilgrimage site for both Hindus and Buddhists</p>', 4, 5, '<p><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<p>Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</p>\r\n<p>Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</p>\r\n<p>Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</p>\r\n<p>Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</p>\r\n<p>Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek</p>', 'mustang-cycling-17-days', 189, 'N208237', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', 173, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'Ride Beyond the Himalayas, Into the Heart of Mustang.', 0, NULL, '2025-06-13 19:12:52', '2025-12-24 08:33:21'),
(257, 'Self travel in Nepal ?', 'For solo travelers, Lhakpa Trekking recommends hiring at least one guide or porter for safety and support. We can handle all logistics, permits, and provide a dedicated companion to ensure a smooth and secure trip.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p data-start=\"56\" data-end=\"300\"><strong data-start=\"56\" data-end=\"70\">Solo Trip?</strong><br data-start=\"70\" data-end=\"73\">For your safety and security, we donâ€™t usually recommend solo travel. However, you can embark solo with at least one guide or porter, ensuring a safer journey while respecting local tourism rules and supporting the community.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"302\" data-end=\"530\">If you wish, Lhakpa Trekking will manage all logistics, provide accurate information, handle reservations, and arrange all necessary legal documents, including permits and local permissions, for a smooth, hassle-free experience.</p>', 1, 1, NULL, 'self-travel-in-nepal', 190, 'N208238', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '1756624141_img-0316-CELOy.jpg', '', 35, 0, '1', '0', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, '2025-06-13 20:00:40', '2025-12-11 22:06:37'),
(258, 'Island Peak & Ama Dablam 25 days', 'Begin with Island Peak for your first Himalayan summit, then take on the amazing Ama Dablam for a true alpine challenge. Together, create the perfect blend of adventure and achievement.', 25, '6812', 'Lukla - Lukla', '4-7 hours walking', '2-15', 'Tea House /camping', 'Summit Journey', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Island Peak is perfect for first-time climbers ready to reach a real Himalayan summit.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trek through beautiful Sherpa villages, forests, and high mountain valleys.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enjoy stunning views of Everest, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam from the top.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our expert guides ensure safety with proper training and climbing gear.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Acclimatization days are included to help your body adjust to the altitude.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ama Dablam offers a technical challenge for experienced and ambitious climbers.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climb two iconic peaks in one unforgettable Himalayan adventure.</p>', 'Plane /Private /Vechile /jeep', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</em></p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climb Island Peak (6,189 m), one of Nepalâ€™s most popular trekking peaks â€” perfect for your first Himalayan summit. Fly to Lukla, trek through Sherpa villages with views of Everest, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam, and acclimatise before the climb. Youâ€™ll cross glaciers, use ropes, and stand on a summit ridge with unforgettable mountain views.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our expert guides will support you all the way. Ready for more? Add the Ama Dablam Expedition â€” a stunning, technical climb on rock, ice, and snow. Together, they make the ultimate journey: from beginnerâ€™s first peak to one of Nepalâ€™s most iconic climbs.</p>', 5, 5, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 5: Very Strenuous/Challenging Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Above 6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 7â€“9 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: High-altitude passes, glaciers, and technical sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for seasoned trekkers with high-altitude experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Circuit with Pisang, Chulu peak via Thorong La Pass, Makalu Base Camp with Larkya peak, Mera peak, 3 passes with Lobuche, Island peak</li>\r\n</ul>', 'island-peak-ama-dablam-25-days', 191, 'N208243', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2-6tCrH.jpg', '1755154653_1-UKmPD.jpg', '1755229131_island-peak-and-ama-dablam-expeditio1-anpyL.pdf', 176, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"From First Summit to Alpine Legend\"', 1, NULL, '2025-07-03 13:30:14', '2025-12-23 15:26:42'),
(259, 'Kanchanjunga & Selele pass 21 days', 'Explore the remote Kanchenjunga North Base Camp with a thrilling Selele Pass crossing, where wild landscapes and mountain views await. Discover hidden villages and untouched Himalayan beauty.', 21, '5160', 'Taplejung - Taplejung', '4-7 hours walking', '4-12 Pax', 'Tea Houses / lodges', 'Kanchenjunga Odyssey', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hike up to 5,160 m at Kanchenjunga North Base Camp.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Visit both North and South Base Camps of the worldâ€™s 3rd highest mountain.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cross high passes like Selele La with great mountain views.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Walk through jungles, rivers, and alpine forests.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">See rare animals like the snow leopard and Red panda.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Explore local villages and visit old Buddhist monasteries.</p>', 'Plane /Private /Vechile /jeep', 1, NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The Kanchenjunga Base Camp and Selele Pass Trek explores the remote eastern region of Nepal, home to Mount Kanchenjunga (8,586 m), the worldâ€™s third-highest mountain. The trek takes place in the quiet and unspoilt Kanchenjunga Conservation Area, known for its rich wildlife, forests and dramatic mountain scenery.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The journey begins with a flight from Kathmandu to Suketar and continues through traditional villages to Kanchenjunga Base Camp. A key challenge and highlight of the trek is crossing Selele Pass, which involves steep and icy trails but rewards trekkers with outstanding mountain views.The route passes through river valleys, forests, alpine landscapes and glacial terrain, offering excellent views of major Himalayan peaks such as Kanchenjunga, Everest, Lhotse and Makalu. Along the way, trekkers experience the culture and lifestyle of Sherpa, Rai, Limbu and Gurung communities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">As a restricted and less-developed region, the trek requires a licensed guide and special permits. Overall, this trek is a demanding but rewarding adventure, ideal for experienced trekkers seeking remote landscapes, rich culture and true Himalayan wilderness.</p>', 4, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 4: Strenuous Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: 4,500â€“6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 6â€“8 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: Steep ascents, rocky paths, and potential snow</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Everest Base Camp Trek, Manaslu Circuit Trek and all the high passes (Tilicho Thorong la, Ganja la, Mesokanta la, Kang la, Larkya la, Chola la, Kongma la, Renjola).</li>\r\n</ul>', 'kanchanjunga-selele-pass-21-days', 192, 'N208245', NULL, NULL, NULL, '550-tyxwq.jpg', '1751781911_kan-x8ksl.jpg', '1753778696_kanchanjunga-with-selele-21-day2-39nrS.pdf', 367, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1620.00, 0, '\"Kanchenjunga Calls, Selele Awaits\"', 1, NULL, '2025-07-06 14:24:17', '2025-12-23 14:49:59'),
(260, 'Chulu Far East 17 days', 'Experience breathtaking Himalayan views and summit Chulu Far East for an unforgettable adventure. Trek through diverse landscapes and traditional villages, discovering new sights at every step.', 17, '6059 m', 'Besishahar - Besisahar', '4-7 hours walking', '4-12', 'Tea House /camping', '\"Peak Wonders\"', '<p>Â Spectacular Views: See the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri ranges.</p>\r\n<p>Summit Chulu Far East: Climb 6059 m for an unforgettable experience.</p>\r\n<p>Varied Landscapes: Trek through valleys, forests, meadows, and mountains.</p>\r\n<p>Cultural Experience: Visit Gurung villages and Tibetan settlements.</p>\r\n<p>Memorable Adventure: Every step brings new sights and experiences.</p>', 'private bus/car', 2, NULL, '', NULL, '', '<div id=\"features\">\r\n<div class=\"uk-font\">\r\n<div class=\" uk-light-bg uk-padding border uk-margin-top uk-responsive-padding\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Gear:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climbing boots (double boots like La Sportiva G2/Sportiva Baruntse). Crampons (compatible with your boots). Ice axe. Climbing harness. Helmet. Carabiners (locking and on-locking). Ascender (Jumar).Belay/rappel device (ATC or figure 8). Prusik loops / slings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Clothing:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Down jacket (800 fill or higher). Base layers (synthetic or merino). Insulated gloves and mittens. Waterproof jacket and pants. Warm hat and balaclava. Buff/neck gaiter</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Personal:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Headlamp with extra batteries. Sunglasses (category 4 recommended). Sunscreen + lip balm (SPF 50+). Water bottles and/or hydration bladders.Â Water purification (tablets, Steripen, etc.). Sleeping bag (-20Â°C or better). Trekking poles. Snacks (energy bars, gels)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><em><strong>NB</strong>: If missing something or needing to hire, please let us know at least one month in advance to reserve your technical materials.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"itinerary\">\r\n<div id=\"itinerary\" class=\"uk-font uk-margin-top uk-margin-bottom\">\r\n<div class=\"uk-flex uk-flex-middle uk-flex-between\">\r\n<div class=\"uk-font uk-text-center\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â </div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Chulu Far East Expedition is an exciting journey for mountain lovers, offering amazing views of the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri ranges. The trek starts in green valleys and climbs through forests, meadows, and rugged mountain terrain to the high-altitude landscapes near Mustang.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The main highlight is climbing Chulu Far East (6059 m), a challenging peak that rewards adventurers with stunning Himalayan panoramas. Along the way, youâ€™ll pass traditional villages, experience diverse cultures, and enjoy ever-changing landscapes, making this expedition an unforgettable Himalayan adventure.</p>', 5, 4, '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although there are no any distinct and universal grading systems for treks, a general rule of grading is followed to understand the difficulty of a trekking. In Nepal, trekking routes are categorized based on difficulty to help trekkers select suitable adventures. These categories consider factors such as altitude, terrain, duration, and required experience.Â </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Grade 5: Very Strenuous/Challenging Treks</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Altitude: Above 6,000 meters</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Duration: 7â€“9 hours of walking per day</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Terrain: High-altitude passes, glaciers, and technical sections</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Experience Required: Suitable for seasoned trekkers with high-altitude experience</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Examples: Annapurna Circuit with Pisang, Chulu peak via Thorong La Pass, Makalu Base Camp with Larkya peak, Mera peak, 3 passes with Lobuche, Island peak</li>\r\n</ul>', 'chulu-far-east-17-days', 193, 'N208247', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '1755674963_chulu-far-easst-expedition-Vri8X.pdf', 78, 0, '1', '0', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '\"Summit, Explore, Remember\"', 1, NULL, '2025-08-20 16:45:05', '2025-12-23 15:03:34'),
