(278, 163, 'when is the best season for this trek?', 'For the Annapurna Circuit, October and November or April and May are widely considered to be the best times for trekking. The weather during these two seasons is generally clear and dry and so itâ€™s not too cold when heading into high altitudes.', 4, 1, '2025-05-28 15:20:46', '2025-12-21 15:54:47'),
(279, 163, 'Can I do this trek in December ?', 'Annapurna Circuit Trek in December is usually less crowded than any other seasons. The trekking trails are mostly empty and peaceful. The weather condition and temperature of the Annapurna region are bearable during December. The weather might be quite chilly in the higher areas.', 5, 1, '2025-05-28 15:20:46', '2025-12-21 15:54:47'),
(280, 163, 'Can I do this trek in 5 days ?', 'Yes, but safety & security risks are higher especially high altitude sickness.', 6, 1, '2025-05-28 15:20:46', '2025-12-21 15:54:47'),
(281, 244, 'What is the typical itinerary for the Khopra Ridge trek?', 'Standard Khopra Ridge trek lasts 7â€“10 days, starting from Nayapul or Ghandruk and passing through Ulleri, Ghorepani, Swanta, Khopra Danda and sometimes Khayar Lake, before descending via Tatopani or Dobato.', 1, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-08-09 17:18:43'),
(282, 244, 'Can I combine Khopra Ridge with other treks?', 'Yes, Khopra Ridge is often combined with the Poon Hill trek or extended to Annapurna Base Camp for a longer adventure.', 2, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-05-29 14:23:45'),
(283, 244, 'What are the main scenic highlights of the Khopra Ridge trek?', 'Panoramic views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna South, Nilgiri and Machhapuchhre; peaceful alpine ridges; and the optional hike to Khayar Lake are major highlights.', 3, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-08-09 17:16:57'),
(284, 244, 'What makes Khopra Ridge different from Poon Hill or ABC treks?', 'Khopra Ridge is less crowded, offers a higher ridge experience with better solitude and features spectacular views with a more local feel.', 4, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-08-09 17:16:57'),
(285, 244, 'How difficult is the Khopra Ridge trek?', 'It is considered moderate in difficulty. The trail includes some steep ascents, especially toward Khopra Danda, but no technical climbing is required.', 5, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-05-29 14:23:45'),
(286, 244, 'Do I need trekking experience?', 'No, prior experience is necessary, but a good fitness level is recommended.', 6, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-12-21 16:02:29'),
(287, 244, 'What accommodations are available along the trail?', 'Basic teahouses and community-run lodges are available at most stops, with more rustic facilities at higher altitudes like Khopra Danda.', 7, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-08-09 17:16:57'),
(288, 244, 'What gear should I pack for the trek?', 'Essentials include hiking boots, warm layers, a rain jacket, headlamp, water bottle and sleeping bag. Trekking poles are also useful for steep sections.', 8, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-08-09 17:16:57'),
(289, 244, 'Is there interesting wildlife on the trail?', 'Yes! The trail passes through rhododendron forests where you may see Himalayan monals (Nepal\'s national bird), yaks and occasionally langurs or deer.', 9, 1, '2025-05-29 14:23:45', '2025-08-09 17:16:57'),
(290, 218, 'What is the Manaslu and Tsum Valley trek?', 'Itâ€™s a remote and culturally rich trek in the Gorkha region of Nepal, combining the Manaslu Circuit with the sacred Tsum Valley. It offers stunning Himalayan views, Tibetan Buddhist culture, and fewer crowds than Everest or Annapurna.', NULL, 1, '2025-05-29 19:05:04', '2025-05-29 19:05:04'),
(291, 218, 'Can I trek alone?', 'No. Solo trekking is not allowed in the restricted areas of Manaslu and Tsum. You must have a registered guide and a minimum of two trekkers in a group.', NULL, 1, '2025-05-29 19:05:04', '2025-05-29 19:05:04'),
(292, 218, 'What gear should I bring?', 'Essential gear includes:  Down jacket and sleeping bag (rated to -10Â°C or lower)  Trekking boots, layers of warm clothing  Water purification tablets or a filter  Headlamp, first-aid kit, sunscreen, and snacks', NULL, 1, '2025-05-29 19:05:04', '2025-05-29 19:05:04'),
(293, 218, 'How difficult is the trek?', 'Itâ€™s considered moderate to challenging, due to high altitude and long walking days. Good fitness and prior trekking experience help.', NULL, 1, '2025-05-29 19:05:04', '2025-05-29 19:05:04'),
(294, 218, 'What are the lodging options on the trail?', 'Tea houses are available along the trail, even in remote parts of Tsum Valley. They are basic but offer warm meals and a place to sleep', NULL, 1, '2025-05-29 19:05:04', '2025-05-29 19:05:04'),
(295, 218, 'What kind of food is available?', 'Dal Bhat (rice and lentils) is the staple. Youâ€™ll also find noodles, potatoes, soups, pancakes, and sometimes yak cheese. Vegetarian options are common', NULL, 1, '2025-05-29 19:05:04', '2025-05-29 19:05:04'),
(296, 218, 'What is special about Tsum Valley culturally?', 'sum Valley is a sacred Himalayan pilgrimage site with strong Tibetan Buddhist roots. Itâ€™s home to ancient monasteries like Mu Gompa and Rachen Gompa and follows unique cultural traditions.', NULL, 1, '2025-05-29 19:05:04', '2025-05-29 19:05:04'),
(297, 246, 'How difficult is the Manaslu and Tsum Valley trek?', 'It is a strenuous trek suitable for experienced trekkers with good physical fitness. It involves long days, high altitude and crossing the 5,160m Larkya La Pass.', 1, 1, '2025-05-30 13:07:03', '2025-08-11 13:15:20'),
(298, 246, 'Do I need a guide?', 'Yes, a registered guide is mandatory as both regions are restricted areas.', 2, 1, '2025-05-30 13:07:03', '2025-08-11 13:15:20'),
(299, 246, 'What makes Tsum Valley special?', 'Tsum Valley is culturally preserved, with ancient Tibetan Buddhist monasteries, traditional villages and a deep spiritual atmosphere.', 3, 1, '2025-05-30 13:07:03', '2025-08-11 13:15:20'),
(300, 246, 'What level of fitness is required for the Manaslu and Tsum Valley trek, and is there an age limit?', 'This trek is physically demanding and requires good cardiovascular fitness, stamina and mental resilience. Youâ€™ll be walking 5â€“8 hours a day over rugged terrain and high altitudes, including crossing the 5,135m.', 4, 1, '2025-05-30 13:07:03', '2025-08-11 13:15:21'),
(301, 141, 'What is the Everest Three Passes Trek?', 'It is a high-altitude trekking route in the Everest region that crosses three challenging mountain passes: Kongma La (5,535m), Cho La (5,420m) and Renjo La (5,360m). It combines the Everest Base Camp trek with more remote and scenic trails', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:06:43', '2025-08-09 17:28:10'),
(302, 141, 'How is it different from the standard Everest Base Camp trek?', 'The Three Passes Trek is longer, more challenging and covers a wider circuit. While EBC is a linear route,Three Passes is a loop that includes Everest Base Camp as part of the journey.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:06:43', '2025-08-09 17:28:10'),
(303, 141, 'When is the best time to trek the Three Passes?', 'The best seasons are spring (Marchâ€“May) and autumn (late Septemberâ€“November), when skies are clear, and trails are safer.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:06:43', '2025-08-09 17:28:10'),
(304, 141, 'Is it possible to do this trek in winter?', 'Itâ€™s possible, but not recommended unless you\'re experienced. Snow and extreme cold make the passes dangerous in winter.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:06:43', '2025-08-09 17:28:10'),
(305, 141, 'How difficult is the Everest Three Passes Trek?', 'Itâ€™s considered one of the most challenging treks in Nepal due to high altitude, steep climbs and long trekking days. Itâ€™s suitable for fit and experienced trekkers.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:06:43', '2025-08-09 17:28:10'),
(306, 141, 'Do I need a guide for this trek?', 'A guide is highly recommended, especially for navigating passes and ensuring safety. Some parts can be difficult to navigate in snow or fog.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:06:43', '2025-06-01 18:06:43'),
(307, 204, 'What is special about Gokyo?', 'Gokyo is famous for its beautiful glacial lakes, Ngozumpa Glacier and Gokyo Ri (5,360m) which offers panoramic views of four 8,000m peaks: Everest, Lhotse, Makalu, and Cho Oyu.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:13:55', '2025-08-09 17:42:03'),
(308, 204, 'Is it worth climbing Gokyo Ri?', 'Absolutely! The sunrise or sunset view from Gokyo Ri is one of the best in the Himalayasâ€”arguably better than Kala Patthar.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:13:55', '2025-06-01 18:13:55'),
(309, 204, 'How difficult is Cho La Pass?', 'It is a challenging and steep high pass at 5,420 meters, with a glacier section on top. It requires careful footing and sometimes microspikes, especially in snow.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:13:55', '2025-06-01 18:13:55'),
(310, 204, 'Is Cho La Pass dangerous?', 'Itâ€™s not technical but can be risky in bad weather or if unprepared. Always check weather conditions and start early in the morning.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:13:55', '2025-06-01 18:13:55'),
(311, 204, 'What is Kala Patthar and why is it famous?', 'Kala Patthar (5,545m) is a viewpoint above Gorak Shep that offers the closest and most iconic view of Mount Everest.', NULL, 1, '2025-06-01 18:13:55', '2025-06-01 18:13:55'),
(312, 200, 'What is the significance of Kyanjin Gompa?', 'Kyanjin Gompa is a sacred Buddhist monastery and a cultural center at the end of the Langtang trail, surrounded by snow-capped peaks.', 5, 1, '2025-06-02 20:08:46', '2025-08-11 13:46:28'),
(313, 200, 'Is altitude sickness a concern on the Langtang Trek?', 'Yes, since the trek reaches over 3,800 meters at Kyanjin Gompa, acclimatization is important to avoid Acute Mountain Sickness (AMS).', 6, 1, '2025-06-02 20:08:46', '2025-08-11 13:46:28'),
(314, 200, 'What is the best place for panoramic views in Langtang?', 'Tserko Ri, a viewpoint near Kyanjin Gompa (4,984m) offers one of the best sunrise and panoramic views in the region.', 7, 1, '2025-06-02 20:08:46', '2025-08-11 13:46:28'),
(315, 200, 'How was the Langtang region affected by the 2015 earthquake?', 'The Langtang Valley was heavily damaged, with many lives lost. However, the trail and villages have since been rebuilt and are safe for trekking.', 8, 1, '2025-06-02 20:08:46', '2025-08-11 13:46:28'),
(316, 152, 'What is the Tamang Heritage Trail?', 'The Tamang Heritage Trail is a cultural trek in the Langtang region that takes you through traditional Tamang villages, offering insight into local customs, lifestyle and architecture.', 1, 1, '2025-06-02 20:15:27', '2025-08-11 13:33:53'),
(317, 152, 'How is the Tamang Heritage Trail connected to the Langtang Trek?', 'The Tamang Heritage Trail is often done as a loop that merges into the Langtang Valley Trek. Trekkers typically start from Syabrubesi, follow the Tamang Heritage route, then join the Langtang trail at Lama Hotel.', 2, 1, '2025-06-02 20:15:27', '2025-08-11 13:33:53'),
(318, 152, 'What villages are visited on the Tamang Heritage Trail?', 'villages include Gatlang, Tatopani, Thuman, Timure and Briddimâ€”each offering a blend of Tamang culture, Buddhist traditions and mountain views.', 3, 1, '2025-06-02 20:15:27', '2025-08-11 13:33:53'),
(319, 152, 'Who are the Tamang people?', 'Tamang are an ethnic group of Tibetan origin with their own language, customs, dress and religious practices, mostly Buddhist.', 4, 1, '2025-06-02 20:15:27', '2025-08-11 13:33:53'),
(320, 152, 'Is wildlife common along the trek?', 'Yes, you might spot langurs, red pandas, Himalayan birds and sometimes even bears in Langtang National Park', 5, 1, '2025-06-02 20:15:27', '2025-08-11 13:33:53'),
(321, 152, 'Is it possible to stay in a monastery or with a family?', 'Yes, Briddim village offers authentic homestays, some of which are run by families who have converted part of their homes for trekkers.', 6, 1, '2025-06-02 20:15:27', '2025-08-11 13:33:53'),
(322, 152, 'Is the region recovered from the 2015 earthquake?', 'Yes, villages, trails and lodges have been rebuilt. Tourism is encouraged to support ongoing recovery and livelihoods.', 7, 1, '2025-06-02 20:15:27', '2025-08-11 13:33:53'),
(323, 179, 'What kind of accommodation is available during the trek?', 'You\'ll stay in basic teahouses or homestays run by local families. Facilities are simple but cozy and youâ€™ll experience authentic Sherpa and Tamang hospitality.', 4, 1, '2025-06-05 13:26:55', '2025-12-21 16:08:52'),
(324, 179, 'Is Pikey Peak good for a short Himalayan experience?', 'Absolutely. Itâ€™s one of the best off-the-beaten-path treks for those who want big views and deep cultural immersion without the crowds or long durations.', 5, 1, '2025-06-05 13:26:55', '2025-12-21 16:08:52'),
(325, 179, 'Why we start from Phaplu ? Why not from Dhap ?', 'Many trekkers prefer to start the Pikey Peak trek from Phaplu rather than Dhap. The ascent from Phaplu is more gradual, making it easier to acclimatise and enjoy the trek. Phaplu sits at a lower elevation (around 2,470â€¯m) compared to Dhap (2,800â€“2,900â€¯m), allowing a safer and more comfortable adjustment to the altitude.', 6, 1, '2025-06-05 13:26:55', '2025-12-21 17:18:59'),
(326, 128, 'Whatâ€™s the difference between Upper Mustang and Lower Mustang?', 'Lower Mustang is more accessible and less restricted, featuring beautiful villages like Jomsom and Muktinath. Upper Mustang on the other hand, requires a special permit and takes you deep into the ancient Kingdom of Lo, with highlights like Lo Manthang, cave monasteries and authentic Tibetan culture.', 1, 1, '2025-06-10 14:58:59', '2025-08-11 13:21:41'),
(327, 128, 'Do I need a special permit to trek in Mustang?', 'The best time is spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November). However, Mustang lies in a rain shadow. So itâ€™s also one of the few regions in Nepal suitable for monsoon trekking (June to August).', 2, 1, '2025-06-10 14:58:59', '2025-08-11 13:21:41'),
(328, 128, 'How difficult is the Mustang trek?', 'The Mustang trek is moderate in difficulty. The trails are not technically challenging, but altitude and dry terrain can be demanding. Good fitness and acclimatization are important, especially for Upper Mustang.', 3, 1, '2025-06-10 14:58:59', '2025-08-11 13:21:42'),
(329, 128, 'Can I do the trek solo, or do I need a guide?', 'For Upper Mustang, you must trek with a registered guide and at least two trekkers due to permit rules. Lower Mustang can be done independently, but we recommend hiring a guide for safety and cultural insight.', 4, 1, '2025-06-10 14:58:59', '2025-08-11 13:21:42');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_faqs` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `title`, `content`, `ordering`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(330, 128, 'What kind of accommodation is available during the trek?', 'Most villages offer teahouses or lodges with basic but comfortable facilities. Youâ€™ll find traditional food, warm hospitality and cozy rooms. We can also arrange camping treks if you prefer.', 5, 1, '2025-06-10 14:58:59', '2025-08-11 13:21:42'),
(331, 128, 'Is Mustang suitable for families or older travelers?', 'Yes, especially Lower Mustang, which has easier access and more gradual trails. We can take the trek to your fitness level and pace, ensuring comfort and safety for all ages.', 6, 1, '2025-06-10 14:58:59', '2025-08-11 13:21:42'),
(332, 128, 'What makes Mustang different from other trekking regions in Nepal?', 'Mustang offers a rare blend of Tibetan Buddhist culture, unique desert landscapes and historical isolation. Unlike the green hills of Everest or Annapurna, Mustang feels like stepping into another worldâ€”quiet, mystical and rich in heritage.', 7, 1, '2025-06-10 14:58:59', '2025-08-11 13:21:42'),
(333, 144, 'Is the Mustang Round Trek worth it?', 'Yes, if you\'re looking for a remote, culturally rich experience in a Tibetan-influenced region of Nepal. The landscapes are unique and the history is deep, making it very rewarding for serious trekkers and culture lovers.', 1, 1, '2025-06-10 17:08:51', '2025-08-11 13:24:46'),
(334, 144, 'What makes the Mustang trek different from Annapurna or Everest treks?', 'Mustang is more arid and desert-like, with fewer crowds and a strong Tibetan Buddhist culture. Unlike Annapurna or Everest, it feels more like a cultural pilgrimage than a typical mountain adventure', 2, 1, '2025-06-10 17:08:51', '2025-08-11 13:24:46'),
(335, 144, 'Is it too expensive because of the restricted area permit?', 'The permit costs $500 for 10 days, which some find expensive. However, many trekkers say the experience is unique enough to justify the costâ€”especially the visit to Lo Manthang and the ancient caves.', 3, 1, '2025-06-10 17:08:51', '2025-08-11 13:24:46'),
(336, 144, 'Are there roads on the trail? Does it spoil the trek?', 'Yes, some parts now have jeep roads. While this makes access easier, some trekkers feel it reduces the wilderness feel. Choosing side trails and experienced guides helps avoid busy sections.', 4, 1, '2025-06-10 17:08:51', '2025-08-11 13:24:46'),
(337, 144, 'Is the trek physically difficult?', 'Itâ€™s moderate to challenging. The altitude (up to 4,200m) and strong winds can be tough, but the trails themselves are not extremely steep. Good preparation is important.', 5, 1, '2025-06-10 17:08:51', '2025-08-11 13:24:46'),
(338, 144, 'What do trekkers love most about Mustang?', 'The spiritual atmosphere, ancient monasteries, friendly locals, dramatic rock formations and the walled city of Lo Manthang are the highlights most people mention', 6, 1, '2025-06-10 17:08:51', '2025-08-11 13:24:46'),
(339, 132, 'What kind of fitness level do I need for this trek and expedition?', 'A moderate level of fitness is required. You should be comfortable walking 5-7 hours a day on uneven terrain and be prepared for some steep climbs, especially on Yala Peak. Regular cardio exercise and hiking practice before the trip are recommended.', 1, 1, '2025-06-20 14:25:56', '2025-08-11 13:28:44'),
(340, 132, 'When is the best time to do the Langtang Trek and Yala Peak expedition?', 'The best seasons are spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) for stable weather, clear views and moderate temperatures.', 2, 1, '2025-06-20 14:25:56', '2025-08-11 13:28:44'),
(341, 132, 'Do I need previous high-altitude trekking experience?', 'No prior experience is necessary, but previous trekking experience is helpful. Our experienced guides will support you throughout and we emphasize proper acclimatization.', 3, 1, '2025-06-20 14:25:56', '2025-08-11 13:58:19'),
(342, 132, 'What should I pack for the trek and Yala Peak climb?', 'Bring layered clothing for varying weather, sturdy trekking boots, a warm jacket, rain gear, sun protection (hat, sunglasses, sunscreen) trekking poles and personal items. For Yala Peak climb, crampons, harness and helmet are essential, which we can provide if needed.', 4, 1, '2025-06-20 14:25:56', '2025-08-11 13:58:19'),
(343, 132, 'How is altitude sickness managed on this expedition?', 'We follow a careful acclimatization schedule with rest days and gradual altitude gain. Drink plenty of water, avoid alcohol and notify your guide if you feel unwell. We carry emergency oxygen and have plans for evacuation if necessary', 5, 1, '2025-06-20 14:25:56', '2025-08-11 13:28:44'),
(344, 132, 'What type of accommodation can I expect?', 'Mostly basic teahouses with simple rooms and shared bathrooms. Some lodges near Kyanjin Gompa are slightly more comfortable. On the peak climb, camping may be involved.', 6, 1, '2025-06-20 14:25:56', '2025-08-11 13:28:44'),
(345, 132, 'What if the weather is bad or I canâ€™t summit Yala Peak?', 'Safety comes first. We have flexible itineraries and reserve days to adjust plans. If conditions donâ€™t allow a summit, alternative activities and trekking routes will be offered.', 7, 1, '2025-06-20 14:25:56', '2025-08-11 13:28:44'),
(346, 259, 'Where is the Kanchenjunga trek located?', 'The Kanchenjunga trek is in the far eastern region of Nepal, close to the border with Sikkim (India) and Tibet. It explores the area around Mt. Kanchenjunga (8,586 m) the worldâ€™s third-highest peak.', 1, 1, '2025-07-19 19:24:31', '2025-08-11 13:41:18'),
(347, 259, 'How difficult is the Kanchenjunga trek?', 'It is considered as strenuous trek due to its remoteness, high passes and long walking days. Trekkers should have good fitness and some previous high-altitude trekking experience.', 2, 1, '2025-07-19 19:24:31', '2025-08-11 13:41:59'),
(348, 149, 'Do I need to apply for my climbing permits?', 'No. All the permits will be arranged by Adventure Sherpa Tracks team after validating a climberâ€™s attempt to climb a definite peak or a route.', 1, 1, '2025-08-11 14:34:55', '2025-08-11 14:34:55'),
(349, 149, 'Do I need to arrange my insurance?', 'Yes, insurance is necessary for all our expeditions and trekking. You are responsible for getting the proper insurance for the trip. Please make sure your policy covers medical as well as rescue evacuation costs. You can find more details about insurance in the â€œTerms & Conditionsâ€ section and the â€œTravel Insuranceâ€ section as well.', 2, 1, '2025-08-11 14:34:55', '2025-08-11 14:34:55'),
(350, 149, 'How can I get a visa to travel Nepal?', 'You will need a valid visa to travel to Nepal. You can get a â€œVISAâ€ to Nepal through the embassy or other diplomatic mission to your country. You can also get a visa at the entry points to Nepal or at the airport. Please make sure that the passport is valid till the expedition ends. You will also be responsible for any kind of visa requirements. And also, do not forget to carry some passport size photos with you while traveling to Nepal.', 3, 1, '2025-08-11 14:34:55', '2025-08-11 14:34:55'),
(351, 149, 'Do I need experienced?', 'Yes, Previous high-altitude experience is required (preferably above 6,000â€“7,000 m).', 4, 1, '2025-08-11 14:34:55', '2025-08-11 14:35:55'),
(352, 202, 'Do you have dietary restrictions that might affect local meal choices?', 'No, you don\'t have to but alcohol and smoking are restricted in this type of areas.', 1, 1, '2025-08-11 15:00:50', '2025-08-11 15:00:50'),
(353, 202, 'Can I communicate with the local people of this sites?', 'Yes, you can but you must be very careful to whom you are speaking with for your safety.', 2, 1, '2025-08-11 15:00:50', '2025-08-11 15:00:50'),
(354, 202, 'Why this places are importance?', 'This places are included in the world\'s heritages sites,  that is why, we consider this places important.', 3, 1, '2025-08-11 15:00:50', '2025-08-11 15:00:50'),
(355, 214, 'What wildlife can you see during a Chitwan Jungle Safari?', 'In a Chitwan Jungle Safari, you can see rhinos, tigers, elephants, deer, crocodiles and many bird species.', 1, 1, '2025-08-11 15:09:52', '2025-08-11 15:09:52'),
(356, 214, 'When is the best time of year to visit Chitwan National Park for a safari?', 'The best time to visit Chitwan National Park for a safari is from October to March, when the weather is dry, cool and ideal for wildlife spotting.', 2, 1, '2025-08-11 15:09:52', '2025-08-11 15:09:52'),
(357, 214, 'How do you think religion has influenced the architecture here?', 'This question helps travelers notice how religious beliefs shape building styles, decorations and the purpose of structures in the area.', 3, 1, '2025-08-11 15:09:52', '2025-08-11 15:09:52'),
(358, 214, 'Is this trip suitable  for all the ages group?', 'Yes, but you must take care of your small children when travelling.', 4, 1, '2025-08-11 15:12:00', '2025-08-11 15:12:00'),
(359, 245, 'What is the daily trekking distance and altitude gain on the Manaslu Circuit?', 'The Manaslu Circuit trek typically involves daily distances of 10 to 20 kilometers (6 to 12 miles) and an average altitude gain of 500 to 1000 meters per day, though this can vary depending on the specific itinerary and the terrain. The trek duration is usually around 10 to 13 days, not including travel to and from Kathmandu.', 1, 1, '2025-08-11 16:29:35', '2025-08-11 16:29:35'),
(360, 245, 'How difficult is the Manaslu Circuit compared to other Nepal treks?', 'The Manaslu Circuit trek is moderately to highly challenging due to its remote location, high altitude, and rugged terrain. It requires good fitness, acclimatization, and self-reliance, though itâ€™s not technically difficult.', 2, 1, '2025-08-11 16:29:35', '2025-08-11 16:29:35'),
(361, 245, 'When is the best season to do the Manaslu Circuit trek?', 'The best seasons for the Manaslu Circuit trek are spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November). These months offer stable weather conditions, clear skies, and moderate temperatures, making for ideal trekking conditions.', 3, 1, '2025-08-11 16:29:35', '2025-08-11 16:29:35'),
(362, 166, 'What is the Tamang Heritage Trek?', 'Itâ€™s a cultural and scenic trek around the Tamang villages near Langtang, offering rich insight into Tamang culture, traditions, and stunning Himalayan views.', 1, 1, '2025-08-11 17:01:48', '2025-08-11 17:01:48'),
(363, 166, 'What is the difficulty level of the Tamang Heritage Trek?', 'Moderate. Itâ€™s suitable for trekkers with basic fitness. The trail includes some steep sections but no technical climbing.', 2, 1, '2025-08-11 17:01:48', '2025-08-11 17:01:48'),
(364, 166, 'What kind of accommodation is available?', 'Mostly teahouses (basic lodges) with simple rooms and meals, offering warm hospitality.', 3, 1, '2025-08-11 17:01:48', '2025-08-11 17:01:48'),
(365, 166, 'Do I need a special permit?', 'Yes, a TIMS card and Langtang National Park permit are required.', 4, 1, '2025-08-11 17:01:48', '2025-08-11 17:01:48'),
(366, 166, 'Is the trek suitable for beginners?', 'Yes, with reasonable fitness and proper acclimatization, beginners can do it comfortably.', 5, 1, '2025-08-11 17:01:48', '2025-08-11 17:01:48'),
(368, 259, 'What is the best time to trek?', 'Spring (April-May) and Autumn (late September to November) for stable weather and clear skies.', 4, 1, '2025-08-11 17:08:11', '2025-08-11 17:08:11'),
(369, 259, 'How remote is the route?', 'Very remote; limited rescue options and minimal infrastructure.', 5, 1, '2025-08-11 17:08:11', '2025-08-11 17:08:11'),
(370, 259, 'What food can I expect?', 'Basic Nepali and Tibetan dishes; carry some snacks for remote stretches.', 6, 1, '2025-08-11 17:08:11', '2025-08-11 17:08:11'),
(371, 259, 'What is the maximum altitude on this trek?', 'Around 5,100 meters (Selele Pass or nearby high points).', 7, 1, '2025-08-11 17:08:11', '2025-08-11 17:08:11'),
(372, 259, 'What is the Kanchanjunga with Selele Trek?', 'A challenging 3-week trek to the majestic Kanchanjunga region, including a crossing of the remote Selele Pass, offering pristine wilderness and spectacular mountain views.', 3, 1, '2025-08-11 17:08:25', '2025-08-11 17:08:25'),
(377, 215, 'How difficult is this trek?', 'Strenuous to very difficult. High altitude passes (up to ~5,200 m), rugged terrain, and long daily walks require good fitness and trekking experience.', 2, 1, '2025-08-11 17:13:33', '2025-08-11 17:13:33'),
(378, 215, 'Best time to trek?', 'Spring (March to May) and Autumn (September to November) for good weather and views.', 3, 1, '2025-08-11 17:13:33', '2025-08-11 17:13:33'),
(379, 215, 'Is it suitable for beginners?', 'No, this trek requires experience with high altitude and challenging conditions.', 4, 1, '2025-08-11 17:13:33', '2025-08-11 17:13:33'),
(380, 215, 'Is a guide or porter recommended?', 'Yes, especially for the Nar and Phu sections and high passes.', 5, 1, '2025-08-11 17:13:33', '2025-08-11 17:13:33'),
(381, 215, 'What is an average daily trekking time?', 'The average walking hours is around 5 to 8 hours per day, depending on route and weather.', 6, 1, '2025-08-11 17:13:33', '2025-12-21 15:59:26'),
(382, 240, 'What is the Nar-Phu & Annapurna Trek?', 'A combined trek exploring the remote Nar and Phu valleys with the classic Annapurna Circuit highlights.', 1, 1, '2025-08-11 17:21:28', '2025-08-11 17:21:28'),
(383, 240, 'Difficulty level?', 'A combined trek exploring the remote Nar and Phu valleys with the classic Annapurna Circuit highlights.', 2, 1, '2025-08-11 17:21:29', '2025-08-11 17:21:29'),
(384, 240, 'when is the best season for this trek?', 'Spring (March-May) and Autumn (September-November). are the best time for this trek.', 3, 1, '2025-08-11 17:21:29', '2025-08-11 17:21:29'),
(385, 240, 'what kind of  accommodation is available during this trek?', 'Basic teahouses, especially simple in Nar-Phu areas.', 4, 1, '2025-08-11 17:21:29', '2025-08-11 17:21:29'),
(386, 240, 'what is an average daily trek time?', 'An average walking hours is 5â€“7 hours.', 5, 1, '2025-08-11 17:21:29', '2025-08-11 17:21:29'),
(387, 254, 'Where is the Nar-Phu Valley located?', 'Nar-Phu Valley lies in the remote northern region of the Annapurna Conservation Area, close to the Tibetan border.', 1, 1, '2025-08-12 12:08:29', '2025-08-12 12:08:29'),
(388, 254, 'How many days will be spent in Nar and Phu villages?', 'Usually, 1 night in Phu village and 1 night in Nar village, allowing time to explore both.', 2, 1, '2025-08-12 12:08:29', '2025-08-12 12:08:29'),
(389, 254, 'Which permits are required for this trek?', 'You need the Nar-Phu Restricted Area Permit, Annapurna Conservation Area Permit (ACAP), and a TIMS card.', 3, 1, '2025-08-12 12:08:29', '2025-08-12 12:08:29'),
(390, 254, 'Is the trek suitable for beginners?', 'It is considered moderate to challenging due to its remoteness and high altitude. Some trekking experience is recommended.', 4, 1, '2025-08-12 12:08:29', '2025-08-12 12:08:29'),
(391, 254, 'How challenging is the Nar-Phu trek compared to other Annapurna treks?', 'It is more remote and less developed than treks like Annapurna Base Camp, making it physically and logistically harder.', 5, 1, '2025-08-12 12:08:30', '2025-08-12 12:08:30'),
(392, 125, 'Where is Island Peak located?', 'Island Peak (6,189 m) lies in the Everest region of Nepal, near the Imja Valley, southeast of Mount Everest.', 1, 1, '2025-08-12 12:14:17', '2025-08-12 12:15:08'),
(393, 125, 'Is it suitable for beginners?', 'Itâ€™s suitable for trekkers with good fitness and some basic climbing training. Previous high-altitude trekking experience is highly recommended.', 2, 1, '2025-08-12 12:14:17', '2025-08-12 12:14:17'),
(394, 125, 'Why is it called Island Peak?', 'The British Everest Expedition in 1953 named it because it looks like an island surrounded by glaciers from Dingboche.', 3, 1, '2025-08-12 12:14:17', '2025-08-12 12:14:17'),
(395, 125, 'What kind of training is needed?', 'Cardio endurance, leg strength, core stability, and prior trekking at high altitude are essential. Technical climbing training before the trip is advised.', 4, 1, '2025-08-12 12:14:17', '2025-08-12 12:14:17'),
(396, 125, 'Is there a training day before the climb?', 'Yes, at Island Peak Base Camp there is a climbing skills session led by your guide.', 5, 1, '2025-08-12 12:14:17', '2025-08-12 12:14:17'),
(397, 157, 'Where is Larke Peak located?', 'Larke Peak (6,249 m) is in the Manaslu region of Nepal, close to the Larkya La Pass on the Manaslu Circuit trail.', 1, 1, '2025-08-12 12:21:15', '2025-08-12 12:21:15'),
(398, 157, 'Best season for this trip?', 'Spring (Marchâ€“May) and Autumn (Septâ€“Nov) offer the best weather and views.', 2, 1, '2025-08-12 12:21:15', '2025-08-12 12:21:15'),
(399, 157, 'Is this trip a combination of trekking and climbing?', 'Yes, it combines the classic Manaslu Circuit trek with a climbing expedition to Larke Peak.', 3, 1, '2025-08-12 12:21:15', '2025-08-12 12:21:15'),
(400, 157, 'How difficult is the Manaslu Circuit with  Larke Peak trip?', 'Itâ€™s considered strenuous due to high altitude, long trekking days, and the summit climb.', 4, 1, '2025-08-12 12:21:15', '2025-08-12 12:21:15'),
(401, 157, 'How many acclimatization days are included?', 'Usually 2â€“3 acclimatization/rest days are built in before the climb.', 5, 1, '2025-08-12 12:21:15', '2025-08-12 12:21:15'),
(402, 258, 'Where are Island Peak and Ama Dablam located?', 'Both are in the Everest region of Nepal. Island Peak  is in the Imja Valley, while Ama Dablam rises above Pangboche.', 1, 1, '2025-08-12 12:27:30', '2025-08-12 12:27:30'),
(403, 258, 'What permits are required?', 'Youâ€™ll need:  Island Peak climbing permit (NMA),  Ama Dablam climbing permit (Nepal Ministry of Tourism), Sagarmatha National Park permit,  Khumbu Pasang Lhamu Rural Municipality permit.', 2, 1, '2025-08-12 12:27:30', '2025-08-12 12:27:30'),
(404, 258, 'Best season for the expedition?', 'Autumn (Octâ€“Nov) is most popular for Ama Dablam; Spring (Aprilâ€“May) is also possible but less common for Ama Dablam.', 3, 1, '2025-08-12 12:27:30', '2025-08-12 12:27:30'),
(405, 258, 'Why combine these two climbs?', 'Island Peak is a perfect acclimatization and skills warm-up for Ama Dablam, which is a more technical and challenging climb.', 4, 1, '2025-08-12 12:27:30', '2025-08-12 12:27:30'),
(406, 258, 'How hard is Ama Dablam compared to Island Peak?', 'Ama Dablam is significantly more technical and exposed, requiring strong rope skills, comfort on steep rock/ice, and high-altitude experience.', 5, 1, '2025-08-12 12:27:30', '2025-08-12 12:27:30'),
(407, 258, 'Do I need prior climbing experience?', 'Yes. Island Peak can be done with basic training, but Ama Dablam requires prior alpine climbing or advanced mountaineering experience.', 6, 1, '2025-08-12 12:27:30', '2025-08-12 12:27:30'),
(408, 260, 'What is the best season to climb?', 'he best seasons are spring (Marchâ€“May) and autumn (Septemberâ€“November) for clear skies and moderate temperatures.', NULL, 1, '2025-08-20 17:20:14', '2025-08-20 17:20:14'),
(409, 260, 'How long does the trek take?', 'Most expeditions range from 10â€“21 days depending on the route and summit plan.', NULL, 1, '2025-08-20 17:20:15', '2025-08-20 17:20:15'),
(410, 260, 'Are rest days included?', 'Yes, we include acclimatization days to reduce the risk of altitude sickness.', NULL, 1, '2025-08-20 17:20:15', '2025-08-20 17:20:15'),
(411, 260, 'Do I need previous mountaineering experience?', 'Basic trekking experience is recommended; for technical climbs, prior experience is helpful but not always required with our expert guides.', NULL, 1, '2025-08-20 17:20:15', '2025-08-20 17:20:15'),
(412, 260, 'Basic trekking experience is recommended; for technical climbs, prior experience is helpful but not always required with our expert guides.', 'We monitor health daily, provide guidance on acclimatization, and can arrange evacuation if necessary.', NULL, 1, '2025-08-20 17:20:15', '2025-08-20 17:20:15'),
(413, 260, 'Are guides and porters provided?', 'Yes, certified guides and experienced porters accompany every expedition.', NULL, 1, '2025-08-20 17:20:15', '2025-08-20 17:20:15'),
(414, 260, 'Can I rent gear locally?', 'Yes, some equipment is available to rent in Kathmandu', NULL, 1, '2025-08-20 17:20:15', '2025-08-20 17:20:15'),
(415, 260, 'Are medical facilities available?', 'Basic health posts are on the trail; our guides carry first aid kits.', NULL, 1, '2025-08-20 17:20:15', '2025-08-20 17:20:15'),
(416, 131, 'How long does the trek take?', 'Typically 12â€“14 days from Lukla, including acclimatisation days in Namche Bazaar and Dingboche.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 16:11:02', '2025-12-21 16:14:15'),
(417, 131, 'Do I need prior trekking experience?', 'No prior experience is required. However, regular walking or trekking experience, stamina, and basic fitness will make your journey much more comfortable.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 16:11:02', '2025-12-21 16:14:15'),
(418, 131, 'What are the main challenges of the trek?', 'The main challenges are altitude, long walking days, and cold weather. Proper acclimatisation, hydration, and a slow pace are vital.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 16:11:02', '2025-12-21 16:14:15'),
(420, 131, 'How long does the trek take?', 'Typically 12â€“14 days from Lukla, including acclimatisation days in Namche Bazaar and Dingboche.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 16:11:26', '2025-12-21 16:14:15'),
(421, 131, 'Do I need prior trekking experience?', 'No prior experience is required. However, regular walking or trekking experience, stamina, and basic fitness will make your journey much more comfortable.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 16:11:26', '2025-12-21 16:14:15'),
(424, 171, 'What are the highlights of this trek?', 'Stunning views of Everest, Lhotse, and Cho Oyu; the turquoise Gokyo Lakes; Ngozumba Glacier (the longest in the region); and cultural experiences in Namche Bazaar and Khumjung Monastery.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 17:15:43', '2025-12-21 17:15:43'),
(425, 171, 'Is the trek safe?', 'Yes, with experienced guides. We prioritise safety, gradual acclimatisation, and secure routes for an enjoyable journey.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 17:15:43', '2025-12-21 17:15:43'),
(426, 171, 'What makes Kongde Resort special?', 'Kongde Resort offers comfortable lodging with panoramic mountain views, combining rest and relaxation with immersion in nature.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 17:15:43', '2025-12-21 17:15:43'),
(427, 171, 'Is safety a concern on these treks?', 'Safety is our priority. Our experienced guides ensure proper acclimatisation, secure routes, and support throughout the journey.', NULL, 1, '2025-12-21 17:15:43', '2025-12-21 17:15:43');
