(1160, 122, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu 1350m. Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2023-07-28 21:03:37', '2025-12-16 16:33:35'),
(1161, 122, '2', NULL, 'Final gear preparation and briefing day', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p> Final gear preparation and briefing day</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b>\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 2, '2023-07-28 21:03:37', '2025-09-24 17:32:21'),
(1162, 122, '3', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ramechhap - Lukla (2860 m) - Phakding (2610 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'We drive early in the morning from Kathmandu, (departure approximately 2:00 AM) to Ramechhap Airport, where breakfast will be provided prior to your scheduled flight to Lukla. This scenic flight, which is strictly weather-dependent, offers passengers spectacular aerial views of the Himalayan mountain range. Upon arrival at Lukla Airport, our team will assist with the proper distribution of equipment and supplies among the porters and Sherpa staff before formally commencing the trekking expedition..<br>Upon arrival in Lukla, your trek will commence with a scenic journey to Phakding. Along the way, you will traverse iconic suspension bridges, pass through charming traditional villages, and immerse yourself in the regionâ€™s breathtaking natural landscapes. <br>Note:<br>â€¢  Due to potential congestion at Kathmandu Airport, the Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN) may mandate that all flights to Lukla operate either from Kathmandu Airport or from Ramechhap Airport.<br>â€¢  In the event that the flight is canceled due to adverse weather conditions, it will be rescheduled for the following day. An additional nightâ€™s accommodation will be provided either in Kathmandu or Ramechhap, depending on the point of departure.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transfer: 4 hours drive. 25 minutes flight.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss : 450 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 3, '2023-07-28 21:03:37', '2025-08-27 20:46:07'),
(1234, 128, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p><p></p>', 1, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-12-16 15:40:32'),
(1235, 128, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p><b></b>We drive to Pokhara with a&nbsp; scenic lakeside city, beautiful views of the Annapurna range. Home to the Magars, Gurungs and Thakalis, this region is rich in culture and history. Upon arrival, enjoy free time to relax at lakeside cafÃ©s, rent a boat on Phewa Lake or prepare for your trek. Shops along the main streets offer local crafts, international food and any gear you may need.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Transport : 5/6 hours drive by jeep (Pokhara).</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 2, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-10-18 12:06:46'),
(1236, 128, '3', NULL, 'Pokhara â€“ Jomsom - Kagbeni (2,800 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>We start the day early with a private jeep ride along the\r\nKaligandaki Valley, Jump up between Nilgiri and Dhaulagiri, with the Annapurna\r\nmountain range surrounding us. Upon arrival in Kagbeni, the gateway to Mustang,\r\nwe meet our local team, including porters and assistant guides.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon.</b><br><b>Transport : 5/6 hours drive by jeep (Kagbeni).</b><br></p>', 3, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-10-18 12:06:46'),
(1237, 128, '4', NULL, 'Kagbeni - Tange (3240 m) - Chhusang (2980 m) - Chele (3070 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>This day takes you through spectacular landscapes along the ancient Mustang\r\nHighway.<b> </b>The climb to the village of Tenge is quite steep but\r\nrewarding, with a beautiful chorten and the impressive 800 years old, Menchin\r\nLhakhang Monastery to explore. We pass through the village of Chhusang and\r\ncontinue onwards to the Gula Pass at 4,070 metres. From there, the path follows\r\nthe dramatic Kali Gandaki gorges, leading us to the village of Chele.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 705 m. Elevation loss: 483 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 4, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-20 14:02:01'),
(1238, 128, '5', NULL, 'Chele - Samar (3,600 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Chele, we walk along the riverbank before the trail\r\nslowly climbs to Taklam Pass. At the top, we enjoy amazing views of Nilgiri,\r\nTilicho Peak and the village of Gyakar across the valley. Samar is a small\r\nvillage offering a peaceful atmosphere and a chance to experience traditional\r\nMustang culture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </b><br><b>Elevation gain: 688 m. Elevation loss: 144 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 5, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-20 14:02:01'),
(1239, 128, '6', NULL, 'Samar â€“ Syanbochen (3800 m) - Gheling (3,570 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>This section is fairly easy, despite crossing several\r\nmountain passes around 4,000 metres. Yamdo La, at 4,010 metres, is the highest\r\npoint of the day. After passing the small village of Syanbochen, we descend to\r\nGheling. Along the way, we stop at the ancient Sakyapa Monastery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 766 m. Elevation loss: 831 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 6, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-12 00:28:21'),
(1240, 128, '7', NULL, 'Gheling â€“ Dhakmar (3,810 m )', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>At the start of the day, we ascend toward the Nyi-La Pass,\r\nfollowed by a descent into the village of Ghami, which is nestled among caves.\r\nThere, we visit the 500 years old monastery, Ghami Shedrup Darkeling Gomba.\r\nAfter the visit, we continue with a gentle half-hour climb, passing by a mani\r\nwall, before reaching the village of Drakmar. We spend the night in a local\r\nfamily\'s home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 700 m. Elevation loss: 513 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 7, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-20 14:02:01'),
(1241, 128, '8', NULL, 'Dhakmar â€“ Charang (3,580 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today is mostly downhill, Starting from Drakmar, we\r\nfollow the riverbank to reach the village of Ghara, where we visit Ghara\r\nMonastery, a Nyingmapa school founded in 775. The journey then continues with a\r\nclimb to Morang La Pass at 4,150 meters. From there, we proceed to the village\r\nof Tsarang, passing through Lo Ghekar along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </b><br><b>Elevation gain: 244 m. Elevation loss: 428 m. 5 hours walking.</b></p>', 8, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-12-21 18:46:26'),
(1242, 128, '9', NULL, 'Charang â€“ Lo manthang (3840 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we start with a steep downhill,\r\nfollowed by a sharp ascent that leads to a high plateau offering spectacular&nbsp; beautiful views. As we progress, the landscape becomes increasingly dry, with\r\nstriking layers of colorful rock formations. We then pass through dramatic\r\ngorges before reaching the valley of Lo Manthang, the historic capital of Upper\r\nMustang.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </b><br><b>Elevation gain: 741 m. Elevation loss: 502 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 9, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-25 16:05:32'),
(1243, 128, '10', NULL, 'Lo Manthang - Nyamdo (4048) - Lo manthang', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Early in the morning, we explore Lo-Manthang and visit the\r\nJamba Lhakhang monastery. In the afternoon, we head to the Gharphu Gomba\r\nmonastery, known for its ancient and exquisite wall paintings. We then return\r\nto Lo-Manthang, passing through the village of Nyaphu. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 276 m. Elevation loss: 114 m. 5 hours walking.</b></p>', 10, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-08-27 19:45:31'),
(1244, 128, '11', NULL, 'Lo Manthang - Day excursion', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Early in the morning, you have the opportunity to attend the\r\ndaily ceremonies at the monasteries of Chhyode Gomba (Sakyapa) or Namgal Gomba.\r\nIf you wish, you can visit the old palace to meet the king, who will welcome\r\nyou with a kata as a traditional gesture of hospitality. You can also ask him\r\nquestions, which his nephew acting as interpreter will gladly answer. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon\r\nevening.</b></p>', 11, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-06-10 17:26:21'),
(1245, 128, '12', NULL, 'Lo Manthang - Drakmar (3800m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The journey from Lo Manthang to Drakmar is a&nbsp; beautiful and\r\nfulfilling stroll across the untamed terrain of Upper Mustang. After a moderate\r\nascent to Chogo La Pass, the day\'s highest point at about 4,200 metres, the\r\ntrail descends sharply past red cliffs, tight gorges and caverns. Along the\r\nway, youâ€™ll pass ancient monasteries like Ghar Gompa and traditional\r\nTibetan-style villages, with amazing views of the Himalayas. The path is rocky\r\nand dusty in places, so good shoes and care are important. This trek offers a\r\npeaceful mix of nature, culture and adventure.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 749m, Elevation loss: 764m. 6 hours walking.</b><b></b><br></p>', 12, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-20 14:02:01'),
(1246, 128, '13', NULL, 'Drakmar -  Ghiling (3810m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The hike from Drakmar to Ghiling follows the same trail as\r\nbefore, offering familiar views of red cliffs, caves and chortens. The path is\r\nmostly downhill with a few gentle climbs, passing through quiet villages and\r\nopen, windswept terrain</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 508m, Elevation loss: 761m. 4/5 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 13, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-20 14:02:01'),
(1247, 128, '14', NULL, 'Ghiling - Chhusang (3050m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>We retrace the trail through Lower Mustangâ€™s windswept landscape from Ghiling to Chhusang, enjoying a scenic descent. Along the way, youâ€™ll pass charming villages, historic stone walls and expansive views of the Annapurna and Nilgiri ranges. The warming air and changing vegetation mark a pleasant return to the lower valleys. With its distinctive red cliffs and peaceful atmosphere, Chhusang is an ideal stop before continuing your Mustang adventure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1104m, Elevation loss: 1676m. 9/10 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 14, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-20 14:02:01'),
(1248, 128, '15', NULL, 'Chhusang - Muktinath (3612m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nThe trek from Chhusang to Muktinath is a beautiful and peaceful journey. As you climb, the dry valleys change to mountain scenery with great views of Dhaulagiri and Nilgiri. You will pass Jharkot, a traditional Tibetan village. When you reach Muktinath, a holy place for both Hindus and Buddhists, you can visit its ancient temple, see 108 holy water spouts, and enjoy the quiet mountain setting\r\n\r\n<br></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1391m, Elevation loss: 596m.8/9 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 15, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-07-12 00:28:22'),
(1249, 128, '16', NULL, 'Muktinath â€“ Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After breakfast, we drive from Muktinath to\r\nPokhara (mostly smooth). The trail descends through dry landscapes and traditional villages like Jharkot and Kagbeni. You then reach Jomsom, a main town in the region. From there, you can take a flight or drive to Pokhara, enjoying views of rivers, waterfalls, and green hills along the way.</p><p></p><div></div>\r\n\r\n<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 6/7 hours drive by jeep (Pokhara).</b></p>', 16, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-10-18 12:06:46'),
(1250, 128, '17', NULL, 'Pokhara - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Once breakfast is finished, you will drive back to\r\nKathmandu. Approximately six or seven hours are needed to finish this\r\npicturesque drive along the Prithvi Highway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 6/7 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b><br></p><p></p>', 17, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-10-18 12:06:46'),
(1251, 128, '18', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 18, '2023-07-30 16:37:01', '2025-12-16 15:40:32'),
(1270, 132, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-12-16 16:10:03'),
(1271, 132, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Dhunche (1965 M)- Syabru Besi (1460 m)', '1,550m', NULL, '7-8 Hours', '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we drive from Kathmandu to Dhunche, along winding mountain roads with scenic views of hills, rivers, and villages. From Dhunche, the road continues downhill for about 1â€“2 hours to Syabru Besi, a small town and the starting point for treks in the Langtang region.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p><p><b></b><b></b>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transfer: 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Syabru Besi).</b>\r\n\r\n<b></b></p><p></p>', 2, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-10-16 17:31:17'),
(1272, 132, '3', NULL, 'Syabru Besi - Lama Hotel (2460 m)', '2,380m', NULL, NULL, '<p>After breakfast the day starts with a trail that winds\r\nthrough landslide-prone areas, featuring several ascents and descents. This\r\nsection ends at a suspension bridge crossing the Langtang Khola. After crossing\r\nanother new river again, we make a steep climb to Rimche (2,250m), followed by\r\na gentle descent to Changtangâ€”commonly known as \"Lama Hotel\", named\r\nafter the first lodge established in the area.</p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:1174 m. Elevation loss :175 m. 6 hours walking.</b><b></b><br>', 3, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-07-12 21:49:39'),
(1273, 132, '4', NULL, 'Lama Hotel â€“Ghora Tabela- Langtang village (3430 m)', '3,430m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today the trial from Lama Hotel climbs steadily through lush\r\nforests of oak, maple and rhododendron, gradually opening to views of\r\nsnow-capped peaks. After about two hours, you reach Ghora Tabela, with wide\r\nviews of the Langtang Himal. From there, the valley widens as you pass yak\r\npastures, Tamang village, mani walls and prayer wheels. The landscape becomes\r\nmore alpine, leading to Langtang Village, a traditional Tamang settlement set\r\nbeneath towering cliffs and glacial peaks.</p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:1015 m. Elevation loss: 80 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br>', 4, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-07-20 17:33:37'),
(1274, 132, '5', NULL, 'Langtang village â€“ Kyangjin (3870 m)', '3,870m', NULL, NULL, '<p>This day is the easy and good trek. The trail reaches a ridge with a\r\nlarge chorten and prayer wall, passing the main settlement before descending to\r\nKyanjinâ€™s lodges and cheese factory. In the afternoon, you can hike Kyanjin Ri\r\nfor stunning mountain views or explore the gently rising Langtang Valley toward\r\nthe yak pastures.</p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:450 m. 3 hours walking.</b><br>', 5, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-07-20 17:33:37'),
(1275, 132, '6', NULL, 'Ascent of Tsergo Ri (4984 M ) or Discover of the Langtang Valley / Acclimatization day', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today is your acclimatisation day\r\nand final climbing gear check. You can choose to hike up Tsergo Ri<b> </b>for\r\namazing panoramic mountain views, including Langtang Lirung, Dorje Lakpa and\r\neven distant Shishapangma. The hike is rewarding but can be tough due to the\r\naltitude. If you prefer an easier day, you\r\ncan explore the beautiful upper Langtang Valley, visit yak pastures, or relax\r\nin the village. In the afternoon, your climbing\r\nguide will check your gear and give a short training session to prepare you for\r\nthe climb ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1105 m. Elevation loss: 1105 m. 7/8 hours Walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 6, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-07-20 17:33:37'),
(1276, 132, '7', NULL, 'Kyangjin - Yala Peak Base Camp (4900 m)', '4,800m', NULL, NULL, '<p>This day takes you from Kyanjin\r\nGompa to Yala Peak Base Camp. The trail takes you across rugged moraine and\r\nopen yak pastures, with beautiful views of the Langtang Himalayas. After\r\nreaching base camp, you\'ll set up camp and rest. In the afternoon, your\r\nclimbing guide conducts basic training on the use of climbing equipment, safety\r\ntechniques, and route briefing to prepare you for the summit push.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1030 m. Elevation loss: 20 m. 5 hours Walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-08-27 21:00:09'),
(1277, 132, '8', NULL, 'Summit Yala Peak (5732 m) - return to Kyanjin Gompa', '5,520m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Start early in the morning, we&nbsp; climb Yala Peak. The climb is\r\nchallenging and involves walking on snow and ice with special gear like\r\ncrampons, ropes, and harnesses. From the top, enjoy amazing views of\r\nShishapangma (8,027 m) in Tibet. After the climb, go back down to base camp and\r\nthen return to Kyanjin Gompa to rest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain:880 m. Elevation loss:1870 m. 5 hours Walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 8, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-07-20 17:33:37'),
(1278, 132, '9', NULL, 'Kyjangjin Gompa - Lama Hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>We retrace our steps back through the Langtang Valley. The\r\ndownhill walk is easier and offers a different perspective of the landscapes we\r\npassed on the way up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain:100 m. Elevation loss:1500 m. 6/7 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 9, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-07-12 21:49:39'),
(1279, 132, '10', NULL, 'Lama Hotel - Thulo Syabru (2130 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>We follow the same trail back down through the Langtang\r\nValley. The descent is more relaxed and reveals new angles of the scenery we previously\r\nclimbed through. This\r\nevening, we share our final moments with the portersâ€”a meaningful time to\r\nreflect on the journey and celebrate the experiences weâ€™ve shared together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 760 m . Elevation loss: 940 m. 5/7 hours Walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 10, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-07-12 21:49:39'),
(1280, 132, '11', NULL, 'Thulo Shyabru â€“  Dunche - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Starting your day from Thulo\r\nShyabru, you trek downhill through beautiful forests and traditional villages\r\nto reach Dunche, the administrative center of Rasuwa District. After arriving\r\nin Dunche, drive back to Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Transfer: 6 hours  drive by jeep (Kathmandu).<b></b>\r\n\r\n<br></b></p><p></p>', 11, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-10-16 17:31:17'),
(1281, 132, '12', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, '7-8 Hours', '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 12, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-12-16 16:10:03'),
(1282, 132, '13', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 13, '2023-07-30 17:21:12', '2025-12-16 16:10:03'),
(1340, 122, '4', NULL, 'Trek from Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3440 m)', '3,440m', NULL, NULL, 'We start the day with a pleasant walk through pine forest along the river, followed by a short climb out of a narrow gorge. After passing the entrance to Khumbu National Park, where permits are checked, we descend to cross the river on a suspension bridge. The trail continues through a wooded valley, crossing the river again before reaching a confluence from Thame and the Khumbu. A final crossing on a high suspension bridge marks the start of a challenging 1.5-hour ascent to Namche Bazaar, with our first views of Everest midway.<br>Upon arrival, we check into a local lodge. Once a quiet village, Namche has evolved into a bustling trekking hub, offering a mix of tradition and modernityâ€”complete with bakeries, cafÃ©s, pubs, and other comforts brought back by well-traveled Sherpas.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m. Elevation loss : 409 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 4, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-09-24 17:28:01'),
(1341, 122, '5', NULL, 'Day Excursion, Everest View Point -Khumjung 4000 m) - Namche', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Today is a well-deserved rest day to acclimatize and enjoy the surroundings. For those inclined, a hike to the Everest View Hotel (3,880 m) offers landscape views of the Himalayas. Alternatively, you may choose to explore Namche Bazaarâ€”relax in a local cafÃ©, browse the lively market for unique items, or visit the Sherpa Museum to gain insight into local culture. The day concludes with an overnight stay in this iconic mountain village.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br> </div>', 5, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-09-24 17:29:29'),
(1342, 122, '6', NULL, 'Nameche Bazaar â€“ Tengbuche (3860 m)', '3,870m', NULL, NULL, 'Today, we trek from Namche Bazaar to Tengboche, offers a truly unforgettable experience, with spectacular views of Mount Everest, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam. The route start with a descent through pine forests and across the Dudh Koshi River via suspension bridges. Upon reaching Phunki Thenga, the trail ascends steeply through rhododendron and pine forests. Despite the challenge, the amazing Himalayan scenery provides constant reward. The day concludes in the serene village of Tengboche, leaving you with lasting memories of the regionâ€™s natural beauty and tranquility.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 921 m. Elevation loss : 700 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 6, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-09-24 17:29:29'),
(1343, 122, '7', NULL, 'Tengbuche â€“ Dingbuche (4410 m)', '4,243m', NULL, NULL, 'After breakfast, the day start with a descent through lush forests, followed by a scenic crossing of the renowned Imja River, an ideal location for capturing memorable photographs. The trail continued with a gradual descent through forested terrain before easing into a gentle ascent toward Dingboche.<br>Along the way, you passed through Pangboche, a charming Sherpa village offering magnificent views of Ama Dablam and other towering Himalayan peaks. The surrounding landscape is truly beautiful, with glacial rivers and snow-draped mountains enhancing the experience.<br>The final stretch included a steady incline leading to the peaceful village of Dingboche. The day concluded with a warm welcome, a comfortable overnight stay, and a delicious local dinner, providing the perfect end to a rewarding day on the trail<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 550 m. Elevation loss: 273 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br> </div>', 7, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-09-24 17:32:22'),
(1344, 122, '8', NULL, 'Rest Day - CLimb to Nagarjun', '4,930m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><b></b>\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 8, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-07-16 21:51:42'),
(1345, 122, '9', NULL, 'Dingbuche â€“ Lobuche (4900 m)', '5,364m', NULL, NULL, 'After breakfast, the journey continues beyond Thukla, where the poignant Everest Memorial stands as a solemn tribute to the climbers who lost their lives on the mountain. From here, the trail start with&nbsp; a steep and demanding ascent toward Lobuche, making this section one of the most challenging yet rewarding.<br>The climb starts gradually through rugged, rocky terrain dotted with yak farms, leading up to the Thukla Pass, a difficult ascent marked by the moving memorial site. Along the way, youâ€™ll be treated to landscape views of majestic peaks such as Pumori, Nuptse and Lobuche Peak, as well as striking glacier moraines that carve the landscape. After five to six hours of trekking, you will arrive in Lobuche, where you can rest and recharge, preparing for the adventures that lie ahead.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 530 m. Elevation loss : 00 m. 5 hours  walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 9, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-08-27 20:46:07'),
(1346, 122, '10', NULL, 'Lobuche â€“ Everest base camp (5364 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Today, we depart from Lobuche, trekkers follow a trail along the Khumbu Glacier, navigating glacial moraines and rugged terrain as they ascend to Gorakshep, the last settlement before Everest Base Camp and a key stop for both trekkers and climbers.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 395 m. Elevation loss : 60 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 10, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-08-27 20:46:07'),
(1347, 122, '11-48', NULL, 'Everest climbing Period', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Everest climbing Period. <div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 11, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-07-16 21:51:42'),
(1348, 122, '49', NULL, 'Packing up base camp', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b>\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 12, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-07-16 21:51:42'),
(1349, 122, '50-51', NULL, 'Reserve day', '4,371m', NULL, NULL, '<p>A reserve days is included in the itinerary to allow flexibility in case of bad weather during the summit push. Due to the unpredictable conditions at high altitude, this extra day helps ensure safety and increases the chances of a successful ascent by waiting for a suitable weather window.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>', 13, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-08-27 20:46:07'),
(1350, 122, '52', NULL, 'Base Camp - Dingbuche', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 14, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-07-16 21:51:42'),
(1351, 122, '53', NULL, 'Dinbuche - Namche', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>You will trek back to Namche Bazaar, where you can rest and celebrate your achievement.\r\n\r\n<br></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div>', 15, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-08-27 20:48:38'),
(1352, 122, '54', NULL, 'Trek back to Lukla.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You will trek back to Lukla, where you will spend the night before flying back to Kathmandu. <div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div>', 16, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-08-27 20:46:07'),
(1353, 122, '55', NULL, 'Back to Kathmandu & transfer to the hotel/dinner.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This day is reserved for leisure. You can explore the city of Kathmandu and do some last-minute shopping. <div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning.</b></div>', 17, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-08-27 20:46:07'),
(1354, 122, '56', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 19, '2023-07-30 18:00:33', '2025-12-16 16:33:35'),
(1470, 125, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', '1400m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-12-16 16:05:30'),
(1471, 125, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Drive Ramechhap - Flight Lukla (2860 m) - Trek to Phakding (2610 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Early morning from Kathmandu, departure (approximately 2:00 AM)\r\nto Ramechhap Airport, where breakfast will be provided prior to your scheduled\r\nflight to Lukla. This scenic flight, which is strictly weather-dependent,\r\noffers passengers spectacular aerial vistas of the Himalayan mountain range.\r\nUpon arrival at Lukla Airport, our team will assist with the proper\r\ndistribution of equipment and supplies among the porters and Sherpa staff\r\nbefore formally commencing the trekking expedition..</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon arrival in Lukla, your trek will commence with\r\na scenic journey to Phakding. Along the way, you will traverse iconic suspension\r\nbridges, pass through charming traditional villages, and immerse yourself in\r\nthe regionâ€™s breathtaking natural landscapes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Note:</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Â§ \r\n<i>Due to potential congestion at Kathmandu Airport,\r\nthe Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN) may mandate that all flights to\r\nLukla operate either from Kathmandu Airport or from Ramechhap Airport.</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Â§ \r\n<i>In the event that the flight is canceled due to\r\nadverse weather conditions, it will be rescheduled for the following day. An\r\nadditional nightâ€™s accommodation will be provided either in Kathmandu or\r\nRamechhap, depending on the point of departure.</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening<br>Transfer: 4 hours drive by jeep (Ramechhap).  flight 25 minutes (Lukla).<br>Elevation gain: 200 m . Elevation loss : 450 m . 6/7 hours of walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 2, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-10-16 17:19:54'),
(1472, 125, '3', NULL, 'Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3440 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we start to climb a\r\nsteep trail to Timang, where the wide Marsyangdi Gorge ends. The path Trek\r\nthrough pine forests along the Dudh Koshi river. Cross suspension bridges.\r\nArrive Namche Bazaar, main Sherpa town and trading hub.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m . Elevation loss : 409 m . 5/6 hours of walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-08-27 20:57:44'),
(1473, 125, '4', NULL, 'Acclimatization day in Namche Bazaar', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Hike day to Everest View Hotel or\r\nnearby hills. Explore local market, Sherpa culture, monasteries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals\r\nincluded: morning noon evening</b></p>', 4, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-06-19 16:59:31'),
(1474, 125, '5', NULL, 'Namche Bazaar - Tengboche (3860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast in Namche Bazaar, we gently ascends, contouring along the hillside with amazing views of Everest, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam. The path leads through pine forests and small villages like Kyangjuma, then descends sharply to the Dudh Koshi River at Phunki Tenga. From here, a steady uphill climb through rhododendron and fir forests takes you to the spiritual village of <strong>Tengboche</strong>, home to the famous <strong>Tengboche Monastery</strong>, the largest in the Khumbu region. The monastery offers dramatic&nbsp; beautiful views, especially during sunset.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 921 m . Elevation loss:700 m . 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 5, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-07-30 19:23:20'),
(1475, 125, '6', NULL, 'Tengboche - Dingboche (4410 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nLeaving Tengboche, we descends through a forest of rhododendron, birch and conifers to <strong>Debuche</strong>, then crosses a suspension bridge over the <strong>Imja Khola</strong>. From here, it gently climbs past <strong>Pangboche</strong>, the highest permanent Sherpa village, offering close-up views of <strong>Ama Dablam</strong>. The trail continues along alpine meadows and mani walls before reaching <strong>Somare</strong> and then <strong>Orsho</strong>. After a final gradual ascent through open landscapes, we reaches the beautiful high-altitude village of <strong>Dingboche</strong>, surrounded by fields enclosed by stone walls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 550 m . Elevation loss : 273 m. 5/6 hours of walking.</b><br></p>', 6, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-07-30 18:29:49'),
(1476, 125, '7', NULL, 'Acclimatization day in Dingboche', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Optional hike to Nagarjun Hill\r\n(5,100 m) or nearby ridges. Prepare for higher altitude.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals\r\nincluded: morning noon evening</b></p>', 7, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-06-19 16:59:31'),
(1477, 125, '8', NULL, 'Dingboche - Chhukung (4730 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nThis day is a shorter and scenic acclimatization hike. We gradually ascends through open yak pastures and glacial valleys, offering landscape views of <strong>Ama Dablam</strong>, <strong>Lhotse</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>Island Peak</strong>. The walk is relatively gentle with no steep climbs, following the <strong>Imja Valley</strong> eastward. After passing stone-walled fields and crossing small streams, you arrive at the small settlement of <strong>Chhukung</strong>, nestled beneath towering peaks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening<br>Elevation gain: 395 m . Elevation loss : 00 m. 3 hours&nbsp; walking</b><br></p>', 8, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-07-30 18:29:49'),
(1478, 125, '9', NULL, 'Chhukung - Island Peak Base Camp (5100 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nLeaving Chhukung, the trail heads southeast through the wide Imja Valley. It gradually ascends along moraines and glacial streams with increasingly rugged terrain. The route passes beneath the looming faces of <strong>Lhotse</strong> and <strong>Island Peak</strong>, with views of the <strong>Imja Glacier</strong> and surrounding icy ridges. After a steady climb over rocky paths and loose scree, you reach <strong>Island Peak Base Camp</strong>, situated beside a glacier at the foot of the southwest face of Island Peak.\r\n\r\n.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 382 m . Elevation loss : 15 m. 4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 9, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-07-30 18:29:49'),
(1479, 125, '10', NULL, 'Reserve day', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Can be used in case of bad weather on summit day, or to rest\r\nand try again. If not used, continue descent or enjoy a slower pace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals\r\nincluded: morning noon evening</b></p>', 10, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-06-19 16:59:31'),
(1480, 125, '11', NULL, 'Summit day â€“ Island Peak summit (6189 m) and descend to Chhukung', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Start very early around midnight. Climb through rocky trail\r\nto glacier, then up snowy slopes with fixed ropes. Reach the summit and enjoy\r\nviews of Lhotse, Ama Dablam, and more. Descend back safely to Base Camp. Have\r\nhot soup, rest briefly, then pack and continue down to Chhukung. Long but\r\nrewarding day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1060 m. . Elevation loss: 2028 m. 8/11 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 11, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-07-30 18:19:23'),
(1481, 125, '12', NULL, 'Chhukung - Tengboche', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Trek back to Tenbuche following the same route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals\r\nincluded: morning noon evening</b></p>', 12, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-07-30 18:29:49'),
(1482, 125, '13', NULL, 'Tenboche - Namche Bazaar', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Retrace your ascent trail and enjoy the beautiful panoramic\r\nscenery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon\r\nevening</b></p>', 13, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-06-19 16:59:31'),
(1483, 125, '14', NULL, 'Namche Bazaar to Lukla', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Trek down to Lukla.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals\r\nincluded: morning noon evening</b></p>', 14, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-06-19 16:59:31'),
(1484, 125, '15', NULL, 'Lukla - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Fly back to Ramechhap and drive to\r\nKathmandu. Rest and relax.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon</b><br><b>Transfer : 25 minutes flight (Ramechhap), 4/5 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b><br></p>', 15, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-10-16 17:19:54'),
(1485, 125, '16', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><b></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 16, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-12-16 16:05:30'),
(1486, 125, '17', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 17, '2023-07-31 19:16:21', '2025-12-16 16:05:30'),
(1526, 141, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', '1,350m', NULL, NULL, '<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-15 18:23:55'),
(1527, 141, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ramechhap - Lukla (2860 m) - Phakding (2610 m)', '2,800m & 2,652m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast, we drive from Kathmandu to Ramechhap (Manthali Airport), which takes about 4 to 5 hours depending on traffic and road conditions. From Ramechhap, you\'ll board a short 20 minute flight to Lukla, the main gateway to the Everest region. Upon arrival in Lukla, the trek starts with a gradual descent through alpine forests, suspension bridges, and charming Sherpa villages. After&nbsp; 3 to 4 hour walk, youâ€™ll reach Phakding, a scenic riverside village and the first overnight stop on the trail toward Everest Base Camp. </p><p>Note:</p><p><i>Due to potential congestion at Kathmandu Airport, the Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN) may mandate that all flights to Lukla operate either from Kathmandu Airport or from Ramechhap Airport.</i><i></i></p><p><i>&nbsp;</i><i>In the event that the flight is canceled due to adverse weather conditions, it will be rescheduled for the following day. An additional nightâ€™s accommodation will be provided either in Kathmandu or Ramechhap, depending on the point of departure.</i></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport </b>:&nbsp;<b>4/5 hours drive&nbsp;by jeep ( Ramechhap), 25 minutes flight (Lukla).</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m . Elevation loss : 450 m . 3/4 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-15 18:28:16'),
(1528, 141, '3', NULL, 'Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3440 m)', '3,440m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, we starts with a pleasant walk through a pine forest along the river, followed by a short climb out of a narrow gorge. After passing the entrance to Khumbu National Park, where permits are checked, we descend to cross the river on a suspension bridge. The trail continues through a wooded valley, crossing the river again before reaching a confluence from Thame and the Khumbu. A final crossing on a high suspension bridge marks the start of a challenging 1.5 hours ascent to Namche Bazaar, with our first views of Everest midway.</p><p>Upon arrival, we check into a local lodge. Once a quiet village, Namche has evolved into a bustling trekking hub, offering a mix of tradition and modernityâ€”complete with bakeries, cafÃ©s, pubs, and other comforts brought back by well-traveled Sherpas.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m . Elevation loss : 409 m . 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-08-27 18:48:16'),
(1529, 141, '4', NULL, 'Day Excursion, Everest View Point -Khumjung (4000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Finally, well-deserved rest day to acclimatize and enjoy the surroundings. For those inclined, a hike to the Everest View Hotel (3,880 m) offers awesome scenic views of the Himalayas. Alternatively, you may choose to explore Namche Bazaarâ€”relax in a local cafÃ©, browse the lively market for unique items, or visit the Sherpa Museum to gain insight into local culture. The day concludes with an overnight stay in this iconic mountain village.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-09-23 14:47:12'),
(1530, 141, '5', NULL, 'Namche Bazaar - Thame (3750m)', '3,870m', NULL, NULL, '<p>As we leave the main Everest trail behind, the peacefulness\r\nof this less-travelled valley becomes immediately apparent, offering a welcome\r\ncontrast to the busier paths from Lukla. After approximately three to four\r\nhours of walking, we reach a dramatic suspension bridge stretched high above\r\nthe river. From here, the trail ascends steadily to the village of Thame,\r\nstrategically located at the historic junction of trading routes from Rolwaling\r\nvia the Tasi Labcha Pass and from Tibet via the Nangpa La.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 520 M Elevation loss: 235 m.&nbsp; 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 5, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:09:22'),
(1531, 141, '6', NULL, 'Thame - Lungden (4,500m)', '4,410m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we trek towards Morulung and Lungden, entering the valley mostly known as the Nangpa La Valley. This old trade route is linked to many local legends and was used by Tibetan traders and monks. Todayâ€™s walk is not difficult, but the altitude is strongly felt. The landscape is open, dry, and almost without vegetation. We continue to Lungden, a small Sherpa village and the starting point for the route to Nangpa La Pass on the Tibetan border.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 640 m Elevation loss: 0 m. 4/5 hours  walking.</b><br></p>', 6, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:09:22'),
(1532, 141, '7', NULL, 'Lungden - Renjola Pass (5360 m) - Gokyo Lake (4800m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nEarly in the morning, we begin this long yet magnificent day with confidence and calm. The ascent to the pass is challenging, but it leads to the best viewpoint. From here, a spectacular panorama unfolds: a chain of the worldâ€™s highest peaks, including Everest, Makalu, and Pumori, stretches to the east, while the turquoise waters of Lake Gokyo lie far below. Nearby rises the imposing south face of Cho Oyu. We then descend towards the Gokyo Glacier, cross it carefully, and continue to the peaceful shores of Lake Gokyo.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1100 m Elevation loss: 600 m.&nbsp; 7/8 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 7, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:09:22');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1533, 141, '8', NULL, 'Gokyo - Gokyo Peak  5357 m - Thangnak (4,700m)', '4,910m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today we climb Gokyo Peak (5,357â€¯m). The views are almost as stunning as from Renjo La Pass. The climb takes around 2 hours. It is steep but very rewarding. From the top, you can see Everest, Lhotse, and the beautiful Gokyo Lakes. After photos, we hike back to Gokyo for lunch. Then we continue to Thngnak, a trek of around 2 hours, crossing the Ngozumba Glacier, the worldâ€™s longest glacier. Walking on the glacier is not easy, so careful attention is required.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> For those who prefer, it is optional to rest in Gokyo instead of climbing Gokyo Peak</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 790 m or 210 m. Elevation loss: 900 m or 300 m.</b><br><b>2 hours 15 minutes (without Gokyo Peak) walking, 5 hours 30 minutes (including).</b><br></p>', 8, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:44:59'),
(1534, 141, '9', NULL, 'Thangnak - Cho La Pass (5420m) - Dzongla (4,855m)', '5,140m & 5,364m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nIn the early morning, we set off for a challenging day, crossing the Cho La Pass. As we approach, we navigate a wide boulder field, left by an ancient moraine. Some sections are steep and may require light scrambling. From the top, we are rewarded with spectacular views, including Ama Dablam from the northwest. We then descend to the grazing pastures below, where the trail becomes easier. Finally, we reach our overnight stop at Dzongla.\r\n\r\n </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 300 m Elevation loss: 200 m.&nbsp; 2/4 hours  walking.</b><br></p>', 9, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:44:59'),
(1535, 141, '10', NULL, 'Dzonla â€“ Goraksheep (5,164M)', '5,545m & 4,910m', NULL, NULL, '<p>We start from Zongla, bottom of Zongla Peak. The surrounding mountains are magnificent. The trail passes above Chola Tso, a green and beautiful lake. The path is easy and scenic. Before joining the Everest Hillary Trail, another panoramic view opens up, including Everest Base Camp, Lhotse, Nuptse, Pumori, Khumbutse, Ama Dablam, Lobuche Peak, and the Everest climbersâ€™ memorial spot. After Lobuche, the trail approaches the Khumbu Glacier, with some sections going up and down. The day ends at Gorakshep, the final stop before Everest Base Camp and an important point for both trekkers and climbers.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 825 m . Elevation loss :545 m . 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 10, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:44:59'),
(1536, 141, '11', NULL, 'Goraksheep  - Everest Base Camp (5364 m) - Goraksheep', '4,830m via 5,420m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nStarting from Gorakshep, the trek to Everest Base Camp follows the Khumbu Glacier for about 3.4â€¯km. The trail is entirely on the glacier, offering close-up views of the surrounding ice and mountains.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 150 m. Elevation loss : 150 m. 3/4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 11, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:44:59'),
(1537, 141, '13', NULL, 'Lobuche - Kongma la (5,535m)- Chhukung (4,730m)', '4,750m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nWe cross the Khumbu Glacier to reach Kongma La Pass. The climb to the pass is steady and demanding. From the top, there are clear views of the glacier and the Everest Valley, with Nuptse rising above. Nearby stands Imja Tse (Island Peak), a popular trekking peak that is also well known as the approach route to the challenging Amphu Lapcha Pass. We then make a long descent to Chukhung, set below the famous south face of Lhotse.\r\n\r\n<b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 670 m. Elevation loss : 1250 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 13, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 22:02:59'),
(1538, 141, '14', NULL, 'Chhukung - Chhukung Ri (5,550 m)- Chhukung', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we set out early to climb Chukhung Ri. This is a non-technical ascent with wide views of the surrounding peaks, including Lhotse, Makalu, Baruntse and the striking Ama Dablam. Thamserku and Cholatse can be seen to the west. The climb is similar in effort and reward to Kala Patthar, making Chukhung Ri one of the finest viewpoints in the region.<b></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note:</strong> Taking this optional rest makes the descent more comfortable.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon&nbsp; evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 900 m Elevation loss: 900  m.&nbsp; 4/5 hours  walking.</b><br></p>', 14, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 22:02:59'),
(1539, 141, '15', NULL, 'Chhukung - Tengboche (3,855m)', '5,360m & 3,820m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nToday, we enjoy a gentle descent into the Khumbu Valley, walking beneath the impressive slopes of Ama Dablam. We pass through the permanent village of Dingboche, where farming remains part of everyday life, and gradually enter a tree-lined landscape. We stop at Pangboche for a short visit to Upper Pangboche. After crossing the bridge, we follow a shaded trail with a short climb to reach Tengboche, the largest monastery in the region, and it has long been the centre of Sherpa religious life and ceremonial gatherings.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning&nbsp; afternoon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :100  m. Elevation loss: 1000 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><b></b><br></p>', 15, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 22:02:59'),
(1540, 141, '16', NULL, 'Tengboche - Namche Bazaar', '3,440m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nFrom Tengboche, we descend through rhododendron and pine woodland. We often hear the sounds of prayer wheels and birds. The path drops steeply to the Dudh Koshi River. We cross it on a suspension bridge. We then follow a steady, well-marked trail, climbing gradually through the trees. As we approach Namche Bazaar, Everest and the surrounding peaks come into view. The trail levels out as we reach the lively Sherpa town of Namche.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 420 m Elevation loss: 420.  5/6  hours  walking.</b><b></b><br></p>', 16, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 22:02:59'),
(1541, 141, '17', NULL, 'Namche â€“Lukla', '2,800m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, the trek from Namche to Lukapa retraces the same scenic\r\nroute taken on the ascent. we share our final moments with the portersâ€”a\r\nmeaningful time to reflect on the journey and celebrate the experiences weâ€™ve\r\nshared together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 600 m. Elevation loss : 1180 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p>', 17, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:44:59'),
(1542, 141, '18', NULL, 'flight from Lukla â€“Ramechap and drive to Kathmandu', '1,350m', NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start the day with an morning flight from Lukla to\r\nRamechhap, offering final views of the Himalayas. From there, enjoy a scenic\r\ndrive back to Kathmandu. The rest of the day is free to relax, explore, and\r\nshop.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning afternoon.</b><br><b>Transport : 30 minutes morning flight (Ramechhap), 4/5 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu)</b></p>', 18, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 22:02:59'),
(1543, 141, '19', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 19, '2024-01-08 06:36:30', '2025-12-23 15:44:59'),
(1575, 144, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', '1,350m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-12-16 15:43:40'),
(1576, 144, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Pokhara (850 m)', '820m', NULL, NULL, '<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>We drive early from Kathmandu to Pokhara, a scenic lakeside city with the&nbsp; nice views of the Annapurna range. Home to the Magars, Gurungs and Thakalis, the region is rich in culture and history. Upon arrival, enjoy free time to relax at lakeside cafÃ©s, rent a boat on Phewa Lake, or prepare for your trek. Shops along the main streets offer local crafts, international food and any gear you may need.</p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div></div></div></div></div><div><div></div></div></div><div><div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning afternoon.</b><br><b>Transport : 5/6 hours drive by jeep (Pokhara).</b></div></div></div></div></div><b><div><div><div><div><div><br></div></div></div></div></div></b><p></p>', 2, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-10-18 12:16:53'),
(1577, 144, '3', NULL, 'Pokhara â€“ Jomsom - Kagbeni (2800 m)', '2,700m & 2,810m', NULL, NULL, '<p>We start the day early with a private jeep ride along the\r\nKaligandaki Valley, Jump up between Nilgiri and Dhaulagiri, with the Annapurna\r\nmountain range surrounding us. Upon arrival in Kagbeni, the gateway to Mustang,\r\nwe meet our local team, including porters and assistant guides.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon.</b><br><b>Transport : 5/6 hours drive (Kagbeni).</b><br></p>', 3, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-10-18 12:16:53'),
(1578, 144, '4', NULL, 'Kagbeni - Tange (3240 m) - Chhusang (2980 m) - Chele (3070 m)', '3,050m', NULL, NULL, '<p>This day takes you through spectacular landscapes along the ancient Mustang\r\nHighway.<b> </b>The climb to the village of Tenge is quite steep but\r\nrewarding, with a beautiful chorten and the impressive 800 years old, Menchin\r\nLhakhang Monastery to explore. We pass through the village of Chhusang and\r\ncontinue onwards to the Gula Pass at 4,070 metres. From there, the path follows\r\nthe dramatic Kali Gandaki gorges, leading us to the village of Chele.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 705 m. Elevation loss: 483 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 4, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-07-20 14:18:15'),
(1579, 144, '5', NULL, 'Chele - Samar (3600 m)', '3,475m', NULL, NULL, '<p>From Chele, we walk along the riverbank before the trail\r\nslowly climbs to Taklam Pass. At the top, we enjoy amazing views of Nilgiri,\r\nTilicho Peak and the village of Gyakar across the valley. Samar is a small\r\nvillage offering a peaceful atmosphere and a chance to experience traditional\r\nMustang culture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br>Elevation gain: 688 m. Elevation loss: 144 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 5, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-07-20 14:18:15'),
(1580, 144, '6', NULL, 'Samar â€“ Syanbochen (3800 m) - Gheling (3570 m)', '3,520m', NULL, NULL, '<p>This section is fairly easy, despite crossing several\r\nmountain passes around 4,000 metres. Yamdo La, at 4,010 metres, is the highest\r\npoint of the day. After passing the small village of Syanbochen, we descend to\r\nGheling. Along the way, we stop at the ancient Sakyapa Monastery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 766 m. Elevation loss: 831 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 6, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-07-12 00:16:14'),
(1581, 144, '7', NULL, 'Gheling â€“ Dhakmar (3810 m )', '3,560m', NULL, NULL, '<p>At the start of the day, we ascend toward the Nyi-La Pass,\r\nfollowed by a descent into the village of Ghami, which is nestled among caves.\r\nThere, we visit the 500 years old monastery, Ghami Shedrup Darkeling Gomba.\r\nAfter the visit, we continue with a gentle half-hour climb, passing by a mani\r\nwall, before reaching the village of Drakmar. We spend the night in a local\r\nfamily\'s home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 700 m. Elevation loss: 513 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 7, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-07-20 14:18:15'),
(1582, 144, '8', NULL, 'Dhakmar â€“ Charang (3580 m)', '3,840m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today is mostly downhill, Starting from Drakmar, we\r\nfollow the riverbank to reach the village of Ghara, where we visit Ghara\r\nMonastery, a Nyingmapa school founded in 775. The journey then continues with a\r\nclimb to Morang La Pass at 4,150 meters. From there, we proceed to the village\r\nof Tsarang, passing through Lo Ghekar along the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </b><br><b>Elevation gain : 244 m. Elevation loss: 428 m. 5 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 8, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-10-18 12:16:53'),
(1583, 144, '9', NULL, 'Charang â€“ Lo manthang (3840 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, the trail continues with a steep downhill,\r\nfollowed by a sharp ascent that leads to a high plateau offering spectacular landscape views. As we progress, the landscape becomes increasingly dry, with\r\nstriking layers of colourful rock formations. We then pass through dramatic\r\ngorges before reaching the valley of Lo Manthang, the historic capital of Upper\r\nMustang.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </b><br><b>Elevation gain: 741 m. Elevation loss: 502 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 9, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-07-25 16:20:31'),
(1584, 144, '10', NULL, 'Lo Manthang - Nyamdo - Lo manthang', '3,820m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Early in the morning, we explore Lo-Manthang and visit the\r\nJamba Lhakhang monastery. In the afternoon, we head to the Gharphu Gomba\r\nmonastery, known for its ancient and exquisite wall paintings. We then return\r\nto Lo-Manthang, passing through the village of Nyaphu. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 276 m. Elevation loss: 114 m. 5 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 10, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-07-12 00:16:14'),
(1585, 144, '11', NULL, 'Lo Manthang - Day excursion', '3,570m', NULL, NULL, '<p>After breakfast, you have the opportunity to attend the\r\ndaily ceremonies at the monasteries of Chhyode Gomba (Sakyapa) or Namgal Gomba.\r\nIf you wish, you can visit the old palace to meet the king, who will welcome\r\nyou with a kata as a traditional gesture of hospitality. You can also ask him\r\nquestions, which his nephew acting as interpreter will gladly answer. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon\r\nevening.</b></p>', 11, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-10-25 15:03:34'),
(1586, 144, '12', NULL, 'Lo Manthang â€“ Yara gaon ( 3650 m)', '3,660m', NULL, NULL, '<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b>After leaving Lo Manthang, the trail descends through a dry, scenic landscape with views of snowy peaks. You reach Dhi Gaon, a quiet riverside village where people farm and raise animals. Crossing a bridge, you walk through narrow valleys to Yara Gaon, known for its cliffside cave houses and nearby Luri Gompa, an ancient monastery. The area is peaceful and rich in culture. Later, visit the Tashi Kabum caves with their beautiful murals, then enjoy a gentle walk past fields and hills back to Yara.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;  </b><br><b>Elevation gain: 610 m. Elevation loss: 810 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p>', 12, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-08-27 19:48:00'),
(1587, 144, '13', NULL, 'Yara gaon - Lori Gomba (3880 m) -  Ghara Gomba (3920 m)', '2,810m', NULL, NULL, '<p>We start the day with a pleasant\r\nwalk through the beautiful landscapes of Upper Mustang, starting from the quiet\r\nvillage of Yara Gaon, perched above the Kali Gandaki Valley. Our first\r\ndestination is Lori Gompa, a cave monastery carved into the cliffs. Inside, we\r\ndiscover ancient Buddhist murals and a rare chorten (a religious monument)\r\nbuilt within the cave itself. After spending time in this peaceful and\r\nspiritual place, we continue to Ghara Gompa, a serene and lesser-visited\r\nmonastery offering wide views of the hills and distant mountains. By late\r\nafternoon, we return to Yara, passing through dry fields and deep\r\nvalleysâ€”completing a day rich in culture, nature, and quiet beauty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 353 m. Elevation loss: 400 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p>', 13, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-07-20 14:18:15'),
(1588, 144, '14', NULL, 'Yara â€“ Tange (3520 m)', '3,800m via 5,416m', NULL, NULL, '<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>On this day, we trek across a desert plateau with&nbsp; beautiful views of Dhaulagiri. After a short descent to the Dhechyang Khola Riverâ€”famous for Vishnu fossilsâ€”we climb to tea shops at 3,420 m, with amazing views of Mustang Himal, Dhaulagiri, and Tukuche Peak. A steep climb follows, then the trail winds through unique rock formations and rough terrain. We end the day at the peaceful village of Tanggye, known for its colorful chortens, flat-roofed houses, and quiet monasteryâ€”offering a glimpse into traditional Mustang life.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 791 m. Elevation loss: 1060 m. 7 hours walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 14, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-08-27 19:49:19'),
(1589, 144, '15', NULL, 'Tange â€“ Chhusang( 2980 m)', '2,700m', NULL, NULL, '<p>This day is the\r\nlongest and most challenging day of the trek (23.5 km). We start our journey in\r\nTangye, where we cross the Yara River and gradually climb to the Cha La Pass,\r\nstanding at an altitude of 4,060 metres. This vantage point provides amazing views of Dhaulagiri. After a short descent, we reach Phaha for a\r\nlunch break. The journey then continues with a long walk along the banks of the\r\nNursing River, eventually bringing us to the village of Chhusang. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1113 m. Elevation loss: 1493 m. 9 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 15, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-07-20 14:18:15'),
(1590, 144, '16', NULL, 'Chhusang â€“ Muktinath (710 m)', '820m', NULL, NULL, '<p>The trek from Chhusang to Muktinath starts with a steady climb through dry, rocky landscapes. You pass Tetang village and then ascend to Gyu La Pass (4,077 m), the highest point of the day, with beautiful mountain views. From the pass, the trail goes downhill through open fields until you reach Muktinath (3,760 m), a sacred site for both Hindus and Buddhists, known for its eternal flame and 108 water spouts.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation</b><b>: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1391 m. Elevation loss: 596 m. 7 hours walking.</b></p>', 16, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-08-27 19:48:00'),
(1591, 144, '17', NULL, 'Muktinath â€“ Pokhara', '1,350m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast, we drive from Muktinath to Pokhara (mostly smooth). The trail descends through dry landscapes and traditional villages like Jharkot and Kagbeni. You then reach Jomsom, a main town in the region. From there, you can take a flight or drive to Pokhara, enjoying views of rivers, waterfalls, and green hills along the way.</p><p></p><div></div><p></p><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 5/6 hours drive by jeep (Pokhara).</b></p><p></p>', 17, '2024-01-08 07:26:06', '2025-10-18 12:20:14'),
(1625, 147, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu 1350m. Transfer to the hotel', '1,350m', NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b><br></p></div>', 1, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-12-16 16:14:05'),
(1626, 147, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani  (1860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Early morning departure to Besisahar. This route main highway between Nepal and India, we allow till Mugling. Throughout passing numerous villages we arrive to Besisahar to change the jeeps. After Besisahar, the road then turns into a stony track, a little bumpy but bordered by beautiful landscapes of rice fields and traditional Nepalese villages. A few landslides can sometimes delay us or force us to change vehicles several times; Faced with these little daily adventures, it is wise to follow the example of the Nepalese who maintain a smile and good humor... We finally arrive at the Dharapani. Installation at the lodge.<div>\r\n\r\n<div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning, afternoon, evening. </b></div><div><b>Transfer: 6h drive (Besi Sahar) + 3 hours track (Dharapani)</b></div>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 2, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-27 21:04:16'),
(1627, 147, '3', NULL, 'Dharapani - Chame (2700 m)', '760m and 840m', NULL, NULL, 'After breakfast, the trail climbs steeply to Timang, which marks the end of the vast Marsyangdi Gorge. From there, it gradually levels out as the landscape shifts from dense pine forests to drier hillsides. Beyond Besisahar, Chame â€” the district headquarters of Manang â€” is the largest settlement in the area.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 750 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 5 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 3, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-27 21:04:16'),
(1628, 147, '4', NULL, 'Chame â€“ Lower (3200 m)', '1,300m', NULL, NULL, 'After breakfast, the trail follows the Marsyangdi River through pine forests to Bhratang, known for its apple orchards. The valley then opens to the impressive curved rock face of Paungda Danda. After crossing a suspension bridge, you climb to Dukur Pokhari (3,240 m) for lunch with great mountain views, before gently descending to Lower Pisang (3,200 m). You can also visit Upper Pisang for its monastery and wider views. This stage combines forests, river views, and striking mountain scenery.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 830 m. Elevation loss: 350 m. 6 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 4, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-27 21:04:16'),
(1629, 147, '5', NULL, 'Pisang (3200 m)', '1,960m', NULL, NULL, 'Today is dedicated to resting and adjusting to the higher altitude. Take it easy to regain energy for the next dayâ€™s trek. You can explore both Upper and Lower Pisang villages, visiting traditional houses, local caves, and Buddhist stupas. Gentle walks, stretching, or light exercises can help build stamina and prepare your body for the journey ahead, all while enjoying the beautiful mountain surroundings.<br><br><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br>', 5, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-18 00:36:49'),
(1630, 147, '6', NULL, 'Pisang - to Pisang Peak Base Camp (4380 m)', '2,710m', NULL, NULL, 'After acclimatizing in Pisang Village, the trek continues through picturesque alpine terrain and rocky paths, gradually gaining altitude. Along the way, you may notice glacial streams, rugged cliffs, and scattered alpine vegetation, offering a glimpse of the high mountain environment. The trail leads to Pisang Peak Base Camp, where you can enjoy stunning panoramic views of the surrounding Himalayan peaks, including Annapurna II, Gangapurna, and Pisang Peak itself. The base camp provides a perfect spot to rest, prepare for the summit climb, and take in the breathtaking high-altitude scenery.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 950 m. Elevation loss: 50 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 6, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-27 21:07:02'),
(1631, 147, '7', NULL, 'BC - High Camp (5400)', '3,700m', NULL, NULL, 'Upon reaching High Camp, tents will be set up, and necessary arrangements will be made in preparation for the Pisang Peak climb. The expedition team will check that you are properly acclimatised for the summit attempt. Since we will spend the night at High Camp, take the opportunity to rest, recover, and adjust to the higher altitude, ensuring your body is ready for the next dayâ€™s climb.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1200 m. Elevation loss: 40 m. 3/5 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 7, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-27 21:07:02'),
(1632, 147, '8', NULL, 'Summit to the Peak -  Back to Base Camp', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Pisang Peak summit is a tough but rewarding climb. We start early in the morning, tackling steep and technical sections. The journey offers breathtaking views of the Himalayas, making the effort worthwhile.<br>With your guide and fixed ropes, you ascend the final ridge to the summit, enjoying panoramic views of Annapurna, Chulu Range, Manaslu, Tilicho Peak, and more. After celebrating and taking photos, you descend carefully back to Base Camp.<br><br><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 671 m. Elevation loss: 1891 m. 3/5 hours walking</b>.<br>', 8, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-18 00:36:49'),
(1633, 147, '9', NULL, 'BC - Manang (3542 m)', '4,380m', NULL, NULL, 'Leaving Pisang Peak Base Camp, the trail winds downhill to meet the Annapurna Circuit. Youâ€™ll trek along river valleys, surrounded by dramatic mountain scenery. The Manang, a peaceful village with stunning Himalayan views and a rich cultural heritage<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, afternoon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 100 m. Elevation loss: 660 m. 4/6 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 9, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-27 21:04:16'),
(1634, 147, '10', NULL, 'Manang - Leather (4217 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Today is a short, easy trek to help your body adjust to the altitude. Youâ€™ll walk through dry, rocky high-altitude desert land, very different from forests and meadows. Along the way, you might see eagles, marmots, yaks, and blue sheep. The slow pace lets you enjoy mountain views and rest before the next climb.<br><br><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 720 m. Elevation loss: 56 m. 4.5 hours walking.</b><br>', 10, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-18 00:36:49'),
(1635, 147, '11', NULL, 'Leder - Thorung Phedi (4500m), at the bottom of Thorong La', '5,400m', NULL, NULL, 'Today is another short but important day on the Annapurna Circuit. This trek brings you closer to the challenging Thorong La Pass (5,416 m), one of the highest trekking passes in the world. Along the way, youâ€™ll enjoy beautiful views of snow-capped peaks, glacial rivers, and the dry, high-altitude landscape. Mountains like Thorong Peak (6,144 m) and Khatung Kang (6,484 m) tower on the horizon, adding to the thrill of this stage.<br><br><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 380 m. Elevation loss: 71 m. 3 hours walking.</b><br>', 11, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-18 00:36:49'),
(1636, 147, '12', NULL, 'Thorung Phedi - Thorong La pass (5416 m) - Muktinath (3760 m)', '6,091m', NULL, NULL, 'Starting vary early, youâ€™ll climb steeply but steadily to Thorong La Pass at 5,416 meters, one of the highest trekking passes in the world. At the top, youâ€™ll see colorful prayer flags, a Buddhist stupa, and piles of stones made by trekkers. Take a break to enjoy the amazing views of snowy mountains and valleys. After the pass, the trail goes down sharply to Chabarbu, passing meadows and a deep gorge before going up a little again. Then the path gets wider as you reach Muktinath, a sacred place for both Buddhists and Hindus, known for its old temple and natural springs believed to have healing powers. This day is tough but very special.Elevation gain: 912 m.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 912 m. Elevation loss: 1691m. 8 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 12, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-27 21:04:16'),
(1637, 147, '13', NULL, 'Muktinath - Lupra (3000 m) â€“ Drive to Tatopani  (1200 m)', '3,540m', NULL, NULL, 'Today is an important day as you spend the morning near Mount Dhaulagiri. After leaving Muktinath, the trail goes to the small, old village of Lupra, avoiding the main road. This area has some of the last BÃ¶n monasteries, an ancient religion before Buddhism. To reach Lupra, you go down a steep path into a riverbed. From there, you take a three-hour jeep ride to Tatopani, a busy town by the Kali Gandaki River. Tatopani means â€œhot waterâ€ in Nepali because of its natural hot springs, where you can relax for a small fee of 150 rupees. Donâ€™t forget your swimming gear !<br><br><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transfer: 3 hours drive by jeep (Tatopani).</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 5 hours walking.</b><br>', 13, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-10-16 17:37:45'),
(1638, 147, '14', NULL, 'Tatopani â€“ Pokhara 800 m', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'If this is a combined group, it\'s time for good-bye (group + Nepali) after breakfast. Take the car to Pokhara to see the amazing city. Pokhara\'s milder climate will undoubtedly improve our mood. If we arrive on time, we can choose from a variety of boating experiences on the calm lake waters that reflect Fishtail Mountain. Near the international airport, you could also go to the Davis Falls and the International Museum of the History of the Himalayas and Ethnology.<br><br><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning, noon. Transfer: 3 hours</b><br>', 14, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-08-18 00:36:49'),
(1639, 147, '15', NULL, 'Pokhara - kathmandu', '4,020m', NULL, NULL, 'After breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours<br><br><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Transfer: 3 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b><br>', 15, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-10-16 17:37:45'),
(1640, 147, '16', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', '4,450m', NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 16, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-12-16 16:14:05'),
(1641, 147, '17', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', '5,416m and 3,800m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 17, '2024-01-08 10:49:38', '2025-12-16 16:14:05'),
(1658, 149, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu 1350m. Transfer to the hotel', '1,400m', NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p></div>', 1, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-12-16 16:30:03'),
(1659, 149, '2', NULL, 'Gear Check and Preparation Day Before Departure', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Before leaving Kathmandu, we spend a day checking all your gear and equipment to make sure everything is ready for the expedition. Our team will help you inspect climbing gear, clothing, and supplies to ensure safety and comfort on the mountain. This day also includes final briefings and preparation so you can start your journey confidently and well-prepared.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 2, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1660, 149, '3', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani  (1860 m)', '760m', NULL, NULL, 'We leave early in the morning for Besisahar, taking the main highway that connects Nepal and India, up to Mugling. Along the way, we pass many villages before reaching Besisahar, where we switch to jeeps.From there, the road becomes rough and rocky, but the views of rice fields and traditional villages make the ride beautiful. Landslides can sometimes delay us or require changing vehicles, but like the locals, it\'s best to stay positive and keep smiling.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transfer: 6 hour drive (Besi Sahar) + 3 hours of road</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 3, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:31:31'),
(1661, 149, '4', NULL, 'Dharapani - Koto (2620 m)', '930m', NULL, NULL, 'After breakfast, we start to climb a steep trail to Timang, where the wide Marsyangdi Gorge ends. The path then becomes easier, and the landscape changes from thick pine forests to drier hills. After Besisahar, Chame is the largest village in the region and serves as the district headquarters of Manang.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 705 m. Elevation loss: 313 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 4, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1662, 149, '5', NULL, 'Koto - Meta (3560 m)', '1,350m', NULL, NULL, 'The towering peaks feel distant as we move forward, with Annapurna II standing tall above Koto, seemingly guarding the entrance to the Naar-Phu Valley. We leave the Marsyangdi Valley behind, crossing a narrow suspension bridge and continuing along a rocky path carved into the cliffside.<br>From here, our route follows the Naar Khola river; in this constricted portion of the gorge, the trail often alternates from one bank of the river to the other. The day concludes with a final push, an uphill climb of 200 metres through a series of switchbacks.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1200 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 5/7 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 5, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:32:54'),
(1663, 149, '6', NULL, 'Meta - Kyang (3840 m)', '1,960m', NULL, NULL, 'We depart from Meta\'s little plateau, which boasts a stunning panorama. The trail winds through an open valley and climbs gradually. As it transitions into a high-altitude, arid desert, the terrain gets more rugged and has fewer trees. Known locally as Kharka, we pass a number of abandoned towns that were once utilized as makeshift shelters by Tibetan yak herders and traders. Rare animals like blue sheep and even snow leopards can be seen in this valley.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 500 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 6, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1664, 149, '7', NULL, 'Kyang - Phu (4100 m)', '2,610m', NULL, NULL, 'Along the way, youâ€™ll see Buddhist chortens and mani stones, showing the area\'s deep spiritual heritage. The valley narrows again until we reach the Phu gate, then the trail drops down to the riverbed. We visit Tashi Lhakhang Monastery, a sacred site believed to have been visited by Guru Rinpoche (Padmasambhava).<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 400 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 3/5 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 7, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:31:31'),
(1665, 149, '8', NULL, 'Rest / Acclimatization day', '3,560m', NULL, NULL, 'At Phu Gaon, you can visit the Tashi Lhakhang Monastery, an old Buddhist temple built by Karmapa Rinpoche. It gives you a chance to learn about Tibetan Buddhism and see beautiful paintings. Walk around the village and see traditional stone houses with colourful prayer flags, mani walls, and chortens. These show the rich Tibetan culture and way of life. Youâ€™ll meet friendly locals and experience their simple, peaceful mountain lifestyle.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 400 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 3/5 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 8, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1666, 149, '9', NULL, 'Phu gaon - Himlung Himal base camp (4900)', '4,080m', NULL, NULL, 'From Phu Gaun, the trail goes up through beautiful mountains and meadows. Youâ€™ll see amazing views of Himlung Himal and other peaks. The walk is a bit hard because of the altitude, so take it slow and enjoy the nature around you<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 819 m. Elevation loss: 60 m. 6 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 9, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1667, 149, '10 - 11', NULL, 'Two days at Base Camp', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Spend two days at Himlung Base Camp for rest, blessings, and training. Our team can organize a traditional blessing ceremony to bring good luck and ensure your safety during the climb. You will also participate in training sessions to prepare for the mountain, including using climbing gear and practicing safety skills. These days help your body acclimatize and get ready for the challenge ahead.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 819 m. Elevation loss: 60 m</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 10, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1668, 149, '12-23', NULL, 'Acclimatization Rotation and Climbing Period', '4,900m', NULL, NULL, 'During the expedition, acclimatisation rotations are essential to help your body adjust safely to high altitude. Typically, you\'ll ascend from Base Camp (4,900 m) to Camp 1 (5,700 m), spend time there, and then return to Base Camp to rest. This process may be repeated to reduce the risk of altitude sickness and build endurance.<br>Once properly acclimatised, youâ€™ll begin your final ascentâ€”moving from Base Camp to Camp 1, then continuing to Camp 2 (6,300 m), and finally reaching Camp 3 (6,700 m). Each camp offers a vital rest point to recover and prepare for the next stage of the climb.<br>Your experienced climbing team will guide you through technical sections, ensuring safety and proper navigation. When the weather and conditions allow, the summit push begins from Camp 3, aiming for the peak of Himlung Himal at 7,126 metres. After reaching the summit, youâ€™ll descend carefully through each camp back to Base Camp.<br>This carefully planned rotation and climbing strategy ensures a safer ascent while allowing you to experience the incredible beauty and challenge of Himlung Himal.<div><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br> </div>', 12, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1669, 149, '24', NULL, 'Base camp - Meta', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'We retrace the same trail we used during the ascent<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 819 m. Elevation loss: 60 m.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 13, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1670, 149, '25', NULL, 'Meta - Koto', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'We retrace the same trail we used during the ascent<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 819 m. Elevation loss: 60 m</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 14, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-08-27 20:29:39'),
(1671, 149, '26', NULL, 'Drive from Koto to Besisahar', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><br>', 15, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-07-30 18:48:44'),
(1672, 149, '27', NULL, 'Besisahar - Kathamandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Once breakfast is finished, you will drive back to Kathmandu. Approximately six or seven hours are needed to finish this picturesque drive along the Prithvi Highway.<div> <div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning.</b><br></div></div>', 16, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-07-09 20:53:56'),
(1673, 149, '28', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><div>\r\n\r\n<p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\n\r\n<br></div> </div>', 17, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-12-16 16:30:03'),
(1674, 149, '29', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 18, '2024-01-09 05:49:49', '2025-12-16 16:30:03'),
(1710, 152, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-12-16 15:46:05'),
(1711, 152, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Dhunche (1965 M) - Syabru Besi (1460 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we drive from Kathmandu to Dhunche, along winding mountain roads with scenic views of hills, rivers, and villages. From Dhunche, the road continues downhill for about 1â€“2 hours to Syabru Besi, a small town and the starting point for treks in the Langtang region.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p><p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Syabru Besi).</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-10-18 12:42:37'),
(1712, 152, '3', NULL, 'Syabru besi - Gatlang (2,240m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After\r\nbreakfast, we will begin our journey toward Gatlang, ascending steadily until\r\nwe reach the summit of Deurali. The trail becomes easier, with a flat and\r\nsmooth path leading forward. Along the way, we will be treated to&nbsp; views of the Langtang mountain ranges, adding to the beauty of the trek.\r\nGatlang, a large Tamang village, promises to be an enriching experience,\r\noffering a glimpse into the local culture and traditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation\r\ngain :1060m Elevation loss:246 m 5/6 hours &nbsp;walking.</b></p>', 3, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-07-20 17:22:08'),
(1713, 152, '4', NULL, 'Gatlang â€“Tatopani (2,600m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>After breakfast, we  starts with a descent to the river, followed by a steady climb through forests and terraced fields. Along the way, youâ€™ll pass small villages and enjoy mountain views. After several hours, you reach <strong></strong>Tatopani<strong></strong>, known for its natural hot springs, where you can relax and soothe your muscles.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p><p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 884 m Elevation loss:582 m 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-08-27 19:52:09'),
(1714, 152, '5', NULL, 'Tatopani - Nagthali (3165 m) - Thuman (2,340m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, the trek from Tatopani climbs through rhododendron-pine forests, passing Tamang villages, mani walls and chortens before reaching Nagthali, a windswept ridge with 360Â° views of Ganesh Himal and Langtang Lirung. The trail then descends through alpine meadows to Thuman, a traditional Tamang village with stone houses and vibrant culture. A perfect blend of nature, culture, and Himalayan vistas.</p><p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 620 m Elevation loss: 900 m 6 hours &nbsp;walking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-08-27 19:52:09'),
(1715, 152, '6', NULL, 'Thuman - Bridhim (2230m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Like wise others day, we <strong></strong>trek from Thuman to Briddhim with a gradual descent through forested trails, passing small villages and crossing a suspension bridge over a river. After the descent, the path begins a gentle uphill climb through terraced fields and scattered homes. Along the way, you can enjoy the natural beauty and local wildlife. After several hours of trekking, you arrive at Briddhim, a peaceful village known for its Tibetan Buddhist culture and welcoming homestays, where you can visit the local monastery and experience traditional hospitality.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p><p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 633 m Elevation loss: 798 m 4/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-08-27 19:52:09'),
(1716, 152, '7', NULL, 'Bridhim â€“ Lama hotel (2450m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, we join the classical trial at Lama Hotel. After about an hour of trekking, we will reach Khamjing village, where the landscape is filled with cultivated fields of potatoes, barley and wheat. Along the journey, we will witness the Lauribinayak Pass, offering an amazing views of Gosainkunda and Langtang Lirung. The trail then continues through Sherpa Gaun and Rimche, eventually leading us to Lama Hotel.</p><p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1300 m Elevation loss: 1006 m 5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-08-27 19:52:09'),
(1717, 152, '8', NULL, 'Lama Hotel â€“ Ghora Tabela - Langtang village (3430 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>After breakfast at Lama Hotel, the trek continues with a gradual climb to Ghora Tabela, a resting spot surrounded by forests and mountain views. From there, the trail leads uphill through rhododendron and pine trees until you reach Langtang Village, a peaceful mountain settlement known for its amazing views and friendly locals.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1015 m. Elevation loss: 80 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p>', 8, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-08-27 19:52:09');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1718, 152, '9', NULL, 'Langtang village â€“ Kyangjin (3870 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, the trail reaches a ridge with a\r\nlarge chorten and prayer wall, passing the main settlement before descending to\r\nKyanjinâ€™s lodges and cheese factory. In the afternoon, you can hike Kyanjin Ri\r\nfor beautiful mountain views or explore the gently rising Langtang Valley toward\r\nthe yak pastures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 450 m. 3 hours walking.</b></p>', 9, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-07-20 17:22:08'),
(1719, 152, '10', NULL, 'Ascent of Tsergo Ri (4984 M ) or Discover of the Langtang Valley', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>This day, is more difficult than exploring the Langtang Valley. It involves a steep, challenging climb with rocky and sometimes slippery terrain, requiring good fitness and stamina. Reaching the summit rewards you with beautiful landscape views but demands more effort and experience compared to the easier, gentler walks through the Langtang Valley.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1105 m. Elevation loss: 1105 meters. 7/8\r\nhours Walking.</b></p>', 10, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-07-20 17:22:08'),
(1720, 152, '11', NULL, 'Kyjangjin Gompa - Lama Hotel (2470m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>We retrace our steps back through the Langtang Valley. The\r\ndownhill walk is easier and offers a different perspective of the landscapes we\r\npassed on the way up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain : 100 m. Elevation loss : 1500 m. 6/7\r\nhours walking.</b></p>', 11, '2024-01-09 06:25:16', '2025-07-12 21:39:14'),
(1778, 157, '1', NULL, 'Arrive in Kathmandu (1300 m)', '1,350m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-12-16 16:16:44'),
(1779, 157, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Permits & Final Preparation', '700m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Your\r\nadventure starts in Kathmandu. We will arrange all the required permits,\r\nincluding the Manaslu Restricted Area Permit, MCAP, ACAP and the Larkya Peak\r\nClimbing Permit. Our team will also help you with a final gear check to make\r\nsure you\'re well-prepared for the trek. If you like, you can enjoy some\r\noptional sightseeing around the beautiful and historic city of Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel. Meals included: morning.</b></p>', 2, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1780, 157, '3', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Arughat (660 m) â€“ Machha Khola (900 m)', '900m', NULL, NULL, '<p>The day continues with a bus journey from Kathmandu to Machhakhola, following the\r\npicturesque Trisuli River. The scenic drive transitions into a rugged track\r\nthat is often affected by past monsoons. The route continues to rise through a\r\nbroad valley, eventually leading to Machha Khola, a village named after its\r\nfishing tradition â€” \"machha\" meaning fish. Fishing remains a key\r\nlivelihood here, with numerous traps visible around the area. Youâ€™ll spend the\r\nnight in a local lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transfer: 7/8 hrs drive.</b><br></p>', 3, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1781, 157, '4', NULL, 'Machha Khola - Jagat (1,430 m)', '1,410m', NULL, NULL, '<p>As we leave\r\nthe cultivated region behind, the terrain becomes significantly steeper, and\r\nthe few remaining fields are sparse and less fertile. We cross a suspension\r\nbridge over the river to bypass the road and continue along a narrow gorge,\r\nwith the river flowing between towering cliffs. After re-crossing the river, we\r\narrive at Tatopaniâ€”named for its natural hot springs. From there, we follow a\r\nscenic balcony trail that leads us to Jagat, where we settle in for the night.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1100 m. Elevation loss: 700 m. 7 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-11 23:49:53'),
(1782, 157, '5', NULL, 'Jagat- Eklebhati (1700 m) - Dyang (1800)', '1,860m', NULL, NULL, '<p>In the\r\nmorning, we set out from Jagat, a quaint village known for its unique\r\narchitecture that marks the gateway to the high mountain valleys. Ahead of us rises\r\nthe impressive Shringi Himal, a modest peak reaching 7,000 metres. We stop for\r\nlunch in Eclebati. As we move forward, the valley narrows dramatically, and the\r\nscenery shifts to a distinctly alpine character. Towering pine forests flank\r\nour route. We follow a dramatic balcony trail etched into the cliffside,\r\noffering beautiful views of the Ganesh Himal and Himal Chuli ranges. Our\r\ndayâ€™s trek ends in the village of Dyang.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1110 m. Elevation loss: 760 m. 5/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1783, 157, '6', NULL, 'Dyang - Bhi Phedi (2050) - Namrung (2680)', '2,630m', NULL, NULL, '<p>The river\r\nwinds its way through a deep, narrow gorge, and we follow its course along a\r\nledge path that offers amazing views of this striking canyon. The trail then\r\nascends steeply, leading us through a remarkable forest that blends features\r\nfrom various vegetation zones. Along the way, we spot numerous monkeys. We\'ve\r\nnow entered the heart of Buddhist territory, as shown by the abundance of mani\r\nwallsâ€”stones etched with intricate Buddhist carvingsâ€”and the colourful prayer\r\nflags dancing in the breeze.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1340 m. Elevation loss: 480 m. 6/5 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1784, 157, '7', NULL, 'Namrung - Syaula (3490 m)', '3,530m', NULL, NULL, '<p>We start through the remarkable \"Tibetan\" villages of Ligaon, Sho and Lo,\r\ntypically alive with activity as locals tend to the fields. Towering above the\r\nlarch forests and temples, the majestic peaks of Manaslu and its neighbouring\r\nsummits come into view. Eventually, we reach the&nbsp; amazing village of Shyaula\r\n(3,480 m), nestled at the base of Manaslu. Itâ€™s an unforgettable\r\nday- beautiful in every sense, one that leaves a lasting impression.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1120 m. Elevation loss: 240 m. 6/7 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1785, 157, '8', NULL, 'Syaula - Pugyen Gumba - Sama Gaon (3360)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we\r\nset out to discover Pung Gyen Monastery, perched at 3,870 metres in a\r\nbeautiful location near towering glaciers. Surrounded by sweeping views of\r\nmajestic peaksâ€”including the mighty Manasluâ€”the scenery is nothing short of\r\nspectacular. This long-awaited moment has finally arrived, and we savour it\r\nwith a picnic amidst the grandeur of the mountains. A truly unforgettable\r\nexperience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 880 m. Elevation loss: 610 m. 5/6 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1786, 157, '9', NULL, 'Samagaon - Lake Birendrea (3560 m) - Samdo (3690)', '3,860m', NULL, NULL, '<p>After our\r\nmorning visit to the monastery, we can choose between a short hike to the beautiful Birendra Lake (3,560 m)â€”a glacial lake nestled at the base of Manaslu,\r\njust an hourâ€™s walk away with a gentle 100-metre ascent and descentâ€”or continue\r\ndirectly to Samdo. The journey to Samdo is brief, offering a welcome\r\nopportunity to rest. Home to around 200 residents, Samdo is considered one of\r\nthe most picturesque villages along the trek. It is also the final settlement\r\nbefore the pass, set in a remote and dramatic location beneath the towering\r\nnorth face of Pan Phuchi. Just three hours away lies the Lajyang Pass (4,998\r\nm), a historically important and relatively easy route into Tibet, once\r\ntravelled by traders and their yak caravans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 460 m. Elevation loss: 160 m. 3/4 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1787, 157, '10', NULL, 'Samdo - Dharmasala (Larkya Phedi) (4300 m)', '4,460m', NULL, NULL, '<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today is a short but steady uphill walk. The trail follows a barren, rocky landscape with views of snowy peaks and glacial valleys. You cross a wooden bridge and pass by yak herders\' shelters before reaching Dharmasala, a simple stone lodge used as the base camp for crossing Larkya La Pass. It\'s a good place to rest and prepare for the challenging pass the next day.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 520 m. 4 hours walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 10, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-08-27 21:10:26'),
(1788, 157, '11', NULL, 'Dharmashala - Larkya Peak Base Camp (5135 m)', '3,720m via 5,160m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we\r\nleave the main Manaslu trail and head towards Larkya Peak Base Camp. Itâ€™s a\r\nshort but steady climb, taking about 3 hours. Once we reach the base camp at 5,200\r\nm, we set up our tents and settle in for the night. This is our first night\r\ncamping at high altitude, surrounded by gorgeous mountain views.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 840 m. 4 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1789, 157, '12', NULL, 'Rest and acclimatisation day', '2,300m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today is all\r\nabout resting and getting used to the altitude. We also use this time for final\r\ngear checks and a short training session with your climbing equipment,\r\nincluding the ice axe, crampons, and harness. Our experienced expedition guide\r\nwill lead ice and snow practice, helping you feel confident and ready for the\r\nclimb ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 12, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-08-27 21:10:26'),
(1790, 157, '13', NULL, 'Climb to High Camp (5600 m)  Prepare for Summit Push', '1,860m', NULL, NULL, '<p>We ascend to High Camp, getting closer to the summit. The\r\nhike is short but more challenging due to the altitude. After setting up camp,\r\nwe have an early dinner and get plenty of rest to prepare for the summit\r\nclimb.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 465 m. 3 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 13, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1791, 157, '14', NULL, 'Reserve day', '1,300m', NULL, NULL, '<p>This reserve\r\ncan be used in case of bad weather on summit day, or to rest and try again. If\r\nnot used, continue descent or enjoy a slower pace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 14, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-08-27 21:10:26'),
(1792, 157, '15', NULL, 'Summit Larkya Peak (6249 m) and return to Base Camp', '1,350m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today is the big day! We start the climb early in the\r\nmorning (around 2â€“3 am) under the stars. The route takes us across glaciers,\r\nsnowfields, and icy sections, requiring steady focus and teamwork. From the\r\nLarkya, you will be rewarded with beautiful landscape views of Manaslu,\r\nHimlung, Cheo, Kang Guru and Annapurna II â€“ an experience that is truly\r\nunforgettable. After soaking in the views and taking photos, we descend\r\ncarefully back to base camp for a well-earned rest</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 652 m. Elevation loss: 1114 m. 10 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 15, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(1793, 157, '16', NULL, 'BC - Larkya la / pass (5106 m) Bhimthang (3650 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After reaching the summit of Larkya Peak yesterday, today we\r\ncross the Larkya La Pass, which offers amazing views of Himlung, Cheo, Kang\r\nGuru, and Annapurna II. The trail is challenging but beautiful, starting with a rocky\r\npath and then descending to the green meadows of Bimthang. Itâ€™s a long day, but\r\nthe changing landscapes make it very rewarding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 100 m. Elevation loss: 1550 m. 5/6 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 16, '2024-01-09 09:22:17', '2025-07-11 23:49:53'),
(1796, 159, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu 1350m. Transfer to the hotel', '1,400m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-12-16 16:36:16'),
(1797, 159, '2', NULL, 'Gear check and preparation day', '1,400m', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Final gear preparation and briefing day</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-09-24 17:36:58'),
(1798, 159, '3', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani  (1860 m)', '1,700m', NULL, NULL, '<p></p>Early morning departure to Besisahar. This route main highway between Nepal and India, we allow till Mugling. Throughout passing numerous villages we arrive to Besisahar to change the jeeps. After Besisahar, the road then turns into a stony track, a little bumpy but bordered by beautiful landscapes of rice fields and traditional Nepalese villages. A few landslides can sometimes delay us or force us to change vehicles several times; Faced with these little daily adventures, it is wise to follow the example of the Nepalese who maintain a smile and good humor... We finally arrive at the Dharapani. Installation at the lodge.<br>\r\n\r\n<b><br></b><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transfer: 6 hours drive (Besi Sahar) + 3 hours walking (Dharapani).</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p><b></b></p> </div>', 3, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:39:03'),
(1799, 159, '4', NULL, 'Dharapani  - Surki Khola (2785 m)', '1,900m', NULL, NULL, 'Start your day by walking along the Dudh Khola River. Pass through small villages and reach Tilje, a calm Gurung village. Then, go uphill to Goa (Gho), a quiet place with great mountain views and continue on to Surki Khola.<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1050 m. Elevation loss: 336 m. 6 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p> </div>', 4, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:37:44'),
(1800, 159, '5', NULL, 'Surki Khola - Bhimthang (3720 m)', '1,340m', NULL, NULL, 'After breakfast, we follows a forested trail with gradual uphill sections. You walk through rhododendron and pine forests, cross wooden bridges and pass small streams along the way. As you gain elevation, the landscape opens up with views of the surrounding peaks. After a steady climb, you arrive at Bhimthang, a scenic open valley surrounded by mountains, perfect for rest and acclimatization.<div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1020 m. Elevation loss: 20 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></div>', 5, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:37:44'),
(1801, 159, '6', NULL, 'Day excursion', '1,860m', NULL, NULL, 'From Bhimthang, go on a day hike nearby. You can visit viewpoints or small villages and enjoy the mountain views and fresh air. Itâ€™s a good way to get used to the altitude.<br><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br> </div>', 6, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:37:44'),
(1802, 159, '7', NULL, 'Bhimthang - Larkya pass (5106 m) - Samdo (3690 m)', '2,630m', NULL, NULL, '<div><div><div><div><div><div><p><b></b>Trek from Bhimthang with a steady climb across rocky and snowy paths, with great views of Manaslu and nearby peaks. You reach Larkya La Pass (5,106 m), the highest point of the trek, with beautiful mountain scenery. From there, the trail goes down steeply through rocky and grassy areas. After a long descent, you arrive at Samdo, a peaceful village near the Tibet border.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><b></b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1460 m. Elevation loss: 1300 m. 8/10 hours walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 7, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:37:44'),
(1803, 159, '8', NULL, 'Samdo - Samagaon (3360 m)', '3,530m', NULL, NULL, '<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today is a gentle downhill walk through open valleys and along the Budhi Gandaki River. The trail offers beautiful views of Manaslu and passes through yak pastures and small stone huts. After a few hours of easy trekking, you reach Samagaon, a large village with traditional houses, chortens and a peaceful monastery. It\'s a good place to rest and explore the local culture.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 00 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 2/3 hours walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><b></b></div> </div>', 8, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:37:44'),
(1804, 159, '9', NULL, 'Rest & acclimatization day', '3,530m', NULL, NULL, 'Spend the day in Samagaon resting and acclimatising. You can take short walks to explore the village and enjoy the mountain views while helping your body adjust to the altitude<br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 9, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-09-24 17:36:58'),
(1805, 159, '10', NULL, 'Samagaon - Manaslu Base Camp (4800 m)', '3,860m', NULL, NULL, 'We continue to the steep and challenging trial towards Base camp. The path climbs through alpine meadows, rocky slopes and past Birendra Tal, a beautiful glacial lake. As you go higher, the air gets thinner, but the views get better. Youâ€™ll see glaciers, snowy peaks and maybe even some wildlife like blue sheep. At the base camp, enjoy close-up views of Mt. Manaslu and the surrounding mountains. <br><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1330 m. Elevation loss: 00 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br> </div>', 10, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:37:44'),
(1806, 159, '11-12', NULL, 'Technical climbing preparation at Base Camp', '3,860m', NULL, NULL, '<p>Spend these days at base camp preparing for the climb. Practice using ropes, crampons, ice axe and other gear. Your guides will review safety techniques and climbing strategies to ensure you\'re ready for the ascent.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p>', 11, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:40:50'),
(1807, 159, '26', NULL, 'Manaslu climbing Period.', '4,460m', NULL, NULL, 'Trek from Samdo to Dharamsala, also known as Larkya Phedi. The trek takes around 4-5 hours and offers&nbsp; beautiful views of the surrounding mountains. <div>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br></div>', 13, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:40:50'),
(1808, 159, '27', NULL, 'Packing up base camp & trek down to Samagaon', '3,720m-5,160m', NULL, NULL, '<p><b></b>Retrace the steep downhill to Sama as before.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p>', 13, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:41:23'),
(1809, 159, '28-29', NULL, 'Reserve days', '3,720m', NULL, NULL, '<strong>Reserve Days</strong>: Include extra days in the itinerary to allow flexibility for the summit push in case of bad weather or other unforeseen delays.', 14, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-07-04 17:29:38'),
(1810, 159, '30', NULL, 'Helicaptor fly to Kathmandu', '8,163m', NULL, NULL, 'Start the ascent of Manaslu. The climbing period can vary depending on weather conditions, team strength, and acclimatization. This period includes establishing higher camps, acclimatization rotations and the final summit push. <div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b></div>', 15, '2024-01-21 20:08:30', '2025-08-27 20:37:44'),
(1818, 163, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After\r\narrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an\r\nafternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear\r\nand prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<div><div><b></b></div></div>', 1, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-09 19:42:55'),
(1819, 163, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani (1860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nEarly morning departure to Besisahar along the main highway between Nepal and India. Passing through villages, we change jeeps at Besisahar. Beyond this point, the road becomes a stony track, bumpy but lined with rice fields and traditional villages. Occasional landslides may cause delays or vehicle changes, so itâ€™s best to follow the Nepalese example and stay cheerful. We finally arrive at Dharapani and settle into the lodge\r\n\r\n<br> </p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6 hours drive (Besi Sahar). 3 hours jeep (Dharapani)</b></div>', 2, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-09 20:48:05'),
(1820, 163, '3', NULL, 'Dharapani - Chame (2700 m)', '2050m/6725 ft', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we climb to Timang througout the Danaquev, at the end of the Marsyangdi Gorge. The trail then becomes gentler, passing from pine forests to drier hills. Chame, the largest settlement beyond Besisahar, is the district headquarters of Manang.&nbsp;</p><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 750 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 5 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></div></div>', 3, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-10 16:10:28'),
(1821, 163, '4', NULL, 'Chame â€“ Lower Pisang (3200 m)', '2,750m/9,020 ft', NULL, '4 - 5 hours trek', '<p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, the trail follows the Marsyangdi River through pine forests to Bhratang, famous for its apple orchards. The valley then opens up to the impressive Paungda Danda rock face. After crossing a suspension bridge, we climb to Dukur Pokhari (3,240â€¯m) for lunch with spectacular mountain views, before gently descending to Lower Pisang (3,200â€¯m). You can also visit Upper Pisang to see its monastery and enjoy broader views. This stage combines forested paths, river scenery and dramatic mountain landscapes.\r\n\r\n<br></p><div><div><b>&nbsp;Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>&nbsp;Elevation gain: 830 m. Elevation loss: 350 m. 6 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></div></div>', 4, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-10 16:10:28'),
(1822, 163, '5', NULL, 'Pisang - Ghyaru (3720) - Tibetan village of Ngawal (3661 m)', '2,700m/8,860ft', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nToday is one of the most scenic days. We climb steeply to Ghyaru, a small Tibetan village at 3,720â€¯m, with amazing mountain views and traditional stone houses. From Ghyaru, the trail crosses open hills to Ngawal (3,661â€¯m), a larger village with a beautiful monastery and ancient stone buildings. This quieter route offers great scenery and helps your body acclimatise before we continue to Manang.\r\n\r\n<br></p><div><b>&nbsp;Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 685 m. Elevation loss: 217 m. 6 hours walking.</b></div>', 5, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-09 21:22:28'),
(1823, 163, '6', NULL, 'Ngawal - Braga Monastery - Manang (3542 m)', '1940m/6360 ft', NULL, '3 - 4 hours', '<p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we follow a scenic, gently descending trail from Ngawal, winding through open alpine terrain with scattered juniper trees, mani walls, and sweeping views of Annapurna III and Gangapurna. After about 1.5 hours, we reach the historic village of Braga, where a 600-year-old monastery perched on a cliff is well worth a short visit for its spiritual atmosphere and outstanding views. From Braga, the trail becomes easy and mostly flat, following the Marsyangdi River until we arrive at Manang, a lively village and important acclimatisation stop on the Annapurna Circuit.\r\n\r\n<br></p><div>&nbsp;<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>&nbsp;Elevation gain: 140 m. Elevation loss: 273 m. 4 hours walking.</b></div>', 6, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-10 16:10:28'),
(1824, 163, '7', NULL, 'Ice Lake (4610 m) (Kicho Tal): Panorama of the Annapurnas / Rest and acclimatization day in Manang', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nFrom Braga or the small village of Manang, the trail climbs steeply through alpine meadows. The high altitude and rough terrain can make the path challenging. The main highlight is a glacier lake with clear turquoise water reflecting the surrounding peaks, with views of Gangapurna and the Annapurna range, including Annapurna II, III, and IV. For an easier option, Gangapurna Lake is shorter to reach and ideal for a quick visit or acclimatization. Alternatively, you can choose to rest in Manang to recover and prepare for the next stage of the trek.\r\n\r\n<br></p><div>\r\n\r\n<div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 1100 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 7 hours  walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 7, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-10 16:10:28'),
(1825, 163, '8', NULL, 'Manang - Leather (4217 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nToday is a short, easy trek to help your body acclimatise to the altitude. You will walk through dry, rocky,, high-altitude desert, very different from forests and meadows. Along the way, you may see eagles, marmots, yaks and blue sheep. The slow pace allows you to enjoy the mountain views and rest before the next climb.&nbsp; </p><div>\r\n\r\n<div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 720 m. Elevation loss: 56 m. 4.5 hours  walking.</b></div></div>', 8, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-10 16:10:28'),
(1826, 163, '9', NULL, 'Leder - Thorung Phedi (4500m) At the bottom of Thorong La', NULL, NULL, '6-8 hours', '<p>\r\n\r\nToday is another short but important day on the Annapurna Circuit. The trek brings you closer to Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m), one of the highest trekking passes in the world. Along the way, you will enjoy beautiful views of snow-capped peaks, glacial rivers, and the dry, high-altitude landscape. Mountains such as Thorong Peak (6,144â€¯m) and Khatung Kang (6,484â€¯m) rise on the horizon, adding to the excitement of this stage.\r\n\r\n<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon&nbsp; evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 380 m. Elevation loss: 71 m. 3 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></div>', 9, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-11 17:44:47'),
(1827, 163, '10', NULL, 'Thorung Phedi - Thorong La pass (5416 m) - Muktinath (3760 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nStarting very early, you climb steadily to Thorong La Pass at 5,416â€¯m, one of the highest trekking passes in the world. At the top, you will see colourful prayer flags, a Buddhist stupa, and stones left by trekkers. Take a break to enjoy the amazing views of snowy mountains and valleys. After the pass, the trail goes down sharply to Chabarbu, passing meadows and a deep gorge, then rises a little before reaching Muktinath. Muktinath is a sacred place for Buddhists and Hindus, known for its old temple and natural springs. It is a tough but very special day.\r\n\r\n<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 912 m. Elevation loss: 1691m. 8 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></div>', 10, '2024-08-21 16:00:10', '2025-12-09 21:22:28'),
(1845, 165, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', '1,300m/4,264ft', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p><p><i></i>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After\r\narrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an\r\nafternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear\r\nand prepare your bags for the journey ahead.<i></i></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-09 19:41:48'),
(1846, 165, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Pokhara (860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p><b>\r\n\r\n</b>The journey from Kathmandu to Pokhara (860 m) typically takes about 6â€“8 hours by road, covering approximately 200 kilometers. The route follows the Prithvi Highway, winding through hills, rivers and small towns, offering scenic views of the countryside and glimpses of the Himalayas on clear days.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Transport : 6/8 h drive (Pokhara).</b></p><div><p></p> </div>', 2, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-09 13:30:29'),
(1847, 165, '3', NULL, 'Pokhara - Nayapul - Ulleri (2050m)', '2050m/6725 ft', NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nToday, we take a short drive to Nayapul. Then we walk along the Burungdi Khola, passing Birethanti and small villages like Tikhedhunga. After crossing a suspension bridge, we climb the stone steps up to Ulleri, a Magar village with beautiful terraced fields and mountain views.&nbsp;<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Transport : 1hour 30 minutes  drive (Nayapul)</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1200m. Elevation loss: 190m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-14 16:20:58'),
(1848, 165, '4', NULL, 'Ulleri- Ghorepani (2860M)', '2,850m/9,351ft', NULL, '4-5 hours', '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we start a steady climb through rhododendron and\r\noak forests. The trail passes small villages such as Banthanti and Nangethanti,\r\nwith occasional views of Annapurna South and Hiunchuli. As we gain altitude,\r\nthe air becomes cooler and the forest grows thicker, especially beautiful in\r\nspring when the rhododendrons are in bloom. The trail then opens into\r\nGhorepani, a lovely ridge-top village with excellent mountain views.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation loss : 900m.5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 4, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-09 21:25:22'),
(1849, 165, '5', NULL, 'Ghorepani - Poonhill (3210) - Tadapni (2620M)', '2,700m/8,859ft', NULL, '6-7 hrs', '<p>\r\n\r\nEarly in the morning, we hike up to see the sunrise over the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri ranges, then return to Ghorepani for breakfast. After breakfast, we climb to Deurali Pass and then descend through dense rhododendron forests. The trail winds through mossy woods with occasional views of Machapuchare (Fishtail) and Annapurna South before reaching Tadapani.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1200m. Elevation loss 1100m.8 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 5, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-09 20:33:06'),
(1850, 165, '6', NULL, 'Tadapani- Chhomrong (2170M)', '(2,170m/7,120ft', NULL, '4- 6 hrs', '<p>\r\n\r\nWe descend through rhododendron and oak forests to Chuile, then pass small villages like Gurjung. After crossing the Kimrong Khola suspension bridge, the trail undulates and climbs through terraced fields to Chhomrong, a picturesque Gurung village with spectacular views of Annapurna South and Machapuchare (Fishtail).\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:510m. Elevation loss: 1000m.6 hours walking.</b></p>', 6, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-09 20:33:06'),
(1851, 165, '7', NULL, 'Chhomrong- Himalaya (2,900M)', '2600m/8528ft', NULL, '4-5 hrs', '<p><b></b>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we descend stone steps to Chhomrong Khola, then climb to Sinuwa. The trail passes through bamboo and rhododendron forests to Bamboo, then gradually ascends to Doban. The final stretch to Himalaya is a gentle climb along the forested Modi Khola, with waterfalls and scenic mountain views.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:1140m. Elevation loss: 550m.7 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 7, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-09 20:33:06'),
(1852, 165, '8', NULL, 'Himalaya- Machhapurchchre B. C (3700M)', '3,230m/10,598ft', NULL, '3-4 hrs', '<p>\r\n\r\nThis morning we climb past Hinku Cave and some avalanche-prone areas to reach Deurali (3,230â€¯m). From there, the trail opens up with&nbsp; beautiful mountain views. The final stretch follows the Modi Khola, offering sights of Machhapuchhre and ends at MBC, a peaceful base camp beneath the Himalayan peaks.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:1200m. Elevation loss: 60m. 5/6 hours walking.</b> <br></p>', 8, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-14 16:20:58'),
(1853, 165, '9', NULL, 'M.B.C - Annapurnas B. C (4130M)', '4,130m/13,550ft', NULL, '4-6 hrs', '<div>The day begins with a gradual ascent through a wide alpine valley, offering close-up views of Annapurna I, Annapurna South, Hiunchuli, and Machhapuchhre. Following the Modi Khola, the trail opens out to majestic mountains, leading to ABC â€” a natural amphitheatre of towering peaks and one of the most spectacular spots in the Annapurna region.\r\n\r\n<br></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 9, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2025-12-10 15:14:24'),
(1854, 165, '10', NULL, 'A.B.C - Sinawa (2340M)', '2310m/7575ft', NULL, '6-8 hrs', '<p>Today we retrace the trail on a long descent of 5â€“6 hours. We pass through alpine meadows and forests, revisiting Deurali and Doban, before reaching the rhododendron and bamboo forests near Sinuwa. The scenery changes from high mountains to lush greenery as we approach the village.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:100m. Elevation loss: 1900m. 7 hours walking (preety long 18km).</b> </p>', 10, '2024-08-23 17:32:32', '2025-12-10 15:14:24'),
(1855, 165, '11', NULL, 'Sinawa- Ghandrung (2012M)', '1780m/5840ft', NULL, '4- 6 hrs', '<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b>We retrace much of the trail to Kumrung Khola, then make a short climb followed by a gentle descent to Ghandrung, a beautiful traditional Gurung village and the largest in the area, where you can visit the Gurung Cultural Museum and a Buddhist monastery.<b>\r\n\r\n<br></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\n<b>Elevation gain:1012m. Elevation loss: 1350m. 5 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n</b>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><br></p>', 11, '2024-08-23 17:32:32', '2025-12-09 20:33:06'),
(1856, 165, '12', NULL, 'Ghandrung- Pokhara', '827m/2,713ft', NULL, '4-6 hrs', '<p></p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, enjoy a 30-minute walk to catch the jeep to Pokhara, followed by a drive of about three hours from Chyamje. You are now on the final stretch of your trek. In Pokhara, take a free day to rest and relax. Your leader can suggest sightseeing, and a boat ride on the lake is highly recommended. There are also cafÃ©s and shops nearby.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning&nbsp;</b><br><b>Transport : 3 hours drive (Pokhara). 30m walking</b></p>', 12, '2024-08-23 17:32:32', '2025-12-09 20:33:07'),
(1857, 165, '13', NULL, 'Drive to Kathmandu free day', '1,350m/4,429ft', NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours.</p><p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6 - 7 hours drive (Kathmandu)</b></div><p></p>', 13, '2024-08-23 17:32:32', '2025-12-14 16:20:58'),
(1858, 165, '15', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>According to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.</p></div></div></div></div><div></div><div><div></div></div></div></div><div></div>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 15, '2024-08-23 17:32:32', '2025-12-09 21:25:22'),
(1870, 166, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-08-26 15:46:11', '2025-12-16 15:48:24'),
(1871, 166, '11', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 11, '2024-08-26 15:46:11', '2025-12-16 15:48:24'),
(1873, 166, '9', NULL, 'Thulo Shyabru â€“  Dunche - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>The journey from Thulo Syabru to Dhunche involves trekking downhill through forests and small villages, enjoying views of the surrounding mountains and rivers. From Dhunche, you can take a drive back to Kathmandu, which usually takes about 6â€“7 hours along winding mountain roads, passing through scenic valleys, rivers, and rural towns. This route marks the end of the trek and returns you to the capital city.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nTransport : 6/7 hours drive(Kathmandu).</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 9, '2024-08-26 15:46:11', '2025-10-18 12:59:12'),
(1874, 166, '8', NULL, 'Lama Hotel - Thulo Syabru (2130 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nThe trek from <strong>Lama Hotel to Thulo Syabru,</strong>&nbsp;takes about <strong>4 to 6 hours</strong> and passes through beautiful forests and villages. The trail starts at Lama Hotel (around 2,400 m) and goes down through <strong>rhododendron, pine, and bamboo forests</strong>, crossing small rivers and <strong>suspension bridges</strong>. After some downhill and flat sections, the path climbs up again along <strong>terraced fields and ridges</strong> to reach Thulo Syabru. The village offers great views of <strong>Ganesh Himal</strong> and a chance to see <strong>Tamang culture</strong>. The route has both uphill and downhill parts and can be <strong>slippery after rain</strong>, so good shoes are important. Itâ€™s best to start early and enjoy the quiet forests and mountain scenery along the way.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon.<br></b><b></b><b>walk : 4/6 hours.&nbsp;</b></p><p><b><br></b></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-08-26 15:46:11', '2025-10-18 12:59:12'),
(1875, 166, '7', NULL, 'Bridhim â€“ Lama hotel (2450m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we join the classical trial at Lama Hotel. After\r\nabout an hour of trekking, we will reach Khamjing village, where the landscape\r\nis filled with cultivated fields of potatoes, barley and wheat. Along the journey,\r\nwe will witness the Lauribinayak Pass, offering an amazing views of Gosainkunda\r\nand Langtang Lirung. The trail then continues through Sherpa Gaun and Rimche,\r\neventually leading us to Lama Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1300 m Elevation loss: 1006 m\r\n5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-08-26 16:22:04', '2025-08-27 19:58:29'),
(1876, 166, '6', NULL, 'Thuman - Bridhim (2230m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Like wise others day, we&nbsp;<strong></strong>trek from Thuman to Briddhim with a gradual descent through forested trails, passing small villages and crossing a suspension bridge over a river. After the descent, the path begins a gentle uphill climb through terraced fields and scattered homes. Along the way, you can enjoy the natural beauty and local wildlife. After several hours of trekking, you arrive at Briddhim, a peaceful village known for its Tibetan Buddhist culture and welcoming homestays, where you can visit the local monastery and experience traditional hospitality.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain : 633 m Elevation loss: 798 m 4/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-08-26 16:22:04', '2025-08-27 19:58:29'),
(1877, 166, '5', NULL, 'Tatopani - Nagthali (3165 m) - Thuman (2,340m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, the trek from Tatopani climbs\r\nthrough rhododendron-pine forests, passing Tamang villages, mani\r\nwalls and chortens before reaching Nagthali, a windswept ridge\r\nwith 360Â° views of Ganesh Himal and Langtang Lirung. The trail then\r\ndescends through alpine meadows to Thuman, a traditional Tamang village\r\nwith stone houses and vibrant culture. A perfect blend of nature, culture,\r\nand Himalayan vistas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 620 m Elevation loss: 900 m 6\r\nhours &nbsp;walking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-08-26 16:22:04', '2025-08-27 19:58:29'),
(1878, 166, '4', NULL, 'Gatlang â€“ Tatopani (2,600 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>After breakfast, we&nbsp; starts with a descent to the river, followed by a steady climb through forests and terraced fields. Along the way, youâ€™ll pass small villages and enjoy mountain views. After several hours, you reach <strong></strong>Tatopani<strong></strong>, known for its natural hot springs, where you can relax and soothe your muscles.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain : 884 m\r\nElevation loss:582 m 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-08-26 16:22:04', '2025-08-27 19:58:29'),
(1879, 166, '3', NULL, 'Syabru besi - Gatlang (2,240m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>On the third day, we starts with a steep uphill climb through forests and small villages. After a few hours of hiking, you reach Gatlang, a traditional Tamang village known for its stone houses and rich culture.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1060 m\r\nElevation loss: 246 m 5/6 hours &nbsp;walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-08-26 16:22:04', '2025-08-27 19:58:29'),
(1880, 166, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Dhunche (1965 M)- Syabru Besi (1460 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we drive from Kathmandu to Dhunche, along winding mountain roads with scenic views of hills, rivers and villages. From Dhunche, the road continues downhill for about 1â€“2 hours to Syabru Besi, a small town and the starting point for treks in the Langtang region.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Syabru Besi).</b><br></p>', 2, '2024-08-26 16:22:04', '2025-10-18 12:59:12'),
(1927, 171, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1,350 m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-12-16 15:19:22'),
(1928, 171, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ramechhap - Lukla (2,860 m) - Phakding (2,610 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast, we drive from Kathmandu to Ramechhap (Manthali Airport), which takes about 4 to 5 hours depending on traffic and road conditions. From Ramechhap, you\'ll board a short 20-minute flight to Lukla, the main gateway to the Everest region. Upon arrival in Lukla, the trek starts with a gradual descent through alpine forests, suspension bridges and charming Sherpa villages. After&nbsp; 3 to 4 hour walk, youâ€™ll reach Phakding, a scenic riverside village and the first overnight stop on the trail toward Everest Base Camp. </p><p>Note:</p><p><i>Due to potential congestion at Kathmandu Airport, the Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN) may mandate that all flights to Lukla operate either from Kathmandu Airport or from Ramechhap Airport.</i><i></i></p><p><i>&nbsp;</i><i>In the event that the flight is canceled due to adverse weather conditions, it will be rescheduled for the following day. An additional nightâ€™s accommodation will be provided either in Kathmandu or Ramechhap, depending on the point of departure.</i></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport :</b> \r\n\r\n<b>4/5 hours drive by jeep (Ramechhap),</b>&nbsp;<b>25 minutes flight (Lukla)</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m.&nbsp; Elevation loss : 450 m. 3/4 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-10-17 13:20:37'),
(1929, 171, '3', NULL, 'Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3,440 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, we starts with a pleasant walk through a pine forest along the river, followed by a short climb out of a narrow gorge. After passing the entrance to Khumbu National Park, where permits are checked, we descend to cross the river on a suspension bridge. The trail continues through a wooded valley, crossing the river again before reaching a confluence from Thame and the Khumbu. A final crossing on a high suspension bridge marks the start of a challenging 1.5 hours ascent to Namche Bazaar, with our first views of Everest midway.</p><p>Upon arrival, we check into a local lodge. Once a quiet village, Namche has evolved into a bustling trekking hub, offering a mix of tradition and modernityâ€”complete with bakeries, cafÃ©s, pubs and other comforts brought back by well-traveled Sherpas.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m. Elevation loss : 409 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-27 19:05:13'),
(1930, 171, '4', NULL, 'Day Excursion - Everest View Point -Khumjung (4000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>On this day, we take a rest to acclimatize and to enjoy the surroundings. For those inclined, a hike to the Everest View Hotel (3,880 m) offers beautiful&nbsp; scenic views of the Himalayas. Alternatively, you may choose to explore Namche Bazaarâ€”relax in a local cafÃ©, browse the lively market for unique items, or visit the Sherpa Museum to gain insight into local culture. The day concludes with an overnight stay in this iconic mountain village.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-09-23 15:10:35');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1931, 171, '5', NULL, 'Namche - Phorste (3,800 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, we leave Namche Bazaar, the trail gently rises above the village, weaving through terraced fields and fragrant juniper bushes to reach a quiet ridgeline. As you cross a small, prayer-flag-adorned pass, the world opens upâ€”revealing the majestic Ama Dablam, the \"Matterhorn of the Himalayas,\" its icy flanks glistening like a jewel in the sunlight. The path then descends into the serene Sherpa village of Khumjung, where emerald-green potato fields surround traditional stone houses, and the whispers of mountain winds carry stories of Everest legends. From here, the trail meanders onward to Phortse, a hidden gem clinging to the hillside, where yaks graze lazily and the snow-capped giants loom even closer. Each step feels like a quiet conversation with the mountains, as the raw beauty of the Khumbu unfolds in slow, amazing waves.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:700 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-27 19:05:14'),
(1932, 171, '6', NULL, 'Phorste -  Machermo (4400m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>With the beautiful morning, we  ascend into the Gokyo Valley with a picturesque hike through a lush rhododendron forest, where vibrant pink and red blooms (best in spring) line the path alongside cascading waterfalls glinting in the Himalayan light. The route follows the Dudh Koshi River, with suspension bridges adding a sense of adventure. After 3â€“4 hours of gradual climbing, youâ€™ll reach Machermo, a tranquil Sherpa village with stone-walled lodges and dramatic views of Cho Oyu (8,188m). This spot serves as a critical acclimatization stop before pushing higher into the valley. Tea houses here offer warm garlic soup and cozy beds, with the sound of the river lulling trekkers to sleep.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:980 m. Elevation loss: 380 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-27 19:05:15'),
(1933, 171, '7', NULL, 'Machermo - Gokyo (4800 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today is a short but scenic journey. The trail gradually ascends through a rugged alpine landscape, following the Dudh Koshi River. Along the way, youâ€™ll pass through small settlements and enjoy amazing views of snow-capped peaks, including Cho Oyu. As you approach Gokyo, youâ€™ll see the beautiful turquoise lakes that the village is famous for. Gokyo sits beside the third lake, Dudh Pokhari, offering beautiful mountain reflections and a peaceful atmosphere.</p><p><b></b></p><div></div><b></b><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:470 m. Elevation loss: 120 m. 5.5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-27 19:05:15'),
(1934, 171, '8', NULL, 'Gokyo - Gokyo Peak (5357 m) - Gokyo', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Finally, we climb Gokyo to reach Gokyo Peak (5,357 m). The climb, which\r\ntakes 2 to 3 hours, is steep but rewarding, offering awesome views of the\r\nmountains. You\'ll see unbelievable views, including Everest, Lhotse and the\r\nbeautiful Gokyo Lakes. After taking photos, hike back down to Gokyo for lunch.\r\nSpend the afternoon resting by the lakes before sleeping at the lodge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Same Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:555 m. Elevation loss: 555 m. 5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-27 19:05:15'),
(1935, 171, '9', NULL, 'Gokyo (4800 m) â€“ Renjo La Pass (5360 m) â€“ Lungden (4350 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, Trekking from Gokyo to Renjo La Pass is an exciting\r\nHimalayan experience. Trekkers start with difficult but worthwhile climb from\r\nGokyo to the Renjo La Pass which offers expansive views of Everest, Lhotse,\r\nMakalu and Cho Oyu. After that, the journey ascends to Lungden via uninhabited\r\nlandscapes and remote valleys. We proceed past the lakes and take a\r\nwell-constructed path with stone stairs that leads nearly to the summit of the\r\nRenjo La. The trail then becomes well-managed once again with stone steps that\r\ndrop towards the lakes of Gokyo following an initially steep, maybe\r\nsnow-covered descent. Compared to other Everest treks, this one is less busy\r\nand provides a peaceful and genuine view of the Khumbu region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge, Meals included morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 603m. Elevation loss: 1008m. walking: 6/8 hours</b></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-27 19:05:15'),
(1936, 171, '10', NULL, 'Lungden â€“ Morulung (4,210 m) â€“ Thame (3,750 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we Trekking to Morulung and Thame. Morulung a peaceful settlement hidden\r\naway beside the Bhote Koshi River. The trail can be challenging, especially\r\nduring the monsoon season, when landslides and slippery conditions are common. Afterwards, the trip continues to Thame a famous Sherpa community known for its rich\r\nmountaineering history and ancient monastery. This path offers a chance to\r\nexperience Sherpa culture and see traditional villages, as well as amazing views of peaks including Thamserku, Kangtega and Kusum Kanguru.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge, Meals included morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 20m,.Elevation loss: 587m. walking: 5 hours.</b><br><br></p><p></p>', 10, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-27 19:05:15'),
(1937, 171, '11', NULL, 'Thame â€“ Kongde (4250 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we trek short but rugged alternative to the busier Khumbu routes,\r\noffering solitude and Himalayan&nbsp; landscape. The trail is narrow and\r\nexposed in sections, occasionally requiring fixed ropes for support,\r\nmaking it more adventurous than standard Everest-region hikes. Passing through\r\nremote Sherpa settlements, alpine pastures and rocky ridges, the route\r\nprovides awesome views of Thamserku, Kusum Kanguru and the\r\nNuptse-Lhotse wall. Due to its technical sections and lack of teahouses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1038m. Elevation loss: 671m. walking: 6 hours</b><br></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-27 19:05:15'),
(1938, 171, '12', NULL, 'Kongde â€“ Lukla / Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we start with a challenging\r\nascent to Taktor, where you\'ll connect with the classic Khumbu route. This\r\njunction marks the start of your descent through picturesque Sherpa villages,\r\nwith Thamserku and the Everest range providing a magnificent backdrop.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Resort. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 494 m. Elevation loss: 1450. Walking: 6/7 hours</b><br></p><p>\r\n\r\n<i></i><b><i>\"</i></b><i>Tired of long, exhausting treks? Skip the hike and choose an exhilarating helicopter transfer from Kongde straight to Lukla or Kathmanduâ€”your adventure in the sky awaits! Whether you\'re a solo traveler or part of a group, our flexible pricing adapts to your needs and destination. Experience the Himalayas like never before as you soar above rugged mountain passes, glacial lakes, and traditional Sherpa villagesâ€”all while enjoying VIP comfort and convenience. This isn\'t just transportation; it\'s a once-in-a-lifetime aerial spectacle that even Nepal\'s elite prefer for efficient, breathtaking travel. Why walk for days when you can witness Everest\'s majesty from your window seat in just hours?\"&nbsp;</i><b><i></i><br></b></p><p><i></i>\r\n\r\n\"If you choose to go directly to Kathmandu, youâ€™ll have extra days to explore more of the city or to prepare for your return home before the itinerary ends.\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>', 12, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-08-25 13:50:27'),
(1939, 171, '13', NULL, 'Flight from Lukla â€“ Ramechap and drive to Kathmandu / Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>&nbsp;We start the day with an early morning flight from Lukla to\r\nRamechhap, offering final views of the Himalayas. From there, enjoy a scenic\r\ndrive back to Kathmandu. The rest of the day is free to relax, explore and\r\nshop. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning afternoon.</b><br><b>Transport : 30 minutes morning flight (Ramechhap), 4/5 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b></p><p><br></p><p></p>', 13, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-10-17 13:20:37'),
(1940, 171, '14', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p></p><p></p>', 14, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-12-16 15:19:22'),
(1941, 171, '15', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 15, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2025-12-16 15:19:22'),
(1957, 179, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>', 1, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-12 19:38:37'),
(1958, 179, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ghurmi (574M) - Patale (2800) - Phaplu (2413 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Early in the morning, we drive to Phaplu. After passing Dhulikhel, the road descends to the Sun Koshi River and then continues to Ghurmi. From Ghurmi to Patale, the jeep travels more slowly. Patale is one of the best places to see Mount Everest, Lhotse, Makalu, Kanchenjunga and many other peaks. On arrival, we enjoy clear mountain views and a first glimpse of the local village life and natural surroundings.</p>\r\n<p>After about an hour in Patale, we continue our drive to Phaplu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7-9 hours drive by jeep (Phaplu).</b><br></p>', 2, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-16 14:31:15'),
(1959, 179, '3', NULL, 'Phaplu - Junbesi (2700m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, we start with an easy walk, descending to the river before gently climbing up the opposite side. The trail follows the riverside, passing terraced fields, small Sherpa villages and lush forests. We arrive in Junbesi, a charming village at the heart of Sherpa culture. Here, you can visit the monastery and explore traditional Sherpa houses. The village also offers fine views of the Himalayan range.</p>\r\n<p>You may also choose to visit the Royal Palace of the Sherpa King, Tsering Tenzing Sherpa, which is located near the end of Phaplu Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n <p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 748 m. Elevation loss : 545 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 3, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-15 16:53:47'),
(1960, 179, '4', NULL, 'Junbesi â€“  Thupten Chholing Gomba (3000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>From Junbesi, the day begins with a gentle climb northwards along the Junbesi Khola. The walk is peaceful and spiritual, leading through pine and rhododendron forests, with fluttering prayer flags and mani walls along the route. We arrive at the sacred Thupten Chholing Monastery, founded by Trulsik Rinpoche in the 1960s. Home to hundreds of monks and nuns, the monastery is well known for its serene atmosphere, daily chanting and traditional Tibetan Buddhist practices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1015 m. Elevation loss: 80 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p>', 4, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-15 16:53:47'),
(1961, 179, '5', NULL, 'Thupten Chholing Gomba â€“ Jasmane Bajyang (3500 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>We start the day by walking back to Junbesi. From there, we follow the Sir Edmund Hillary Trail, which climbs gently through beautiful scenery and traditional Sherpa villages. The walk to Taktor is easy and culturally interesting. At Taktor, we leave the main trail and begin a steeper climb to cross a quiet, little-used pass. After the climb, we descend into the open pastureland of Jasmane Bayang, where we camp and enjoy the surrounding mountain views.</p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1,154 m. Elevation loss: 668 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 5, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-15 16:53:47'),
(1962, 179, '6', NULL, 'Jasmane Bajyang - Pikey Summit (4065m) - PK Base Camp', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>The day begins with a gentle climb from Jasmane Bajyang, crossing rocky ridges and open alpine meadows. As you go higher, the views widen, with clear sights of nearby valleys and distant snow-covered peaks. After two to three hours of walking, you reach the summit of Pikey Peak (4,065 m). From here, there are 360-degree views of the Himalayas, including Everest, Makalu, Kanchenjunga and Annapurna on a clear day.</p>\r\n<p>After enjoying the views, the trail descends gradually to Pikey Base Camp along a scenic ridge with low alpine bushes and prayer flags. This quiet place is perfect for an overnight stay, with beautiful sunset views and a peaceful atmosphere.</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 100 m. Elevation loss : 320 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 6, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-15 16:53:47'),
(1963, 179, '7', NULL, 'PK Base Camp - Jhapre (2800 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>After enjoying the morning views, we begin a gentle descent. The trail passes through quiet forests, old mani walls and sometimes yaks grazing along the way. It is a peaceful and scenic walk, full of natural beauty and local culture.</p></div></div></div></div><div></div><div><div></div></div></div></div></div><div></div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon&nbsp; evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 100 m. Elevation loss : 884 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-15 16:53:47'),
(1964, 179, '8', NULL, 'Jhapre - Dhap (2900 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>From Jhapre, we walk downhill through forested hills and terraced farmland. The path is easy and comfortable, making for a relaxed day. Along the way, we pass small villages and open fields, with occasional views of distant mountains. The walk is peaceful and offers a look into the traditional life of the lower Everest (Khumbu) region before we reach Dhap.</p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 420 m . Elevation loss: 346 m. 5/7 hours Walking.</b><br></p>', 8, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-15 16:53:47'),
(1965, 179, '9', NULL, 'Dhap â€“  Chagesthan Viewpoint ( 3,050 M) - (Kundar 2100 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Early in the morning, those who wish can walk up to the Chagesthan Viewpoint. From here, there are wide views of the landscape, including the lower Solu hills. The viewpoint is also a quiet and spiritual place. After enjoying the views, we return to the lodge for breakfast. We then walk downhill to Kundar. The trail passes through farmland, small houses and subtropical forest. Along the way, we may see local people going about their daily work. We arrive in Kundar, a peaceful village in a warm valley surrounded by green hills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: inhabitant/School. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 150 m. Elevation loss: 950 m. 4/6 hours Walking.</b></p>', 9, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-15 16:53:47'),
(1966, 179, '10', NULL, 'Kundar - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we travel to Kathmandu by 4x4. The drive takes several hours and goes through Okhaldhunga. Some parts of the road are rough, with only basic tracks.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.<br>Transport : 7/9 hours Drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b><br></p>', 10, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-15 16:53:47'),
(1967, 179, '11', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 11, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-12 19:38:37'),
(1968, 179, '12', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 12, '2024-08-28 17:15:31', '2025-12-12 19:38:37'),
(1970, 180, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-10 00:21:29'),
(1971, 180, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Pokhara (860m) - Ulleri (2050m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nAfter your flight to Pokhara, you arrive at Pokhara International Airport, where a private car will take you to Hile. After Birethanti, the road becomes quite rough. We take a short break, then begin our trek to Ulleri. The trail climbs steadily on stone-paved steps until we reach Ulleri, a traditional Magar village.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 2/3 hours drive (Hile). 25 minutes of flight</b><div><b>Elevation gain: 570 m. Elevation loss: 00m. 4 hours walking.</b></div><div><p></p><p></p> </div>', 2, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-10 15:06:37'),
(1972, 180, '3', NULL, 'Ulleri - Ghorepani (2860m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we start a steady climb through rhododendron and oak forests. The trail passes small villages such as Banthanti and Nangethanti, with occasional views of Annapurna South and Hiunchuli. As we gain altitude, the air becomes cooler and the forest grows thicker, especially beautiful in spring when the rhododendrons are in bloom. The trail then opens into Ghorepani, a lovely ridge-top village with excellent mountain views.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 865m. Elevation loss: 35m.  4/5 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-10 00:21:29'),
(1973, 180, '4', NULL, 'Ghorepani - Poon Hill (3210m) - Tadapani (2620m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>Today is one of the most beautiful and scenic days of the trek. Early in the morning, we hike up to watch the sunrise over the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri ranges, then return to Ghorepani for breakfast. After breakfast, we climb toward Deurali Pass and descend through dense rhododendron forests. The trail winds through mossy woodland, eventually leading us to Tadapani.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 635m. Elevation loss: 815m. 4/5 hours walking</b></p><p></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-10 15:12:48'),
(1974, 180, '5', NULL, 'Tadapani - Ghandrung (2012m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nToday, we trek from Tadapani to Ghandruk. The trail descends through the same kind of forests as yesterday and leads us to Ghandruk, one of the most famous Gurung villages. From the village, you can enjoy beautiful views of Annapurna South (7,219 m), Gangapurna (7,454 m), Machhapuchhre (6,997 m), Annapurna III (7,555 m), Hiunchuli (6,441 m) and other nearby peaks.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>&nbsp;Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 685m. Elevation loss: 18m. 4 hours walking</b></p><p></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-10 15:18:16'),
(1975, 180, '6', NULL, 'Ghandrung - Kimche (1690 m) - Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, enjoy a 30-minute walk to catch the jeep to Pokhara, followed by a drive of about three hours from Chyamje. You are now on the final stretch of your trek. In Pokhara, take a free day to rest and relax. Your leader can suggest sightseeing, and a boat ride on the lake is highly recommended. There are also cafÃ©s and shops nearby.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport: 3/4 hours (Pokhara).</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 685m. Elevation loss: 18m. 1 hour walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-10 00:26:23'),
(1976, 180, '7', NULL, 'Pokhara- Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours.</p><p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6-7 hours drive (Kathmandu)</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>', 7, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-11 16:21:55'),
(1977, 180, '8', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 8, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-11 16:25:11'),
(1978, 180, '9', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onwards journey.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>', 9, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2025-12-10 00:26:23'),
(2018, 184, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu 1350m. Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Your happy holiday starts in Kathmandu. You will have time to freshen up before briefing with guide in the late afternoon. According to the time, you can walk/drive to Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) and from here watch your first Nepali sunset over the Kathmandu Valley, from the oldest stupas. This is one of the most Important world heritage sites of Nepal and an important center for Buddhism in Nepal.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-10-16 19:56:14'),
(2019, 184, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Dakshinkali - Kirtipur - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start your day in Kathmandu by taking a morning drive to\r\nthe Dakshinkali Temple (Approx. 19km from Kathmandu), another location honoring\r\nGoddess Kali that is surrounded by peaceful forests. Visit Kirtipur, a historic\r\nNewari town renowned for its beautiful streets, Bagh Bhairab Temple, and\r\namazing valley views, after taking in its spiritual atmosphere (Approx. 15km\r\nfrom Dakshinkali). After a restoring and culturally rich day trip, enjoy some\r\nlocal Newari food before heading back to Kathmandu in the evening (Approx. 8km\r\nfrom kirtipur). </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transport : Around&nbsp; 2/3 hours&nbsp; drive.</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-10-16 22:13:20'),
(2020, 184, '3', NULL, 'Kathmandu Heritage Circuit', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Visit Budhanilkantha, where a statue of Lord Vishnu rests\r\npeacefully on a bed of snakes, to start your day in Kathmandu (Approx. 9km from\r\nKathmandu). Next, visit the magnificent Boudhanath Stupa, a focal point of\r\nTibetan Buddhism (Approx. 9km from Budhanilkantha). Visit the Pashupatinath\r\nTemple, a significant Hindu pilgrimage site on the banks of the Bagmati River,\r\nafter taking in its serene atmosphere (Approx. 3km from Pashupatinath). After a\r\nday of spiritual fulfillment, head back to Kathmandu in the evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transport : Around 4 hours drive.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-10-16 22:13:20'),
(2021, 184, '4', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Enjoy the breathtaking views of Phewa Lake and the\r\nAnnapurna range during the lengthy drive from Kathmandu to Pokhara. After a\r\nboat ride to Tal Barahi Temple, explore the World Peace Pagoda, Gupteshwor\r\nCave, and Davis Falls. As you finish your day, take your time strolling around\r\nthe vibrant lake (Approx. 230km from Kathmandu).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><b></b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening<br>Transport : Around&nbsp; 5 hours drive.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-10-16 22:13:20'),
(2022, 184, '5', NULL, 'Pokhara - Sarangkot  - Tibetan Refugee', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start your day in Sarangkot, which offers amazing views of the Annapurna\r\nrange. Take a leisurely boat ride on Phewa Lake and visit Tal Barahi Temple.\r\nContinue on to Davis Falls, Gupteshwor Cave, and the Tibetan Refugee Camp.\r\nAfter admiring the beautiful surroundings from the World Peace Pagoda, spend\r\nthe afternoon at the International Mountain Museum. To cap off the day, have\r\ndinner and take a leisurely stroll along Pokhara\'s wonderful lakeshore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transport : Around 8/9 hours drive.</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 5, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-10-16 22:13:20'),
(2023, 184, '6', NULL, 'Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Take a leisurely walk down to Naundanda after starting the day with a\r\nbeautiful drive to Sarangkot for beautiful Himalayan views. In the\r\nafternoon, take a leisurely walk through the vibrant narrow streets and visit\r\nthe peaceful monastery as you explore the neighboring Tibetan towns. Enjoy\r\ndelicious meals and unwind overnight while taking in the peace and beauty of\r\nthe day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p><b>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</b><br><p></p>', 6, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-10-16 22:13:21'),
(2024, 184, '7', NULL, 'Pokhara - Tansen - Lumbini - birthplace of Buddha', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Enjoy a charming drive from Pokhara to\r\nTansen, a small hill town that offers a welcoming, cultural atmosphere with\r\nbustling bazaars and Newari architecture (Approx. 120km from Pokhara). Explore\r\nits charming streets, enjoy the beautiful surroundings, and experience the\r\nlocal way of life. Next, proceed to Lumbini, where Lord Buddha was born in\r\npeace (Approx. 79km from Tansen). Heading towards to feel a deep spiritual\r\ncalm, stroll leisurely among beautiful monasteries, the Maya Devi Temple, and\r\nthe sacred garden.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\nAccommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening<br>Transport : Around 8/9 hours drive.\r\n\r\n</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 7, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-10-16 22:13:21'),
(2025, 184, '8', NULL, 'Visit Lumbini - Lumbini Museum - Ashoka Pillar', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Early in the morning, pay a visit to the Maya Devi Temple, the well-known\r\nsite recognizing the birthplace of Buddha. Explore the beautiful Lumbini\r\nGarden, which is home to a number of magnificent monasteries that symbolize\r\ndifferent Buddhist traditions. Visit the Lumbini Museum to spend some time\r\nlearning about the life and teachings of Buddha. Take in the calm surroundings\r\nand explore them. After that, take some time to relax by the Ashoka Pillar\r\nbefore going back to the hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 8, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-08-21 18:17:49'),
(2026, 184, '9', NULL, 'Lumbini - Chitawan National Park', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Explore the revered Maya Devi Temple and neighboring monasteries to begin\r\nyour day in Lumbini. After that, take an exhilarating afternoon safari by jeep\r\nor elephant in Chitwan National Park to witness wildlife like deer and rhinos\r\nafter having driven from Lumbini (Approx. 160km from Lumbini). Take a boat ride\r\non the Rapti River to see birds and crocodiles, explore forest trails, and\r\nvisit a Tharu village. Finish with dinner, an overnight stay close to the park,\r\nand a traditional Tharu cultural performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transport : Around 3/6 hours drive.</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 9, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2025-10-16 22:13:21'),
(2204, 198, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1,350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-12-16 15:23:26'),
(2205, 198, '3', NULL, 'Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3,440 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, we starts with a pleasant walk through a pine forest along the river, followed by a short climb out of a narrow gorge. After passing the entrance to Khumbu National Park, where permits are checked, we descend to cross the river on a suspension bridge. The trail continues through a wooded valley, crossing the river again before reaching a confluence from Thame and the Khumbu. A final crossing on a high suspension bridge marks the start of a challenging 1.5 hours ascent to Namche Bazaar, with our first views of Everest midway.</p><p>Upon arrival, we check into a local lodge. Once a quiet village, Namche has evolved into a bustling trekking hub, offering a mix of tradition and modernityâ€”complete with bakeries, cafÃ©s, pubs, and other comforts brought back by well-traveled Sherpas.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m. Elevation loss : 409 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-08-27 19:11:38'),
(2206, 198, '4', NULL, 'Day Excursion Everest View Point - Khumjung (4000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>On the this day, we take a rest day to acclimatize and enjoy the surroundings. For those inclined, a hike to the Everest View Hotel (3,880 m) offers beautiful scenic views of the Himalayas. Alternatively, you may choose to explore Namche Bazaarâ€”relax in a local cafÃ©, browse the lively market for unique items or visit the Sherpa Museum to gain insight into local culture. The day concludes with an overnight stay in this iconic mountain village.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-08-27 19:11:38'),
(2207, 198, '5', NULL, 'Namche - Phorste (3800 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, we leave Namche Bazaar behind, the trail gently rises above the village, weaving through terraced fields and fragrant juniper bushes to reach a quiet ridgeline. As you cross a small, prayer-flag-adorned pass, the world opens upâ€”revealing the majestic Ama Dablam, the \"Matterhorn of the Himalayas,\" its icy flanks glistening like a jewel in the sunlight. The path then descends into the serene Sherpa village of Khumjung, where emerald-green potato fields surround traditional stone houses, and the whispers of mountain winds carry stories of Everest legends. From here, the trail meanders onward to Phortse, a hidden gem clinging to the hillside, where yaks graze lazily and the snow-capped giants loom even closer. Each step feels like a quiet conversation with the mountains, as the raw beauty of the Khumbu unfolds in slow, amazing waves.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:700 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-08-27 19:11:38'),
(2208, 198, '6', NULL, 'Phorste - Machermo (4400m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>With the beautiful morning, we  ascend into the Gokyo Valley with a picturesque hike through a lush rhododendron forest, where vibrant pink and red blooms (best in spring) line the path alongside cascading waterfalls glinting in the Himalayan light. The route follows the Dudh Koshi River, with suspension bridges adding a sense of adventure. After 3â€“4 hours of gradual climbing, youâ€™ll reach Machermo, a tranquil Sherpa village with stone-walled lodges and dramatic views of Cho Oyu (8,188m). This spot serves as a critical acclimatization stop before pushing higher into the valley. Tea houses here offer warm garlic soup and cozy beds, with the sound of the river lulling trekkers to sleep.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:980 m. Elevation loss: 380 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-08-27 19:11:38'),
(2209, 198, '7', NULL, 'Machermo - Gokyo (4800 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today is a short but scenic journey. The trail gradually ascends through a rugged alpine landscape, following the Dudh Koshi River. Along the way, youâ€™ll pass through small settlements and enjoy beautiful views of snow-capped peaks, including Cho Oyu. As you approach Gokyo, youâ€™ll see the beautiful turquoise lakes that the village is famous for. Gokyo sits beside the third lake, Dudh Pokhari, offering beautiful mountain reflections and a peaceful atmosphere.</p><p><b></b></p><div></div><b></b><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:470 m. Elevation loss: 120 m. 5.5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-08-27 19:11:38'),
(2210, 198, '8', NULL, 'Gokyo - Gokyo Peak (5357 m) - Thangnak (4,700m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Finally, we summit Gokyo Peak today, we resume our trek by navigating the rugged terrain alongside the Ngozumpa Glacier. The trail presents a mix of ascents and descents â€” demanding yet deeply rewarding. As we descend into the valley, following the eastern glacial moraine, the dramatic alpine scenery keeps our spirits high. By afternoon, we arrive in Thangnak, a quiet cluster of lodges nestled at the foot of the Cho La Pass â€” an ideal spot to rest and prepare for the challenging crossing ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 790 m or 210 m. Elevation loss: 900 m or 300 m.</b><br><b>walking: 2 hours 15 minutes (without Gokyo Peak), 5 hours 30 minutes (including)</b></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-10-15 19:41:49'),
(2211, 198, '9', NULL, 'Thangnak - Cho La Pass (5420m) - Dzongla (4855m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today  is one of the most challenging and rewarding sections of the Everest region. The journey start early to cross the steep and icy Cho La Pass. The trail involves a tough ascent over rocky terrain and possibly snow or ice, with spectacular views of surrounding peaks. After reaching the pass, you descend carefully on a slippery trail, eventually reaching Dzongla, a small, scenic settlement surrounded by towering mountains. Itâ€™s a demanding but unforgettable day on the trek. </p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 300 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 2/4 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-08-27 19:11:38'),
(2212, 198, '10', NULL, 'Lobuche â€“ Kalpathar (5644 m) - Goraksheep (5164M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast we trek to Gorakshep, the last stop before Everest Base Camp. Then, you make a steep 2â€“3 hour round-trip climb to Kala Patthar for amazing views of Mount Everest and surrounding peaks. Afterward, you return to Gorakshep to rest.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening<br>Elevation gain: 825 m. Elevation loss :545 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 10, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-08-27 19:11:38'),
(2213, 198, '11', NULL, 'Gorasheep - Everest Base Camp (5364 m) - Goraksheep and fly to Lukla / Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trek from Gorakshep to Everest Base Camp covers\r\napproximately 3 km across the rugged terrain of the Khumbu Glacier. Although\r\nbrief, this walk is profoundly rewarding, with the excitement of reaching\r\nEverest Base Camp, fuelling trekkers through the rocky and challenging\r\nlandscape. After spending time at the base camp, hikers return along the same\r\nroute to Gorakshep, savouring the spectacular scenery and lasting memories.\r\nAfter \"Take a helicopter from Gorakshep directly to Lukla or Kathmandu to\r\navoid descending back to Lukla on foot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 205 m. Elevation loss: 205 m. 4 hours walking.</b><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\"If you choose to go directly to Kathmandu, youâ€™ll have\r\nextra days to explore more of the city or to prepare for your return home\r\nbefore the itinerary ends.</p><p></p><p><b><i></i></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>You are\r\nprovided with hotel accommodation and breakfast</i></b></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-08-27 19:11:38'),
(2214, 198, '12', NULL, 'flight from Lukla â€“ Ramechap and drive to Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start the day with an early morning flight from Lukla to\r\nRamechhap, offering final views of the Himalayas. From there, enjoy a scenic\r\ndrive back to Kathmandu. The rest of the day is free to relax, explore and\r\nshop. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning, afternoon.</b><br><b>Transport : 30 minutes flight (Ramechhap), 5/6 hours drive (Kathmandu) by jeep.</b></p><p>If come direct to Kathmandu you can do itinerary day 13</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p><p><b><i>You are\r\nprovided with hotel accommodation and breakfast.</i></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 12, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-10-17 13:34:30'),
(2215, 198, '13', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 13, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-12-16 15:23:26'),
(2216, 198, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ramechhap - Lukla (2,860 m) - Phakding (2,610 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast, we drive from Kathmandu to Ramechhap (Manthali Airport), which takes about 4 to 5 hours depending on traffic and road conditions. From Ramechhap, you\'ll board a short 20 minute flight to Lukla, the main gateway to the Everest region. Upon arrival in Lukla, the trek begins with a gradual descent through alpine forests, suspension bridges and charming Sherpa villages. After 3 to 4 hour walk, youâ€™ll reach Phakding, a scenic riverside village and the first overnight stop on the trail toward Everest Base Camp. </p><p>Note:</p><p><i>Due to potential congestion at Kathmandu Airport, the Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN) may mandate that all flights to Lukla operate either from Kathmandu Airport or from Ramechhap Airport.</i><i></i></p><p><i>&nbsp;</i><i>In the event that the flight is canceled due to adverse weather conditions, it will be rescheduled for the following day. An additional nightâ€™s accommodation will be provided either in Kathmandu or Ramechhap, depending on the point of departure.</i></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : \r\n\r\n<b></b>4/5 hours drive (Kathmandu) by jeep.&nbsp;25 minutes flight (Lukla).&nbsp;</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss : 450 m. 3/4 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-09-04 20:50:49', '2025-10-17 13:34:30'),
(2236, 195, '1', NULL, 'Arrival in Kathmandu (1,300m). Transfer to hotel.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-09-05 13:28:06', '2025-12-10 15:57:56'),
(2237, 195, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani (1860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Early morning departure to Besisahar along the main highway between Nepal and India. Passing through villages, we change jeeps at Besisahar. Beyond this point, the road becomes a stony track, bumpy but lined with rice fields and traditional villages. Occasional landslides may cause delays or vehicle changes, so itâ€™s best to follow the Nepalese example and stay cheerful. We finally arrive at Dharapani and settle into the lodge<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, and evening.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6 hours drive (Besi Sahar). 3 hours jeep (Dharapani)</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>', 2, '2024-09-05 13:28:06', '2025-12-10 15:57:56'),
(2244, 195, '9', NULL, 'Tilicho BC â€“ Tilicho lake (4920 m) â€“ Shree Kharka (4080 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we leave Manang within 1 hour, we explore the beautiful village (Khangsar) an unusual village with its unique houses and culture. Expansive views of snow-capped peaks and \r\n\r\nToday is the final stage to reach Tilicho Lake. After a gentle climb, you are rewarded with breathtaking views of the lake at 4,930â€¯metres. The only sounds are the occasional avalanches from Tilicho Peak or ice breaking into the lake, adding to the wild beauty of the surroundings. If the lakeside tea stall is open, it is the perfect place to enjoy a hot drink while taking in the scenery. After spending time at Tilicho Lake, we retrace our steps along the trail back to Shree Kharka.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 860 m. Elevation loss: 266 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-09-05 13:28:06', '2025-12-17 16:33:52'),
(2258, 195, '6', NULL, 'Ngawal - Braga Monastery - Manang (3542 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, we follow a scenic, gently descending trail from Ngawal, winding through open alpine terrain with scattered juniper trees, mani walls, and sweeping views of Annapurna III and Gangapurna. After about 1.5 hours, we reach the historic village of Braga, where a 600-year-old monastery perched on a cliff is well worth a short visit for its spiritual atmosphere and stunning views. From Braga, the trail becomes easy and mostly flat, following the Marsyangdi River until we arrive at Manang, a lively village and important acclimatisation stop on the Annapurna Circuit.<br></p><div>&nbsp;<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>&nbsp;Elevation gain: 140 m. Elevation loss: 273 m. 4 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 6, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 15:57:56'),
(2260, 195, '8', NULL, 'Manang - Tilicho Base Camp (4150 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, the day begins with a trek through remote, high-altitude terrain. The trail gradually ascends to Khangsar, a small stone-built village, before continuing to Siri Kharka, where trekkers are treated to scenic views of Tilicho Peak. From there, the path becomes more demanding, crossing narrow, landslide-prone sections, before descending slightly to Tilicho Base Camp, where trekkers rest prior to the hike to Tilicho Lake.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 860 m. Elevation loss: 266 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 16:12:19'),
(2265, 195, '13', NULL, 'Tatopani - Sikha (2000 m) â€“ Ghorepani  (2860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The day starts with a short walk along a road and across a bridge. You then climb uphill through farms and small traditional villages, which are more authentic and different from the ones you have seen before. No heavy winter gear is needed todayâ€”just a couple of t-shirts will be enough. Near the top, enjoy the stunning views of the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri mountains from Ghorepani.<br></p><div><b></b></div><div><b>\r\n\r\nAccommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening&nbsp;</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 150 m. 5 hours  walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>', 13, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-11 14:44:08'),
(2266, 195, '14', NULL, 'Ghorepani â€“ Poonhil (3210 m) Phulbari (3000 m) â€“ Mohare Danda (3030 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To catch the sunrise from Poon Hill, you start with a steep climb of around one hour early in the morning over stone steps. The trail passes through rhododendron forests, away from the busier paths, with stunning views of Annapurna and Dhaulagiri. It then follows the ridge to Mohare Danda community lodge, where you can enjoy views of many peaks, including Annapurna, Machapuchare, Hiunchuli, Mardi Himal, Lamjung Himal, and the towering Dhaulagiri. You also have the option to return to the lodge for breakfast before continuing on to Mohare Danda.<br></p><p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Community lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 700 m. Elevation loss: 274 m. 5 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>', 14, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 16:19:21');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2267, 195, '15', NULL, 'Mohare Danda â€“ Pokhara (850 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After enjoying the sunrise, the trek continues along beautiful ridges with rhododendron and tropical forests, before descending steeply to the village of Ulleri via long stone steps. After lunch in Ulleri, you will take jeeps to Pokhara.<br></p><p></p><p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 3 hours drive</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 1260 m. Elevation loss: 72 m. 3 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>', 15, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 16:19:21'),
(2268, 195, '16', NULL, 'Pokhara - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours.<p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6-7 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>', 16, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-11 16:14:20'),
(2272, 195, '3', NULL, 'Dharapani - Chame (2700 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, we climb to Timang througout the Danaque villages, at the end of the Marsyangdi Gorge. The trail then becomes gentler, passing from pine forests to drier hills. Chame, the largest settlement beyond Besisahar, is the district headquarters of Manang. </p><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 750 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 5 hours  walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<div><div><b></b></div></div><p></p>', 3, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 15:57:56'),
(2273, 195, '4', NULL, 'Chame â€“ Lower Pisang (3200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, the trail follows the Marsyangdi River through pine forests to Bhratang, famous for its apple orchards. The valley then opens up to the impressive Paungda Danda rock face. After crossing a suspension bridge, we climb to Dukur Pokhari (3,240â€¯m) for lunch with spectacular mountain views, before gently descending to Lower Pisang (3,200â€¯m). You can also visit Upper Pisang to see its monastery and enjoy broader views. This stage combines forested paths, river scenery, and dramatic mountain landscapes.<br></p><div><div><b>&nbsp;Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>&nbsp;Elevation gain: 830 m. Elevation loss: 350 m. 6 hours  walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 4, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 15:57:56'),
(2274, 195, '5', NULL, 'Pisang - Ghyaru (3720) - Tibetan village of Ngawal (3661 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today is one of the most scenic days. We climb steeply to Ghyaru, a small Tibetan village at 3,720â€¯m, with amazing mountain views and traditional stone houses. From Ghyaru, the trail crosses open hills to Ngawal (3,661â€¯m), a larger village with a beautiful monastery and ancient stone buildings. This quieter route offers great scenery and helps your body acclimatise before we continue to Manang.<br></p><div><b>&nbsp;Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 685 m. Elevation loss: 217 m. 6 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 5, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 15:57:56'),
(2276, 195, '7', NULL, 'Ice Lake (4610 m) (Kicho Tal): Panorama of the Annapurnas/Rest and acclimatization day in Manang', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From Braga or the small village of Manang, the trail climbs steeply through alpine meadows. The high altitude and rough terrain can make the path challenging. The main highlight is a glacier lake with clear turquoise water reflecting the surrounding peaks, with views of Gangapurna and the Annapurna range, including Annapurna II, III, and IV. For an easier option, Gangapurna Lake is shorter to reach and ideal for a quick visit or acclimatisation. Alternatively, you can choose to rest in Manang to recover and prepare for the next stage of the trek.<br></p><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 1100 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 7 hours walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 15:57:57'),
(2279, 195, '10', NULL, 'Shree Kharka - Thorong Phedi (4500m) At the bottom of Thorong La', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nToday, the trail gradually climbs through alpine meadows and barren landscapes. This less-travelled route from Manang to Thorong Phedi offers a quieter and more scenic alternative. Trekking through rugged high-altitude terrain, you will enjoy beautiful views of the Annapurna range and the Marsyangdi Valley, making it a peaceful and less crowded option compared to the main Annapurna Circuit route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1180 m. Elevation loss: 715 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 10, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-11 17:46:04'),
(2280, 195, '11', NULL, 'Thorung Phedi - Thorong La pass (5416 m) - Muktinath (3760 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Starting very early, you climb steadily to Thorong La Pass at 5,416â€¯m, one of the highest trekking passes in the world. At the top, you will see colourful prayer flags, a Buddhist stupa, and stones left by trekkers. Take a break to enjoy the amazing views of snowy mountains and valleys. After the pass, the trail goes down sharply to Chabarbu, passing meadows and a deep gorge, then rises a little before reaching Muktinath. Muktinath is a sacred place for Buddhists and Hindus, known for its old temple and natural springs. It is a tough but very special day.<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 912 m. Elevation loss: 1691m. 8 hours  walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b><br></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-10 16:19:21'),
(2281, 195, '12', NULL, 'Muktinath - Lupra (3000 m) â€“ Drive to Tatopani  (1200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<div>Today is an important day as you spend the morning near Mount Dhaulagiri. After leaving Muktinath, the trail goes to the small, old village of Lupra, away from the main road. This area has some of the last BÃ¶n monasteries, an ancient religion before Buddhism. To reach Lupra, you go down a steep path into a riverbed. From there, you take a three-hour jeep ride to Tatopani, a busy town by the Kali Gandaki River. Tatopani means â€œhot waterâ€ in Nepali because of its natural hot springs, where you can relax for a small feeâ€”donâ€™t forget your swimming gear!<br></div><div><br></div><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Transport : 3 hours drive.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 4 hours walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p><p></p>', 12, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-11 17:46:04'),
(2286, 195, '17', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p><div><div>\r\n\r\n<p></p><p></p> </div></div>', 17, '2024-09-05 13:28:07', '2025-12-11 16:27:14'),
(2287, 194, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu 1350m. Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-12-16 16:22:28'),
(2288, 194, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ramechhap - Lukla (2860 m) - Phakding (2610 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Early morning from Kathmandu, departure (approximately 2:00\r\nAM) to Ramechhap Airport, where breakfast will be provided prior to your\r\nscheduled flight to Lukla. This scenic flight, which is strictly\r\nweather-dependent, offers passengers spectacular aerial vistas of the Himalayan\r\nmountain range. Upon arrival at Lukla Airport, our team will assist with the\r\nproper distribution of equipment and supplies among the porters and Sherpa\r\nstaff before formally commencing the trekking expedition..</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon arrival in Lukla, your trek will commence with a scenic\r\njourney to Phakding. Along the way, you will traverse iconic suspension\r\nbridges, pass through charming traditional villages, and immerse yourself in\r\nthe regionâ€™s&nbsp; beautiful natural landscapes. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Note:</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><i>Due to potential congestion at Kathmandu Airport, the\r\nCivil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN) may mandate that all flights to Lukla\r\noperate either from Kathmandu Airport or from Ramechhap Airport.</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p><i>In the event that the flight is canceled due to adverse\r\nweather conditions, it will be rescheduled for the following day. An additional\r\nnightâ€™s accommodation will be provided either in Kathmandu or Ramechhap,\r\ndepending on the point of departure.</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transfer : 4 hours drive by jeep (Ramechhap), 25 minutes flight (Lukla).</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m . Elevation loss : 450 m . 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-10-16 18:51:19'),
(2289, 194, '3', NULL, 'Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3440 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The day begins with a pleasant walk through pine forest\r\nalong the river, followed by a short climb out of a narrow gorge. After passing\r\nthe entrance to Khumbu National Park, where permits are checked, we descend to\r\ncross the river on a suspension bridge. The trail continues through a wooded\r\nvalley, crossing the river again before reaching a confluence from Thame and\r\nthe Khumbu. A final crossing on a high suspension bridge marks the start of a\r\nchallenging 1.5-hour ascent to Namche Bazaar, with our first views of Everest\r\nmidway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon arrival, we check into a local lodge. Once a quiet\r\nvillage, Namche has evolved into a bustling trekking hub, offering a mix of\r\ntradition and modernityâ€”complete with bakeries, cafÃ©s, pubs, and other comforts\r\nbrought back by well-traveled Sherpas.<b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m&nbsp; Elevation loss : 409 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2290, 194, '4', NULL, 'Day Excursion, Everest View Point -Khumjung 4000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today is a well-deserved rest day to acclimatize and enjoy\r\nthe surroundings. For those inclined, a hike to the Everest View Hotel (3,880\r\nm) offers stunning panoramic views of the Himalayas. Alternatively, you may\r\nchoose to explore Namche Bazaarâ€”relax in a local cafÃ©, browse the lively market\r\nfor unique items, or visit the Sherpa Museum to gain insight into local\r\nculture. The day concludes with an overnight stay in this iconic mountain\r\nvillage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon\r\nevening</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2291, 194, '5', NULL, 'Namche Bazaar - Thame (3750m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we climb above Namche Bazaar, following a\r\nscenic trail that gently contours the ridgeline while tracing the course of the\r\nBhote Khosi River. This picturesque route leads us through the tranquil\r\nvillages of Phurte, Thamo, Thomde, and Somde, beneath forest canopies of oak,\r\nbirch, and juniper. Along the way, we pass beautifully crafted mani wallsâ€”stone\r\ntablets intricately inscribed with Tibetan prayersâ€”silent yet powerful symbols\r\nof the regionâ€™s deep spiritual roots.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As we leave the main Everest trail behind, the peacefulness\r\nof this less-travelled valley becomes immediately apparent, offering a welcome\r\ncontrast to the busier paths from Lukla. After approximately three to four\r\nhours of walking, we reach a dramatic suspension bridge stretched high above\r\nthe river. From here, the trail ascends steadily to the village of Thame,\r\nstrategically located at the historic junction of trading routes from Rolwaling\r\nvia the Tasi Labcha Pass and from Tibet via the Nangpa La.<b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 520 M Elevation loss: 235 m 5/6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2292, 194, '6', NULL, 'Thame - Lungden (4,500m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Todayâ€™s journey leads you through picturesque villages,\r\nshowcasing breathtaking views of the surrounding landscape, lush vegetation,\r\nand towering mountains. Bathed in crisp morning light, the scenery transforms\r\ninto a dreamlike panorama, vividly illuminated rocks, colorful lichens, grazing\r\nyaks, and snow-capped peaks. While Taranga marks the valleyâ€™s final village,\r\nthe trek continues to Marulung (4,200m) and onward to Lungden, todayâ€™s\r\ndestination. If time allows, you may explore Nakpa Valley, a historic trade\r\nroute to Tibet, or take a short hike to the stunning Cho Relmo Lake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 640 m Elevation loss: 0 m 4/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2293, 194, '7', NULL, 'Lungden - Renjola Pass (5360 m) - Gokyo Lake (4800m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Now well acclimatised, we begin this long yet magnificent\r\nday with confidence and serenity. From the pass, a breathtaking panorama\r\nunfolds â€” a chain of the worldâ€™s highest summits, including Everest, Makalu,\r\nand Pumori, stretches to the east, while the turquoise waters of Lake Gokyo\r\nshimmer far below. Towering nearby is the imposing south face of Cho Oyu. We\r\nthen descend toward the Gokyo Glacier, which we must traverse before reaching\r\nthe tranquil shores of the lake that shares its name.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1100 m Elevation loss: 600 m 7/8 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2294, 194, '8', NULL, 'Gokyo - Gokyo Peak  (5357 m) - Thangnak (4,700m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After summiting Gokyo Peak, we resume our trek by navigating\r\nthe rugged terrain alongside the Ngozumpa Glacier. The trail presents a mix of\r\nascents and descents â€” demanding yet deeply rewarding. As we descend into the\r\nvalley, following the eastern glacial moraine, the dramatic alpine scenery\r\nkeeps our spirits high. By afternoon, we arrive in Thangnak, a quiet cluster of\r\nlodges nestled at the foot of the Cho La Pass â€” an ideal spot to rest and\r\nprepare for the challenging crossing ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 790 m or 210 m. Elevation loss: 900 m or 300 m.</b><br><b>walking: 2 hours 15 minutes (without Gokyo Peak), 5 hours 30 minutes (including)</b></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-10-16 18:51:20'),
(2295, 194, '9', NULL, 'Thangnak - Cho La Pass (5420m) - Dzongla (4,855m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>An early morning starts for the long and challenging day\r\nahead, crossing the Cho La Pass. As we approach the pass, we navigate a vast\r\nboulder field, remnants of an ancient moraine. The ascent becomes steeper in\r\nsections and may require some light scrambling. From the top, we\'re rewarded\r\nwith spectacular views, including a striking perspective of Ama Dablam from the\r\nnorthwest. Continuing down to the grazing pastures below, the trail gradually\r\nbecomes clearer as we make our way to our overnight stop at Dzongla </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 300 m Elevation loss: 200 m 2/4 hours walking.</b><br><br></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2296, 194, '10', NULL, 'Lobuche â€“ Kalpathar (5644 m) - Gorasheep (5,164M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trek from Lobuche to Kala Patthar and onward to\r\nGorakshep offers one of the most breathtaking journeys through the Everest\r\nregionâ€™s stunning landscapes. Departing from Lobuche, trekkers follow a trail\r\nalong the Khumbu Glacier, navigating glacial moraines and rugged terrain as\r\nthey ascend to Gorakshep, the last settlement before Everest Base Camp and a\r\nkey stop for both trekkers and climbers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 825 m. Elevation loss:545 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 10, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2297, 194, '11', NULL, 'Gorasheep  - Everest Base Camp (5364 m) - Lobuche (4,940 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trek from Gorakshep to Everest Base Camp covers\r\napproximately 3 km across the rugged terrain of the Khumbu Glacier. Although\r\nbrief, this walk is profoundly rewarding, with the excitement of reaching\r\nEverest Base Camp, fuelling trekkers through the rocky and challenging\r\nlandscape. After spending time at the base camp, hikers return along the same\r\nroute to Gorakshep, savouring the spectacular scenery and lasting memories.\r\nAfter lunch at Gorakshep direction to Lobuche.<b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 205 m. Elevation loss : 424 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2298, 194, '12', NULL, 'Lobuche - Kongma La Pass (5,535m)- Chhukung (4,730m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>From Lobuche, we cross the slow-moving Khumbu Glacier,\r\nfollowing a well-marked trail over moraine. A steep ascent leads us to Kongma\r\nLa (5,535m), first through grassy slopes and then zigzagging up a scree path.\r\nThe final stretch is more level, traversing boulders to the prayer-flag-lined\r\nsummit. The panoramic views are stunningâ€”Everest, the Lhotse-Nuptse wall,\r\nMakalu, Cho Oyu, and distant Tibetan peaks. Descending past a usually frozen\r\nlake, we enter the beautiful Imja Valley. After a final steep descent, we reach\r\nDingboche (4,410m), a Sherpa village nestled below Ama Dablam and the south\r\nface of Lhotse.<b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 670 m. Elevation loss : 1250 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 12, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:44'),
(2299, 194, '13', NULL, 'Chukhung - Island Peak Base Camp (5100 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>From Chhukhung, we follow a gentle trail through the upper\r\nImja Valley, with stunning views of Lhotse and Ama Dablam behind us. The route\r\nwinds past glacial moraines and open alpine terrain as we approach Island Peak\r\nBase Camp (around 5,100m). The hike is not too strenuous, allowing us to\r\nconserve energy and continue acclimatizing in preparation for the climb ahead. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the afternoon, your mountain guide will provide a full\r\nbriefing, including technical training and essential safety procedures, to\r\nprepare you for tomorrowâ€™s summit push.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 390 m. Elevation loss : m. 3/4 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 13, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:45'),
(2300, 194, '14', NULL, 'Island Peak Base Camp - Summit of Island Peak (6189 m) - Back to Chhukung', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We start our summit push from base camp around 2 a.m.,\r\nclimbing slowly under the stars. The initial trail is gradual, leading to a\r\nsteep scree slope that takes us up to about 5,800. From here, we reach the\r\nglacier, crevassed but manageable, where we gear up with crampons and\r\nharnesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A steady climb brings us above 6,000 meters, followed by the\r\nmost technical section: a 130-meter ice and snow slope angled at 60â€“70 degrees,\r\ndepending on conditions. Using fixed ropes, we ascend to the exposed summit\r\nridge, where the dramatic face of Lhotse comes into view. Following the ridge\r\ncarefully, we make the final steps to the summit of Island Peakâ€”surrounded by a\r\nbreathtaking amphitheatre of Himalayan giants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After enjoying the views and capturing the moment, we\r\ndescend the same route, return to base camp, and continue down to Chhukhung for\r\na well-earned rest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1060 m. Elevation loss : m. 811 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></p><p></p>', 14, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:45'),
(2301, 194, '15', NULL, 'Chhukung - Tengboche (3,855m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We enjoy a beautiful descent into the Khumbu Valley, winding\r\nbeneath the majestic slopes of Ama Dablam. Passing through the permanent\r\nsettlement of Dingboche, where farming is part of daily life, we gradually\r\nre-enter forested terrain. We pause in Pangboche, with Ama Dablam still\r\ndominating the skyline, before continuing to Tengboche, where we spend the\r\nnight near its iconic monastery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :100  m Elevation loss: 1000 m 6/7 hours walking.</b><br><br></p><p></p>', 15, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:45'),
(2302, 194, '16', NULL, 'Tengboche - Namche Bazaar', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>From Tengboche, downhill through lush rhododendron and\r\npine forests, often accompanied by the sounds of prayer wheels and birdsong.\r\nThe trail drops steeply to the Dudh Koshi River, which we cross via a\r\nsuspension bridge. After the crossing, we begin a steady ascent along a\r\nwell-trodden path, gradually climbing through the forest. As we approach Namche\r\nBazaar, glimpses of Everest and surrounding peaks reappear. The trail flattens\r\nout as we reach the vibrant Sherpa town of Namche, where we settle in for the\r\nnight amid shops, bakeries, and a welcome return to relative comfort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, afternoon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 420 m Elevation loss: 420.  5/6  hours  walking.</b></p><p></p>', 16, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-08-27 21:19:45'),
(2303, 194, '17', NULL, 'Namche â€“Lukla', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trek from Namche to Lukapa retraces the same scenic\r\nroute taken on the ascent. we share our final moments with the portersâ€”a\r\nmeaningful time to reflect on the journey and celebrate the experiences weâ€™ve\r\nshared together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 600 m . Elevation loss : 1180 m . 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 17, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-07-30 19:17:43'),
(2304, 194, '18', NULL, 'flight from Lukla â€“Ramechap and drive to Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Begin the day with an early morning flight from Lukla to\r\nRamechhap, offering final views of the Himalayas. From there, enjoy a scenic\r\ndrive back to Kathmandu. The rest of the day is free to relax, explore, and\r\nshop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Transfer : 30 minutes flight (Ramechhap), 4/5 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b></p><p></p>', 18, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-10-16 18:51:20'),
(2305, 194, '19', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 19, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-12-16 16:22:28'),
(2306, 194, '20', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 20, '2024-09-05 21:17:33', '2025-12-16 16:22:28'),
(2353, 131, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-09-09 17:13:15', '2025-12-12 16:11:37'),
(2354, 131, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ramechhap - Lukla (2860 m) - Phakding (2610 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast, we drive to Ramechhap, which takes about 4 to 5 hours\r\ndepending on traffic. From Ramechhap, you take a short flight to Lukla, the main gateway to the\r\nEverest region. The trek starts from Lukla with a gentle walk\r\nthrough forests, over suspension bridges, and past Sherpa villages. After 3 to\r\n4 hours, you reach Phakding, a riverside village and the first overnight stop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><i>Note: Flights to Lukla may be from Kathmandu\r\nor Ramechhap Airport due to airport congestion. If flight is cancelled\r\nbecause of bad weather, it will be rescheduled for the next day, and an extra\r\nnightâ€™s stay will be provided in Kathmandu or Ramechhap.</i></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><i></i></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : \r\n\r\n<b></b>4/5 hours drive (Ramechhap),&nbsp;25 minutes flight (Lukla).&nbsp;</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m . Elevation loss : 450 m . 3/4 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-09-09 17:22:03', '2025-12-18 18:49:12'),
(2355, 131, '3', NULL, 'Trek from Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3440 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p><p>Today, we start with a pleasant walk through a\r\npine forest along the river, followed by a short climb out of a narrow gorge. The permits are checked before entering into the Khumbu National Park entrance, then we\r\ncross the river on a suspension bridge. The trail goes through a wooded valley\r\nand crosses the river again before reaching the meeting point of the Thame and\r\nKhumbu rivers. A final high suspension bridge (Hillary Bridge) marks the start of a 1.5h climb to Namche Bazaar, with our first views of Everest on the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On arrival, we stay in a local lodge. Namche,\r\nonce a quiet village, is now a busy trekking hub with bakeries, cafÃ©s, pubs and other comforts brought back by well-travelled Sherpas.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m. Elevation loss : 409 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-09-09 17:22:03', '2025-12-18 18:49:12'),
(2356, 131, '4', NULL, 'Day Excursion, Everest View Point -Khumjung (4000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p><p>Today is the rest day to acclimatise and enjoy\r\nthe area. This is also to hike to the Everest View Hotel (3,880 m) for beautiful views\r\nof the Himalaya.You can also explore Namche Bazaarâ€”relax in a cafÃ©, browse the\r\nmarket, or visit the Sherpa Museum to learn about local culture. We spend the two night in this famous mountain village.</p><p><b>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 680 m. Elevation loss : 680 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-09-09 17:22:03', '2025-12-18 18:49:12'),
(2357, 131, '5', NULL, 'Namche Bazaar â€“ Tengbuche (3860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, enjoy a short climb and stay along a well-maintained trail, built with tourist donations, giving the feel of walking on a natural balcony. You then descend through pine forests and cross the Dudh Koshi River via suspension bridges. At Phunki Thenga, the trail rises steeply through rhododendron and pine trees. The day ends in the peaceful village of Tengboche, surrounded by breathtaking natural scenery, from Tengboche.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b></b><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 921 m. Elevation loss : 700 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-09-09 17:31:22', '2025-12-18 19:42:14'),
(2358, 131, '6', NULL, 'Tengbuche â€“Dingbuche (4410 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nA perfect day following the <strong></strong>Hillary Trail. Walk through lush forests and descend to the Imja River and cross it. Then gently ascend toward Dingboche; the climb is easy because it is not steep. Pass Pangboche village&nbsp;with views of Ama Dablam and Himalayan peaks. End the day in Dingboche with a warm welcome.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<br></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 550 m . Elevation loss : 273 m. 6 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-09-09 17:31:22', '2025-12-18 19:42:14'),
(2359, 131, '8', NULL, 'Dingbuche â€“Lobuche (4900 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nToday, we continue with an easy ascent toward Thukla. After a short break, we climb for about an hour on a good trail to reach Thukla Pass, where the Everest Memorial honours climbers who lost their lives. From here, the trail becomes less steep as we head toward Lobuche, one of the more challenging sections of the trek. \r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 530 m. Elevation loss : 00 m. 5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-09-09 17:31:22', '2025-12-18 19:42:14'),
(2360, 131, '9', NULL, 'lobuche â€“ Kalpathar (5644 m) - Gorasheep (5,164M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nIn the morning, the trek <strong></strong>starts on a gentle trail. After half an hour, it passes through rocky terrain and glacial moraines. You see Everest, Lhotse, Nuptse, Ama Dablam, Pumori, Lingtren, and Lobuche Peak. We reach Gorakshep, the last lodge before Everest Base Camp, for lunch and rest. Then we hike to Kala Patthar, where you enjoy close-up views of Everest and surrounding peaks. The day ends with a descent back to Gorakshep, one of the trekâ€™s most memorable experiences.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 825 m. Elevation loss :545 m. 67 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-09-09 17:31:22', '2025-12-18 19:42:14'),
(2361, 131, '10', NULL, 'Goraksheep  - Everest Base Camp (5364 m) - Lobuche (4,940 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nToday, we trek to Everest Base Camp, covering about 3 km across the rugged Khumbu Glacier. Although short, the walk is highly rewarding, with the excitement of reaching Everest Base Camp carrying you through the rocky terrain. After spending time at the base camp, we return to Gorakshep, enjoying the spectacular scenery. Following lunch at Gorakshep, we continue toward Lobuche.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 205 m. Elevation loss : 424 m. 6/7 hours  walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 10, '2024-09-09 17:35:57', '2025-12-18 19:52:43'),
(2362, 131, '11', NULL, 'Lobuche â€“Tengbuche (3,860 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b>\r\n\r\n</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>\r\n\r\nToday, we retrace much of the route, enjoying familiar landscapes and mountain views. We follow the same path as before, skipping the Dingboche section and taking the Pheriche section instead, which shortens the trek while still letting you experience the beauty of the Khumbu Valley. This offers a relaxed pace and plenty of time to take in the scenery along the way.\r\n\r\n</p><p><strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 90 m . Elevation loss : 1120 m. 8 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-09-09 17:35:57', '2025-12-18 19:52:43'),
(2363, 131, '12', NULL, 'Tengbuche - Namche', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe retrace the entire route, but the stretch between Kyangjuma and Namche never seems long enough to fully enjoy the scenery.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 700 m. Elevation loss : 921 m. 5/6 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></p><p></p>', 12, '2024-09-09 17:35:57', '2025-12-18 20:24:55'),
(2364, 131, '13', NULL, 'Namche â€“Lukla', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe trail from <strong></strong>Namche to Lukla is the same as before. As itâ€™s the last night, itâ€™s the perfect time to thank the porters and assistant guides for their support. Most treks end with dancing, drinks, and celebrations, sharing memories together as a group.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 600 m . Elevation loss : 1180 m . 67 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 13, '2024-09-09 17:35:57', '2025-12-18 20:24:55'),
(2365, 131, '14', NULL, 'flight from Lukla â€“Ramechap and drive to Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe day starts with morning flight to Ramechhap, offering final views of the Himalayas. From there, we enjoy a scenic drive back to Kathmandu. The rest of the day is free to relax, explore, or shop.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning afternoon.</b><br><b>Transport :30 minutes flight (Ramechhap), 4/5 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu)</b></p><p></p>', 14, '2024-09-09 17:35:57', '2025-12-18 20:24:55'),
(2366, 131, '15', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 15, '2024-09-09 17:35:57', '2025-12-18 20:24:55'),
(2367, 131, '16', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onwards journey.\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>', 16, '2024-09-09 17:35:57', '2025-12-18 20:24:55'),
(2370, 199, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-09-09 17:56:04', '2025-12-16 15:51:01'),
(2371, 199, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Dhunche (1965 M)- Syabru Besi (1460 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, the journey to&nbsp;&nbsp;Dhunche&nbsp;is a scenic drive through hills, forests and riverside villages. From Dhunche, the road descends for about 1â€“2 hours to reach Syabru Besi, a small town that serves as the gateway to the Langtang Valley trek.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Syabru Besi).</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-09-09 17:56:04', '2025-10-18 13:10:05'),
(2372, 199, '3', NULL, 'Syabru Besi - Lama Hotel (2460 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast the day starts with a trail that winds\r\nthrough landslide-prone areas, featuring several ascents and descents. This\r\nsection ends at a suspension bridge crossing the Langtang Khola. After crossing\r\nanother new river again, we make a steep climb to Rimche (2,250m), followed by\r\na gentle descent to Changtangâ€”commonly known as \"Lama Hotel\", named\r\nafter the first lodge established in the area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1174 m . Elevation loss :175 m. 6 hours\r\nwalking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-09-09 18:02:00', '2025-07-12 21:26:04'),
(2373, 199, '4', NULL, 'Lama Hotel â€“ Ghora Tabela - Langtang village (3430 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trail from Lama Hotel climbs steadily through lush\r\nforests of oak, maple and rhododendron, gradually opening to views of\r\nsnow-capped peaks. After about two hours, you reach Ghora Tabela, with wide\r\nviews of the Langtang Himal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From there, the valley widens as you pass yak pastures,\r\nTamang village, mani walls and prayer wheels. The landscape becomes more\r\nalpine, leading to Langtang Village, a traditional Tamang settlement set\r\nbeneath towering cliffs and glacial peaks.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1015 m. Elevation loss: 80 m  6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-09-09 18:02:00', '2025-07-20 16:46:58'),
(2374, 199, '5', NULL, 'Langtang village â€“ Kyangjin (3870 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today is the easy and good trial, the trail reaches a ridge with a\r\nlarge chorten and prayer wall, passing the main settlement before descending to\r\nKyanjinâ€™s lodges and cheese factory. In the afternoon, you can hike Kyanjin Ri\r\nfor beautiful mountain views or explore the gently rising Langtang Valley toward\r\nthe yak pastures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation\r\ngain: 450 m. 3 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-09-09 18:02:00', '2025-08-27 20:01:39'),
(2375, 199, '6', NULL, 'Ascent of Tsergo Ri (4984 M ) or Discover of the Langtang Valley', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, you can choose between two options. If you\'re up for a challenge, hike up to Tsergo Ri. It\'s a steep climb, but the views of Langtang Lirung, Yala Peak and the Himalayas from the top are amazing. For an easier day, explore the Langtang Valley. Walk through yak pastures, visit local Tamang villages and enjoy beautiful mountain and glacier views. Itâ€™s a great way to relax and experience the local culture.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1105 m. Elevation loss: 1105 meters. 7/8 hours Walking.</b></p><p></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-09-09 18:02:00', '2025-08-27 20:01:39'),
(2376, 199, '7', NULL, 'Kyjangjin Gompa - Lama Hotel (2470m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We retrace our steps back through the Langtang Valley. The\r\ndownhill walk is easier and offers a different perspective of the landscapes we\r\npassed on the way up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain : 100 m. Elevation loss : 1500 m. 6/7\r\nhours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-09-09 18:07:59', '2025-07-12 21:26:05'),
(2377, 199, '8', NULL, 'Lama Hotel - Thulo Syabru (2130 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We follow the same trail back down through the Langtang\r\nValley. The descent is more relaxed and reveals new angles of the scenery we\r\npreviously climbed through.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Elevation gain: 760 m . Elevation loss: 940 m. 5/7 hours Walking.</b>.</p><p></p>', 8, '2024-09-09 18:07:59', '2025-08-27 20:01:39'),
(2378, 199, '9', NULL, 'Thulo Shyabru â€“  Sing Gompa (Chandanbari) ( 3,320 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>After breakfast, we trek to Sing Gompa, a steady uphill walk through beautiful forests of pine and rhododendron. Along the way, youâ€™ll get views of Ganesh Himal and the Langtang range. After a few hours of climbing, you reach Sing Gompa, a peaceful village known for its monastery and local cheese factory.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1,230 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-09-09 18:07:59', '2025-08-27 20:01:39'),
(2379, 199, '10', NULL, 'Sing Gompa - Gosainkunda Lake (4,380m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, the trial is a gradual but steady climb through alpine forests and rugged hills. As you gain height, the views open up to the Langtang and Ganesh Himal ranges. The trail passes small lodges and shrines before reaching the sacred Gosainkunda Lake, a beautiful high-altitude lake surrounded by snow-capped peaks. It\'s an important pilgrimage site for both Hindus and Buddhists.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1050 m.\r\nElevation loss:20 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 10, '2024-09-09 18:07:59', '2025-08-27 20:01:39'),
(2380, 199, '11', NULL, 'Gosaikunda - Laurebina Pass (4,610m) -  Ghopte (3,440m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Early in the morning, after breakfast. We climb towards\r\nLaurebina Pass, the entry point to the Helambu region. The rocky, cairn-marked\r\npath passes three tiny lakes and spans moraines. We reach an area with\r\nbeautiful views of the mountains. After passing Surya Kunda, we descend to\r\nPhedi and follow on ups and downspath through the forest to Gopte.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 490\r\nm. Elevation loss: 1490 m. 6 hours walking</b></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-09-09 18:07:59', '2025-08-27 20:01:39'),
(2382, 199, '12', NULL, 'Ghopte - Kutumsang (2470 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we move towards several ups and downs\r\nbefore reaching Thadepati, a key junction where the Helambu trail divides. We\r\ntake the shorter route, passing scenic ridges, rhododendron forests, and Tamang\r\nvillages. After a lunch stop, we continue downhill to Kutumsang.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation\r\ngain: 656 m. Elevation loss: 1580 m. 6/7 hours walking</b></p><p></p>', 12, '2024-09-09 18:15:20', '2025-08-27 20:01:39'),
(2383, 199, '13', NULL, 'Kutumsang - Chisapani (2200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Leaving Kutumsang, the trail winds gracefully through serene\r\nforests, terraced hillsides, and charming Tamang villages that offer glimpses\r\ninto local life. The routeâ€™s gentle ups and downs keep the trek dynamic and\r\nrewarding, with every turn revealing new scenery. As you near Chisapani, the\r\nlandscape opens up to beautiful landscape views of the Langtang and Ganesh Himal\r\nranges, making this section both visually and culturally enriching. This evening, we\r\nshare our final moments with the portersâ€”a meaningful time to reflect on the\r\njourney and celebrate the experiences weâ€™ve shared together.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation\r\ngain: 1095 m. Elevation loss: 1400 m. 6/7 hours walking</b></p><p></p>', 13, '2024-09-09 18:15:20', '2025-08-27 20:01:39'),
(2384, 199, '14', NULL, 'Chisapani - Sundarijal (1460 m) - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After leaving Chisapani, we gently climb to a small pass\r\nbefore descending through the peaceful forests of Shivapuri National Park. The\r\ntrail passes the charming Tamang village of Mulkharka, with terraced fields and\r\ntraditional homes. A final descent brings us to Sundarijal, where we end our\r\ntrek and drive back to Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 2 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 294 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 4 hours walking</b><br></p><p></p>', 14, '2024-09-09 18:15:20', '2025-10-18 13:10:05'),
(2385, 199, '15', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 15, '2024-09-09 18:15:20', '2025-12-16 15:51:01'),
(2386, 199, '16', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 16, '2024-09-09 18:15:20', '2025-12-16 15:51:02'),
(2388, 200, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-12-16 15:53:33'),
(2389, 200, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Dhunche (1965 M) - Syabru Besi (1460 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we drive&nbsp;to Dhunche,&nbsp;through winding mountain roads with scenic views of hills, rivers, and villages. After a short break in Dhunche, the journey continues downhill to Syabru Besi, a small town and the starting point for treks into the Langtang region.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Syabru Besi).</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 2, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-10-18 13:21:25');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2390, 200, '3', NULL, 'Syabru Besi - Lama Hotel (2460 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, the day starts with a trail that winds\r\nthrough landslide-prone areas, featuring several ascents and descents. This\r\nsection ends at a suspension bridge crossing the Langtang Khola. After crossing\r\nanother new river again, we make a steep climb to Rimche (2,250m), followed by\r\na gentle descent to Changtangâ€”commonly known as \"Lama Hotel\", named\r\nafter the first lodge established in the area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1174 m .\r\nElevation loss : 175 m . 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-07-20 15:34:31'),
(2391, 200, '4', NULL, 'Lama Hotel â€“ Ghora Tabela - Langtang village (3430 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trail from Lama Hotel climbs steadily through lush\r\nforests of oak, maple and rhododendron, gradually opening to views of\r\nsnow-capped peaks. After about two hours, you reach Ghora Tabela, with wide\r\nviews of the Langtang Himal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From there, the valley widens as you pass yak pastures,\r\nTamang village, mani walls and prayer wheels. The landscape becomes more\r\nalpine, leading to Langtang Village, a traditional Tamang settlement set\r\nbeneath towering cliffs and glacial peaks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1015 m. Elevation\r\nloss: 80 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-07-20 15:34:31'),
(2392, 200, '5', NULL, 'Langtang village â€“ Kyangjin (3870 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today the trial is easy and short, the trail reaches a ridge with a\r\nlarge chorten and prayer wall, passing the main settlement before descending to\r\nKyanjinâ€™s lodges and cheese factory. In the afternoon, you can hike Kyanjin Ri\r\nfor&nbsp; beautiful mountain views or explore the gently rising Langtang Valley toward\r\nthe yak pastures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 450 m. 3 hours\r\nwalking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-07-20 15:34:31'),
(2393, 200, '6', NULL, 'Ascent of Tsergo Ri (4984 M ) or Discover of the Langtang Valley', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today is the best and hardest day, so you can choose to hike\r\nup Tsergo Ri or spend the day exploring the upper Langtang Valley. From Tsergo\r\nRiâ€™s wide, rounded summit, youâ€™ll enjoy landscape views of Langtang Lirung\r\n(7,246 m), Naya Kanga (5,846 m), Dorje Lakpa (6,966 m), Langshisa Ri (6,427 m),\r\nGanchenpo (6,378 m) and distant Shishapangma (8,013 m). Itâ€™s a rewarding\r\nfull-day trekâ€”challenging mainly due to the altitude, as the trail itself is\r\ngenerally manageable, except for the rocky section near the summit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1105 m.\r\nElevation loss: 1105 meters. 7/8 hours Walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-07-20 15:34:31'),
(2394, 200, '7', NULL, 'Kyjangjin Gompa - Lama Hotel (2470m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We retrace our steps back through the Langtang Valley. The\r\ndownhill walk is easier and offers a different perspective of the landscapes we\r\npassed on the way up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain : 100 m.\r\nElevation loss : 1500 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-07-12 21:15:02'),
(2395, 200, '8', NULL, 'Lama Hotel - Thulo Syabru (2130 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We follow the same trail back down through the Langtang\r\nValley. The descent is more relaxed and reveals new angles of the scenery we\r\npreviously climbed through.This evening, we share our final moments with\r\nthe portersâ€”a meaningful time to reflect on the journey and celebrate the\r\nexperiences weâ€™ve shared together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 760 m . Elevation loss: 940 m. 5/7 hours\r\nWalking</b></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-08-27 19:55:21'),
(2396, 200, '9', NULL, 'Thulo Shyabru â€“  Dunche- Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Starting\r\nyour day from Thulo Shyabru, you trek downhill through beautiful forests and\r\ntraditional villages to reach Dunche, the administrative center of Rasuwa\r\nDistrict. After arriving in Dunche, redrive to Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nTransport : 6 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-09-09 21:17:00', '2025-10-18 13:21:25'),
(2397, 202, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Your happy holiday starts in Kathmandu. You will have time to freshen up before briefing with guide in the late afternoon. According to the time, you can walk/drive to Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) and from here watch your first Nepali sunset over the Kathmandu Valley, from the oldest stupas. This is one of the most Important world heritage sites of Nepal and an important center for Buddhism in Nepal.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-10-17 13:38:23'),
(2398, 202, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Pashupatinath Temple â€“ Patan â€“ Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>&nbsp;Today, we visit the holy Pashupatinath Temple, a renowned Hindu shrine on the banks\r\nof the Bagmati River, first thing in the morning. There, you can respectfully observe spiritual ceremonies and cremation\r\nceremonies. Then, drive a short distance to Patan, a city rich in history and\r\nart, to explore the Patan Durbar Square, which is home to the Golden Temple,\r\nthe Krishna Mandir and beautifully carved temples (Approx. 9km from\r\nPashupatinath). In the afternoon, head back to Kathmandu after exploring the\r\nlocal handicraft stores.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>', 2, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2399, 202, '3', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Bhaktapur â€“ Panauti â€“ Balthali', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Start your\r\nday in Bhaktapur (Approx. 15km from Kathmandu), which is known for its ancient\r\nart and architecture and is a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Discover Nepal\'s rich\r\npast by touring the 55-Window Palace, Nyatapola Temple, and the lively Pottery\r\nSquare. Proceed to Panauti (Approx. 19km from Bhaktapur), a tranquil Newari\r\ntown filled with spiritual attractions. Check out the ancient Indreshwor\r\nMahadev Temple, renowned for its golden pinnacle and elaborate wood carvings.\r\nFinish with a lovely 1.5â€“2 hour hike from Khopasi to Balthali Village (Approx.\r\n6km from Panauti), a peaceful haven encircled by terraced fields and lush\r\nforests that provides amazing views of the foothills of the Himalayas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>', 3, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2400, 202, '4', NULL, 'Balthali â€“ Namobuddha â€“ Dhulikhel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we start a day with a scenic hike from Khopasi to Namobuddha (Approx. 10km\r\nfrom Balthali), passing through terraced fields and traditional villages. Visit\r\nthe sacred Namobuddha Monastery and stupa, soak in the peaceful atmosphere, and\r\nobserve monks\' rituals. Enjoy scenic hill views before driving to Dhulikhel\r\n(Approx.11km from Namobuddha). Explore this charming hill town known for Newari\r\narchitecture and Himalayan vistas, with an optional walk to Kali Temple or\r\nsunset viewpoints.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation Gain: 668 m. Elevation loss: 424 m.  2/3 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 4, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2401, 202, '5', NULL, 'Dhulikhel â€“ Kirtipur â€“ Swayambhunath â€“ Bandipur', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>&nbsp;After breakfast, we travel through the lovely Newari lanes and start the day with a drive to\r\nthe tranquil hilltop village of Kirtipur (Approx. 40km from Dhulikhel), where\r\nyou may explore its historic temples, including Bagh Bhairab and Uma Maheshwar.\r\nProceed to the Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) for a blend of Hindu and\r\nBuddhist culture and magnificent views of Kathmandu (Approx. 7km from Kirtipur).\r\nNext, take a leisurely drive to Bandipur (Approx. 170 km from Swayambhunath),\r\narriving by early evening to take in the breathtaking mountain views and the\r\ncity\'s traditional charm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p>', 5, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2402, 202, '6', NULL, 'Bandipur - Ramkot â€“ Bandipur', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we enjoy breakfast in the quaint hill village of Bandipur before\r\nstarting the peaceful ascent to Ramkot. Discover serene villages, terraced\r\nfarms, and lush forests while observing beautiful Himalayan views. Before\r\ndeparting, take some time to explore Ramkot (Approx. 60km from Bandipur), a\r\nsmall Magar village with unique round mud houses; talk with the friendly\r\nlocals; and enjoy the amazing mountain views.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>', 6, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2403, 202, '7', NULL, 'Bandipur - Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>&nbsp;After breakfast, you will Enjoy a pleasant trip through lush terrain and beautiful villages from\r\nBandipur to Pokhara (Approx. 75km from Bandipur). Reach the peaceful splendor\r\nof the Annapurna mountains and Phewa Lake. Enjoy a leisurely afternoon boating\r\non the lake, touring the serene Peace Pagoda or spending time in the lively\r\nlakefront shops and cafÃ©s. You can also take a short hike to the nearby hills\r\nfor scenic views of the surrounding landscapes. As the sun\r\nsets, the sky transforms into a canvas of vibrant colors, creating the perfect\r\nbackdrop for a memorable evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>', 7, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2404, 202, '8', NULL, 'Pokhara - Autrelian camp / Pothana - Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Early in the\r\nmorning, we drive to Kade via Sarangkot in Pokhara. Take a break at Sarangkot,\r\nthen continue our journey to Kade. From there, start climbing through forests\r\nand farmland to reach the charming village of Australian Camp/Pothana. After\r\nexploring the area, return to Kade and drive back to Pokhara. (Approx. 30km\r\nfrom Pokhara). Enjoy the beautiful views of the Annapurna and Machapuchare\r\nmountains while immersing yourself in the welcoming Gurung culture. Return to\r\nPokhara in the afternoon, after unwinding or completing a lovely circuit for the\r\nperfect day of culture and nature.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b><b></b><b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><b></b><br><b>Elevation Gain: 355 m. Elevation loss: 355 m. 2/4 hours  walking</b><b></b><br></p>', 8, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2405, 202, '9', NULL, 'Pokhara â€“ Chitwan national park', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After breakfast, Start your day with a scenic drive from Pokhara to Sauraha, the gateway to\r\nChitwan National Park (Approx. 150km from Pokhara). After checking into a cozy\r\njungle lodge, spend the afternoon exploring a Tharu village to discover local\r\nculture or enjoy a peaceful sunset walk by the Rapti River, spotting crocodiles\r\nand birds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals excluded: morning noon evening</b></p>', 9, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2406, 202, '10', NULL, 'Chitwan national park', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we enjoy a relaxing canoe trip down the Rapti River in the morning, where you\r\ncan see crocodiles and vibrant ducks. Thereafter, take a guided jungle walk\r\nthrough the forest, where you may spot one-horned rhinoceroses, deer, and\r\nmonkeys. Take a jeep safari in the afternoon to see more of the park and\r\npossibly get a look at elusive creatures like Bengal tigers or sloth bears.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning&nbsp; noon evening</b></p>', 10, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2407, 202, '11', NULL, 'Chitwan National Park - Kathmandu -  Visit Boudhanath Stupa', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After enjoying the natural beauty and\r\nwildlife of Chitwan National Park, return to Kathmandu by road (Approx. 200km\r\nfrom Chitwan national park). Upon arrival, head to Boudhanath Stupa, one of the\r\nlargest and most sacred Buddhist sites in Nepal. Spend the afternoon soaking in\r\nthe peaceful atmosphere, walking around the stupa with pilgrims, visiting\r\nnearby monasteries, and enjoying traditional Tibetan food at one of the rooftop\r\ncafes overlooking the stupa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>', 11, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-07-16 16:28:55'),
(2408, 202, '12', NULL, 'Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>According to your flight schedule the\r\ngrand departure. We will come to drive you to the airport.</p>', 12, '2024-09-19 15:20:57', '2025-06-08 19:28:44'),
(2438, 204, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1,350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p><p></p> </div>', 1, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-12-16 15:26:09'),
(2439, 204, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ramechhap - Lukla (2,860 m) - Phakding (2,610 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we drive from Kathmandu to Ramechhap (Manthali Airport), which takes about 4 to 5 hours depending on traffic and road conditions. From Ramechhap, you\'ll board a short 20 minute flight to Lukla, the main gateway to the Everest region. Upon arrival in Lukla, the trek starts with a gradual descent through alpine forests, suspension bridges and charming Sherpa villages. After&nbsp; 3 to 4 hour walk, youâ€™ll reach Phakding, a scenic riverside village and the first overnight stop on the trail toward Everest Base Camp.&nbsp;</p><p>Note:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><i>Due to potential congestion at\r\nKathmandu Airport, the Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN) may mandate\r\nthat all flights to Lukla operate either from Kathmandu Airport or from\r\nRamechhap Airport. </i><i></i></p>\r\n\r\n<p><i>&nbsp;</i><i>In the event that the flight is\r\ncanceled due to adverse weather conditions, it will be rescheduled for the\r\nfollowing day. An additional nightâ€™s accommodation will be provided either in\r\nKathmandu or Ramechhap, depending on the point of departure.</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 25 minutes flight. 4/5 hours drive.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m . Elevation loss : 450 m . 3/4 hours  walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-10-17 13:48:47'),
(2440, 204, '3', NULL, 'Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3,440 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we starts with a\r\npleasant walk through a pine forest along the river, followed by a short climb\r\nout of a narrow gorge. After passing the entrance to Khumbu National Park,\r\nwhere permits are checked, we descend to cross the river on a suspension\r\nbridge. The trail continues through a wooded valley, crossing the river again\r\nbefore reaching a confluence from Thame and the Khumbu. A final crossing on a\r\nhigh suspension bridge marks the start of a challenging 1.5 hours ascent to\r\nNamche Bazaar, with our first views of Everest midway. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon arrival, we check\r\ninto a local lodge. Once a quiet village, Namche has evolved into a bustling\r\ntrekking hub, offering a mix of tradition and modernityâ€”complete with bakeries,\r\ncafÃ©s, pubs, and other comforts brought back by well-traveled Sherpas.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m . Elevation loss : 409 m . 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-08-27 19:16:13'),
(2441, 204, '4', NULL, 'Day Excursion, Everest View Point -Khumjung 4000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>On this day, we take a&nbsp; rest to acclimatize and enjoy the surroundings. For those inclined, a hike to the\r\nEverest View Hotel (3,880 m) offers&nbsp; scenic views of the Himalayas.\r\nAlternatively, you may choose to explore Namche Bazaarâ€”relax in a local cafÃ©,\r\nbrowse the lively market for unique items or visit the Sherpa Museum to gain\r\ninsight into local culture. The day concludes with an overnight stay in this\r\niconic mountain village.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals\r\nincluded: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-08-27 19:16:13'),
(2442, 204, '5', NULL, 'Namche-Phorste (3,800 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we leave Namche Bazaar behind, the trail gently rises above the village,\r\nweaving through terraced fields and fragrant juniper bushes to reach a quiet\r\nridgeline. As you cross a small, prayer-flag-adorned pass, the world opens\r\nupâ€”revealing the majestic Ama Dablam, the \"Matterhorn of the\r\nHimalayas,\" its icy flanks glistening like a jewel in the sunlight. The\r\npath then descends into the serene Sherpa village of Khumjung, where\r\nemerald-green potato fields surround traditional stone houses, and the whispers\r\nof mountain winds carry stories of Everest legends. From here, the trail\r\nmeanders onward to Phortse, a hidden gem clinging to the hillside, where yaks\r\ngraze lazily and the snow-capped giants loom even closer. Each step feels like\r\na quiet conversation with the mountains, as the raw beauty of the Khumbu\r\nunfolds in slow, amazing waves. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:700 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-07-16 15:46:28'),
(2443, 204, '6', NULL, 'Phorste- Machermo (4,400m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>On the sixth day, we&nbsp; ascend into\r\nthe Gokyo Valley with a picturesque hike through a lush rhododendron\r\nforest, where vibrant pink and red blooms (best in spring) line the path\r\nalongside cascading waterfalls glinting in the Himalayan light. The route\r\nfollows the Dudh Koshi River, with suspension bridges adding a sense of\r\nadventure. After 3â€“4 hours of gradual climbing, youâ€™ll reach Machermo,\r\na tranquil Sherpa village with stone-walled lodges and dramatic views of Cho\r\nOyu (8,188m). This spot serves as a critical acclimatization stop before\r\npushing higher into the valley. Tea houses here offer warm garlic soup and cozy\r\nbeds, with the sound of the river lulling trekkers to sleep. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:980 m. Elevation loss: 380 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-08-27 19:16:13'),
(2444, 204, '7', NULL, 'Machermo - Gokyo (4800 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today is a short but scenic journey. The trail gradually ascends through a rugged alpine landscape, following the Dudh Koshi River. Along the way, youâ€™ll pass through small settlements and enjoy beautiful views of snow-capped peaks, including Cho Oyu. As you approach Gokyo, youâ€™ll see the beautiful turquoise lakes that the village is famous for. Gokyo sits beside the third lake, Dudh Pokhari, offering beautiful mountain reflections and a peaceful atmosphere.</p><p><b></b></p><div></div><b>\r\n\r\n</b><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:470 m. Elevation loss: 120 m. 5.5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-08-27 19:16:13'),
(2445, 204, '8', NULL, 'Gokyo - Gokyo Peak 5357 m - Thangnak (4,700m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we summit Gokyo\r\nPeak, we resume our trek by navigating the rugged terrain alongside the\r\nNgozumpa Glacier. The trail presents a mix of ascents and descents â€” demanding\r\nyet deeply rewarding. As we descend into the valley, following the eastern\r\nglacial moraine, the dramatic alpine scenery keeps our spirits high. By\r\nafternoon, we arrive in Thangnak, a quiet cluster of lodges nestled at the foot\r\nof the Cho La Pass â€” an ideal spot to rest and prepare for the challenging\r\ncrossing ahead. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 790 m or 210 m. Elevation loss: 900 m or 300 m.</b><br><b>2 hours 15 minutes (without Gokyo Peak), walking 5 hours 30 minutes (including)</b><br></p><p></p>', 8, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-08-27 19:16:13'),
(2446, 204, '9', NULL, 'Thangnak - Cho La Pass (5420m) - Dzongla (4,855m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today&nbsp; is one of the most challenging and rewarding sections of the Everest region. The journey start early to cross the steep and icy Cho La Pass. The trail involves a tough ascent over rocky terrain and possibly snow or ice, with spectacular views of surrounding peaks. After reaching the pass, you descend carefully on a slippery trail, eventually reaching Dzongla, a small, scenic settlement surrounded by towering mountains. Itâ€™s a demanding but unforgettable day on the trek.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 300 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 2/4 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 9, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-08-27 19:16:13'),
(2447, 204, '11', NULL, 'Lobuche â€“ Kalpathar (5644 m) - Gorasheep (5,164M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b>After breakfast we trek to Gorakshep, the last stop before Everest Base Camp. Then, you make a steep 2â€“3 hour round-trip climb to Kala Patthar for amazing views of Mount Everest and surrounding peaks. Afterward, you return to Gorakshep to rest.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening<br>Elevation gain: 825 m. Elevation loss :545 m. 6/7 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-09-18 12:03:42'),
(2448, 204, '12', NULL, 'Gorasheep - Everest Base Camp (5364 m) - Lobuche (4,940 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b>Today, we&nbsp; trek to Everest Base Camp, where you can explore the famous glacier and expedition camps. After visiting the base camp, you return to Gorakshep for lunch, then descend for about 3 hours back &nbsp;to spend the night.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 205 m. Elevation loss : 424 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 12, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-09-18 12:03:42'),
(2449, 204, '13', NULL, 'Lobuche â€“Tengbuche (3,860 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, the trek involves a gradual descent through varied terrain. Starting at Lobuche, you head down along a rocky trail to reach Dughla (4,620 m), a small settlement near glacial moraines. From there, the path continues downhill to Pheriche (4,280 m), passing through high-altitude alpine terrain. After Pheriche, the trail descends more steeply through rhododendron and pine forests, offering beautiful natural scenery. Finally, you arrive at Tengboche, known for its famous monastery and spectacular views of Everest, Ama Dablam, and surrounding peaks.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 90 m . Elevation loss: 1120 m. 8 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 13, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-09-18 12:03:42'),
(2450, 204, '14', NULL, 'Tengbuche - Namche', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trek from Tengboche\r\nto Namche Bazaar retraces the same scenic route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 700 m. Elevation loss : 921 m. 5/6 hours  walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 14, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-09-18 12:03:42'),
(2451, 204, '15', NULL, 'Namche â€“Lukla', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trek from Namche to\r\nLukapa retraces the same scenic route taken on the ascent. we share our final\r\nmoments with the portersâ€”a meaningful time to reflect on the journey and\r\ncelebrate the experiences weâ€™ve shared together. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 600 m. Elevation loss: 1180 m. 6/7 hours  walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 15, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-09-18 12:03:42'),
(2452, 204, '16', NULL, 'flight from Lukla â€“Ramechap and drive to Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start the day with an\r\nearly morning flight from Lukla to Ramechhap, offering final views of the\r\nHimalayas. From there, enjoy a scenic drive back to Kathmandu. The rest of the\r\nday is free to relax, explore, and shop. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning, afternoon.</b><br><b>Transport : 30 minutes flight. 4/5 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b></p><p></p>', 16, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-10-17 13:48:47'),
(2453, 204, '17', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 17, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-12-16 15:26:09'),
(2454, 204, '18', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 18, '2024-09-19 15:56:43', '2025-12-16 15:26:09'),
(2482, 169, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-12-16 16:19:26'),
(2483, 169, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Ghurmi (574M) -  Patale (2800M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>Early in the morning, drive from\r\nKathmandu to Patale. Following Dulikhel, we progressively descend to the\r\nSunkoshi River and then continue on to Ghurmi. The jeep moves more slowly from\r\nGhurmi to Patale than it did this morning. Dhap / Patale is one of the greatest\r\nplaces to see Mount Everest, Lhotse, Makalu, Kanchenjunga, and a number of\r\nother majestic peaks. As we approach the village, the breathtaking views unfold\r\nbefore us, showcasing the grandeur of the Himalayas and inviting us to explore\r\nthe rich culture and natural beauty that Patale has to offer. of other peaks.\r\nPerfect for photographing the snow-capped mountains in breathtaking golden\r\ntones at day break and sunset.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Transfer : 7/8 hours morning drive (Patale).</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-10-16 18:39:19'),
(2484, 169, '3', NULL, 'Patale - Bung (1800M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We start the day by climbing early to\r\nthe View Point, where we may have a great view of the spectacular mountains,\r\nincluding Mount Everest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Back to the lodge for breakfast, your\r\njeep takes you up to the beautiful Rai village Bung. Visit these beautiful\r\nvillage of Rai, Sherpa and Newar. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Transfer: 4/5 hours by jeep (Bung).</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-10-16 18:39:19'),
(2485, 169, '4', NULL, 'Bung - Khiraule (2550 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We start our journey by climbing\r\nupwards from Bung. Trek through a number of farmlands to arrive in Khiraule. A\r\nlovely view of the valley may be seen from a certain point in the settlement. Significant\r\nvillage in Solukhumbu, one of the oldest Buddhist monasteries in the region and\r\nserene landscapes. Today\'s hike takes you through remote trails, rhododendron\r\nforests, and traditional Rai and Sherpa settlements. After crossing the river,\r\nthe trail ascends gradually through rhododendron forests and terraced field</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 850 m Elevation loss: 10 m. 4/6 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 4, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2486, 169, '5', NULL, 'Khiraule - Chulei (3550M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Todayâ€™s hike takes you deeper into the breathtaking landscapes of Solukhumbu, passing through forests, ridges, and small traditional villages. This trail is less frequented, offering a peaceful and tranquil experience. Along the way, we will pass numerous revered Buddhist stupas and mani walls. Upon reaching Chulei, many magnificent Himalayan ranges will come clearly into view</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1070 m Elevation loss: 50 m. 5 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 5, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2487, 169, '6', NULL, 'CHulei - Chole Kharka  (4240M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>We start our journey with a hike to the summit of Panch Pokhari Hill (4,350 m). This route is ideal for experienced trekkers and those seeking a less-travelled path. From the hilltop, enjoy a breathtaking panorama that includes Mt Khangteka, Brunche Peak, and even the distant Mt Kanchenjunga, especially magical at sunset. We then descend to Panch Pokhari, a sacred lake revered by both Hindus and Buddhists.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 935 m Elevation loss: 250 m. 6 hours hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2488, 169, '7', NULL, 'Chole Kharka  - Kothe (3600M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>As we take in the stunning scenery, we can hear the gentle rustle of the grass in the breeze and the distant calls of wildlife. It\'s the perfect spot to rest, reflect, and appreciate the sheer beauty of our surroundings before we descend to the next part of our adventure. The trail leads through beautiful tropical forests of pine and rhododendron. From there, we make a steep descent into the Hinku Valley. Our first major stop in this region is the village of Kothe. Along the way, enjoy stunning views of Mt Kesharkang (6,300 m), Mt Keriyung, and the vast Mahakulung Valley.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1025 m. Elevation loss: 350 m. 6 hours hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2489, 169, '8', NULL, 'Kothe - Thangnak (4350M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After all permits are verified at the checkpoint, the trail follows the picturesque Hinku Khola River, offering serene views of Kusum Kanguru, Mera Peak, and Charpate before arriving in Thagnak. In this village, climbers often visit a monastery over 200 years old to receive blessings for a successful ascent.</p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 695 m. Elevation loss: 00 m. 6 hours hours walking.</b><br><p></p>', 8, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-14 13:56:28'),
(2490, 169, '10', NULL, 'Thangnak - Khare (5025 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Although relatively short, todayâ€™s\r\ntrek will be demanding due to the significant elevation gain. From Thagnak, the\r\nwell-marked trail ascends steadily, crossing a glacial moraine en route to\r\nKhare. After about half an hour, youâ€™ll reach a cairn-marked high point with\r\nstunning views of a glacial lake. The path then continues upward alongside a\r\nkhola (stream), leading to the open meadow of Dig Kharka before finally\r\narriving at Khare, the last settlement before Mera Peak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 600 m. Elevation loss: 00 m. 6 hours hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 10, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2491, 169, '11', NULL, 'Khare - Rest & Acclimatisation -  Climbing Trainning', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today is a dedicated rest and climbing preparation day.</p><p>According to the time, your guide will lead you for training to practise essential climbing skills and review the safety procedures. Khare also offers several rewarding day hikes. One particularly challenging trail climbs to a ridge, demanding but well worth the effort for the breathtaking panoramic views at the top. Weâ€™ll also take this time to pack our mountain gear and complete final equipment checks.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b></p><p></p>', 11, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2492, 169, '12', NULL, 'Khare - Mera High Camp (5780M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The entire journey is roughly four km,\r\nbut it\'s difficult. It can be a little challenging to get to the glacier this\r\nmorning. Reaching the higher camp requires a lengthy climb up the gently\r\nsloping glacier. Kanchenjunga (8,586 m), Chamlang (7,319 m), Makalu (8,485 m),\r\nBaruntse (7,129 m), Everest (8,848 m), Lhotse (8,516 m), Cho Oyu (8,188 m), and\r\nother peaks exceeding 7,000 and 8,000 meters can be seen from there. This vista\r\nis regarded as one of the most breathtaking in Nepal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 900 m. Elevation loss: 00 m. 4/6 hours hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 12, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2493, 169, '13', NULL, 'High Camp - Mera Summit (6476M) - Khare', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Itâ€™s about 2 km to the summit, which\r\ntakes around 4 to 5 hours of climbing. The group will put on crampons and rope\r\nup before departing for the summit at around 2:00 am. Weâ€™ll start using\r\nheadlights and climb in the dark for about an hour before dawn breaks. The\r\nclimb isnâ€™t technically difficultâ€”you simply keep moving forward, and before\r\nyou know it, youâ€™ll reach the top, where the views are absolutely breathtaking.\r\nThe feeling of accomplishment is indescribable, and the sunrise from the summit\r\nis truly worth all the effort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After a soup break, we continue our\r\ndescent toward Khare, with the air getting thinner as we make our way down the\r\nrugged terrain. Itâ€™s a challenging journey, but the stunning views of the\r\nHimalayan peaks keep us motivated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 625 m. Elevation loss: 1460 m. 8/10 hours hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 13, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2494, 169, '14', NULL, 'Khare - Khothe', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We take the same route used for the\r\nascent through the Hinku Valley, which offers a peaceful ambiance for trekkers\r\nto rest and rejuvenate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge.\r\nMeals included: morning, noon, evening.</b></p><p></p>', 14, '2024-10-09 05:46:33', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2495, 169, '15', NULL, 'Kothe - Chhetra Bhok (4300M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>You will have the chance to witness\r\nMera Peak and take in the splendour of the Hinku Valley. The vibrant blooms of\r\nthese trees create a stunning contrast against the lush greenery, making the\r\njourney even more enchanting. As you approach Chhetra Bhok, the air becomes\r\ncrisper, and the sounds of nature envelop you, heightening the sense of\r\nadventure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1155 m. Elevation loss: 523 m. 6 hours hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 15, '2024-10-09 05:49:06', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2496, 169, '16', NULL, 'Chhetra Bhok - Chhetra La (4610) - Lukla (2800M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Our last climb of the trek will be the\r\nfinal 300â€“400 metres of the Chhetra La ascent, which offers breathtaking views\r\nof the Middle Hills of Nepal\'s ridge and valley panorama to the south. We\r\ndescend over 2,000 metresâ€”sometimes very steeply, from the top of the pass to\r\nthe warm lodges of Lukla.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 446 m. Elevation loss: 1822 m. 6 hours hours walking.</b><br><p></p>', 16, '2024-10-09 05:49:06', '2025-08-14 14:04:07'),
(2497, 169, '17', NULL, 'Lukla - Ramechhap - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><b></b></p><p>After our long mountain trek, we take\r\nan early morning flight to Ramechap, followed by a 128-kilometre drive to\r\nKathmandu. If the flight is on time, you can spend the rest of the day relaxing\r\nand unwinding at the hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning, noon.</b><br><b>Transport: 4/5 hours of driving</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 446 m. Elevation loss: 1822 m. 6 hours hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 17, '2024-10-09 05:49:06', '2025-08-27 21:15:27'),
(2498, 215, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani  (1860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Early morning departure to Besisahar along the main highway between Nepal and India. Passing through villages, we change jeeps at Besisahar. Beyond this point, the road becomes a stony track, bumpy but lined with rice fields and traditional villages. Occasional landslides may cause delays or vehicle changes, so itâ€™s best to follow the Nepalese example and stay cheerful. We finally arrive at Dharapani and settle into the lodge<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6 hours drive (Besi Sahar). 3 hours jeep (Dharapani)</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>', 2, '2025-03-26 05:30:57', '2025-12-11 16:17:31'),
(2500, 215, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', '1350', NULL, '20 drive', '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>', 1, '2025-03-26 05:31:02', '2025-12-11 16:17:31'),
(2502, 215, '3', NULL, 'Dharapani - Kotho (2,650 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we climb to Timang \r\n\r\nthrough\r\n\r\nthe Danaquev, at the end of the Marsyangdi Gorge. The trail then becomes gentler, passing from pine forests to drier hills.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>Kotho<strong></strong>, is just before Chameâ€”the largest settlement beyond Besisahar and the district headquarters of Manang</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 750 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 5 hours  walking.</b></div></div><p></p>', 3, '2025-03-26 05:31:04', '2025-12-11 16:17:31'),
(2512, 215, '4', NULL, 'Kotho- Meta (3560 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p></p><p>Koto is the gateway to the restricted area of the Narâ€“Phu Valley.\r\nFrom here, the trail leaves the Marsyangdi Valley and follows the Nar Khola. In\r\nthis narrow section, the gorge forces the trail to cross the river several\r\ntimes. By the end of the day, after a small climb of around 250â€¯m, you reach Meta,\r\na windswept plateau offering expansive views of Annapurna II and Lamjung Himal,\r\nfollowing a day of trekking through pristine forests and rugged gorges.â€</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1200 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 5/7hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-03-26 05:34:09', '2025-12-21 16:59:23'),
(2516, 218, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', '1350', NULL, '20 drive', '<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p>', 1, '2025-04-15 14:05:28', '2025-12-16 15:29:51'),
(2518, 218, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu (Rest Day)', '1350', NULL, '20 drive', '<p>Spend\r\nyour free day however you like. Explore the local sights, relax at a cafÃ©,\r\nenjoy optional activities or simply unwind. In the evening, join your guide\r\nfor a briefing to go over the plans for the days ahead, get important details and ask any questions you may have.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel.\r\n</b><b>Meals included:\r\nmorning.</b></p>', 2, '2025-04-15 14:05:34', '2025-07-25 15:09:54'),
(2520, 218, '3', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Barpak (1900 m)', '1350', NULL, '20 drive', '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we drive from Kathmandu to Barpak. The road passes through Gorkha and goes up through hills and villages. Barpak is a scenic Gurung village with great mountain views.</p><p>A<b>ccommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Barpak).</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><b> </b></p>', 3, '2025-04-15 14:06:02', '2025-10-17 13:56:48'),
(2531, 215, '5', NULL, 'Meta - Kyang (3,840 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, the trail takes us deeper into the remote Narâ€“Phu Valley. From Meta, we follow a rugged path along a high ridge above the Phu Khola, with dramatic views of deep gorges and jagged cliffs. After crossing several suspension bridges, we pass Junam Goth, a seasonal yak pasture with simple stone shelters, and continue through barren, high-altitude terrain. The trail then leads to Chyakhu, a former Khampa settlement set in wide-open landscapes. A gradual climb from here brings us to Kyang, an isolated plateau with scattered ruins and magnificent mountain views, offering a true sense of wilderness and solitude.</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 450 m. Elevation loss: 145 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-04-18 20:14:50', '2025-12-11 17:03:11'),
(2532, 215, '6', NULL, 'Kyang - Phu (4100 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today is a scenic and relatively short walk. The trail follows the Phu Khola, winding through a wide, arid valley framed by dramatic cliffs and barren hills. Along the way, you pass ancient chortens, mani walls, and the ruins of old settlements. As you approach <strong>Phu</strong>, the valley opens up to reveal this medieval Tibetan village, perched on a ridge with stunning views of the surrounding peaks. The entrance is marked by a line of impressive stone chortens, welcoming you into the culturally rich and isolated village.</p><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 400 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 3/4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 6, '2025-04-18 20:19:05', '2025-12-11 17:03:11'),
(2533, 215, '7', NULL, 'Phu â€“Mahendra Pul (3840 m) (Sartek Thrangu Gomba)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nToday, we retrace much of the previous route, revisiting key sections of the trail through the Narâ€“Phu Valley while taking in the surrounding scenery from a new perspective.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 700 m. 3/5 hours walking.</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div><b></b> </div>', 7, '2025-04-18 20:25:10', '2025-12-11 17:03:11'),
(2535, 215, '8', NULL, 'Mahendra Pul - Tibetan village of Naar (4200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nToday, we ascend through a dry, rugged valley adorned with mani walls and chortens, reflecting the regionâ€™s rich spiritual and cultural heritage. The trail gradually climbs, offering occasional views of distant peaks and the surrounding valleys, before reaching the traditional Tibetan village of <strong></strong>Naar<strong></strong>. As the largest settlement in the Narâ€“Phu area, Naar is celebrated for its ancient monasteries, stone houses, and narrow alleys, all set against a backdrop of dramatic mountain scenery. The village provides a remarkable insight into local life, where centuries-old traditions continue to thrive amidst the high-altitude landscape, making it a memorable highlight of the trek.<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 600 m. Elevation loss: 00 m. 4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 8, '2025-04-18 20:28:01', '2025-12-11 17:03:11'),
(2536, 215, '9', NULL, 'Naar - Khang La Pass (5313 m) - Ngawal (3660 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nEarly this morning, the day begins with a challenging yet initially gentle climb towards <strong></strong>Kang La Pass<strong></strong>. After a couple of hours, the trail becomes steeper and rocky, passing moraines and glacial streams, with sweeping views of the Annapurna and Manaslu ranges. After crossing the pass, the descent to <strong></strong>Ngawal <strong></strong>is steep but scenic, winding through rhododendron forests and traditional villages. This route offers spectacular mountain views and a highly rewarding high-altitude trekking experience.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1250 m. Elevation loss: 1600 m. 10 hours of walking.</b><br></p>', 9, '2025-04-18 20:55:59', '2025-12-11 17:03:11'),
(2537, 215, '10', NULL, 'Ngawal - Braga Monastery - Manang (3542 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, we follow a scenic, gently descending trail from Ngawal, winding through open alpine terrain with scattered juniper trees, mani walls, and sweeping views of Annapurna III and Gangapurna. After about 1.5 hours, we reach the historic village of Braga, where a 600-year-old monastery perched on a cliff is well worth a short visit for its spiritual atmosphere and outstanding views. From Braga, the trail becomes easy and mostly flat, following the Marsyangdi River until we arrive at Manang, a lively village and important acclimatisation stop on the Annapurna Circuit.<br></p><div>&nbsp;<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>&nbsp;Elevation gain: 140 m. Elevation loss: 273 m. 4 hours walking</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div></div>', 10, '2025-04-18 20:58:45', '2025-12-11 17:03:11'),
(2538, 215, '11', NULL, 'Manang - Tilicho Base Camp (4150 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><b>\r\n\r\n<div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></b><div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast, the day begins with a trek through remote, high-altitude terrain. The trail gradually ascends to Khangsar, a small stone-built village, before continuing to Siri Kharka, where trekkers are treated to scenic views of Tilicho Peak. From there, the path becomes more demanding, crossing narrow, landslide-prone sections, before descending slightly to Tilicho Base Camp, where trekkers rest prior to the hike to Tilicho Lake.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 860 m. Elevation loss: 266 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p></div></div><div><b></b></div>', 11, '2025-04-18 21:19:44', '2025-12-11 17:03:11');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2539, 215, '12', NULL, 'Tilicho BC â€“ Tilicho lake (4920 m) â€“ Shree Kharka (4080 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, we leave Manang within 1 hour, we explore the beautiful village (Khangsar) an unusual village with its unique houses and culture. Expansive views of snow-capped peaks and Today is the final stage to reach Tilicho Lake. After a gentle climb, you are rewarded with breathtaking views of the lake at 4,930â€¯metres. The only sounds are the occasional avalanches from Tilicho Peak or ice breaking into the lake, adding to the wild beauty of the surroundings. If the lakeside tea stall is open, it is the perfect place to enjoy a hot drink while taking in the scenery. After spending time at Tilicho Lake, we retrace our steps along the trail back to Shree Kharka.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 860 m. Elevation loss: 266 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 12, '2025-04-18 21:22:30', '2025-12-17 16:39:04'),
(2540, 215, '13', NULL, 'Shree Kharka - Thorong Phedi (4500m) At the bottom of Thorong La', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, the trail gradually climbs through alpine meadows and barren landscapes. This less-travelled route from Manang to Thorong Phedi offers a quieter and more scenic alternative. Trekking through rugged high-altitude terrain, you will enjoy beautiful views of the Annapurna range and the Marsyangdi Valley, making it a peaceful and less crowded option compared to the main Annapurna Circuit route.</p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1180 m. Elevation loss: 715 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 13, '2025-04-18 21:24:24', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2542, 215, '14', NULL, 'Thorung Phedi - Thorong La pass (5416 m) - Muktinath (3760 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><b><p></p></b><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Starting very early, you climb steadily to Thorong La Pass at 5,416â€¯m, one of the highest trekking passes in the world. At the top, you will see colourful prayer flags, a Buddhist stupa, and stones left by trekkers. Take a break to enjoy the amazing views of snowy mountains and valleys. After the pass, the trail goes down sharply to Chabarbu, passing meadows and a deep gorge, then rises a little before reaching Muktinath. Muktinath is a sacred place for Buddhists and Hindus, known for its old temple and natural springs. It is a tough but very special day.<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 912 m. Elevation loss: 1691m. 8 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>\r\n\r\n</div><div><b></b></div>', 14, '2025-04-18 21:25:51', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2543, 215, '15', NULL, 'Muktinath - Lupra (3000 m) â€“ Drive to Tatopani  (1200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<div>Today is an important day as you spend the morning near Mount Dhaulagiri. After leaving Muktinath, the trail goes to the small, old village of Lupra, away from the main road. This area has some of the last BÃ¶n monasteries, an ancient religion before Buddhism. To reach Lupra, you go down a steep path into a riverbed. From there, you take a three-hour jeep ride to Tatopani, a busy town by the Kali Gandaki River. Tatopani means â€œhot waterâ€ in Nepali because of its natural hot springs, where you can relax for a small feeâ€”donâ€™t forget your swimming gear!<br></div><div><br></div><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Transport : 3 hours drive.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 4 hours walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<div><div><div><b></b></div></div></div></div>', 15, '2025-04-18 21:27:26', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2544, 215, '16', NULL, 'Tatopani - Sikha (2000 m) â€“ Ghorepani  (2860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>The day starts with a short walk along a road and across a bridge. You then climb uphill through farms and small traditional villages, which are more authentic and different from the ones you have seen before. No heavy winter gear is needed todayâ€”just a couple of t-shirts will be enough. Near the top, enjoy the stunning views of the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri mountains from Ghorepani.<br></p><div><b></b></div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening </b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 150 m. 5 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p></div>', 16, '2025-04-18 21:29:23', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2545, 215, '17', NULL, 'Ghorepani â€“ Poonhil (3210 m) Phulbari (3000 m) â€“ Mohare Danda (3030 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><b>\r\n\r\n<p></p></b><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>To catch the sunrise from Poon Hill, you start with a steep climb of around one hour early in the morning over stone steps. The trail passes through rhododendron forests, away from the busier paths, with stunning views of Annapurna and Dhaulagiri. It then follows the ridge to Mohare Danda community lodge, where you can enjoy views of many peaks, including Annapurna, Machapuchare, Hiunchuli, Mardi Himal, Lamjung Himal, and the towering Dhaulagiri. You also have the option to return to the lodge for breakfast before continuing on to Mohare Danda.<br></p><p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Community lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 700 m. Elevation loss: 274 m. 5 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p></div>', 17, '2025-04-18 21:31:11', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2546, 215, '18', NULL, 'Mohare Danda â€“ Pokhara (850 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After enjoying the sunrise, the trek continues along beautiful ridges with rhododendron and tropical forests, before descending steeply to the village of Ulleri via long stone steps. After lunch in Ulleri, you will take jeeps to Pokhara.<br></p><p></p><p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 3 hours drive</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 1260 m. Elevation loss: 72 m. 3 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p></div>', 18, '2025-04-18 21:32:37', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2547, 215, '19', NULL, 'Pokhara - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours.<p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6-7 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><div><div><div><b></b></div></div></div> </div></div>', 19, '2025-04-18 21:34:05', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2548, 215, '20', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\n\r\n<p></p><p></p>', 20, '2025-04-18 21:39:15', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2549, 215, '21', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'According to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey. ccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.', 21, '2025-04-18 21:40:52', '2025-12-11 17:03:12'),
(2581, 242, '1', NULL, 'Arrival in Kathmandu (1,300m). Transfer to hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:03:15', '2025-12-11 18:35:31'),
(2582, 242, '2', NULL, 'Flight Pokhara - Drive Kande (1,770m) - Pothana (1,890m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nAfter a scenic 25-minute flight, you arrive at <strong></strong>Pokhara International Airport<strong></strong>. A private car then transfers you to <strong></strong>Kande<strong></strong>. Between Kande and <strong></strong>Pothana<strong></strong>, the route passes through a short but attractive section of the Annapurna region, featuring woodland paths, stone steps, and stunning mountain views. We stop briefly in the beautiful Gurung village before beginning our trek to <strong></strong>Pothana<strong></strong>.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 25 mins flight (Pokhara), 40 minutes of drive (Kande).&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 460m. Elevation loss :  340m.&nbsp; 2</b><b>&nbsp;hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:03:15', '2025-12-11 18:35:31'),
(2583, 242, '3', NULL, 'Pothana - Dudh Karka (2525m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>\r\n\r\nToday we trek along peaceful forest trails and remote hillside paths. From Pothana, the trail gently climbs through rhododendron and oak forests to Deurali. From here, we leave the Annapurna Base Camp route, moving away from the main tourist trail into a quieter, more secluded area. After approximately four hours of walking in this pleasant environment, including a short climb, we reach our camp.\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon evening.</b><br><b></b><b>Elevation gain: 680 m. Elevation loss: 180m. &nbsp;</b><b></b><b>5 hours  walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:05:52', '2025-12-11 19:19:03'),
(2584, 242, '4', NULL, 'Dudh Karka - low camp (3,000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today, the day is quite challenging, so be sure to have the right gear. From Dudh Kharka, the trail gently climbs through pastures with herder huts and grazing yaks. It then rises through rhododendron and oak forests, with some clearings giving views of Annapurna South and Machapuchhre (Fishtail). Small streams and mossy paths make the walk peaceful. As the forest thins, the trail opens into alpine meadows with wide, beautiful views. We end the day at Low Camp, a quiet and scenic spot, one of the highlights of the Mardi Himal Trek.</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain: 590 m. Elevation loss: 120m.&nbsp;4 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></p><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:05:52', '2025-12-11 19:23:04'),
(2585, 242, '5', NULL, 'Low Camp - High Camp (3,640m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nToday is a short but steep climb through rhododendron and juniper forests. The trail gradually rises above the tree line, opening up views of Mardi Himal, Machapuchhre, and the Annapurna range. As you gain height, the vegetation becomes sparse and alpine. A few teahouses along the way provide opportunities to rest and have refreshments. After 2â€“3 hours of climbing, we reach High Camp, a ridge with stunning mountain viewsâ€”an ideal place to acclimatise before continuing to Mardi Himal Base Camp.\r\n\r\n<br></p><div></div>\r\n\r\n<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain: 560 m. Elevation loss: 00 m.&nbsp;<b></b>3 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:05:52', '2025-12-11 19:19:03'),
(2586, 242, '6', NULL, 'High Camp - Upper View Point (4200m) - Mardi Himal Base Camp (4500m) - Badal Danda (3268m', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Start your day early to catch the magnificent sunrise from the Upper View Point. After/Before breakfast, we follow a narrow ridge trail with stunning views of Machapuchhre and the Annapurna range. After about two hours, we reach the viewpoint to enjoy the sunrise. The trail then continues along a rocky path for another 1â€“1.5 hours to Mardi Himal Base Camp. After taking in the views, we return to High Camp, then descend steeply through alpine grasslands and rhododendron forests to reach Badal Danda (3,268 m), a scenic ridge overlooking valleys often filled with clouds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p></p></div></div></div><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning afternoon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 700 m. Elevation loss: 960m. 7/8 hours walking.</b></div></div><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:05:52', '2025-12-11 19:23:04'),
(2587, 242, '7', NULL, 'Badal Dada - Kalimati (1850m) - Drive to Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, we descend from Badal Danda, retracing most of the trail, and continue to Sidhing, a village offering a glimpse of traditional life. From Sidhing, we take a jeep to Pokhara. This is a great chance to explore the beautiful city and enjoy views of the Himalayan ranges from lakeside cafÃ©s and bars. If time allows, you can also enjoy boating on the calm lake, where the water reflects the stunning Fishtail Mountain.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning.</b><br><b>Transport : 2/3 hours&nbsp; jeep (Pokhara)</b><br> <b>Elevation gain: 100 m. Elevation loss: 1200m.\r\n\r\n</b><b></b><b>4/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:05:53', '2025-12-11 19:19:03'),
(2588, 242, '8', NULL, 'Pokhara - Flight to Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Pokhara, we take a scenic flight back to Kathmandu, enjoying aerial views of the Himalayan ranges and the stunning landscapes below.\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning.</b><br><b>Transport : 25 minutes flight ( Kathmandu)</b><br></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:05:53', '2025-12-11 19:19:03'),
(2589, 242, '9', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-26 18:05:53', '2025-12-11 19:23:04'),
(2609, 242, '10', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<div><p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onwards journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p></div><p></p></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 11:29:25', '2025-12-11 19:19:03'),
(2614, 243, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350 m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<div><div><b></b></div> </div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:16:19', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2615, 243, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani  (1860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Early morning departure to Besisahar along the main highway between Nepal and India. Passing through villages, we change jeeps at Besisahar. Beyond this point, the road becomes a stony track, bumpy but lined with rice fields and traditional villages. Occasional landslides may cause delays or vehicle changes, so itâ€™s best to follow the Nepalese example and stay cheerful. We finally arrive at Dharapani and settle into the lodge<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6 hours drive (Besi Sahar). 3 hours jeep (Dharapani)</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:17:33', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2616, 243, '3', NULL, 'Dharapani - Chame (2700 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, we climb to Timang througout the Danaquev, at the end of the Marsyangdi Gorge. The trail then becomes gentler, passing from pine forests to drier hills. Chame, the largest settlement beyond Besisahar, is the district headquarters of Manang. </p><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 750 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 5 hours  walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<div><div><b></b></div></div><div> </div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:20:23', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2617, 243, '4', NULL, 'Chame â€“ Lower Pisang (3200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, the trail follows the Marsyangdi River through pine forests to Bhratang, famous for its apple orchards. The valley then opens up to the impressive Paungda Danda rock face. After crossing a suspension bridge, we climb to Dukur Pokhari (3,240â€¯m) for lunch with spectacular mountain views, before gently descending to Lower Pisang (3,200â€¯m). You can also visit Upper Pisang to see its monastery and enjoy broader views. This stage combines forested paths, river scenery and dramatic mountain landscapes.<br></p><div><div><b>&nbsp;Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>&nbsp;Elevation gain: 830 m. Elevation loss: 350 m. 6 hours  walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<div><div><b></b></div></div><p></p></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2618, 243, '5', NULL, 'Pisang - Ghyaru (3720) - Tibetan village of Ngawal (3661 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today is one of the most scenic days. We climb steeply to Ghyaru, a small Tibetan village at 3,720â€¯m, with amazing mountain views and traditional stone houses. From Ghyaru, the trail crosses open hills to Ngawal (3,661â€¯m), a larger village with a beautiful monastery and ancient stone buildings. This quieter route offers great scenery and helps your body acclimatise before we continue to Manang.<br></p><div><b>&nbsp;Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 685 m. Elevation loss: 217 m. 6 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2619, 243, '6', NULL, 'Ngawal - Braga Monastery - Manang (3542 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast, we follow a scenic, gently descending trail from Ngawal, winding through open alpine terrain with scattered juniper trees, mani walls, and sweeping views of Annapurna III and Gangapurna. After about 1.5 hours, we reach the historic village of Braga, where a 600-year-old monastery perched on a cliff is well worth a short visit for its spiritual atmosphere and outstanding views. From Braga, the trail becomes easy and mostly flat, following the Marsyangdi River until we arrive at Manang, a lively village and important acclimatisation stop on the Annapurna Circuit.<br></p><div>&nbsp;<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>&nbsp;Elevation gain: 140 m. Elevation loss: 273 m. 4 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2620, 243, '7', NULL, 'Ice Lake (4610 m) (Kicho Tal): Panorama of the Annapurnas / Rest and acclimatization day in Manang', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From Braga or the small village of Manang, the trail climbs steeply through alpine meadows. The high altitude and rough terrain can make the path challenging. The main highlight is a glacier lake with clear turquoise water reflecting the surrounding peaks, with views of Gangapurna and the Annapurna range, including Annapurna II, III, and IV. For an easier option, Gangapurna Lake is shorter to reach and ideal for a quick visit or acclimatization. Alternatively, you can choose to rest in Manang to recover and prepare for the next stage of the trek.<br></p><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 1100 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 7 hours walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2621, 243, '8', NULL, 'Manang - Leather (4217 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today is a short, easy trek to help your body acclimatise to the altitude. You will walk through dry, rocky,, high-altitude desert, very different from forests and meadows. Along the way, you may see eagles, marmots, yaks and blue sheep. The slow pace allows you to enjoy the mountain views and rest before the next climb. </p><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 720 m. Elevation loss: 56 m. 4.5 hours walking.</b></div></div>\r\n\r\n<div><div><b></b></div></div></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2622, 243, '9', NULL, 'Leder - Thorung Phedi (4500m) At the bottom of Thorong La', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><div><div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today is another short but important day on the Annapurna Circuit. The trek brings you closer to Thorong La Pass (5,416â€¯m), one of the highest trekking passes in the world. Along the way, you will enjoy beautiful views of snow-capped peaks, glacial rivers, and the dry, high-altitude landscape. Mountains such as Thorong Peak (6,144â€¯m) and Khatung Kang (6,484â€¯m) rise on the horizon, adding to the excitement of this stage.<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 380 m. Elevation loss: 71 m. 3 hours  walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div></div> </div> </div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2623, 243, '10', NULL, 'Thorung Phedi - Thorong La pass (5416 m) - Muktinath (3760 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Starting very early, you climb steadily to Thorong La Pass at 5,416â€¯m, one of the highest trekking passes in the world. At the top, you will see colourful prayer flags, a Buddhist stupa, and stones left by trekkers. Take a break to enjoy the amazing views of snowy mountains and valleys. After the pass, the trail goes down sharply to Chabarbu, passing meadows and a deep gorge, then rises a little before reaching Muktinath. Muktinath is a sacred place for Buddhists and Hindus, known for its old temple and natural springs. It is a tough but very special day.<br></p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 912 m. Elevation loss: 1691m. 8 hours  walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2624, 243, '11', NULL, 'Muktinath - Lupra (3000 m) â€“ Drive to Tatopani  (1200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<div>Today is an important day as you spend the morning near Mount Dhaulagiri. After leaving Muktinath, the trail goes to the small, old village of Lupra, away from the main road. This area has some of the last BÃ¶n monasteries, an ancient religion before Buddhism. To reach Lupra, you go down a steep path into a riverbed. From there, you take a three-hour jeep ride to Tatopani, a busy town by the Kali Gandaki River. Tatopani means â€œhot waterâ€ in Nepali because of its natural hot springs, where you can relax for a small feeâ€”donâ€™t forget your swimming gear!<br></div><div><br></div><div><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Transport : 3 hours drive.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 4 hours walking.</b></div></div><br>\r\n\r\n<div><div><div><b></b></div></div></div></div> </div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2625, 243, '12', NULL, 'Tatopani â€“ Dirve Pokhara 800 m (Free day in Pokhra)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>If this is a combined group, itâ€™s time to say goodbye (group + Nepali team). Then take a car or jeep to Pokhara. This is a great chance to explore the beautiful city and enjoy views of the Himalayan ranges from lakeside cafÃ©s and bars. If time allows, you can also enjoy boating on the calm lake, where the water reflects the stunning Fishtail Mountain.</p>\r\n<p>Near the international airport, you can visit Davis Falls and the International Mountain Museum, which features the history of the Himalayas and local ethnology.</p><div><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 4 hours ( Pokhara) by jeep.</b></div></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2626, 243, '13', NULL, 'Pokhra- Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours.<p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6-7 hours drive (Kathmandu</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div></div>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2627, 243, '14', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; \r\n\r\n<p></p><p></p>', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2628, 243, '15', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'According to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.', NULL, '2025-05-27 18:26:54', '2025-12-11 18:09:43'),
(2637, 163, '11', NULL, 'Muktinath - Lupra (3000 m) â€“ Drive to Tatopani (1200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div><div>Today is an important day as you spend the morning near Mount Dhaulagiri. After leaving Muktinath, the trail goes to the small, old village of Lupra, away from the main road. This area has some of the last BÃ¶n monasteries, an ancient religion before Buddhism. To reach Lupra, you go down a steep path into a riverbed. From there, you take a three-hour jeep ride to Tatopani, a busy town by the Kali Gandaki River. Tatopani means â€œhot waterâ€ in Nepali because of its natural hot springs, where you can relax for a small feeâ€”donâ€™t forget your swimming gear!\r\n\r\n<br></div><div><br></div><div>\r\n\r\n<div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Transport : 3 hours drive.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 4 hours  walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<br></div> </div>', 11, '2025-05-28 13:41:13', '2025-12-11 17:44:47'),
(2638, 163, '12', NULL, 'Tatopani - Sikha (2000 m) â€“ Ghorepani (2860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nThe day starts with a short walk along a road and across a bridge. You then climb up hill through farms and small traditional villages, which are more authentic and different from the ones you have seen before. No heavy winter gear is needed todayâ€”just a couple of t-shirts will be enough. Near the top, enjoy the amazing views of the Annapurna and Dhaulagiri mountains from Ghorepani.\r\n\r\n<br></p><div><b></b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 150 m. 5 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></div><p></p><p></p>', 12, '2025-05-28 13:44:30', '2025-12-11 14:45:11'),
(2639, 163, '13', NULL, 'Ghorepani â€“ Poonhill (3210 m) - Phulbari (3000 m) â€“ Mohare Danda (3030 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nTo catch the sunrise from Poon Hill, you start with a steep climb of around one hour early in the morning over stone steps. The trail passes through rhododendron forests, away from the busier paths, with beautiful views of Annapurna and Dhaulagiri. It then follows the ridge to Mohare Danda community lodge, where you can enjoy views of many peaks, including Annapurna, Machapuchare, Hiunchuli, Mardi Himal, Lamjung Himal and the towering Dhaulagiri. You also have the option to return to the lodge for breakfast before continuing on to Mohare Danda.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: Community lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 700 m. Elevation loss: 274 m. 5 hours walking.</b></div><p></p><p></p>', 13, '2025-05-28 13:44:30', '2025-12-12 14:48:07'),
(2640, 163, '14', NULL, 'Mohare Danda â€“ Pokhara (850 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\nAfter enjoying the sunrise, the trek continues along beautiful ridges with rhododendron and tropical forests, before descending steeply to the village of Ulleri via long stone steps. After lunch in Ulleri, you will take jeeps to Pokhara.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 3 hours drive</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 1260 m. Elevation loss: 72 m. 3 hours walking.</b></div><p></p><p></p>', 14, '2025-05-28 13:44:30', '2025-12-09 21:22:28'),
(2641, 163, '15', NULL, 'Pokhara- Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours.\r\n\r\n<p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6-7 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b></div><p></p><p><b></b></p><p></p>', 15, '2025-05-28 13:44:30', '2025-12-11 16:28:55'),
(2642, 163, '16', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour\r\noffers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art,\r\nguided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s\r\nunique heritage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved\r\nvehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3&nbsp; People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10&nbsp; People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<p></p><p></p>', 16, '2025-05-28 13:44:30', '2025-12-16 15:57:31'),
(2643, 163, '17', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>According to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>', 17, '2025-05-28 13:44:30', '2025-12-09 21:22:28'),
(2644, 244, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-11 19:45:00'),
(2645, 244, '2', NULL, 'Flight to Pokhara (850 m) â€“ Drive to Kimche (1740 m) â€“ Trek to Ghandruk (2,000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After your&nbsp;\r\n\r\npicturesque\r\n\r\n flight to Pokhara, you arrive at Pokhara International Airport, where a private car will take you to Kimche. After Birethanti, the road becomes quite rough. We take a short break, then begin our trek to Ghandruk . The trail climbs gently on stone-paved steps until we reach Ghandurk. A&nbsp;traditional Gurung village, where you can visit the Gurung Cultural Museum and a Buddhist monastery</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals excluded: morning included.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 25 minutes flight (Pokhara), 3&nbsp;hours drive (Kimchel).<b></b></b></div><div><b>Elevation Gain: 360M. Elevation loss: 00.\r\n\r\n<b></b>1 hours walking.</b></div><p></p>', 2, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-23 14:05:21'),
(2646, 244, '3', NULL, 'Gandruk - Tadapani (2690 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nOur journey continues toward Tadapani, a name that means â€˜far waterâ€™ in Nepali. We climb again to reach the Komrong Danda pass, then follow a scenic balcony trail through the traditional villages of Melanje and Chiule at about 2,050 meters. From here, the path becomes steeper and leads us into a forest of tall rhododendron trees, which bloom beautifully from March onward. Tadapani sits high on a ridge, offering dramatic views of the deep valley stretching toward the Annapurna Sanctuary. Above it all, Annapurna III (7,555 m) and Gangapurna (7,454 m) rise proudly on the horizon\r\n\r\n<br></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included : morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation Gain: 750 M. Elevation loss: 100. 5/6 hours walking.</b></div><p></p>', 3, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:11:40'),
(2647, 244, '4', NULL, 'Tadapani- Dobato(3450 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we leave the\r\nwell-trodden trail to Ghorepani behind and take a lesser-known path, used\r\nmostly by locals. The trail ascends gently through a dense forest of\r\nrhododendrons, creating a tunnel of greenery. As we climb higher, the forest\r\ngives way to open pastures where water buffalo graze, short grass here is highly\r\nvalued by the nearby villages. As we break above the tree line, beautiful views\r\nof the Annapurna range unfold before us. We end the day in the quiet hamlet of\r\nDobato, where we spend the night.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included:&nbsp;\r\n\r\n morning noon evening.\r\n\r\n</b></div><div><b>Elevation Gain: 800 M. Elevation loss: 90. 4/5 hours walking.</b></div><p></p>', 4, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:11:40'),
(2648, 244, '5', NULL, 'Dobato - Muldai viewpoint (3630) - Dobato - Chistibung (3030 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nWe set out before dawn to catch the sunrise, moving quietly through a shadowy rhododendron forest. As we reach the summit, the majestic Dhaulagiri appears in the morning light, joined by stunning views of Annapurna South, Hiunchuli, and the iconic Machapuchare. The Muldai viewpoint rivals the famous Poon Hill but without the crowds. After soaking in the panorama, we descend to the lodge. Following breakfast, the trail leads us toward Chistibung along a scenic ridgeline. We cross small passes before making a long descent through more rhododendron forest to the valley floor, then continue with a steady climbâ€”still surrounded by the vibrant colors and towering trunks of the rhododendrons.<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>NB:</strong><em>&nbsp; For the\r\nMuldai view point, up/down1 hour: \r\nand &nbsp;4 to 5 hours to reach Chistibung.</em></p><p><em>\r\n\r\n</em></p><div><em><b></b></em><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included:&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n morning noon evening.\r\n\r\n</b></div><div><b>Elevation Gain: 300 M. Elevation loss: 700 M. 4/5 hours walking.</b><em><b></b></em></div><p></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:11:40'),
(2649, 244, '6', NULL, 'Chistibung - Khopra Ridge - Hike up (4000 m) - Khopra Ridge (3660 m).', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>The day starts with a gentle walk through a quiet\r\nrhododendron forest. As we climb higher, the landscape opens up and the path\r\nwinds between large scattered rocks. A final stretch brings us to the Khopra\r\nCommunity Lodge. From here, the views are breathtakingâ€”Annapurna South rises\r\nclose by, while Fang, Nilgiri, and the wide Dhaulagiri range tower above the\r\ndeep Kali Gandaki Valley. After lunch, we follow the ridge above Khopra on a\r\nhike towards Khayar Lake (4,025 m), an important pilgrimage site. Today, we aim\r\nto reach a viewpoint at about 4,000 metres, which still offers stunning\r\nmountain scenery. We then return to the lodge for the night, surrounded by the\r\ncalm and peace of the high Himalayas</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon\r\nevening.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<strong><i>Note:</i></strong><i> 2\r\nto 3 hours of climbing to reach <strong>Kopra Ridge</strong>, with an elevation gain <strong>650 meters</strong>.\r\nFor those choosing the optional hike to <strong>4000m</strong>, plan for about <strong>3 hours round\r\ntrip</strong>, with an elevation </i>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 6, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-16 18:28:25'),
(2650, 244, '7', NULL, 'Khopra - Swanta (2200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nToday is a long descent all the way to Swanta. We retrace our steps to Chistibung, following a pleasant and easy-to-follow path. Eventually, we arrive at the picturesque hamlet of Swanta, set among terraced rice fields, providing a peaceful end to the dayâ€™s walk. This area is rich in wildlife, so keep your eyes openâ€”you might spot the Himalayan tahr, a sure-footed mountain goat, or the colourful Danphe pheasant, Nepalâ€™s national bird.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: Lodge.&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMeals included: morning noon\r\nevening.\r\n\r\n</b></div><div><b>Elevation Gain: 220 M. Elevation loss: 1640 M. 5/6 hours walking</b></div><p></p>', 7, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:11:40'),
(2651, 244, '8', NULL, 'Swanta- Mohare viewpoint (Dada) (3320 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After a warm breakfast, we begin a gentle descent to a small river, pausing to see a traditional watermill, an important source of power for the local villages. We cross a well-used path to Ghorepani and then turn south onto a quieter trail. Passing through a beautiful tropical forest, we reach NakakoBisaune Pass at 2,670 metres, and continue to the small hamlet of Phulbari at 2,925 metres, where we stop for lunch in a peaceful mountain setting. In the afternoon, we make a final climb to the high ridge connecting Poon Hill with Mohare Danda. The views are spectacular, with the Dhaulagiri and Annapurna massifs stretching out before us. Following the ridge, with the majestic Dhaulagiri always in sight, we arrive at the Mohare Danda Community Lodge</p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation Gain: 1140 M. Elevation loss: 160 M. 5/6 hours walking</b></div><p></p><p></p>', 8, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:13:32'),
(2652, 244, '9', NULL, 'Mohare viewpoint -Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After enjoying the sunrise, the trek continues along beautiful ridges with rhododendron and tropical forests, before descending steeply to the village of Ulleri via long stone steps. After lunch in Ulleri, you will take jeeps to Pokhara.<br></p><p></p><p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 3 hours drive</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 1260 m. Elevation loss: 72 m. 3 hours walking.</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p>', 9, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:11:40'),
(2653, 244, '10', NULL, 'Pokhara â€“ Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours.<p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport : 6-7 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div><div><b></b></div></div><p></p>', 10, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:11:40'),
(2654, 244, '11', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p></p><p></p>', 11, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:11:40'),
(2655, 244, '12', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 12, '2025-05-29 13:22:09', '2025-12-12 14:11:40'),
(2657, 218, '4', NULL, 'Barpak - Laprak  (2200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>After breakfast, we climbs steadily through forests and along ridges with beautiful views of the mountains. After a scenic walk, you reach Laprak, a traditional Gurung village surrounded by terraced fields.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div></div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 939 m Elevation loss: 784 m. 6 hours walking.</b></p><b><p><b></b></p></b><p></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2658, 218, '5', NULL, 'Laprak â€“ Singla -  Khorlabesi (970 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today the trek to&nbsp; Khorlabesi via Singla, first climbs up to Singla Pass, offering landscape views of Ganesh Himal and surrounding peaks. Then it descends steeply through forests and small villages. You continue downhill until you reach Khorlabesi, a riverside village known for its hot springs and peaceful setting.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain : 610 m Elevation loss: 1,776 m. 6/7 hours walking.<br><b></b></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2659, 218, '6', NULL, 'Khorla besi - Jagat (1370 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we\r\nfollow the trail through the narrow Bhuri Gandaki Gorge, moving at a steady\r\npace as the river rushes below. The path takes us across a suspension bridge to\r\nthe other side, where we start a steep climb through terraced hillsides and\r\nsmall settlements. After a final push uphill, we arrive at the charming village\r\nof Jagat, with its stone houses and mountain views, marking our entry into the\r\nManaslu Conservation Area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain : 1,342 m Elevation loss: 900 m. 5/6 hours walking.<br><b></b></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 6, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2660, 218, '7', NULL, 'Jagat - Lokpa (2040 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we enter the gateway to the Tsum Valley and start a gradual\r\nascent toward the village of Philim. The trail winds through pine forests and\r\nterraced fields, with occasional glimpses of local life along the way. As we\r\nclimb higher, the landscape opens up to reveal beautiful views of the Ganesh\r\nHimal and Shringi Himal ranges. Continuing on a quieter path, we eventually\r\nreach the secluded village of Lokpa, nestled on a forested ridge and offering a\r\npeaceful resting place for the night.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 1,150 m Elevation loss: 250 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2661, 218, '8', NULL, 'Lokpa  - Chumling (2316 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we steep descent through dense pine and rhododendron forests. The narrow, rocky trail winds down to the river, where you cross a long suspension bridge over the Shiar Khola. From here, the trail climbs steadily uphill along a forested ridge, offering occasional glimpses of surrounding hills and distant snow peaks. As you ascend, you pass small waterfalls, mani walls and prayer flags that reflect the deep spiritual atmosphere of the region. After hours of trekking, you reach <strong>Chumling</strong>, a charming village with stone houses, ancient monasteries and scenic views of Ganesh Himal. This section of the trail is moderately challenging and rich in both natural beauty and cultural experiences.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain : 250  m Elevation loss: 90 m. 3/4 hours walking<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 8, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2662, 218, '9', NULL, 'Chumling - Chhokangparo (3010 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>Today, our path\r\ncontinues along the riverâ€™s right bank, with occasional rises and dips. At the\r\njunction of the Syar and Sarpu rivers, we come across a beautiful chorten and\r\ncross a suspension bridge. We then walk through the picturesque village of Gho\r\nand begin our ascent to Chhokungparo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 700 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p><p></p>', 9, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:21:32'),
(2663, 218, '10', NULL, 'Chhokangparo â€“ Chuleâ€“Nile (3361 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After finisghing breakfast, we make\r\nour way through several Tibetan settlements, we stop to explore the peaceful\r\nRachen Gompa monastery at 3,240 metres. Perched above the village on a cliff,\r\nthe Piren Phu hermitage holds spiritual significance, believed to be where\r\nMilarepa meditated â€” his footprint still marked in the cave. We then continue\r\nin the direction of the Nile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 300 m. Elevation loss: 450 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p><p></p>', 10, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:21:32'),
(2664, 218, '11', NULL, 'Nile  â€“ Mu Gompa (3700 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we make our\r\nway up to Mu Gompa Monastery, the final settlement before reaching the Tibetan\r\nborder. This historic monastery, built between 1895 and 1936 by a high lama\r\nfrom Bhutan and restored in 1998, is a well-known centre for meditation\r\naffiliated with the Gelugpa monastery of Kopan near Kathmandu. Its main prayer\r\nhall honours Chenrezig, the Buddha of Compassion. From here, we take a scenic\r\nbalcony path for about 45 minutes to visit the Choyong Gompa nunnery, enjoying\r\nbeautiful&nbsp; mountain views and glimpses of the ancient caravan route to Tibet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain : 700 m Elevation loss: 100 m. 4/5 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 11, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2665, 218, '12', NULL, 'Mu Gompa - Rachen Gompa (3020 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we&nbsp; trek &nbsp;to Rachen Gompa -&nbsp;mostly downhill and easy. You follow the trail along the Shiar Khola, passing yak pastures, mani walls and chortens. As you go lower, the area becomes greener. After a few hours, you reach Rachen Gompa, a peaceful nunnery surrounded by fields and traditional houses\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain : 250 m Elevation loss: 100 m. 4 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 12, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2666, 218, '13', NULL, 'Rachen Gompa - Dumje (2440 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Our day starts with a gentle descent,\r\nallowing us to ease into the rhythm of the trail as we move through terraced\r\nfields and scattered pine forests. The path winds slowly downward, offering\r\nsweeping views of the surrounding hills and distant snow-capped peaks. After\r\nthis calm introduction, the terrain starts to changeâ€”growing steeper and more\r\nrugged. We carefully navigate a sharper descent, the trail cutting through\r\ndense woodland and rocky outcrops. As we descend further, the distant rooftops\r\nof Dumje come into view, nestled in a quiet valley below. This small village,\r\nsurrounded by farmland and prayer flags fluttering in the breeze, marks the end\r\nof this leg of our journey and offers a peaceful setting to rest and reconnect\r\nwith the rhythm of the mountains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain : 150 m Elevation loss: 1000 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 13, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2667, 218, '14', NULL, 'Dumje â€“ Lungdang Gumpa (3290 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>Today,from Dumje,\r\nthe trail start to climb steadily, winding through lush forest filled with\r\nrhododendrons, pines, and occasional glimpses of wildlife. As we gain altitude,\r\nthe air grows cooler and the views more expansive. The path, though narrow and\r\nsometimes steep, rewards us with a sense of seclusion and serenity. After\r\nseveral hours of ascent, we reach Lungdang Gumba, a remote monastery\r\nperched high on the hillside. Surrounded by prayer flags and backed by dramatic\r\nmountain scenery, the Gumba offers a peaceful retreat and a rare glimpse into\r\nthe spiritual life of the regionâ€™s Tibetan Buddhist community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain 1000 : m Elevation loss: 100 m. 4 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 14, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2668, 218, '15', NULL, 'Lungdang Gumpa - Ripchet (2468 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p>We commenced our ascent to Ganesh\r\nHimal Base Camp early in the morning. The undulating trail led us through\r\nforests of oak, rhododendron and conifer, offering a tranquil and scenic\r\njourney. Along the way, we passed through the charming village of Ripchet,\r\nwhere we were rewarded with beautiful views of the surrounding peaks.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 100 m Elevation loss: 900 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 15, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2669, 218, '16', NULL, 'Ripchet - Dobhan (1070 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p><p></p><p>After a fresh morning, the trail from&nbsp; Dobhan\r\nstarts with a gentle descent through oak and rhododendron forests. It then\r\nbecomes steeper and rockier as we move down into the valley, where the forest\r\ngradually opens up to reveal scenic views before reaching the tranquil village\r\nof Dobhan</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 40 m Elevation loss: 1260 m. 5/6 hours walking</b></p><p><b><b></b></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 16, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-08-27 19:20:28'),
(2670, 218, '17', NULL, 'Dobhan - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we drive to Kathmandu by jeep, depending on road conditions. The route follows the Budi Gandaki River down to Arughat or Soti Khola, then joins the main highway through Gorkha, Muglin and finally reaches Kathmandu. Itâ€™s a long but scenic journey through hills, rivers, and villages.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning.</b><br><b>Transport : 8/9 hour drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b></p><p></p>', 17, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-10-17 13:56:48'),
(2671, 218, '18', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 18, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-12-16 15:29:51'),
(2672, 218, '19', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 19, '2025-05-29 17:37:33', '2025-12-16 15:29:51'),
(2673, 245, '1', NULL, 'Arrival in Kathmandu (1350 m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-12-16 15:33:56'),
(2674, 245, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Machhakhola (900 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we drive from Kathmandu to Machhakhola (900 m)&nbsp;by jeep. We first follow the highway to Muglin, then head toward Arughat. After that, the road becomes rough and passes through villages like Soti Khola, following the Budi Gandaki River. The drive is scenic with hills, rivers and fields, ending at Machhakhola, the starting point of the Manaslu trek.</p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div></div></div></div></div><div><div></div></div></div><div><div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport: 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Machhakhola).</b></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 2, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-10-23 01:53:26'),
(2675, 245, '3', NULL, 'Machha Khola - Jagat (1,430 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b>After breakfast, we hike&nbsp;to Jagat &nbsp;following the Budi Gandaki River, crossing suspension bridges and passing small villages. The trail gently climbs through forests and farmland. After about 5â€“6 hours, you reach Jagat, a stone-paved village and the entry point to the Manaslu Conservation Area. The route offers nice river views and local village life.\r\n\r\n.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1100 m. Elevation\r\nloss: 700 m. 7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-08-27 19:24:25'),
(2676, 245, '4', NULL, 'Jagat- Eklebhati (1700 m) - Dyang (1800)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we starts with a gentle uphill walk through forests and small villages along the Budi Gandaki River. After crossing a suspension bridge, the trail continues to climb gradually. From Eklebhati, the path leads to <strong></strong>Dyang<strong></strong>, passing through terraced fields and local farms. The walk is peaceful and scenic, with views of surrounding hills and traditional villages.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1110\r\nm. Elevation loss: 760 m. 7.5 hours walking.</b><b></b></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-07-17 17:43:51'),
(2677, 245, '5', NULL, 'Dyang - Bhi Phedi (2050) - Namrung (2680)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Early morning, we hike with a gradual climb through forests and farmland, crossing a suspension bridge along the way. From Bhi Phedi, the trail becomes steeper as you continue ascending toward <strong></strong>Namrung<strong></strong>. Along the way, you pass traditional villages, terraced fields and enjoy beautiful mountain views. The hike is steady but rewarding, leading to Namrung, a charming village known for its rich culture and stunning scenery.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1340\r\nm. Elevation loss: 480 m. 6/5 hours&nbsp; walking.</b><b></b></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-07-20 13:42:41'),
(2678, 245, '6', NULL, 'Namrung - Syaula (3490 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>&nbsp;On the sixth day, we climb steady&nbsp; through forests and fields. As you go higher, the trees become fewer and you see beautiful mountains. After a few hours, you reach <strong>Syaula</strong>, a peaceful village perfect for resting and getting used to the altitude.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 1120 m.\r\nElevation loss: 240 m. 6 / 7 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-08-27 19:24:25'),
(2679, 245, '7', NULL, 'Syaula - Pugyen Gumba - Sama Gaon (3360)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><p>From Syaula,&nbsp; We trek&nbsp; through forests and yak pastures to the peaceful Pungyen Gumba, a serene monastery with close views of Mt. Manaslu. After visiting the Gumba, the path gradually descends and rejoins the main trail. Passing through alpine meadows, mani walls and small villages, the trail gently climbs to the beautiful village of Sama Gaon (3360m), rich in Tibetan culture and surrounded by majestic mountain scenery.&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 880 m. Elevation\r\nloss: 610 m. 5 / 6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-08-27 19:24:25'),
(2680, 245, '8', NULL, 'Samagaon - Lake Birendrea (3560 m) - Samdo (3690)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>After finishing breakfast, we walk a short, easy trail to <strong></strong>Lake Birendra,<strong></strong> a beautiful lake with great views of Manaslu. Then you return to the main path and continue to <strong></strong>Samdo<strong></strong>, a small mountain village good for rest and acclimatization.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 460 m. Elevation loss: 160 m. 3 to 4 hours walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 8, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-08-27 19:24:25'),
(2681, 245, '9', NULL, 'Samdo - Dharmasala (Larkya High Camp) (4300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we&nbsp; ascends through a barren, rocky valley with impressive views of surrounding snow-covered peaks. After crossing a wooden bridge over the Budhi Gandaki River, the path continues through alpine terrain, becoming increasingly rugged and remote. The walk is steady but not overly steep, passing through scattered yak pastures. After a few hours of trekking, you arrive at Dharmasala, also known as Larkya High Camp (4300 m), a basic resting point used by trekkers before crossing the challenging Larkya La Pass.</p></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 520 m. 4 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></p><p></p>', 9, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-08-27 19:24:25'),
(2682, 245, '10', NULL, 'Dharmasala - Larkya la / pass (5106 m) Bhimthang (3650 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we&nbsp; ascent\r\nalong the eastern side of the pass, start graduallyâ€”almost too\r\ngraduallyâ€”creating the illusion of little progress. Ahead, the striking Larkya\r\nPeak dominates the view. From this point and throughout the long descent across\r\na vast moraine, weâ€™re treated to&nbsp; beaufitul landscape views of the Peri Himal\r\nmountain cirque.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 750 m. Elevation\r\nloss: 1550 m. 7/9 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></p><p></p>', 10, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-08-27 19:24:25'),
(2683, 245, '11', NULL, 'Bhimthang - Tilje (2300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today\r\nmarks the final day of our Manaslu trek, featuring a long descent through the\r\nlower hills. We eventually cross a suspension bridge over the Marsyangdi River\r\nto arrive at the village of Dharapani. From there, we continue on foot along\r\nthe roadâ€”the only available routeâ€”to reach the picturesque village of Tal,\r\nknown for its scenic beauty. After passing through Tal, we descend further,\r\nbriefly leaving the road to cross a final suspension bridge and switch to the\r\nopposite side of the valley. A short walk along the road then brings us to the\r\nvillage of Jagat. This evening, we share our final moments with the portersâ€”a\r\nmeaningful time to reflect on the journey and celebrate the experiences weâ€™ve\r\nshared together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 100 m. Elevation\r\nloss: 1300 m. 5 / 6 hours&nbsp; walking.</b></p><p></p>', 11, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-08-27 19:24:25'),
(2684, 245, '12', NULL, 'Tilje - Dharapani (1900 m) - Jagat (1300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><p>On this day, we descends through lush forests and small settlements, crossing several suspension bridges along the way. After a short trek, you reach Dharapani (1900 m), a busy junction where the Annapurna and Manaslu trekking routes meet. Continuing downhill, the path follows the Marsyangdi River, passing through beautiful landscapes, waterfalls and terraced fields. The trail then leads to the village of Jagat (1300 m), a charming settlement with traditional stone houses and a relaxed atmosphere.</p></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 100\r\nm. Elevation loss: 1200 m. 6 hours walking.</b><b></b></p><p></p>', 12, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-07-25 15:22:18'),
(2685, 245, '13', NULL, 'Jagat - Kathamdnu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We set off\r\nearly in the morning by vehicle, heading toward Besisahar. After a drive of\r\nabout two to three hours, we arrive at the main road in Dumre, where we\r\ntransfer to a bus for the journey back to Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon.<br>Transport: 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Besisahar).</b></p><p></p>', 13, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-10-23 01:53:26'),
(2686, 245, '14', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 14, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-12-16 15:33:56'),
(2687, 245, '15', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 15, '2025-05-29 21:32:47', '2025-12-16 15:33:56'),
(2688, 246, '1', NULL, 'Arrival in Kathmandu (1,350 m). Transfer to hotel.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p>\r\n\r\n<div><b></b></div><p></p></div><p></p>', 1, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-12-16 15:36:47'),
(2689, 246, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Machha Khola (900 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today, we drive from Kathmandu to Machhakhola by jeep. We first follow the highway to Muglin, then head toward Arughat. After that, the road becomes rough and passes through villages like Soti Khola, following the Budi Gandaki River. The drive is scenic with hills, rivers and fields, ending at Machhakhola, the starting point of the Manaslu trek.</p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div></div></div></div></div><div><div></div></div></div><div><div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Machhakhola).</b></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 2, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-10-17 14:08:55'),
(2690, 246, '3', NULL, 'Machha Khola â€“ Jagat (1,430 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast, we hike to Jagat &nbsp;following the Budi Gandaki River, crossing suspension bridges and passing small villages. The trail gently climbs through forests and farmland. After about 5â€“6 hours, you reach Jagat, a stone-paved village and the entry point to the Manaslu Conservation Area. The route offers nice river views and local village life. .</p><p><b><b></b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1100 m. Elevation loss: 700 m. 7 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2691, 246, '4', NULL, 'Jagat â€“ Lokpa (2,040 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b>Today is a scenic journey that gradually leads deeper into the secluded Tsum Valley region. Starting from the stone-paved village of Jagat, the trail descends to cross a suspension bridge before climbing gently through terraced fields and lush subtropical forests. Along the way, trekkers pass through the picturesque village of Sirdibas and continue to Philim, a larger Gurung settlement known for its cultural charm and checkpoint for permits. From Philim, the route branches off from the main Manaslu Circuit and heads toward Tsum Valley. The path winds through dense pine forests, waterfalls and narrow gorges, offering a peaceful and immersive nature experience. After hours of trekking, you reach Lokpa, a small village perched on a ridge â€” the first entry point into the culturally rich and remote Tsum Valley.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :1150 m Elevation loss: 250 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2692, 246, '5', NULL, 'Lokpa â€“ Chumling (2,316 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b>Today, we&nbsp; starts with a steep descent through forest to a river, followed by a suspension bridge crossing. From there, the trail climbs steadily along a narrow gorge with waterfalls and views of Ganesh Himal. After several hours of uphill walking, you arrive at the traditional village of Chumling, rich in Tibetan culture and home to ancient monasteries.&nbsp;<b></b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain :250 m Elevation loss: 90 m. 3/4 hours walking<br></b></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-10-23 02:24:50'),
(2693, 246, '6', NULL, 'Chumling â€“ Chhokangparo (3,010 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b>Early morning, we start a steady but rewarding journey deeper into the heart of the Tsum Valley. As you leave Chumling, the trail starts with a gentle descent and crosses a long suspension bridge over the Shiar Khola. After the crossing, the trail gradually ascends through dense pine and rhododendron forests, with scattered mani walls and chortens hinting at the deep Buddhist culture of the region. You pass by small traditional villages and cultivated fields with barley and buckwheat, with the landscape opening up as you climb higher. The route offers striking views of Ganesh Himal and other snow-capped peaks as you approach the wider upper valley. After hours of trekking, you reach <strong></strong>Chhokangparo<strong></strong>, a picturesque twin village perched on a broad plateau. From here, youâ€™re greeted with sweeping mountain views and a warm welcome into a deeply spiritual, remote community.&nbsp;<b></b></p><p><b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :700 m Elevation loss: 200 m. 4/5 hours walking</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-10-23 02:24:50'),
(2694, 246, '7', NULL, 'Chhokangparo â€“ Chuleâ€“Nile (3,361 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>From Chhokangparo, we follows the Shiar Khola, passing mani walls and small villages. You first reach Chule, a traditional village with stone houses. Then, a short uphill walk takes you to Nile (3,361 m), the last village before the Tibetan border, known for its peaceful setting and mountain views.</p><p></p><div><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :300 m Elevation loss: 450 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b></p></div><p></p>', 7, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:31:34'),
(2695, 246, '8', NULL, 'Nile â€“ Mu Gompa (3,700 m) â€“ Lamagoun (3,300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, the trail gently ascends along the Shiar Khola, passing mani walls and yak pastures, with amazing views of Ganesh Himal. After&nbsp; hours, you reach <strong>Mu Gompa (3,700 m)</strong>, the highest and most spiritual monastery in Tsum Valley. After exploring the monastery and its surroundings, you retrace your steps downhill and continue past Nile to reach <strong></strong>Lamagoun&nbsp;for an overnight stay. The route blends scenic beauty with deep cultural experience.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain :350 m Elevation loss: 450 m. 5/6 hours walking</b><br></p><p></p>', 8, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2696, 246, '9', NULL, 'Lamagoun â€“ Ripchet (2,470 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today\'s trek is mostly downhill, passing through alpine meadows and forests. You follow the Shiar Khola, cross a suspension bridge and walk through pine and rhododendron woods. The trail is peaceful and lined with prayer flags and chortens. After a few hours, you reach <strong></strong>Ripchet<strong></strong>, a quiet village with traditional homes and farmland, offering a glimpse into the simple life of Tsum Valley.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain :100 m Elevation loss: 700 m. 4/5 hours walking</b><br></p><p></p>', 9, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2697, 246, '10', NULL, 'Rupchet â€“ Dyang (1,800 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we steep descent through dense forest and terraced fields. You retrace your steps toward Lokpa, crossing a suspension bridge and continuing along the trail that winds above the Budi Gandaki River. The path includes several ups and downs, passing small settlements and waterfalls along the way. As you lose elevation, the air gets warmer and the vegetation more lush. After several hours of trekking, you reach <strong></strong>Dyang<strong></strong>, a small village nestled in a narrow valley, surrounded by cliffs and forest. It offers a peaceful stop with views of waterfalls and the surrounding hills.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain :500 m Elevation loss: 1335 m. 5/7 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 10, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2698, 246, '11', NULL, 'Dyang - Bhi Phedi (2,050 m) - Namrung (2,680 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we starts with a gradual climb through mixed forests and terraced fields. After crossing a small suspension bridge, the trail continues uphill, passing traditional villages and farmland. From Bhi Phedi, the path becomes steeper as you ascend toward <strong></strong>Namrung, a larger village known for its beautiful mountain views and welcoming teahouses. Along the way, youâ€™ll enjoy scenic&nbsp; landscape of the surrounding peaks and valleys, making this section both challenging and rewarding.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain :1340 m Elevation loss: 480 m. 5/6 hours walking</b><br></p><p></p>', 11, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2699, 246, '12', NULL, 'Namrung - Syaula (3,490 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>After breakfast, we climb steady uphill&nbsp; through forests and terraced fields. As you go higher, the trees thin out and you see beautiful mountain views. After a few hours, you reach Syaula, a quiet village surrounded by amazing peaksâ€”perfect for resting and getting used to the altitude.</p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div></div></div></div></div><div><div></div></div></div><div></div></div><div><div><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :1120 m Elevation loss: 240 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b></div></div><p></p>', 12, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:32:47'),
(2700, 246, '13', NULL, 'Syaula - Pugyen Gumba - Sama Gaon (3,360 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>On this day, we hike you off the main trail on a scenic side route. You walk through alpine meadows and peaceful forests with perfect views of Manaslu and the surrounding peaks. After a few hours, you reach Pugyen Gumba, a small, serene monastery nestled in a quiet valley. After exploring the gompa, you return to the main trail and continue towards Sama Gaon. The path is gentle and scenic, passing chortens, mani walls and yak pastures. Sama Gaon is a large, traditional village at the foot of Manaslu, offering amazing views and rich Tibetan culture.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain :880 m Elevation loss: 610 m. 5/6 hours walking</b><br></p><p></p>', 13, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2701, 246, '14', NULL, 'Samagaon - Lake Birendra (3,560 m) - Samdo (3,690 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we start with a short detour. A gentle trail leads you to this beautiful glacial lake, located at the base of Manaslu. The turquoise water, set against snow-capped peaks, makes it a peaceful and scenic stop. After enjoying the lake, you return to the main trail and&nbsp; start ascending gradually toward Samdo. The path follows the Budi Gandaki River through yak pastures and wide alpine valleys. Along the way, youâ€™ll see mani walls, chortens and occasional wildlife. After&nbsp; hours of trekking, you reach Samdo, a windswept Tibetan village near the Tibetan border, ideal for acclimatization.\r\n\r\n<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain :460 m Elevation loss: 160 m. 3/4hours walking</b><br></p><p></p>', 14, '2025-05-30 12:21:19', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2702, 246, '15', NULL, 'Samdo - Dharmasala (Larkya High Camp) (4,300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today is a short but steady climb that prepares you for the Larkya La Pass. Leaving Samdo, the trail ascends gradually through a barren, windswept valley with&nbsp; landscape views of Manaslu, Samdo Peak and the Larkya Glacier. You cross a wooden bridge over a stream and continue along rocky trails and alpine meadows. As you gain elevation, the landscape becomes more rugged and dry. After hours of trekking, you reach Dharmasala, also known as Larkya Phedi, a basic overnight stop used by trekkers to rest and acclimatize before crossing the high pass.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :520 m Elevation loss: 00 m. 4 hours walking</b></p><p></p>', 15, '2025-05-30 12:21:20', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2703, 246, '16', NULL, 'Dharmasala - Larkya La (5,106 m) - Bhimthang (3,650 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After breakfast, we hike&nbsp; tough climb over rocky and snowy terrain, but offers amazing mountain views. After reaching the pass, you descend steeply for several hours to reach Bhimthang, a beautiful valley surrounded by peaks. Itâ€™s a long and challenging day,&nbsp;<br></p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :750 m Elevation loss: 1550 m. 7/9 hours walking.</b></p>', 16, '2025-05-30 12:21:20', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2704, 246, '17', NULL, 'Bhimthang - Tilje (2,300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p><b></b>Today is mostly downhill and much easier than previous days. The trail descends through alpine meadows, crosses wooden bridges, and passes through beautiful rhododendron and pine forests. Along the way, you enjoy views of Manaslu and other surrounding peaks. You pass small villages like Kharche and Gho before finally reaching Tilje, a charming Gurung village with terraced fields and traditional houses. The trek offers a peaceful end to the high-altitude adventure.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain :100 m Elevation loss: 1200 m. 6/7 hours walking</b><br></p><p></p>', 17, '2025-05-30 12:21:20', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2705, 246, '18', NULL, 'Tilje - Dharapani (1,900 m) - Jagat (1,300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we start with a short descent through forests and farmlands. You cross a suspension bridge and pass through several small villages before joining the main Annapurna Circuit trail at <strong></strong>Dharapani<strong></strong>. From there, the trail continues downhill along the Marsyangdi River, passing waterfalls, stone-paved paths, and charming settlements. After hours of easy trekking, you arrive at <strong></strong>Jagat<strong></strong>, marking the end of your Manaslu Circuit journey.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain :100 m Elevation loss: 1300 m. 5/6 hours walking</b><br></p><p></p>', 18, '2025-05-30 12:21:20', '2025-08-27 19:30:28'),
(2706, 246, '19', NULL, 'Jagat â€“ Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p>An early morning vehicle transfer departs for Besisahar. From Besisahar, you will change vehicles and continue the journey back to Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Elevation gain :100 m Elevation loss: 700 m. </b><br><b>Transport : 7/8 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b><br></p><p></p>', 19, '2025-05-30 12:21:20', '2025-10-17 14:08:55'),
(2707, 246, '20', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 20, '2025-05-30 12:21:20', '2025-12-16 15:36:47'),
(2708, 246, '21', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p></p><p></p></div><div><div><i></i></div></div><br>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 21, '2025-05-30 12:21:20', '2025-12-16 15:37:53'),
(2709, 141, '20', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>', 20, '2025-06-01 17:46:58', '2025-12-23 15:44:59'),
(2710, 152, '12', NULL, 'Lama Hotel - Thulo Syabru (2130 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We follow the same trail back down through the Langtang\r\nValley. The descent is more relaxed and reveals new angles of the scenery we\r\npreviously climbed through.This evening, we share our final moments with\r\nthe portersâ€”a meaningful time to reflect on the journey and celebrate the\r\nexperiences weâ€™ve shared together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nElevation gain: 760 m . Elevation loss: 940 m. 5/7 hours\r\nWalking.</b></p><p></p>', 12, '2025-06-02 19:35:43', '2025-08-27 19:52:09'),
(2711, 152, '13', NULL, 'Thulo Shyabru â€“  Dunche - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Starting\r\nyour day from Thulo Shyabru, you trek downhill through beautiful forests and\r\ntraditional villages to reach Dunche, the administrative center of Rasuwa\r\nDistrict. After arriving in Dunche, redrive to Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>\r\n\r\nTransport : 6 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu)</b></p><p></p>', 13, '2025-06-02 19:35:43', '2025-10-18 12:42:37'),
