(2717, 169, '19', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 19, '2025-06-05 14:54:48', '2025-12-16 16:19:26'),
(2718, 240, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-12-16 16:00:01'),
(2719, 240, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani  (1860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Early morning departure to Besisahar. This route main highway between Nepal and India, we allow till Mugling. Throughout passing numerous villages we arrive to Besisahar to change the jeeps. After Besisahar, the road then turns into a stony track, a little bumpy but bordered by beautiful landscapes of rice fields and traditional Nepalese villages. A few landslides can sometimes delay us or force us to change vehicles several times; Faced with these little daily adventures, it is wise to follow the example of the Nepalese who maintain a smile and good humor... We finally arrive at the Dharapani. Installation at the lodge.</p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Transport: 6 hours drive (Besi Sahar). 3 hours jeep (Dharapani)</b></div><p></p>', 2, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-10-18 15:31:31'),
(2720, 240, '3', NULL, 'Dharapani - Koto (2620 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Today the trail follows the Marsyangdi River and passes through the village of Bagarchhap, where Tibetan-style houses start to appear and the views of Annapurna II start to open up. After a short walk, you reach Danakyu, a forested village from where the trail climbs steeply to Timang, an amazing viewpoint offering views of Manaslu and Annapurna II. The path then descends gently through forests to Thanchowk, a peaceful settlement, and continues on an easier trail to Koto, a quiet village that also serves as the entry point to the Nar Phu Valley. Koto has a checkpost and basic lodges, making it a convenient overnight stop.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 705 m. Elevation loss: 313 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 3, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2721, 240, '4', NULL, 'Koto - Meta (3560 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we move forward,\r\nwith Annapurna II standing tall above Koto, seemingly guarding the entrance to\r\nthe Naar-Phu Valley. We leave the Marsyangdi Valley behind, crossing a narrow\r\nsuspension bridge and continuing along a rocky path carved into the cliffside.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From here, our route follows the Naar Khola river; in\r\nthis constricted portion of the gorge, the trail often alternates from one bank\r\nof the river to the other. The day concludes with a final push, an uphill climb\r\nof 200 metres through a series of switchbacks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> <b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1200 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 5/7hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2722, 240, '5', NULL, 'Meta - Kyang (3840 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>On the 5th day the trial leads you deeper into the remote and wild Nar Phu Valley. Starting from Meta, the trail follows a rugged and narrow path along the side of a deep gorge, with dramatic views of jagged cliffs and snow-covered peaks. Youâ€™ll cross several suspension bridges over the roaring Phu Khola and pass through isolated yak pastures and seasonal herder shelters. The landscape becomes more barren and high-altitude as you approach Kyang, a former Khampa settlement with wide open spaces and ruins of old stone buildings. With no permanent villages along the way, the route offers a true sense of wilderness and solitude.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 500 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 5, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2723, 240, '6', NULL, 'Kyang - Phu (4100 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, youâ€™ll see Buddhist chortens and mani\r\nstones, showing the area\'s deep spiritual heritage. The valley narrows again\r\nuntil we reach the Phu gate, then the trail drops down to the riverbed. We\r\nvisit Tashi Lhakhang Monastery, a sacred site believed to have been visited by\r\nGuru Rinpoche (Padmasambhava).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 400 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 3/5 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 6, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2724, 240, '7', NULL, 'Phu â€“ Mahendra Pul (3840 m) (Sartek Thrangu Gomba)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, we descend through rocky gorges and past the herder settlement of Kyang and Jhunam. The trail crosses a suspension bridge over the Phu Khola before reaching Mahendra Pul, a quiet riverside spot near Sartek Thrangu Gomba, ideal for rest before continuing toward Nar.</p><p>A<b>ccommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><b></b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 700 m. 3/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2725, 240, '8', NULL, 'Mahendra Pul - Tibetan village of Naar (4200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we&nbsp; start with a bridge crossing and a steady uphill climb through a dry, rugged valley. The trail passes chortens and mani walls, offering views of Pisang Peak and Kang Guru, before reaching the traditional Tibetan village of Naar, known for its rich culture and ancient monasteries.&nbsp;</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><b></b><br><b>Elevation gain: 600 m. Elevation loss: 00 m. 4 hours walking.</b></p><p></p>', 8, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2726, 240, '9', NULL, 'Naar - Khang La Pass (5313 m) - Ngawal (3660 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, the day\r\nstarts with early in the morning, the path gradually climb towards the Kangla\r\npass. Gaining more altitude, more you\'ll be rewarded with unparalleled views of\r\nthe Himalayan peaks. The pass will be pretty challenging as well steep descent\r\nafter pass to Ngawal.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1250 m. Elevation loss: 1600 m. 10 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 9, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-07-14 16:05:28'),
(2727, 240, '10', NULL, 'Ngawal - Braga Monastery (3519 m) - Manang (3542 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast we follows a scenic, gradually descending trail. Leaving Ngawal, the path winds through open alpine terrain with scattered juniper trees, mani walls, and sweeping views of Annapurna III and Gangapurna. After about 1.5 hours, we reach the historic village of Braga, home to a 600-year-old monastery perched on a cliffâ€”well worth a short visit for its spiritual ambiance and amazing views. From Braga, the trail becomes easy and mostly flat, following the Marsyangdi River until we reach Manang, a vibrant village and key acclimatization stop on the Annapurna Circuit.</p><div>&nbsp;<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>&nbsp;Elevation gain: 140 m. Elevation loss: 273 m. 4 hours walking.</b></div><p></p>', 10, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2728, 240, '11', NULL, 'Ice Lake (4610 m) (Kicho Tal): Panorama of the Annapurnas / Rest and acclimatization day in Manang', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Starting from Braga or the small hamlet of Manang, the trail climbs steeply through alpine meadows. Due to the high elevation and rugged terrain, the path can be difficult to follow. The highlight of this trek is a Beautiful glacier lake with crystal-clear turquoise waters that beautifully reflect the surrounding peaks. From here, youâ€™ll enjoy landscape views of Gangapurna and the Annapurna range, including Annapurna II, III, and IV. As an option, Gangapurna Lake offers a shorter and easier alternative for a quick visit or acclimatization, requiring less effort to reach.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 1100 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 7 hours  walking.</b></div><p></p>', 11, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2729, 240, '12', NULL, 'Manang - Ledar (4217 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today is a short, easy trek to help your body adjust to the altitude. Youâ€™ll walk through dry, rocky high-altitude desert land, very different from forests and meadows. Along the way, you might see eagles, marmots, yaks, and blue sheep. The slow pace lets you enjoy mountain views and rest before the next climb.</p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 720 m. Elevation loss: 56 m. 4.5 hours walking.</b></div><p></p><p></p>', 12, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2730, 240, '13', NULL, 'Ledar - Thorung Phedi (4500m), at the bottom of Thorong La', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today is another short but important day on the Annapurna Circuit. This trek brings you closer to the challenging Thorong La Pass (5,416 m), one of the highest trekking passes in the world. Along the way, youâ€™ll enjoy beautiful views of snow-capped peaks, glacial rivers, and the dry, high-altitude landscape. Mountains like Thorong Peak (6,144 m) and Khatung Kang (6,484 m) tower on the horizon, adding to the thrill of this stage.</p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon  evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 380 m. Elevation loss: 71 m. 3 hours  walking.</b></div><p></p>', 13, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2731, 240, '14', NULL, 'Thorung Phedi - Thorong La pass (5416 m) - Muktinath (3760 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Starting vary early, youâ€™ll climb steeply but steadily to Thorong La Pass at 5,416 meters, one of the highest trekking passes in the world. At the top, youâ€™ll see colorful prayer flags, a Buddhist stupa, and piles of stones made by trekkers. Take a break to enjoy the amazing views of snowy mountains and valleys. After the pass, the trail goes down sharply to Chabarbu, passing meadows and a deep gorge before going up a little again. Then the path gets wider as you reach Muktinath, a sacred place for both Buddhists and Hindus, known for its old temple and natural springs believed to have healing powers. This day is tough but very special.Elevation gain: 912 m.</p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 912 m. Elevation loss: 1691m. 8 hours  walking.</b></div><p></p>', 14, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-08-27 20:18:03'),
(2732, 240, '15', NULL, 'Muktinath - Lupra (3000 m) â€“ Drive to Tatopani  (1200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Today is an important day as you spend the morning near Mount Dhaulagiri. After leaving Muktinath, the trail goes to the small, old village of Lupra, avoiding the main road. This area has some of the last BÃ¶n monasteries, an ancient religion before Buddhism. To reach Lupra, you go down a steep path into a riverbed. From there, you take a three-hour jeep ride to Tatopani, a busy town by the Kali Gandaki River. Tatopani means â€œhot waterâ€ in Nepali because of its natural hot springs, where you can relax for a small fee of 150 rupees. Donâ€™t forget your swimming gear !</p><div><div>\r\n\r\n<div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></div><div><b>Transport: 3 hours drive by jeep (Tatopani).</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 5 hours walking.</b></div></div></div><p></p>', 15, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-10-18 15:31:32'),
(2733, 240, '16', NULL, 'Tatopani - Pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We drive to Pokhara&nbsp; for your lunch. You can explore the city. It&nbsp; is a beautiful city for tourists. There is a big lake,\r\nmountain views, and many fun things to do like boating, paragliding, and short\r\ntreks. The city is peaceful, clean, and good for relaxing or exploring nature.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Transport: 4/5 hours driving by jeep (Pokhara).</b></p><p></p>', 16, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-10-16 16:38:36'),
(2734, 240, '17', NULL, 'Pokhara - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>After breakfast, you will drive back to Kathmandu. The scenic journey along the Prithvi Highway takes approximately six to seven hours</p><p></p><div><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b></div><div><b>Transport: 3 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).</b></div><p></p>', 17, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-10-18 15:31:32'),
(2735, 240, '18', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 18, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-12-16 16:00:01'),
(2736, 240, '19', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 19, '2025-06-06 16:30:59', '2025-12-16 16:00:01'),
(2737, 254, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport: 20 M drive hotel</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-06-06 19:11:20', '2025-12-16 16:02:30'),
(2738, 254, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani  (1860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We leave early in the morning for Besisahar, taking the main\r\nhighway that connects Nepal and India, up to Mugling. Along the way, we pass\r\nmany villages before reaching Besisahar, where we switch to jeeps. From there,\r\nthe road becomes rough and rocky, but the views of rice fields and traditional\r\nvillages make the ride beautiful. Landslides can sometimes delay us or require\r\nchanging vehicles, but like the locals, it\'s best to stay positive and keep\r\nsmiling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport: 6 hour drive (Besi Sahar) + 3 hours off road.</b><br></p><p></p>', 2, '2025-06-06 19:11:20', '2025-10-18 16:09:04'),
(2739, 254, '3', NULL, 'Dharapani - Koto (2620 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'After breakfast, we start to climb a steep trail to Timang, where the wide Marsyangdi Gorge ends. The path then becomes easier, and the landscape changes from thick pine forests to drier hills. After Besisahar, Chame is the largest village in the region and serves as the district headquarters of Manang.\r\n\r\nAccommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.\r\nElevation gain: 705 m. Elevation loss: 313 m. 5/6 hours walking.<div><p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 705 m. Elevation loss: 313 m. 5/6 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p></div>', 3, '2025-06-06 19:13:52', '2025-08-27 20:22:20'),
(2740, 254, '4', NULL, 'Koto - Meta (3560 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The towering peaks feel distant as we move forward,\r\nwith Annapurna II standing tall above Koto, seemingly guarding the entrance to\r\nthe Naar-Phu Valley. We leave the Marsyangdi Valley behind, crossing a narrow\r\nsuspension bridge and continuing along a rocky path carved into the cliffside.</p><p>From here, our route follows the Naar Khola river; in\r\nthis constricted portion of the gorge, the trail often alternates from one bank\r\nof the river to the other. The day concludes with a final push, an uphill climb\r\nof 200 metres through a series of switchbacks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1200 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 5/7 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-06-06 19:13:53', '2025-08-27 20:22:20'),
(2741, 254, '5', NULL, 'Meta - Kyang (3840 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We depart\r\nfrom Meta\'s little plateau, which boasts a beautiful views. The trail winds\r\nthrough an open valley and climbs gradually. As it transitions into a\r\nhigh-altitude, arid desert, the terrain gets more rugged and has fewer trees.\r\nKnown locally as Kharka, we pass a number of abandoned towns that were once\r\nutilized as makeshift shelters by Tibetan yak herders and traders. Rare animals\r\nlike blue sheep and even snow leopards can be seen in this valley.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 500 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 4/5 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-06-06 19:13:53', '2025-08-27 20:22:20'),
(2747, 254, '11', NULL, 'Besisahar - Kathamandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Once breakfast is finished, you will drive back to Kathmandu.\r\nApproximately six or seven hours are needed to finish this picturesque drive along the Prithvi Highway.\r\n<b></b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning.</b><br><b>Transport: 4 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b><br><p></p>', 11, '2025-06-06 19:22:40', '2025-10-18 16:09:04'),
(2750, 254, '6', NULL, 'Kyang - Phu (4100 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Along the way, youâ€™ll see Buddhist chortens and mani\r\nstones, showing the area\'s deep spiritual heritage. The valley narrows again\r\nuntil we reach the Phu gate, then the trail drops down to the riverbed. We\r\nvisit Tashi Lhakhang Monastery, a sacred site believed to have been visited by\r\nGuru Rinpoche (Padmasambhava).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 400 m. Elevation loss: 200 m. 3/5 hours walking.<br><br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 6, '2025-06-06 19:22:41', '2025-08-27 20:22:20'),
(2751, 254, '7', NULL, 'Phu â€“ Mahendra Pul (3840 m) (Sartek Thrangu Gomba)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The trail from Phu Gaon to Nar is both challenging and\r\nrewarding, with steep climbs, deep gorges, high plateaus, and striking rock\r\nformations. These remote villages offer a peaceful spiritual atmosphere and a\r\nrare mix of natural beauty, rich culture, and adventureâ€”making the journey\r\ntruly unforgettable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 700 m. 3/5 hours walking.</b></p><p></p><p></p>', 7, '2025-06-06 19:22:41', '2025-08-27 20:22:20'),
(2752, 254, '8', NULL, 'Mahendra Pul - Tibetan village of Naar (4200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>You start a steep climb at first and gradually smooth with spectacular\r\nviews of snow-capped peaks like Kang Guru, and Pisang Peak. Tibetan-style chortens, prayer walls, and mani stones along the trail.\r\nAfternoon free day. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 600 m. Elevation loss: 00 m. 4 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 8, '2025-06-06 19:22:41', '2025-08-27 20:22:20'),
(2753, 254, '9', NULL, 'Naar - Khang La Pass (5313 m) - Ngawal (3660 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>The day\r\nstarts with early in the morning, the path gradually climb towards the Kangla\r\npass. Gaining more altitude, more you\'ll be rewarded with unparalleled views of\r\nthe Himalayan peaks. The pass will be pretty challenging as well steep descent\r\nafter pass to Ngawal.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 1250 m. Elevation loss: 1600 m. 10 hours&nbsp; walking.<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 9, '2025-06-06 19:22:41', '2025-07-12 22:16:38'),
(2754, 254, '10', NULL, 'Ngawal - Gyaru (3720 m) - Pisang (3200 m) - Drive to Besisahar (760 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>From the\r\nbeautiful village Ngawal, you hike up and down along a balcony trail that\r\noffers panoramic mountain views. At Gyaru, you can see traditional\r\nTibetan-style houses and enjoy the peaceful atmosphere. After taking in the\r\nscenery, you walk downhill to reach Pisang. This part of the trail passes\r\nthrough forests and continues to offer beautiful views of the mountains. From\r\nPisang, you take a jeep and drive to Besisahar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Transport: 4 hours drive by jeep (\r\n\r\nBesisahar).<br>Elevation gain: 200 m. Elevation loss: 300 m. 3 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 10, '2025-06-06 19:22:41', '2025-10-18 16:09:04'),
(2756, 254, '12', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 12, '2025-06-06 19:22:41', '2025-12-16 16:02:30'),
(2757, 254, '13', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 13, '2025-06-06 19:22:41', '2025-12-16 16:02:30'),
(2758, 184, '10', NULL, 'Chitawan National Park - Safari - Tharu Village', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start your day with a thrilling jungle\r\nsafari in Chitwan National Park to see rhinos, deer, and more. Visit a Tharu\r\nvillage to experience local culture, then enjoy a boat ride on the Rapti River,\r\nspotting crocodiles and birds. End with a traditional Tharu dance and dinner,\r\nfollowed by a cozy overnight stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 10, '2025-06-08 15:16:25', '2025-07-20 22:53:30'),
(2759, 184, '11', NULL, 'Chitawan National Park - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start your day with a morning safari\r\nor nature walk in Chitwan National Park to catch any wildlife you may have\r\nmissed. After breakfast, begin your drive back to Kathmandu (Approx. 200km from\r\nKathmandu), enjoying the changing landscapes along the way. Arrive in Kathmandu\r\nby evening and relax, reflecting on your amazing wildlife adventure and\r\ncultural experiences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transport : Around 5/6 hours drive.</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 11, '2025-06-08 15:16:25', '2025-10-16 22:13:21'),
(2760, 184, '12', NULL, 'Bhaktapur - Changu Narayan - Nagarkot', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Explore the ancient city of Bhaktapur to start your day in Kathmandu\r\n(Approx. 15km from Kathmandu). Admire its gorgeous Newari architecture, its\r\ncharming squares, and its well-known 55-window castle. Next, proceed to Changu\r\nNarayan, one of the oldest Hindu temples in Nepal, which is situated on a hill\r\nwith stunning views of the valley (Approx. 6km from Bhaktapur). Observe the\r\nHimalayas and an incredible sunset when you visit Nagarkot in the afternoon.\r\nRelax and enjoy the stunning mountain view while spending the night in Nagarkot\r\n(Approx. 20km from Changu Narayan).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transport : Around 8/9 hours drive.</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 12, '2025-06-08 15:16:25', '2025-10-16 22:13:21'),
(2761, 184, '13', NULL, 'Nagarkot - Dhulikhel - Panauti - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Enjoy amazing Himalayan views as you\r\nbegin your day with a refreshing sunrise in Nagarkot. After that, take a journey\r\nto Dhulikhel, a beautiful village renowned for its expansive views and lively\r\nculture (Approx. 25km from Nagarkot). Head to Panauti, a historic town renowned\r\nfor its ancient temples and typical Newari architecture, explore its charming\r\nalleys and nearby temples (Approx. 10km from Dhulikhel). Return to Kathmandu by\r\nevening after enjoying the peaceful surroundings, capping a day rich in\r\nhistory, culture, and magnificent scenery (Approx. 35km from Panauti).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transport : Around 5/6 hours drive.</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 13, '2025-06-08 15:16:25', '2025-10-16 22:13:21'),
(2762, 184, '14', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Patan - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start your day in Kathmandu and travel\r\na short distance to Patan (Approx. 6km from Kathmandu), a historic city\r\nrenowned for its rich cultural heritage, art, and beautifully preserved\r\narchitecture. Explore Patan Durbar Square and pay a visit to the Patan Museum,\r\nthe Golden Temple, and ancient temples. Explore tiny lanes rich with local\r\nculture and traditional crafts. After taking in the cultural charm, head back\r\nto Kathmandu in the evening, having gained a greater understanding of the\r\nhistory of the Kathmandu Valley.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel, Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Transport : Around 4/5 hours drive.</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 14, '2025-06-08 15:16:25', '2025-10-16 22:13:21'),
(2763, 184, '15', NULL, 'Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>According to your flight schedule the\r\ngrand departure. We will come to drive you to the airport.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 15, '2025-06-08 15:16:25', '2025-06-08 19:24:15'),
(2764, 214, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Your happy holiday starts in Kathmandu. You will have time to freshen up before briefing with guide in the late afternoon. According to the time, you can walk/drive to Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) and from here watch your first Nepali sunset over the Kathmandu Valley, from the oldest stupas. This is one of the most Important world heritage sites of Nepal and an important center for Buddhism in Nepal.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-06-08 20:03:53', '2025-10-17 12:20:32'),
(2765, 214, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Chitwan', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today, we&nbsp; drive to Chitwan (Sauraha). The route follows the Prithvi Highway via Thankot, Naubise, and Mugling, then turns south toward Narayanghat and Bharatpur before reaching Sauraha. It\'s a scenic journey through hills, rivers, and finally into the Chitwan.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 6/7 hours by jeep.</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2025-06-08 20:03:53', '2025-10-17 12:20:32'),
(2766, 214, '3', NULL, 'Canoe Ride, Jungle Walk and Jeep Safari', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Enjoy a\r\npeaceful deep-water canoe ride on the Rapti River to start your day, where you\r\nmight see marsh mugger crocodiles and beautiful aquatic birds passing by.\r\nProceed on a guided jungle walk through the verdant forest, where you can spot\r\nmonkeys, deer, rhinos, and a wide variety of plants. Experience a thrilling\r\njeep safari deep into Chitwan National Park in the afternoon, where you may\r\ncome across sloth bears, one-horned rhinos, wild boars, and possibly even the\r\nelusive Bengal tiger. Visit Tharu village to experience the unique culture and\r\ntraditions of this indigenous community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2025-06-08 20:03:53', '2025-08-27 18:15:25'),
(2767, 214, '4', NULL, 'Chitwan - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start your\r\nmorning with a leisurely stroll around the beautiful surroundings with a local\r\nexpert to see birds. Chitwan is home to more than 500 distinct bird species,\r\nsuch as dancing peacocks, elegant egrets and vibrant hornbills. Next, proceed\r\nin the direction of Kathmandu after having a breakfast. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 6/7 hours drive by Jeep (Kathmandu)</b><br></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-06-08 20:03:53', '2025-10-17 12:20:32'),
(2768, 214, '5', NULL, 'Kathamandu - Souvenirs day sightseeing day or free day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Among the\r\noptions, if you are heading for sightseeing, this day-day cultural tour will\r\noffer you a well-rounded experience of Kathmandu\'s history, spirituality and\r\nart while being guided by an expert, certified guide who can enrich your\r\nunderstanding of the city\'s unique heritage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;here\'s a\r\nsuggested itinerary and price that balances history, culture, and local\r\nexperiences. Maximum visited only three sites in day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\nSwayambunath\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\nBhaktapur</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\nBoudhanath</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\nPatan\r\nDarbar square</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\nKathmandu\r\nDarbar square</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;In this price, an\r\nexpert and certified cultural and tour guide a vehicle reserved and a\r\nprofessional driver for whole during the sightseeing. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>2-3 pp 70â‚¬.&nbsp; 4-6 pp 50â‚¬.&nbsp; 7-10 pp 35â‚¬.&nbsp; 11-15+ 30â‚¬.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-06-08 20:03:53', '2025-08-27 18:15:25'),
(2769, 214, '6', NULL, 'Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>According to\r\nyour flight schedule the grand departure. We will come to drive you to the\r\nairport. </p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning.</b></p><p></p>', 6, '2025-06-08 20:03:53', '2025-08-27 18:15:25'),
(2770, 178, '1', NULL, 'Welcome to Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Your happy holiday starts in Kathmandu. You will have time to freshen up before briefing with guide in the late afternoon. According to the time, you can walk/drive to Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) and from here watch your first Nepali sunset over the Kathmandu Valley, from the oldest stupas. This is one of the most Important world heritage sites of Nepal and an important center for Buddhism in Nepal.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-06-08 21:04:49', '2025-10-16 19:46:16'),
(2771, 178, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Self Visit Swayambunath Stupa', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After\r\nbreakfast, enjoy a day tour of Kathmanduâ€™s cultural gems. Visit the hilltop\r\nSwayambhunath Stupa for sweeping valley views, then explore the sacred\r\nPashupatinath Temple and the peaceful, prayer-flag-lined Boudhanath Stupa. Wrap\r\nup with a walk through the historic Kathmandu Durbar Square before returning to\r\nthe hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included morning, noon, evening</b></p><p></p>', 2, '2025-06-08 21:04:49', '2025-09-24 17:18:59'),
(2772, 178, '3', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Bardia', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>A 50-minute\r\nflight to Nepalgunj and a 2-3 hour drive to Thakurdwara, the primary entrance\r\nto Bardia National Park, are the fastest routes to Bardia from Kathmandu. The\r\ntrip provides travelers with a quick, cozy, and picturesque option and takes\r\nabout 3 to 4 hours in total. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Or, it takes\r\nabout 12 to 15 hours to drive from Kathmandu to Bardia in a private vehicle.\r\nThe route travels through the beautiful Terai region of Nepal for approximately\r\n580 km. Even though the trip is lengthy, it\'s reasonably priced and allows you\r\nto take in a variety of scenery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included morning, noon, evening</b></p><p></p>', 3, '2025-06-08 21:04:49', '2025-09-24 17:18:59'),
(2773, 178, '4', NULL, 'Bardia - Bardia National Park on a full board plan', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Spend the\r\nday exploring the wilderness of Bardia National Park on a full board plan.\r\nEnjoy thrilling jungle activities like jeep safaris, nature walks, and wildlife\r\nspotting, all while surrounded by pristine nature. Return in the evening to\r\nyour hotel or resort for a relaxing overnight stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-06-08 21:04:49', '2025-09-24 17:18:59'),
(2774, 178, '5', NULL, 'Bardia â€“ Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After\r\nbreakfast, start your return journey to Kathmandu with a local bus ride, a\r\nscenic drive of around 8 hours through the lowlands and hills of Nepal. Upon\r\narrival in the evening, check into your hotel.&nbsp;Or, Have a\r\nflight</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel, Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></p><p><b>Transport : 8 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-06-08 21:04:49', '2025-10-16 19:46:16'),
(2775, 178, '6', NULL, 'Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>According to your flight schedule the\r\ngrand departure. We will come to drive you to the airport.</p><p></p>', 6, '2025-06-08 21:04:49', '2025-09-24 17:18:59'),
(2776, 128, '19', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 19, '2025-06-10 14:24:21', '2025-12-16 15:40:32'),
(2777, 144, '18', NULL, 'Pokhara - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Once breakfast is finished, you will drive back to\r\nKathmandu. Approximately six or seven hours are needed to finish this\r\npicturesque drive along the Prithvi Highway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning<br>Transport : 6/7 hours drive by jeep (Kathmandu).<b></b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p></p>', 18, '2025-06-10 16:50:42', '2025-10-18 12:20:14'),
(2778, 144, '19', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 19, '2025-06-10 16:50:42', '2025-12-16 15:43:40'),
