(2781, 256, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>Your happy holiday starts in Kathmandu. You will have time to freshen up before briefing with guide in the late afternoon. According to the time, you can walk/drive to Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) and from here watch your first Nepali sunset over the Kathmandu Valley, from the oldest stupas. This is one of the most Important world heritage sites of Nepal and an important center for Buddhism in Nepal.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-10-16 19:34:41'),
(2782, 256, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Pokhara (860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>Drive early from Kathmandu to Pokhara, a peaceful lakeside city with views of the Annapurna range. It\'s a great place to relax and prepare for your trek. The region is home to Magars, Gurungs and Thakalisâ€”known for their farming, bravery as Gurkhas, and business skills. After arrival, you may have time to enjoy a boat ride on the lake, explore shops with Nepali and Tibetan items or relax in one of the many cafÃ©s. Trekking gear is also easy to find in local stores.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Transport : 6 hours drive (Pokhara).</b><br></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><p></p>', 2, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-10-16 19:34:41'),
(2783, 256, '3', NULL, 'Pokhara - Jomsom (2700 m) - Kagbeni (3710 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast your bike and luggage will be transferred to Pokharaâ€™s airport for a short, scenic 25-minute flight to Jomsom. On arrival, the crew will help set up the bikes before starting the first ride along the Kali Gandaki River towards Kagbeni, the gateway to Upper Mustang. In Kagbeni, you can explore its narrow alleyways and even stop at the famous Yak Donaldâ€™s for a yak burger and local apple cider.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 25 minutes flight (Jhomsom).</b><br><b>Elevation Gain: 250.Cycling distance:10 KM.</b><br></p><p></p>', 3, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-10-16 19:34:41'),
(2785, 256, '4', NULL, 'Kagbeni - Muktinath (3710m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, you will begin the uphill ride to Muktinath. With the altitude and steep climbs, the journey may take up to three hours, but the ride offers incredible views of Dhaulagiri and Nilgiri. On arrival, youâ€™ll have time for a short hike to visit the famous Hindu temple at Muktinath.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1100 m. Elevation loss: 80 m. (2 option upper one is 21km)10 km.</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 22:03:15'),
(2786, 256, '5', NULL, 'Muktinath - Samar (3490m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After breakfast, the real adventure starts today with an early start to enjoy the best views. After leaving Muktinath, youâ€™ll pass through a village before climbing to the Gyu La Pass at 4,066 m. From the top, a thrilling 1,200 m descent on technical single track takes you to Chhusang, where youâ€™ll cross the Kali Gandaki and begin one of the toughest climbs of the trip to reach Samar. Now in Upper Mustang, the terrain is remote, and the accommodation becomes more basic, but the scenery is truly beautiful.</p><div><div></div><div><div></div></div></div><div></div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1300 M. Elevation loss: 1200 m. 7/8 hours biking 29 km.</b></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 21:56:20'),
(2787, 256, '6', NULL, 'Samar - Ghami (3560m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\nDay six takes you over five high passes above 3,800 m: Bhena La, Yamdo La, Syanboch La, Nya La, and Ghami La. The trail is challenging but less steep than the climb to Samar, with a mix of uphills and fast downhill sections. After a lunch stop in Ghiling, itâ€™s about two more hours to Ghami, with a 5 km climb followed by a long descent to the teahouse.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1120 M. Elevation loss: 920 m. Biking : 28 km.</b><br><br></p><p></p>', 6, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 22:03:52'),
(2788, 256, '7', NULL, 'Ghami - Lo manthang (3840m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\nTodayâ€™s ride is more than 50% single track, crossing two high passes: Chogo La (4,280 m, the highest of the trip) and Mui La (4,170 m). From the teahouse, youâ€™ll ride or hike along trekking trails to Dhakmar, then climb towards Ghargumba where the single track begins. Some rocky sections may require pushing, but they soon give way to a flowy ride all the way to Lo Manthang. After checking into the teahouse, youâ€™ll have time to explore the ancient walled city, visit the Kingâ€™s Palace, and enjoy the colorful village with its rich history and stunning views.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1050M. Elevation loss: 820 m. Biking 21 km.</b></p><p></p>', 7, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 21:56:20'),
(2789, 256, '8', NULL, 'Lo mangthang - Chusar cave - Lomangthang', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\nAfter five days of riding, todayâ€™s ride is optional. You can cycle to Kamaling, a village above Lo Manthang near the Chinese border, perfect for scenic photos. The ride also includes a visit to Garphu to see ancient cave dwellings and a monastery once home to Tibetan residents. On a clear day, youâ€™ll enjoy panoramic views of Nilgiri and the Annapurna Mountains while passing through villages that feel untouched by time.\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 650 m. Elevation loss: 620 m. 4/5 hours biking 21 km.</b><br><br></p><p></p>', 8, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 21:56:20'),
(2790, 256, '9', NULL, 'Lo mangthang - Yara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<div><div><div><div><div><div><p>The day starts with a climb to Lo Pass (4,000 m) for beautiful views of Lo Manthang, followed by a loose, steep, and fun descent to Dhee village at 3,400 m. From there, youâ€™ll follow the riverbed and climbs to reach Yara, your overnight stop. Yara is a small village with limited teahouses, but if you have energy, you can take an optional 4 km ride up to Ghara village, all above 3,500 m.</p></div></div></div></div><div></div><div><div></div></div></div></div><div></div>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 720 m. Elevation loss: 790 m. 4/5 hours biking 17 km.</b></p><p></p>', 9, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 22:05:51'),
(2791, 256, '10', NULL, 'Yara - Tange', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nThe day begins with a short climb and rolling trails leading to Dhey Khola at 3,400 m, with a steep, loose-rock descent at the end. After crossing the river, youâ€™ll stop for lunch before riding or hike-a-biking up to a 3,900 m pass. From there, enjoy an exciting descent into Tange village, finishing with a fast and fun ride through a canyon on loose terrain.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 850 m. Elevation loss: 1100 m. 18 km.</b><br><br></p><p></p>', 10, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 21:56:20'),
(2792, 256, '11', NULL, 'Tange - Chusang', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nStarting straight from the hotel, youâ€™ll ride 3 km and hike-a-bike 5 km to Paa Pass at 4,180 m. The climb is tough, but the ridge offers beautiful views. From there, enjoy a thrilling descent from 4,200 m down to 2,900 m, with fast, flowy trails and a rocky, loose final section leading to Chusang villageâ€”one of the most exciting days of the trip!\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1200 m. Elevation loss: 1500 m. 6/7 hours biking 25 km.</b></p><p></p>', 11, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-09-24 17:23:13'),
(2793, 256, '12', NULL, 'Chusang - Jhomsom via Lupra valley', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>\r\n\r\nToday youâ€™ll leave Upper Mustang and head back into Lower Mustang along the Annapurna Circuit. From Chhuksang, the trails go up and down to Kagbeni, where youâ€™ll take a shuttle bus to Muktinath. From there, youâ€™ll climb to Lupra Pass at 4,100 m, then enjoy an amazing 8 km descent dropping over 1,000 m, eventually meeting the Kali Gandaki and the trails from the first day, returning to Jomsom for the evening.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 340 m. Elevation loss: 1280 m. 5 hours biking 22km.</b><br><br></p><p></p>', 12, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 21:56:20'),
(2794, 256, '13', NULL, 'Jhomsom - pokhara', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After days of adventure on your mountain bike, today is all\r\nabout rest and comfort. Youâ€™ll leave Kalopani behind and take a jeep to Pokhara\r\nâ€“ no more pedalling, just a relaxing drive through scenic valleys and rolling\r\nhills. Pokhara is one of Nepalâ€™s most popular and beloved cities, known for its\r\ntranquil lakes, beautiful views of the Annapurna range, and easy-going vibe.\r\nItâ€™s the perfect place to unwind, reflect on your journey and enjoy the\r\nwell-earned peace at the end of an unforgettable trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Transport: 5/6 hours&nbsp; jeep /bus (Pokhara) 90km.</b></p><p></p>', 13, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-10-16 19:34:41'),
(2795, 256, '14', NULL, 'Pokhara - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Once breakfast is finished, you will drive back to\r\nKathmandu. Approximately six or seven hours are needed to finish this\r\npicturesque drive along the Prithvi Highway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon\r\nevening.</b></p><p></p>', 14, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 21:56:20'),
(2796, 256, '15', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day, sightseeing day or free day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Among the option, if you are heading for sightseeing, this\r\nday-day cultural tour will offer you a well-rounded experience of Kathmandu\'s\r\nhistory, spirituality and art while being guided by an expert, certified who\r\ncan enrich your understanding of the city\'s unique heritage. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>here\'s a suggested itinerary and price that balances\r\nhistory, culture and local experiences. Maximum visited only three sites in\r\nday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Swayambunath</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Bhaktapur</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Boudhanath</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Patan Darbar square</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Kathmandu Darbar square</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;In this price, an expert and certified cultural and\r\ntour guide a vehicle reserved and a professional driver for whole during the\r\nsightseeing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2-3 pp 70â‚¬.&nbsp; 4-6 pp 50â‚¬.&nbsp; 7-10 pp 35â‚¬.&nbsp; 11-15+ 30â‚¬.</p><p></p>', 15, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-09-24 17:23:13'),
(2797, 256, '16', NULL, 'Back to the native land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>According to your flight schedule\r\nthe grand departure. We will come to drive you to the airport.</p><p></p>', 16, '2025-06-13 19:24:04', '2025-08-22 21:56:20'),
(2798, 157, '17', NULL, 'Bhimthang - Tilje (2300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>For several\r\nhours, the scenery is so spectacular it\'s hard to know where to lookâ€”between\r\nthe Peri Himal range and the vast western cirque of Manaslu, the views are\r\nsimply awesome. The forest exudes a magical ambiance, with towering trees,\r\nblooming rhododendrons and lichen-draped branches set against a backdrop of\r\ndistant glaciers. We follow the Dudh Khola, a powerful, churning river, before\r\na short ascent to the Karche La. From there, we reach Tilje, a tranquil\r\ntraditionel village where we spend the night.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 100 m. Elevation loss: 1200 m. 6 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 17, '2025-06-20 16:09:18', '2025-07-20 14:52:43'),
(2799, 157, '18', NULL, 'Tilje - Dharapani (1900 m) - Jagat (1300 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Today marks\r\nthe final day of our Manaslu trek, featuring a long descent through the lower\r\nhills. We eventually cross a suspension bridge over the Marsyangdi River to\r\narrive at the village of Dharapani. From there, we continue on foot along the\r\nroadâ€”the only available routeâ€”to reach the picturesque village of Tal, known\r\nfor its scenic beauty. After passing through Tal, we descend further, briefly\r\nleaving the road to cross a final suspension bridge and switch to the opposite\r\nside of the valley. A short walk along the road then brings us to the village\r\nof Jagat. This evening, we share our final moments with the portersâ€”a\r\nmeaningful time to reflect on the journey and celebrate the experiences weâ€™ve\r\nshared together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>Elevation gain: 100 m. Elevation loss: 1300 m. 5/6 hours walking.<br></b></p><p></p><p></p>', 18, '2025-06-20 16:09:18', '2025-08-27 21:11:24'),
(2800, 157, '19', NULL, 'Jagat - Kathamdnu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We set off\r\nearly in the morning by vehicle, heading toward Besisahar. After a drive of\r\nabout two to three hours, we arrive at the main road in Dumre, where we\r\ntransfer to a bus for the journey back to Kathmandu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon.<br>Transfer: 7/8 hours drive.</b></p><p></p>', 19, '2025-06-20 16:09:18', '2025-08-27 21:10:26'),
