(2803, 131, '7', NULL, 'Rest and Accalimatization day in Dingbuche (4410 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The hike from Dingboche to Nagarjun Hill helps your body adjust to high altitude and prevents altitude sickness. The gentle climb allows your lungs and heart to adapt while you enjoy stunning Himalayan views. Optional visits around the village can also be done on this rest or acclimatisation day.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div><b><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></b></div><div><b><b>Elevation gain: 690 m . Elevation loss : 690 m. 5 hours  walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></b></div>\r\n\r\n<br></div>', 7, '2025-07-04 13:58:07', '2025-12-18 19:42:14'),
(2804, 159, '31', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><b>\r\n\r\n</b></p><div><p></p></div><div><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p></div>', 16, '2025-07-04 17:01:41', '2025-12-16 16:36:16'),
(2805, 159, '32', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 17, '2025-07-04 17:22:24', '2025-12-16 16:36:16'),
(2807, 122, '57', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 20, '2025-07-04 18:18:18', '2025-12-16 16:33:35'),
(2808, 259, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport: 20 M drive hotel</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-07-06 14:34:38', '2025-12-16 15:56:20'),
(2809, 259, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu -  Bhadrapur (91m) - Ilam (1200m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nOn the second day of your Kanchenjunga itinerary, we arrange all the required permits for the trek. Our experienced team manages the process to ensure everything is in order for a smooth journey. In the afternoon, you take a scenic flight from Kathmandu to Bhadrapur. After landing, you continue by jeep on a pleasant drive to the hill town of Ilam, enjoying wide views of Nepalâ€™s countryside along the way. Ilam is well known for its tea gardens and the local Himalayan cheese.\r\n\r\n<br></p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 45 minutes flight (Bhadrapur). 4/5 hours drive by jeep (Ilam).</b><br></p>', 2, '2025-07-06 14:34:38', '2025-12-16 19:20:30'),
(2810, 259, '3', NULL, 'Ilam -  Taplejung - Sekathum (1576m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p> We drive through the scenic hills of Ilam and Phidim to reach Taplejung. From there, we continue on a rough mountain road via Mitlung and Chiruwa, following the Tamor River to Sekathum.</p><p>&nbsp;<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7/8  hours drive by jeep (Taplejung).</b><br></p>', 3, '2025-07-06 14:34:38', '2025-10-18 15:04:35'),
(2811, 259, '4', NULL, 'Sekathum - Amjilosa (2510m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we walk from Sukathum to Amjilosa. The trail includes steep uphill sections and passes through open, rugged terrain, offering impressive scenery along the way. You cross several bridges over the Ghusna Khola before reaching Amjilosa. \r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 2,186 m. Elevation loss: 1425 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 4, '2025-07-06 14:34:38', '2025-12-16 19:20:30'),
(2812, 259, '5', NULL, 'Amjilosa - Gyabla (2725m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, the route leads through lush forest filled with rhododendrons and bamboo. Along the way, you pass a striking waterfall before continuing over steep climbs and descents to reach Gyabla.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 998 m. Elevation loss: 691 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 5, '2025-07-06 14:34:38', '2025-12-16 19:20:30'),
(2813, 259, '6', NULL, 'Gyabla - Ghunsa (3475m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nOn the sixth day of the Kanchenjunga trek, you leave Gyabla and walk towards Ghunsa, passing through a wide meadow. After a gentle climb over a small hill and a descent towards the river, you reach the village of Ghunsa. The village is known for its attractive wooden houses, as well as a school, health post and a small hydropower plant, which add to its charm.&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 925 m. Elevation loss: 213 m. 5 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 6, '2025-07-06 14:34:38', '2025-12-16 19:20:30'),
(2814, 259, '7', NULL, 'Ghunsa - Khangpachen (4050m )', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>On this day, the walk begins along forested trails beside the Ghunsa Khola. You pass several attractive chortens and mani walls while making your way towards Khangpachen. The route also provides impressive views of glacial moraines before reaching the Tibetan-influenced settlement of Khangpachen. From here, there are superb views of the north face of Jannu.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 769 m. Elevation loss: 110 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 7, '2025-07-06 14:34:38', '2025-12-16 19:20:30'),
(2815, 259, '8', NULL, 'Acclimatization day hike to Jannu Himal Base Camp (4600m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p> Today is your rest day so you can visit the surroundings. Khambachen is perfect for rest and acclimatization, with a hike to the Janu Viewpoint ffering spectacular views of Mt. Janu, its glacier, and surrounding peaks. The spiritually important Phaktalung site attracts many pilgrims during Augustâ€™s full moon festival.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 8, '2025-07-06 14:34:38', '2025-08-27 20:04:28');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_itinerary` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `days`, `meals`, `title`, `max_altitude`, `distance`, `duration`, `content`, `ordering`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2816, 259, '9', NULL, 'Khambachen - Lhonak (4761 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After the breakfast, you begin by walking along the left side of the Kanchenjunga Glacier. The trail follows a high plateau and leads to the campsite at Lhonak, which offers outstanding views of vast snow-covered peaks, including Mera Peak (6,364 m), Wedge Peak (6,802 m), Twins Peak (7,350 m) and Nepal Peak (7,177 m).&nbsp;</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 672 m. Elevation loss: 0 m. 4/5 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 9, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-12-16 19:20:30'),
(2817, 259, '10', NULL, 'Lhonak - Kanchenjunga North base camp (Pang Pema) (5143m) â€“ Lhonak', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p> Today, we will  spend extra time exploring this stunning region, soaking in the majestic peaks and the serene atmosphere. The circular hike and  descent back down to Lhonak.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 547 m. Elevation loss: 547 m. 6/7 hrs hours walking.</b><br></p>', 10, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-12-16 19:22:18'),
(2818, 259, '11', NULL, 'Lhonak - Ghunsa (3475m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Trek from Lhonak descends through alpine meadows and rocky trails, passing Ramtang and Khambachen before reaching Ghunsa.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 71 m. Elevation loss: 1405 m. 7/8 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 11, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-08-27 20:04:28'),
(2819, 259, '12', NULL, 'Ghunsa - Sele Le Base Camp (4240m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Ghunsa, the trail ascends steadily through forests and alpine terrain to Sele Le Base Camp.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b> Elevation gain: 834  m. Elevation loss: 53 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 12, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-08-27 20:04:28'),
(2820, 259, '13', NULL, 'Sele Le Base Camp (across Sale Le pass) - Tseram (3870 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Sele Le Base Camp, cross Sale Le Pass, then descend to Tseram.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 635 m. Elevation loss: 976 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 13, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-08-27 20:04:28'),
(2821, 259, '14', NULL, 'Tseram - Ramche - Oktang (Yalung, Kanchanjunga South Base Camp Viewpoint (4740m) - Tseram', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The scenic trek from Tseram to Ramche follows the glacierâ€™s edge, offering views of peaks like Koktang and Rathong, passes a lake, meadows, and stone houses before returning to Tseram.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 558 m. Elevation loss: 558 m. 7/8 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 14, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-08-27 20:04:28'),
(2822, 259, '15', NULL, 'Tseram - Tortong (2980m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Tseram, the trail descends through forests and crosses rivers before reaching Tortong.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 0 m. Elevation loss: 880 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 15, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-08-27 20:04:28'),
(2823, 259, '16', NULL, 'Tortong - Yamphudin (2080 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Todayâ€™s trek involves a descent, starting with a steep drop down to Imja Khola. After crossing the Dubi Pass, the trail continues with a gentler descent for a couple of hours until we reach the village of Yamphudin. This village is home to diverse communities, including Sherpas, Rais, Limbus, and Gurungs.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain:  879 m. Elevation loss: 2188 m. 6/7 hours walking.</b><br><br></p>', 16, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-07-12 22:03:24'),
(2824, 259, '17', NULL, 'Yamphudin -  Khebang (1,910m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>This section involves a gentle walk through villages, terraced fields, and forested areas. Along the way, youâ€™ll pass through Limbu and Rai settlements. It takes around 5 to 6 hours to reach Khebang.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 901 m. Elevation loss: 808 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 17, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-08-27 20:05:58'),
(2825, 259, '18', NULL, 'Khebang -  Kanyam (1910m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The drive from Khebang to Kanyam  pass  through hillside villages and scenic landscapes. As you descend, the road leads to the famous tea gardens of Kanyam.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 5/6 hours drive by jeep (Kanyam).</b><br></p>', 18, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-10-18 15:04:35'),
(2826, 259, '19', NULL, 'Kanyam - Bhadrapur â€“  Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Kanyam, we drive to  Bhadrapur. Then, we board a flight back to Kathmandu.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport: 4/5 hours driving by jeep (Bhadrapur). 45 minutes flight (Kathmandu)</b><br></p>', 19, '2025-07-06 14:37:54', '2025-10-18 15:04:35'),
