(2830, 166, '10', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 10, '2025-07-20 17:06:38', '2025-12-16 15:48:24'),
(2831, 169, '9', NULL, 'Rest Day at Thangnak â€“ Optional Thangnak Ri Hike (5000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'We spend the day in Thangnak to rest and acclimatise before climbing higher. Those feeling energetic can take a short hike towards Thangnak Ri for great views of Mera Peak, Charpate Himal, and the Hinku Valley. Back in Thangnak, we relax and prepare for the trek to Khare.<div><br><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, noon, evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain : 680m. Elevation loss: 680m. 5 hours hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n</div>', 9, '2025-08-14 14:04:07', '2025-08-27 21:15:26'),
(2832, 195, '18', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'According to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.', 18, '2025-08-14 14:17:14', '2025-12-11 16:14:20'),
(2833, 258, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transfer: 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-12-16 16:25:05'),
(2834, 258, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Drive Ramechhap - Flight Lukla (2860 m) - Trek to Phakding (2610 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Early morning drive to to Ramechhap around 2/3 AM. According\r\nto your flight schedule flight to Lukla. Start trek to Phakding </p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><i>Note:</i></b></p><p><b></b></p><p></p><p><b><i>- Due to potential congestion at Kathmandu\r\nAirport, the Civil Aviation Authority of Nepal (CAAN) may mandate that all flights\r\nto Lukla operate either from Kathmandu Airport or from Ramechhap Airport.</i></b></p><p><b><i>- In the event that the flight is canceled\r\ndue to adverse weather conditions, it will be rescheduled for the following\r\nday. An additional nightâ€™s accommodation will be provided either in Kathmandu\r\nor Ramechhap, depending on the point of departure.</i></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><b></b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening<br>Transfer : 4 hours drive by jeep (Ramechhap), 25 minutes flight (Lukla)<br>Elevation gain: 200 m . Elevation loss : 450 m . 6-7 hours of walking.<b></b></b></p><p></p>', 2, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-10-16 18:57:29'),
(2835, 258, '3', NULL, 'Phakding - Namche Bazaar (3440 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Trek through pine forests along the Dudh Koshi river. Cross\r\nsuspension bridges. Arrive Namche Bazaar, main Sherpa town and trading hub.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 1178 m . Elevation loss : 409 m . 5/6 hours&nbsp; walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 3, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-10-16 18:57:29'),
(2836, 258, '4', NULL, 'Acclimatization day in Namche Bazaar', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Hike day to\r\nEverest View Hotel or nearby hills.Explore local market, Sherpa culture,\r\nmonasteries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>&nbsp;</b><b>Accommodation:\r\nlodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p><p></p>', 4, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2837, 258, '5', NULL, 'Namche Bazaar - Tengboche (3860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Trek through\r\nrhododendron forest to Tengboche. Visit famous Tengboche Monastery with\r\nspectacular views of Everest, Lhotse, Ama Dablam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 921 m . Elevation loss : 700 m . 5/6 hours&nbsp; walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 5, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-10-16 18:57:29'),
(2838, 258, '6', NULL, 'Tengboche - Dingboche (4410 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Trek crossing Imja Khola valley. Pass through Pangboche\r\nvillage. Arrive Dingboche, a beautiful alpine valley.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 550 m . Elevation loss : 273 m. 5/6 hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 6, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-10-16 18:57:29'),
(2839, 258, '7', NULL, 'Acclimatization day in Dingboche', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Optional hike to Nagarjun Hill (5,100 m) or nearby ridges.\r\nPrepare for higher altitude.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nlodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p>', 7, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-15 15:01:44'),
(2840, 258, '8', NULL, 'Dingboche - Chhukung (4730 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Trek along Imja Khola valley. Arrive in Chhukung, base for\r\nIsland Peak climb. Meet climbing guides, review climbing plan and gear.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 395 m . Elevation loss : 00 m. 3 hours of walking.</b></p><p></p>', 8, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2841, 258, '9', NULL, 'Chhukung - Island Peak Base Camp (5100 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Trek up the\r\nmoraine to base camp below Island Peak.Practice using crampons, ice axe, rope\r\ntechniques.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 382 m . Elevation loss : 15 m. 4 hours of walking.</b></p><p></p>', 9, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2842, 258, '10', NULL, 'Reserve day', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Can be used in case of bad weather on summit day, or to rest\r\nand try again. If not used, continue descent or enjoy a slower pace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included:\r\nmorning noon evening</b></p><p></p>', 10, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2843, 258, '11', NULL, 'Summit day â€“ Island Peak summit (6189 m) and descend to Chhukung', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Start very early around midnight. Climb through rocky trail\r\nto glacier, then up snowy slopes with fixed ropes. Reach the summit and enjoy\r\nviews of Lhotse, Ama Dablam, and more. Descend back safely to Base Camp. Have\r\nhot soup, rest briefly, then pack and continue down to Chhukung. Long but\r\nrewarding day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening<br>Elevation gain: 1060 m . Elevation loss :2028 m . 8-11 hours of walking.<br></b><br></p><p></p>', 11, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2844, 258, '12', NULL, 'Chhukung - Pangbuche', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Retrace back\r\nto Pangbuche.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening<br>4 hours of walking.</b></p><p></p>', 12, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2845, 258, '13', NULL, 'Pangbuche - Ama Dablam Base Camp (4570 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>From\r\nPangboche, cross the Imja Khola and climb steeply to Ama Dablam Base Camp. The\r\ntrail offers stunning views of Ama Dablam, Everest, and Lhotse. At base camp,\r\nerect tents and arrange climbing equipment. Meet the team, get a safety\r\nbriefing, check health, and rest before the climb begins.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 711 m . Elevation loss : 86 m . 3 hours of walking.</b></p><p></p>', 13, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2846, 258, '14', NULL, 'Rest day at Basecamp - Acclimatisation walk & Technical Training Day', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b></b>Rest day\r\nat Basecamp - Acclimatisation walk &amp; Technical Training Day</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>&nbsp;</b><b>Accommodation:\r\nTent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p><p></p>', 14, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2847, 258, '15', NULL, 'ADC - Camp 1 (5700 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>A steep climb follows a rocky trail and grassy slopes. The\r\nroute goes up a narrow ridge with loose rocks in places, requiring careful\r\nsteps. Camp 1 sits on a small flat spot above the ridge with amazing views.\r\nTents are set up closely together on rocky platforms, often exposed to windy\r\nand chilly conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 711 m . Elevation loss : 86 m . 3 hours of walking.</b></p><p></p>', 15, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2848, 258, '16', NULL, 'Camp 1 - Camp 2 (6040 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>This is a short but technical climb of 4â€“5 hours over mixed\r\nterrainâ€”rock slabs, snow patches, and fixed ropes. The route includes exposed\r\nsections and crosses the famous Yellow Tower, a near-vertical rock wall that\r\nrequires focus and good rope skills. Camp 2 is set up on a narrow ledge with\r\nlimited space, surrounded by steep drops and stunning views.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 340 m . Elevation loss : 00 m . 3 hours of walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 16, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2849, 258, '17', NULL, 'Summit Day (6812 m) - back to Camp 2 or Camp 1', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>We face a challenging yet rewarding ascent with steep,\r\nexposed, and slippery rocky sections requiring careful navigation. The route is\r\nsecured with fixed ropes over steep rock and snow terrain, including the\r\nwell-known narrow Mushroom Ridge. From the summit of Ama Dablam, climbers are\r\nrewarded with magnificent 360-degree panoramic views of Everest, Lhotse,\r\nMakalu, and the Khumbu Valley. After a brief rest at the top, climbers descend\r\nsafely back to Camp 2 or Camp 1 under the guidance of our experienced Sherpa\r\nteam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 772 m . Elevation loss : 772/ 1112 m . 3 hours of walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 17, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2850, 258, '18', NULL, 'Camp 2 or Camp 1 - Base camp', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Retrace to base camp</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nTent. Meals included: morning noon evening</b></p><p></p>', 18, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2851, 258, '19', NULL, 'Reserve day', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>One day is reserved as a rest or waiting day in case of\r\nunfavourable weather conditions for climbing. If the weather improves, this day\r\ncan be used flexiblyâ€”please consult with your guide to discuss your options. If\r\nyou plan to fly from Lukla to Kathmandu, kindly inform us in advance so we can\r\nassist with your hotel reservation and ticketing arrangements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Lodge/Tent. Meals\r\nincluded: morning noon evening.</b></p><p></p>', 19, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2852, 258, '20/21', NULL, 'Base Camp - Namche - Lukla', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included:\r\nmorning noon evening</b></p><p></p>', 20, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2853, 258, '22', NULL, 'Lukla -  fly to Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Fly back to Ramechhap and drive to Kathmandu. Rest and\r\nrelax.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation:\r\nHotel. Meals included: morning noon</b></p><p></p>', 21, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-08-27 21:23:11'),
(2854, 258, '23', NULL, 'Lukla - Ramechhap - Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>After our long mountain trek, we take an early morning flight\r\nto Ramechap, followed by a 128 kilometer drive to Kathmandu. If the flight is\r\non time, you can spend the rest of the day relaxing and unwinding at the hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning, noon.</b><br><b>Transport: 25 minutes flight (Ramechhap), 4/5 hours of drive (Kathmandu)</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 446 m. Elevation loss: 1822 m. 6 hours hours walking.</b><br></p><p></p>', 22, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-10-16 18:57:29'),
(2855, 258, '24', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3  People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10  People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 23, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-12-16 16:25:05'),
(2856, 258, '25', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 25, '2025-08-15 13:44:55', '2025-12-16 16:25:05'),
(2857, 260, '1', NULL, 'Arrive Kathmandu (1350 m). Transfer to the hotel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\nYour memorable holiday begins in Kathmandu. After arrival, you will have time to freshen up before meeting your guide for an afternoon briefing. This is the perfect moment to organize your trekking gear and prepare your bags for the journey ahead.\r\n\r\n</p><p><b>Accommodation: Hotel. Meals included: morning</b><br><b>Transport : 20 M drive hotel.</b></p><p></p>', 1, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-12-16 16:27:32'),
(2858, 260, '2', NULL, 'Kathmandu - Besi Sahar (760 m) - Dharapani  (1860 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Early morning departure to Besisahar. This route main highway between Nepal and India, we allow till Mugling. Throughout passing numerous villages we arrive to Besisahar to change the jeeps. After Besisahar, the road then turns into a stony track, a little bumpy but bordered by beautiful landscapes of rice fields and traditional Nepalese villages. A few landslides can sometimes delay us or force us to change vehicles several times; Faced with these little daily adventures, it is wise to follow the example of the Nepalese who maintain a smile and good humor... We finally arrive at the Dharapani. Installation at the lodge.<br><br><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning, afternoon, evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 6h drive (Besi Sahar) + 3 hours track (Dharapani)</b><br><br></p>', 2, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-10-16 19:18:51'),
(2859, 260, '3', NULL, 'Dharapani - Chame (2700 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After breakfast, the trail climbs steeply to Timang, which marks the end of the vast Marsyangdi Gorge. From there, it gradually levels out as the landscape shifts from dense pine forests to drier hillsides. Beyond Besisahar, Chame â€” the district headquarters of Manang â€” is the largest settlement in the area.<br><br> <b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 750 m. Elevation loss: 340 m. 5 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 3, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2860, 260, '4', NULL, 'Chame â€“ Lower Pisang (3200 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After breakfast, the trail follows the Marsyangdi River through pine forests to Bhratang, known for its apple orchards. The valley then opens to the impressive curved rock face of Paungda Danda. After crossing a suspension bridge, you climb to Dukur Pokhari (3,240 m) for lunch with great mountain views, before gently descending to Lower Pisang (3,200 m). You can also visit Upper Pisang for its monastery and wider views. This stage combines forests, river views, and striking mountain scenery.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 830 m. Elevation loss: 350 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 4, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2861, 260, '5', NULL, 'Pisang - Ghyaru (3720) - Tibetan village of Ngawal (3661 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we climb steeply to Ghyaru, a small Tibetan village at 3,720 meters, known for its amazing mountain views and traditional stone houses. From Ghyaru, the trail crosses open hills to Ngawal (3,661 m), a larger village featuring a beautiful monastery and ancient stone buildings. This quieter route offers beautiful scenery and helps your body acclimatize to the higher altitude before continuing on to Manang.<br></p><p>\r\n\r\n</p><div><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b></div><div><b>Elevation gain: 685 m. Elevation loss: 217 m. 6 hours walking.</b></div><p></p>', 5, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2862, 260, '6', NULL, 'Ngawal Rest Day / Excursion', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Ngawal is an ideal place to rest and explore. Travelers can spend the day relaxing, acclimatizing, and enjoying the peaceful village atmosphere with its traditional houses, prayer wheels, and monasteries. For those who prefer activity, short hikes around Ngawal reveal stunning views of Annapurna II, III, IV, and Pisang Peak, along with hidden gompas and meditation cavesâ€”offering the perfect balance of recovery and discovery before continuing the expedition.<br><br><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 685 m. Elevation loss: 217 m. 6 hours walking.</b><br><br></p>', 6, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-20 17:12:02'),
(2863, 260, '7', NULL, 'Ngawal  - Yak Kharka (4000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Ngawal, we head north toward our goal of ascending Chulu Far East, departing from the Annapurna circuit trail. As we continue our slow climb, we arrive at Yak Kharka, which offers breathtaking views of the Himalayas<br><br><b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning, afternoon, evening. </b><br><b>Elevation gain: 350 m. Elevation loss: 55 m. 4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 7, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2864, 260, '8', NULL, 'Yak Kharka - Chulu Far East Base Camp (4885)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Yak Kharka, we go up the Chulu Gaon trail to Chulu Far East Base Camp. You will hike up charming communities and stunning scenery in the Annapurna region, where you may enjoy charming views of multiple mountain ranges. You will arrive at Chulu Far East Base Camp after traveling across the stunning glaciers, where you will locate a suitable campsite for camp setup.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 920 m. Elevation loss: 15 m. 3/4 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 8, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:28:10'),
(2865, 260, '9', NULL, 'Climbing course and preparation', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Our climbing guide will give you pre-climb instructions on this day. You will receive training on how to climb peaks. Additionally, you will receive instruction on how to properly use climbing equipment such as an ice axe, crampons, harness, and ascender. Moving up and down will teach you how to use ropes.</p><p><b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br></p>', 9, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2866, 260, '10', NULL, 'B.C - High Camp  (5400 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>As you go north into the High Camp, you will pass through breathtaking scenery. Trekking the uphill trail will provide you with breathtaking views of the Annapurna valley and mountains, including Chulu East, Chulu West, Pisang Peak, and Chulu Far East.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 480 m. Elevation loss: 00 m. 3/4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 10, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2867, 260, '11', NULL, 'Summit Chulu Far East (6038) - back to base camp', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>With our headlamps on, we depart the high camp early in the morning in an attempt to reach the peak of Chulu Far East. The climb is simple and non-technical, but it can be a little difficult due to the steep ascent and a few exposed ridges. From the high camp, we travel southwest to the summit. We get to the summit after a few hours of climbing. You will be able to observe the magnificent surroundings at the summit. You will return to base camp after savoring the time at the top.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Tent. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 660 m. Elevation loss: 1771 m. 3/4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 11, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2868, 260, '12', NULL, 'Base Camp - Ngawal', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>We retrace the same trail back down from Base Camp to the traditional village of Ngawal</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: Lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 150 m. Elevation loss: 1350 m. 3/4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 12, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2869, 260, '13', NULL, 'Ngawal - Braga Monastery - Manang (3542 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>After breakfast we follows a scenic, gradually descending trail. Leaving Ngawal, the path winds through open alpine terrain with scattered juniper trees, mani walls, and sweeping views of Annapurna III and Gangapurna. After about 1.5 hours, we reach the historic village of Braga, home to a 600-year-old monastery perched on a cliffâ€”well worth a short visit for its spiritual ambiance and amazing views. From Braga, the trail becomes easy and mostly flat, following the Marsyangdi River until we reach Manang, a vibrant village and key acclimatization stop on the Annapurna Circuit.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Elevation gain: 140 m. Elevation loss: 273 m. 4 hours walking.</b><br></p>', 13, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-08-27 21:26:59'),
(2870, 260, '14', NULL, 'Manang â€“ Besisahar', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>From Manang we retrace the same trail back, but this time the perspective changes. Instead of trekking, we take a jeep ride down the Marsyangdi Valley. The drive offers different scenery as we pass through alpine forests, waterfalls, and villages, gradually descending to the warmer lowlands of Besisahar.<br><br><b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.</b><br><b>Transport : 7/8 hours drive (\r\n\r\nMarsyangdi Valley).</b><br><br></p>', 14, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-10-16 19:18:51'),
(2871, 260, '15', NULL, 'Besisahar â€“ Kathmandu', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>We retrace our route back from Besisahar to Kathmandu by jeep or bus along the Prithvi Highway. <br></p><p>\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon.</b><br><b>Transport : 6 hours drive (Kathmandu).</b>\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 15, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-10-16 19:18:51'),
(2872, 260, '16', NULL, 'Kathmandu â€“ Souvenirs day | Sightseeing Day.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>If you choose sightseeing, this full-day cultural tour offers a well-rounded experience of Kathmanduâ€™s history, spirituality, and art, guided by a certified expert who will enrich your understanding of the cityâ€™s unique heritage.</p><p><b>Suggested itinerary (maximum three sites per day):</b></p>- Swayambunath<br>- Bhaktapur<br>- Boudhanath<br>- Patan Durbar Square<br>- Kathmandu Durbar Square<p></p><p>&nbsp;The price includes a certified cultural guide, a reserved vehicle, and a professional driver for the day.</p><p><b>Pricing per person:</b></p>&nbsp; 2 - 3 People: â‚¬70<br>&nbsp; 4 - 6 People: â‚¬50<br>&nbsp; 7 - 10 People: â‚¬35<br>&nbsp; 11 - 15 + People: â‚¬30 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 16, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-12-16 16:27:33'),
(2873, 260, '17', NULL, 'Final Departure / Back to Native Land', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\nAccording to your flight schedule, we will drive you to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n<br></p>', 17, '2025-08-20 16:58:43', '2025-12-16 16:27:33'),
(2874, 204, '10', NULL, 'Dzongla - Lobuche (4910 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>\r\n\r\n</p><p>This is a short and easy walk. The trail is mostly gentle, crossing meadows and small streams with beautiful views of Ama Dablam, Cholatse, and the Pheriche Valley.On the way, you will see the Everest Memorial, where stone monuments honour climbers who lost their lives in the Himalayas.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Accommodation: lodge. Meals included: morning noon evening</b><br><b>Elevation gain : 80 m. Elevation loss: 70 m. 2/4 hours walking.</b>\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 10, '2025-09-18 12:03:42', '2025-09-18 12:08:45'),
(2875, 261, '1', NULL, 'ArrivÃ©e Ã  Katmandou (1 350 m) â€“ Transfert Ã  lâ€™hÃ´tel', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Bienvenue au\r\nNÃ©pal ! Votre belle aventure commence Ã  Katmandou, le cÅ“ur vibrant du pays.\r\nAprÃ¨s votre transfert Ã  lâ€™hÃ´tel, votre guide vous donnera un briefing sur le\r\ndÃ©roulement du trek, selon la disponibilitÃ© du groupe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En fonction de\r\nvotre heure dâ€™arrivÃ©e, vous pourrez faire une petite balade ou un court trajet\r\nen voiture jusquâ€™Ã  la stupa de Swayambhunath, Ã©galement connue sous le nom de <i>Temple\r\ndes Singes</i>. Ce lieu sacrÃ© est lâ€™un des sites bouddhistes les plus anciens\r\net les plus emblÃ©matiques du NÃ©pal. Depuis son sommet, vous profiterez dâ€™un\r\nmagnifique coucher de soleil sur la vallÃ©e de Katmandou â€” une superbe faÃ§on de\r\ncommencer votre voyage.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>HÃ©bergement : hÃ´tel. Repas inclus : petit-dÃ©jeuner<br>\r\nTransfert : environ 20 minutes de route</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 1, '2025-12-18 16:16:17', '2025-12-18 16:30:27'),
(2876, 261, '2', NULL, 'JournÃ©e libre Ã  Katmandou', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Prenez le temps de vous dÃ©tendre et de dÃ©couvrir Katmandou Ã  votre rythme.\r\nVous pourrez vous promener dans les ruelles animÃ©es, visiter les temples et\r\nsites historiques les plus emblÃ©matiques de la ville, ou encore profiter de\r\nlâ€™ambiance authentique des marchÃ©s locaux pour vous imprÃ©gner de la vie\r\nnÃ©palaise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>HÃ©bergement : hÃ´tel. Repas inclus : petit-dÃ©jeuner</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 2, '2025-12-18 16:16:17', '2025-12-18 16:30:27'),
(2877, 261, '3', NULL, 'Katmandou â€“ Vol pour Pokhara (850 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Nous prenons un\r\ncourt vol Ã  Pokhara, charmante ville paisible situÃ©e au bord du lac Phewa.\r\nCette Ã©tape offre une vue remarquable sur le Machapuchare et la chaÃ®ne des\r\nAnnapurna.Dans\r\nlâ€™aprÃ¨s-midi, profitez dâ€™une promenade au bord du lac et partez Ã  la dÃ©couverte\r\ndes boutiques et cafÃ©s locaux, au cÅ“ur dâ€™une atmosphÃ¨re sereine et\r\naccueillante.<b>&nbsp;</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>HÃ©bergement : hÃ´tel. Repas inclus : petit-dÃ©jeuner<br>\r\nVol : environ 25 minutes<br>\r\nTransfert : environ 20 minutes</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 3, '2025-12-18 16:16:18', '2025-12-18 16:30:27'),
(2878, 261, '4', NULL, 'Pokhara â€“ Route pour Kimche et trek jusquâ€™Ã  Ghandruk (2 000 m)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>Nous partons en\r\n4x4 jusquâ€™Ã  Kimche, dâ€™oÃ¹ commence notre trek vers Ghandruk, un joli village de Gurung.\r\nÃ€ votre arrivÃ©e, la visite le monastÃ¨re local et de flÃ¢ner dans les ruelles du\r\nvillage, en dÃ©couvrant la chaleur et la convivialitÃ© des habitants.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>HÃ©bergement : Lodge. Repas inclus : </b>petit-dÃ©jeuner, dÃ©jeuner, dÃ®ner<b><br>\r\nTransfert </b><b>&nbsp;: 2h30 en 4X4</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>DÃ©nivelÃ© &nbsp;:</b> &nbsp;+300. DÃ©nivelÃ©: -0. <b>1h de marche</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 4, '2025-12-18 16:16:18', '2025-12-18 16:30:27'),
(2879, 261, '5', NULL, 'Ghandruk - Baisi Kharka (2500 M)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p></p><p>AprÃ¨s le petit-dÃ©jeuner, dÃ©part de Ghandruk en direction de Baisi Kharka.\r\nLâ€™itinÃ©raire emprunte un agrÃ©able sentier traversant de superbes forÃªts et\r\ncollines verdoyantes, offrant de magnifiques panoramas sur les paysages\r\nhimalayens.<br>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>&nbsp;</b><b>Accommodation:\r\nlodge. Meals included: morning noon evening.<br>\r\nElevation gain: 500m. Elevation loss: 10m. </b><b>4 hours walking. 4.5km</b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><p></p>', 5, '2025-12-18 16:16:18', '2025-12-18 16:30:27'),
